-- Meeting: Powerhouse Gym & Ideometry: Weekly Sync (2026-01-07 16:00:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    'e7336694-2c40-4fcf-a7ef-4d0460f053c8',
    '2026-01-07 16:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KE4R0W312AHKES88S2N8HJ2H',
    'Powerhouse Gym & Ideometry: Weekly Sync',
    '{"Milan Wagner","Nina Belina","Robert"}'::text[],
    2089,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/88636878393?pwd=TfdWsZCl10zRsv4cBAbOaWpJ7sz5iM.1',
    '{"id":"01KE4R0W312AHKES88S2N8HJ2H","title":"Powerhouse Gym & Ideometry: Weekly Sync","summary":{"notes":"## **Meta Advertising Campaigns**\n\nThe current Meta campaigns are underperforming due to frequent changes disrupting algorithm learning and misuse of AI-generated copy, requiring a more disciplined approach to ad management.\n\n- **Campaigns were over-managed with frequent pausing of ad sets and ads, causing constant resets of the learning phase and leading to rising CPL despite a monthly spend of around 6,000 to 7,000 USD without reaching 30 leads per day** (14:00)\n    - The algorithm needs at least **two weeks** of stability to optimize properly before any major changes.\n    - Milan Wagner noted the team was pausing entire campaigns or assets too often, which Nina Belina confirmed disrupts performance.\n    - Best practice is to maintain at least **five active ad sets**, adding replacements before pausing any underperforming ones.\n    - This approach aims to minimize re-learning periods and improve cost efficiency.\n\n- **AI-generated ad copy introduced errors and outdated references, damaging campaign authenticity, especially for the gym and fitness audience** (19:00)\n    - Examples included outdated year references in promotional texts, which were flagged and corrected.\n    - Nina recommended stopping AI copy use or strictly reviewing and approving all content before publishing.\n    - Milan called this lax oversight \"laziness,\" highlighting the need for human checks to preserve genuine messaging.\n    - This quality control is critical given the audience’s preference for authentic human communication.\n\n- **To increase qualified leads from current 12 to the target 30 per day, the budget must nearly double from 2,500 USD to about 4,500 USD monthly, paired with improved campaign management** (27:00)\n    - Nina explained that the current spend delivers around 12 leads, but optimized campaigns with stable ad sets and better targeting can hit 30 leads.\n    - Milan pointed out prior spend of 6,000–7,000 USD without results was due to poor management resetting learning phases.\n    - Colin from Nina’s team is tasked to provide pricing and estimated hours to manage Meta ads properly, with a prompt update expected the same day.\n    - This cost versus results analysis drives the decision to possibly switch campaign management to Nina’s team.\n\n- **Campaign structure should diversify traffic paths to test lead quality, not just rely on a single HubSpot lead form** (17:00)\n    - Nina suggested using multiple ad sets directing users to different destinations: direct lead forms, website conversion pages, and “Join Now” pages.\n    - This multi-path approach helps identify which lead source performs best and extends the customer journey strategically.\n    - Milan confirmed current practice funnels all leads to a single HubSpot form, limiting testability.\n    - Adjusting this will improve data-driven optimization and lead qualification.\n\n## **Website Engagement and Conversion**\n\nVisitors spend less time than initially thought on the site, with most leaving on the pricing page, indicating potential barriers that need testing and possible lead capture improvements.\n\n- **Actual average session engagement is closer to 30 seconds, not 1.5 minutes, due to Google Analytics audience segmentation, with the pricing page seeing the highest drop-off** (22:00)\n    - Nina clarified that longer engagement metrics reflect repeat or engaged users, but average engagement across all visitors is low.\n    - Milan raised concerns that the pricing page might be turning visitors away due to perceived high costs.\n    - Nina suggested this drop-off might reflect typical gym decision processes rather than outright rejection.\n    - Retargeting offers like 20% off the first three months could help pull visitors back.\n\n- **Introducing gating on the pricing page by requiring visitor information before viewing prices could increase lead capture if paired with a compelling offer** (24:00)\n    - Nina emphasized the need to give visitors a clear value, such as a discount or a free workout, for surrendering their contact details.\n    - Milan proposed alternatives including a strong call to action like scheduling a visit or a free trial to justify gating.\n    - This tactic aims to convert curious browsers into engaged leads by providing immediate benefits.\n    - Implementation would require UX adjustments and clear communication of incentives.\n\n- **Tracking visitor interactions on key pages is currently insufficient; adding tools like Hotjar for heatmaps and detailed user behavior analysis is recommended** (26:00)\n    - Nina highlighted Hotjar’s ability to show click patterns, scrolling, and user focus areas, which Google Analytics alone cannot provide.\n    - Milan requested the link to Hotjar to evaluate it for immediate adoption.\n    - Better tracking will inform website improvements and help optimize conversion funnels.\n    - This complements Meta campaign data to provide a fuller picture of user engagement.\n\n## **HubSpot Integration and Campaign Automation**\n\nThe HubSpot platform is being enhanced with new forms and automated SMS/email campaigns to support lead capture and nurture, with content and compliance details still pending finalization.\n\n- **Two new HubSpot lead capture forms are created for Miami and Fort Lauderdale clubs, each with detailed properties to track user responses and interests** (30:00)\n    - Nina explained that every user answer is stored as a separate property for precise segmentation.\n    - Terms and conditions, including liability waivers and marketing consent, will be mandatory checkboxes on these forms.\n    - Milan confirmed that the waiver and marketing communication terms will mirror existing documentation.\n    - These forms will integrate with Meta campaign leads to ensure accurate data flow.\n\n- **A trial campaign is being set up to funnel Meta leads into HubSpot lists and trigger automated emails offering complimentary day passes, with Milan writing the email content** (30:00)\n    - Campaign setup includes separate forms per club and automated follow-up emails.\n    - Nina will send the email drafts for review before launch.\n    - No SMS or emails will be sent before final approval to maintain control over messaging.\n    - This campaign aims to increase trial participation and move leads down the funnel.\n\n- **HubSpot SMS automation is under development based on text content Milan provided, with full integration pending content confirmation** (29:00)\n    - Nina confirmed no further input needed besides finalizing email content.\n    - The SMS campaign will complement email outreach to maximize lead touchpoints.\n    - Monitoring and review processes will ensure quality before live deployment.\n    - This layered communication strategy is designed to boost lead engagement.\n\n## **Budget and Resource Planning**\n\nDecisions on campaign management responsibility and cost implications are pending, with quick turnaround needed to improve lead generation results.\n\n- **Nina’s team can run Meta ads properly if engaged, but exact cost and resource estimates are pending from Colin, with a commitment to respond today** (28:00)\n    - Milan requested a clear breakdown of hours and fees to decide on switching campaign management quickly.\n    - Robert confirmed willingness to evaluate and proceed based on cost-benefit.\n    - The urgency stems from current ineffective spend and the need to reach 30 leads daily.\n    - This evaluation will determine whether outsourcing ad management improves outcomes.\n\n- **Current campaign management is not handled by Nina’s team; the audit was to identify flaws and offer better service options** (33:00)\n    - Robert initially misunderstood the responsibility but agreed to further discussion after clarification.\n    - Nina’s team highlighted that the audit revealed common mistakes their team can avoid.\n    - This positions Nina’s team as a strong candidate for managing future campaigns.\n    - A final decision depends on pricing and resource allocation details from Colin.\n\n## **Strategic Recommendations and Next Steps**\n\nImplementing disciplined campaign management, enhanced tracking, and integrated lead nurturing will improve lead volume and quality while optimizing budget use.\n\n- **Milan and Nina agreed on key improvements: keep campaigns stable for two weeks, replace ad sets before pausing, diversify traffic paths, and review AI-generated copy carefully** (16:00)\n    - These steps address campaign performance and audience expectations.\n    - They collectively aim to reduce wasted spend and improve lead quality.\n    - Adoption of these practices will require training or oversight of current marketing teams.\n    - This disciplined approach forms the foundation for scaling lead generation.\n\n- **Implement website behavior tracking tools like Hotjar and consider gating pricing pages with compelling offers to increase lead capture** (26:00)\n    - These changes will complement Meta campaigns by converting more visitors into leads.\n    - Tracking user behavior will identify friction points and guide UX improvements.\n    - Gating with offers aligns with observed user hesitation and decision-making patterns.\n    - Together, these tactics enhance the overall marketing funnel effectiveness.\n\n- **Finalize HubSpot campaign content and forms, ensuring legal compliance and seamless integration with Meta campaigns, before launching automated email and SMS sequences** (31:00)\n    - Milan will provide email copy promptly; Nina will prepare the systems accordingly.\n    - Mandatory terms checkboxes maintain compliance and protect the business.\n    - Automated follow-ups aim to increase conversion from lead to trial.\n    - Careful rollout and monitoring are planned to optimize results.\n\n- **Await Colin’s cost proposal for Meta campaign management and evaluate the potential switch to Nina’s team to improve campaign outcomes and budget efficiency** (28:00)\n    - This decision point is critical to operationalizing the audit recommendations.\n    - Robert and Milan will lead the evaluation based on pricing and expected impact.\n    - Quick action is needed given the current underperformance and budget waste.\n    - Successful transition could unlock the goal of 30 qualified leads daily.","outline":null,"keywords":["Meta audit","ad campaigns","lead generation","website analytics","campaign management","HubSpot forms"],"overview":"- **Meta Ad Campaign Challenges:** Frequent changes and AI copy misuse hindered performance, causing rising CPL with 6,000-7,000 USD monthly spend. \n\n- **Budget Increase for Leads:** Doubling budget from 2,500 to 4,500 USD is necessary to boost qualified leads from 12 to 30 per day.\n\n- **Website Engagement Insights:** Average site visit drops to 30 seconds; pricing page likely deters visitors, needing value-driven adjustments to retain interest.\n\n- **Gating Strategy Proposal:** Implementing visitor information requirements on pricing page could enhance lead capture with enticing offers.\n\n- **HubSpot Integration Improvements:** Launching new forms and automated emails for lead nurturing; compliance ensures a smooth integration with Meta campaigns.\n\n- **Action on Budget Management:** Timely cost estimates from Colin will determine if ad management switches to Nina’s team for better outcomes.","action_items":"\n**Milan Wagner**\nWrite and send email content for the trial campaign''s automated email for review (31:22)\nReview and approve the punch platforms/forms with extra qualifying questions once received (31:50)\nRequest and receive Hotjar platform link from Nina for heatmap and behavior tracking (26:40)\n\n**Nina Belina**\nShare detailed meta audit and website audit documents with Milan for review (25:40)\nConfirm terms and conditions for use in lead forms aligned with existing waivers (31:20)\nGet pricing and estimated hours required from Colin for managing Meta ads and communicate to Milan and team by end of day (28:47)\nSend HubSpot SMS campaign email content draft for Milan’s review (32:30)\nProvide Hotjar platform link and setup guidance to Milan (26:40)\n\n**Robert Rudder**\nEvaluate decision on whether to have Marketers In Demand manage ad sets after pricing/info is received (34:15)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nProvide cost and hours estimate for ongoing Meta ads management to Nina and Milan promptly (28:47)\n"},"duration":34.81999969482422,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Milan Wagner"},{"id":1,"name":"Nina Belina"},{"id":2,"name":"Robert"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hey, Nina, what''s up?","index":0,"end_time":655.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":654.489,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Hi.","index":1,"end_time":656.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":655.85,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"How you doing?","index":2,"end_time":657.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":657.21,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"I''m sorry, we had a shipment for all of our boxing equipment, so I had to be available for that.","index":3,"end_time":664.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":657.89,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"No worries.","index":4,"end_time":666.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":665.76,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Do you have time today to go through, you know, the meta audit and website and everything?","index":5,"end_time":671.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":666.4,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Let''s do it.","index":6,"end_time":672.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":671.76,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Let''s do it.","index":7,"end_time":673.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":672.48,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Okay, let me share my screen just a second.","index":8,"end_time":676.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":673.44,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Actually, you know what?","index":9,"end_time":679.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":678.72,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"I''m gonna send this link to somebody else as well, at least for the meta audit.","index":10,"end_time":686.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":679.68,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Give me two seconds.","index":11,"end_time":690.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":686.96,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"It.","index":12,"end_time":690.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":690.49,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":13,"end_time":722.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":721.46,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Just jumping on.","index":14,"end_time":723.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":722.42,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Right.","index":15,"end_time":723.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":723.18,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Will this be on for the.","index":16,"end_time":727.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":725.54,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"The meta audit?","index":17,"end_time":730.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":728.5,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":18,"end_time":734.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":733.78,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Are we waiting for anybody or is it okay?","index":19,"end_time":736.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":734.42,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re waiting for one person for two seconds.","index":20,"end_time":741.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":736.98,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"So we did both the meta audit and the website audit.","index":21,"end_time":745.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":741.87,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So we''ll go through both of them today.","index":22,"end_time":747.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":745.07,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":23,"end_time":749.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":748.59,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Didn''t we go already through the website audit?","index":24,"end_time":752.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":750.19,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Oh, no, this is, you know, ife asked if we can pull out anything that''s, you know, positive and doesn''t need to be changed for the new website.","index":25,"end_time":761.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":753.07,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And then also to check how people.","index":26,"end_time":765.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":761.87,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":27,"end_time":766.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":765.79,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And what.","index":28,"end_time":766.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":766.19,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Why people were.","index":29,"end_time":768.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":766.79,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"It was showing that people were staying for like over a minute and a half on the website.","index":30,"end_time":774.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":768.64,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So what was the reason behind that?","index":31,"end_time":776.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":774.16,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Okay, all right, cool.","index":32,"end_time":778.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":777.04,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"She''s on so we can go through it.","index":33,"end_time":780.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":778.4,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Okay.","index":34,"end_time":781.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":780.72,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So for the meta audit, one of the main things that we noticed that the campaign seemed to be a little bit over managed.","index":35,"end_time":789.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":781.92,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Which usually means that, for example, when you set up a campaign, the algorithm needs at least two weeks to learn how to work and how to optimize the campaign.","index":36,"end_time":800.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":789.36,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So for example, if you have a certain target audience, if you have exclusions, if you have anything that''s, you know, interests, that''s more related to narrowing down the target audience.","index":37,"end_time":812.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":800.87,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"The audit, the algorithm needs a bit more time to learn.","index":38,"end_time":816.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":812.79,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Like sometimes you can even see like really good results at the very beginning.","index":39,"end_time":820.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":816.15,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"But it doesn''t mean that the algorithm has learned everything that it should.","index":40,"end_time":826.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":820.27,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So it''s good to kind of leave it untouched for two weeks or at least a month.","index":41,"end_time":830.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":826.06,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Like, it''s good to, you know, keep it the same as it one with is set primarily.","index":42,"end_time":837.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":830.98,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And then when you see, you know, after a month, when you can have some monthly, you know, analytics, then you can see like, oh, do I need to optimize something or not?","index":43,"end_time":846.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":837.74,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Or if anything is changing, but just, you know, just to go through that learning phase from the beginning to the end.","index":44,"end_time":854,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":846.26,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And also the CPL rose, but that was due to like manual resets and fragmenting.","index":45,"end_time":863.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":854.88,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And you know, you can see it''s like we wrote all of this down, but the main parts that were a bit problematic with the campaigns, we shared it a little bit down below.","index":46,"end_time":876.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":863.04,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And so one of the things was the learning phase.","index":47,"end_time":880.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":877.28,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And then the second thing was the.","index":48,"end_time":884.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":881.49,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Before we, before we switch over.","index":49,"end_time":887.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":885.09,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"So the learning phase.","index":50,"end_time":888.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":887.81,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"I also thought that they were manipulating our ads too often.","index":51,"end_time":893.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":889.97,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"And I asked them if they keep pausing and adding different ad sets, that kind of stuff, is it messing up?","index":52,"end_time":906.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":894.53,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"And are we continuously going into that learning phase section so that our ad sets are not as efficient as possible?","index":53,"end_time":914.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":906.45,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"They said no, as long as the overall campaign is active, then it, it would be fine.","index":54,"end_time":920.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":914.46,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Well, definitely, like you always have a campaign group and you have a certain ad set within that campaign group.","index":55,"end_time":926.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":920.86,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And the main thing is that you shouldn''t pause anything that for, for example, you, for the first two weeks, you should keep it as it is.","index":56,"end_time":935.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":926.86,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And then after those two weeks, if you see that like an ad set within that campaign group is underperforming, you can see how you might go down to change.","index":57,"end_time":945.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":935.9,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Like, does it need new visuals?","index":58,"end_time":946.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":945.17,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Is the copy not working?","index":59,"end_time":948.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":946.69,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Like, what might be the issue?","index":60,"end_time":949.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":948.33,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And then one of the assets, you need to add one more, which is different, and then only then pause an asset, but not pause everything or pause the campaign group or, you know, just, I mean, from my experience, the best thing is to keep it from, for at least two weeks without any changes.","index":61,"end_time":968.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":949.93,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And then when you want to change something to keep, you know, anything that needs to be paused, keep it paused, keep it to a minimal, and always have something to replace it.","index":62,"end_time":976.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":968.19,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So for example, always have at least five ad sets to working.","index":63,"end_time":981.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":976.87,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Okay.","index":64,"end_time":982.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":982.31,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"So before you pause or change an ad set, you must add an ad set first.","index":65,"end_time":988.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":982.87,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":66,"end_time":989.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":989.11,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And then do the pause.","index":67,"end_time":991.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":989.59,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":68,"end_time":991.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":991.11,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And see why the one that you want to change isn''t working.","index":69,"end_time":993.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":991.43,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So sometimes if it''s just copy, you know, sometimes you can still, still add something or, you know, if the ad is not like you can, if, if you can still add, change the copy, maybe that''s the best, you know, solution instead of changing the whole ad within the ad set.","index":70,"end_time":1008.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":993.99,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So.","index":71,"end_time":1009.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1009.07,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah, but still.","index":72,"end_time":1010.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1009.43,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Okay, but so what you''re, what you''re saying is that the campaigns have been paused, not just the ad sets.","index":73,"end_time":1017.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1010.51,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Well, from what we saw is that most of it was that the ads ad assets were turned off and on frequently and that disrupts it.","index":74,"end_time":1030.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1018.19,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Okay.","index":75,"end_time":1033.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1032.92,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"And so, I mean, that''s the first thing that you usually should look out for ads.","index":76,"end_time":1040.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1034.92,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Just, you know, when you set it, keep it as it is for a certain amount of time.","index":77,"end_time":1044.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1040.88,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And then another thing that we noticed was that you need to optimize the campaigns.","index":78,"end_time":1053.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1044.84,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"For example, if you want lead generation, you need to see where the traffic is guiding your lead.","index":79,"end_time":1061.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1054.14,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So is it a form that''s directly connected to meta and our platform or is it leading it to a second platform?","index":80,"end_time":1068.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1061.26,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So like for example, it''s always good to have one ad set that''s linking them to a form that''s direct to, I don''t know, join us or something like that.","index":81,"end_time":1077.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1068.3,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"But then another one that''s a website conversion that''s leading them to their website and prolonging the customer path so you can, you know, test it to see what works better.","index":82,"end_time":1087.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1077.58,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And so what we''re current, what we''re currently doing is we''re just, we''re running an ad set and then there''s a HubSpot lead form and that''s it.","index":83,"end_time":1096.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1088.44,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"And that''s usually, I mean the shorter it is, the better.","index":84,"end_time":1100.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1096.92,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And so we also just wrote some things down that are better for like if you want to achieve a certain goal by the end of next year.","index":85,"end_time":1111.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1101.4,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Because I know that TFA said that he wants 30 leads per day, which requires a bit like almost double of the budget that is being used.","index":86,"end_time":1120.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1111.05,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"But on a positive scale like the Advantage plus thing is working.","index":87,"end_time":1125.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1120.57,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"The only thing that we noticed that if you''re using AI that you need to check for the copy being accurate.","index":88,"end_time":1133.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1125.77,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Because uh, when we were doing the meta audit we noticed that some of the texts, for example December for December free campaign, the AI copy was saying kickstart your 2023 journey.","index":89,"end_time":1145.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1133.05,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah, we saw that.","index":90,"end_time":1147.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1146.6,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"We, we told them to change that.","index":91,"end_time":1149.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1147.72,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"So I mean it''s not like a huge.","index":92,"end_time":1153.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1150.52,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"But you know, everything that''s in the like last couple of months linked to AI.","index":93,"end_time":1158.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1154.04,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"It''s usually like, doesn''t really give a good impression.","index":94,"end_time":1163.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1158.44,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Okay, and so.","index":95,"end_time":1165.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1163.71,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Okay, how would you manage that?","index":96,"end_time":1169.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1166.83,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"You just tell them stop using AI and and send me what you''re writing before.","index":97,"end_time":1174.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1169.31,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Yeah, definitely.","index":98,"end_time":1175.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1174.59,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"We approve it.","index":99,"end_time":1176.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1175.43,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"I mean you like with AI, everything needs to be checked and rechecked.","index":100,"end_time":1180.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1176.67,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Because I mean it, it, the systems are good but they''re not like they don''t need human interaction like just rechecking the copy.","index":101,"end_time":1191.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1180.47,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So.","index":102,"end_time":1193.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1193.5,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":103,"end_time":1194.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1193.82,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Okay, so that''s just laziness.","index":104,"end_time":1197.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1195.42,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":105,"end_time":1197.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1197.66,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And also like it.","index":106,"end_time":1198.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1197.98,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I mean especially because it''s gym and fitness, you know, AI in anything like isn''t real.","index":107,"end_time":1204.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1198.82,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Like people won''t like genuine like human school.","index":108,"end_time":1207.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1204.54,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Of course.","index":109,"end_time":1209.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1208.46,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":110,"end_time":1209.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1209.06,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"So yeah.","index":111,"end_time":1210.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1209.74,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Okay, so biggest thing, sorry, just to reiterate, is that they were being over managed.","index":112,"end_time":1216.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1211.02,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":113,"end_time":1217.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1217.05,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"They''re using AI and they''re not double checking their work so that it''s coming off as incorrect.","index":114,"end_time":1222.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1217.49,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"And then the last one was that to get more qualified leads, we need to have different, for the different assets, we need to drive the consumer into different areas.","index":115,"end_time":1233.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1223.05,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"So one to the join now online page, one to the just the HubSpot lead forms and then another one to our website.","index":116,"end_time":1240.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1233.69,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Website, yeah.","index":117,"end_time":1242.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1241.29,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And you can even see like if you notice that people are interested in for example, groups or like group sessions, maybe if you have a dedicated page for what our coaches are doing or like anything regards to like some additional information.","index":118,"end_time":1256.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1242.38,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Like usually people like to know who''s going to train them or things like that.","index":119,"end_time":1261.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1256.38,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So that might be something that''s even better than just, you know, shortening sort of everything to a long form or something like that.","index":120,"end_time":1268.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1261.06,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And then for the website audit, we went through the whole website.","index":121,"end_time":1274.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1269.02,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So let me just open this and.","index":122,"end_time":1280.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1274.91,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Here you can see Nina, before we do the website, just give me two seconds here.","index":123,"end_time":1285.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1280.67,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"I''m writing some notes on this.","index":124,"end_time":1286.909,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1285.39,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"This has been a massive pain point for me.","index":125,"end_time":1291.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1288.99,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"So this is good information.","index":126,"end_time":1292.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1291.67,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Hold.","index":127,"end_time":1293.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1292.91,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"On.","index":128,"end_time":1296.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1295.89,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"All right, go for it.","index":129,"end_time":1318.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1317.64,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":130,"end_time":1318.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1318.44,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Okay, just let me just.","index":131,"end_time":1321.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1320.28,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So yeah, we went through the Google Analytics and one of the things that TFE mentioned was that he was seeing a large number of the visitors stay longer than a minute and a half.","index":132,"end_time":1334.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1322.12,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And I asked our team to look into it to see what might be the reason they''re staying.","index":133,"end_time":1342.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1335.96,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And the reason is that there are two separate metrics for the average engagement time.","index":134,"end_time":1348.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1342.6,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And for example, if you''re looking from the audience view, that view will always focus on people who have returned to the site or have like, for example, if you have one user who clicked on one page and then clicked on another but stayed on the website, they will focus more on those people and put the users that are like short term users who only click and go out of the webpage in like the second row.","index":135,"end_time":1376.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1349.16,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So if you, if you go and look at average engagement time per session, which is more like behavior accurate.","index":136,"end_time":1383.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1376.85,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So for all users, users not like the ones that are there longer and then the ones that are there shorter, but all of them together, the average session time is close to closer to 30 seconds.","index":137,"end_time":1395.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1383.61,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And most of the people leave on the pricing page.","index":138,"end_time":1398.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1395.03,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Classic.","index":139,"end_time":1402.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1401.63,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"So yeah, why, why do we think they''re leaving on the pricing page?","index":140,"end_time":1408.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1404.75,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"It''s not pretty.","index":141,"end_time":1409.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1408.11,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Prices are too high.","index":142,"end_time":1411.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1410.36,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Is that something that we can even figure out?","index":143,"end_time":1414.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1411.72,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Well, I wouldn''t say that it''s necessarily negative.","index":144,"end_time":1419.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1416.28,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I would say that maybe people, you know, because there are A lot of gyms and people, like, have a longer decision process.","index":145,"end_time":1426,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1419.56,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Maybe like, they want to just see, oh, how much this, this one costs and then how much the other one costs and do they have a plan where, you know, six months is less than paying one month per month in a year?","index":146,"end_time":1438.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1426,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So I would say that that might be the, the thing.","index":147,"end_time":1441.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1438.29,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"But then, you know, for example, retargeting with something that''s, you know, an offer for, I don''t know, the first three months, 20% off is something that would maybe bring them back.","index":148,"end_time":1452.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1441.77,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Okay, is there.","index":149,"end_time":1454.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1453.65,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Yes.","index":150,"end_time":1456.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1456.21,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Is there also something that we can do where, for example, they do the pricing page, we have them fill out their information first before even seeing the pricing.","index":151,"end_time":1467.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1457.33,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"That something that we could do.","index":152,"end_time":1468.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1467.79,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Is that an annoying thing to do?","index":153,"end_time":1471.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1469.07,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"And then let.","index":154,"end_time":1473.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1472.35,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"So that''s option number one.","index":155,"end_time":1475.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1474.03,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Option number two is, let''s say on the pricing page we also have like a, you know, a big thing which says like, schedule your visit and, you know, find out why we''re worth it or something like that.","index":156,"end_time":1485.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1475.23,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"I would say that for anything.","index":157,"end_time":1487.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1485.95,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Like, if you''re asking them to give you information just to, you know, see information, you have to give them something.","index":158,"end_time":1495.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1487.55,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So you know how sometimes when you want to see how much something costs on a, I don''t know, a shop or an online shop, you, they say like, oh, get 15, $15 free from your first purchase.","index":159,"end_time":1509.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1495.23,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Like, that''s the kind of thing that makes me want to, you know, put in my email address, but just to put in my email address to see how much it costs.","index":160,"end_time":1517.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1509.73,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"That''s kind of, you know, that, that makes me wonder.","index":161,"end_time":1519.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1517.21,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, no, that''s fair.","index":162,"end_time":1522.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1521.01,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"So what about like a free workout or something?","index":163,"end_time":1524.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1522.17,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Yeah, I think that''s, that could probably work out.","index":164,"end_time":1526.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1524.37,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"And also people like to like, have like, maybe the first day, you know, free and just to see, like to get comfortable in the space.","index":165,"end_time":1535.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1526.92,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So.","index":166,"end_time":1536,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1535.64,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":167,"end_time":1536.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1536,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah, exactly.","index":168,"end_time":1537.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1536.52,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Okay.","index":169,"end_time":1538.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1538.12,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"All right, cool.","index":170,"end_time":1539.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1538.68,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"So, but you can.","index":171,"end_time":1540.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1539.8,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"I, I, I sent the meta audit and I will send the webpage audit as well, so you can go through them in more detail.","index":172,"end_time":1546.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1540.72,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I have another question on this Join Online now page.","index":173,"end_time":1550.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1547.4,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"So we know now that people are, are leaving from that Join Online now page.","index":174,"end_time":1557.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1550.6,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Do we know like, which, if they''re pressing any buttons or anything like that on that Join Online now page?","index":175,"end_time":1563.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1557.3,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Well, you would need like tracking within HubSpot to see, like, you would have to set tracking metrics to, or go from Google GA4 to see specific parts of the webpage.","index":176,"end_time":1575.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1564.18,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Also, like, one of, one of the, the platforms that I really like to use is hotjar.","index":177,"end_time":1581.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1575.58,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And then there you can see like really specific movements from people on the page.","index":178,"end_time":1586.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1581.67,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Like it creates like almost like a heat map of where people are clicking, where they''re staying the longest and everything.","index":179,"end_time":1594.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1586.43,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And we, we currently don''t have that ability.","index":180,"end_time":1597.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1594.91,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"I mean, you can get like, on hotjar.","index":181,"end_time":1600.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1598.19,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I don''t know if they have like a free version.","index":182,"end_time":1602.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1600.07,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"You can check it out, see how it works.","index":183,"end_time":1603.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1602.03,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Okay.","index":184,"end_time":1604.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1604.33,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Okay.","index":185,"end_time":1605.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1605.05,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Can you send me the, the link to that platform?","index":186,"end_time":1609.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1605.93,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"All right, Robert, do you have questions on that?","index":187,"end_time":1616.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1613.13,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"No.","index":188,"end_time":1618.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1618.33,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Yeah, and we also, like, in both in Meta and Google Analytics, you will see like, what''s necessary to get to the lead number that DeFei mentioned, which is, you know, it does like, require a bit of an increase from time.","index":189,"end_time":1633.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1619.37,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I had a. Yeah, I had a question on that.","index":190,"end_time":1635.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1633.41,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Was that 3,000 to 4,000 increase over like last month''s spend or was it over like the year spent?","index":191,"end_time":1647.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1635.89,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"So currently two and a half.","index":192,"end_time":1649.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1647.73,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So, so we, the way that we were working was that we now have 12 leads per month and the ideal is 30 leads per month and the current monthly budgets is two and a half K and then you need four and a half K to get to 30, and that''s 30 days with, you know, with optimizing the campaign.","index":193,"end_time":1670.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1650.61,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So when, once you start them, you don''t touch them for a while.","index":194,"end_time":1674.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1670.44,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah, because what we, I mean, we spent 7,000 last month.","index":195,"end_time":1677.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1674.12,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"I think it was 6,000 in November and then around that same amount in November as well.","index":196,"end_time":1683,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1678.12,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"And we got nowhere near 30 leads.","index":197,"end_time":1686.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1683.6,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"So that''s because of how they''re managing our assets and our campaigns.","index":198,"end_time":1690.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1686.48,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Yeah, because if you''re constantly changing something, it''s like you''re constantly starting the algorithm.","index":199,"end_time":1696.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1691.36,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"From the very people.","index":200,"end_time":1697.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1696.68,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"I told them this and they reassured me that that wasn''t the case.","index":201,"end_time":1702.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1698.56,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"I think it''s very human that you feel like you need to show that you''re working and then people feel the need to show that they''re constantly working on something when sometimes you just need to let it, you know.","index":202,"end_time":1714.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1703.2,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So are you, are you guys able to run our ad sets?","index":203,"end_time":1719.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1716.32,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"What''s the cost?","index":204,"end_time":1721.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1720.96,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Well, I don''t know what.","index":205,"end_time":1723.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1722.96,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I''m not sure at the moment, but I can ask calling to, to get back.","index":206,"end_time":1727.559,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1723.88,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Can you, can you give that over to us today?","index":207,"end_time":1729.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1727.559,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Because we''re looking to make a change fairly quickly.","index":208,"end_time":1733.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1729.8,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"If you can get us the cost or if it''s not a, a costly thing, but it''s more of like an hours work thing, let us know how many hours need to be set for meta ads.","index":209,"end_time":1745.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1734.24,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Was that fair to ask Robert?","index":210,"end_time":1750.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1748.23,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Yes, absolutely.","index":211,"end_time":1755.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1754.309,"speaker_name":"Robert"},{"text":"Sorry I needed on you.","index":212,"end_time":1756.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1755.19,"speaker_name":"Robert"},{"text":"Yeah, for sure.","index":213,"end_time":1757.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1756.87,"speaker_name":"Robert"},{"text":"Okay, I''ll ask Colin and he will get back to today.","index":214,"end_time":1762.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1758.95,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And then for.","index":215,"end_time":1765.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1763.91,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So those were our project updates.","index":216,"end_time":1768.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1766.47,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And then for the HubSpot SMS and for the trial campaign, we are currently working on it.","index":217,"end_time":1776.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1768.07,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"For the SMS campaign we are building the automated HubSpot messages and that, that''s specific to the text that you shared with us already, Milan.","index":218,"end_time":1787.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1776.55,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And for the trial campaign we already have most of it set up.","index":219,"end_time":1792.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1787.43,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"The only thing that the team asked me was to ask about the email body.","index":220,"end_time":1796.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1792.27,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So like what would the campaign actually say?","index":221,"end_time":1799.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1796.63,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Okay, that''s fine.","index":222,"end_time":1801.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1800.05,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Just, just, just to confirm though.","index":223,"end_time":1805.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1803.17,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"So the way it''s being set up is we''re going to run a campaign on Meta, which is a trial campaign.","index":224,"end_time":1812.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1805.57,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"It''s going to have the hubs platforms that you''ve created, one for each club and then it''s going to drop into the hot list for each club as well and it''s going to send an automated email which is saying you''ve just received like a complimentary day pass.","index":225,"end_time":1826.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1812.69,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"I''ll create the content of that email, but that''s how it''s going to work.","index":226,"end_time":1829.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1826.45,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":227,"end_time":1830.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1830.33,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So for, from our side, what we needed to build was we needed to create two separate forms that had all of those categories that you mentioned.","index":228,"end_time":1838.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1830.73,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"But for all of those categories we need to, needed to create separate property properties in HubSpot.","index":229,"end_time":1844.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1838.73,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So for example, when you have a contact they usually have their, you know, email last name, first name listed.","index":230,"end_time":1849.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1844.01,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"But in HubSpot everything needs be to, to be a property on its own.","index":231,"end_time":1853.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1849.49,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So any question that they answered it needs to be a property somewhere.","index":232,"end_time":1856.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1853.06,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Well where the system will track it.","index":233,"end_time":1858.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1856.38,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So now there''s two separate forms that have all of those properties in them.","index":234,"end_time":1863.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1858.74,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And yeah, that''s, you know, for the Meta campaign you have one form for Miami, one form for Fort Lauderdale.","index":235,"end_time":1869.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1863.86,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And then you know, we also need the terms and conditions that you mentioned if there''s anything specific the terms.","index":236,"end_time":1876.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1869.54,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Well, the, it still needs to be the same as like our normal waiver.","index":237,"end_time":1882.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1877.5,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"So it can be the same one.","index":238,"end_time":1884.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1882.94,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah, the actual terms and conditions where it has like our, our liability waiver in one of them and then the, the communication marketing communications one as well and they both need to be mandatory for them to check off.","index":239,"end_time":1897.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1884.78,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"And then the email, I will get that written up and I''ll send that over to you asap.","index":240,"end_time":1904.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1898.86,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"In terms of the punch platforms, can you send them over to me so I can see like what it looks like with those extra like qualifying questions.","index":241,"end_time":1912.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1904.64,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":242,"end_time":1914,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1913.52,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And then, then when.","index":243,"end_time":1917.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1914.8,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"That''s okay.","index":244,"end_time":1918.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1917.48,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"We can create the pages, you know, the non index pages that have to show up on the web page for it to work.","index":245,"end_time":1925.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1918.68,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"But that''s, that''s when we have everything already sorted out.","index":246,"end_time":1928.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1925.84,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So for the.","index":247,"end_time":1930.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1929.68,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"What does.","index":248,"end_time":1932.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1932.49,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Oh yeah, for the HubSpot SMS campaign that''s.","index":249,"end_time":1937.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1933.37,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I don''t need anything additional.","index":250,"end_time":1938.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1937.37,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"The only things were to confirm the context, the content for the emails, and I will send you for the review to see how it looks like in HubSpot so you can see how it all comes together.","index":251,"end_time":1953.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1938.85,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"All right, cool.","index":252,"end_time":1955.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1954.49,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":253,"end_time":1955.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1955.45,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Obviously don''t send any of those automated SMS''s out until.","index":254,"end_time":1960.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1956.93,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"No, no, no.","index":255,"end_time":1961.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1960.69,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"We need to have everything for certain.","index":256,"end_time":1964.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1962.13,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"But I have like just two minutes.","index":257,"end_time":1966.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1964.69,"speaker_name":"Robert"},{"text":"Can you go back to that, that cost slide with the bar graphs on the legion?","index":258,"end_time":1972.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1966.37,"speaker_name":"Robert"},{"text":"Yeah, just a second.","index":259,"end_time":1974.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1973.09,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And just FYI, I''m on hold with the city of Miami.","index":260,"end_time":1979.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1975.89,"speaker_name":"Robert"},{"text":"If they pick up after an hour, I may have to jump.","index":261,"end_time":1983.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1979.25,"speaker_name":"Robert"},{"text":"Just FYI.","index":262,"end_time":1985,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1983.48,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"So right now we''re spending 2500 to generate 12 leads a day.","index":263,"end_time":1990.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1986.2,"speaker_name":"Robert"},{"text":"I know there was a meeting and this was.","index":264,"end_time":1993.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1991.24,"speaker_name":"Robert"},{"text":"I''m sorry, I''m having the wrong conversation.","index":265,"end_time":1996.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1994.36,"speaker_name":"Robert"},{"text":"Apparently.","index":266,"end_time":1997.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1996.84,"speaker_name":"Robert"},{"text":"It''s like you guys are, Are you responsible for our marketing campaigns?","index":267,"end_time":2002.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1997.36,"speaker_name":"Robert"},{"text":"No.","index":268,"end_time":2004.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2004.2,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"No.","index":269,"end_time":2005.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2004.68,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"You''re not.","index":270,"end_time":2005.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2005.04,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Okay, then I''m on the wrong call.","index":271,"end_time":2007.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2005.56,"speaker_name":"Robert"},{"text":"My apologies.","index":272,"end_time":2008.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2007.4,"speaker_name":"Robert"},{"text":"They were just, they, they were just doing an audit of our meta ads from Flavio''s team, basically.","index":273,"end_time":2018.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2012.38,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"So they were just telling us like what they''re doing right, what they''re doing wrong, most of it is wrong.","index":274,"end_time":2024.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2019.58,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"And then giving us the opportunities and pushing their services, basically.","index":275,"end_time":2029.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2025.34,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Oh, so if it was us, if, if they''re doing, if they''re doing everything wrong, can you do it better?","index":276,"end_time":2037.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2030.14,"speaker_name":"Robert"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean most of it like this was done by our team.","index":277,"end_time":2042.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2038.41,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So the meta, the meta audit.","index":278,"end_time":2043.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2042.05,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So they can do it correctly if it''s necessary.","index":279,"end_time":2046.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2043.85,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Like they wouldn''t do it wrong if they know how to do it right.","index":280,"end_time":2049.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2046.37,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So.","index":281,"end_time":2049.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2049.41,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":282,"end_time":2050.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2049.69,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Interesting.","index":283,"end_time":2051.329,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2050.57,"speaker_name":"Robert"},{"text":"Okay, well, more to come on that.","index":284,"end_time":2054.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2051.329,"speaker_name":"Robert"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":285,"end_time":2057.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2055.77,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Colin''s going to send us over pricing or how many hours they would need a month to do something like this and then.","index":286,"end_time":2065.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2057.29,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Yeah, Robert, we should evaluate that.","index":287,"end_time":2067.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2065.32,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":288,"end_time":2069.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2068.32,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":289,"end_time":2070.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2069.92,"speaker_name":"Robert"},{"text":"All right, cool.","index":290,"end_time":2071.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2071.04,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":291,"end_time":2072.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2071.84,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Thank you, Nina.","index":292,"end_time":2073.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2072.28,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Okay, thank you.","index":293,"end_time":2074.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2073.36,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Bye.","index":294,"end_time":2076,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2075.6,"speaker_name":"Robert"},{"text":"Bye.","index":295,"end_time":2076.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2076,"speaker_name":"Milan Wagner"},{"text":"Bye.","index":296,"end_time":2077.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2076.96,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"}],"dateString":"2026-01-07T16:00:00.000Z","host_email":"nina.belina@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/88636878393?pwd=TfdWsZCl10zRsv4cBAbOaWpJ7sz5iM.1","participants":["yefei@yhatinvest.com,alex.white@yhatinvest.com,tatiana@powerhousegymsoflo.com,wyattc@yhatinvest.com,robert.rudder@powerhousesoflo.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,tatiana.fernandez@powerhousesoflo.com,milan.wagner@powerhousesoflo.com,nina.belina@marketersindemand.com,cristina@pgmia.com,mila