INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Powerhouse Gym & Ideometry: Weekly Sync',
  '## **Meta Advertising Campaigns**

The current Meta campaigns are underperforming due to frequent changes disrupting algorithm learning and misuse of AI-generated copy, requiring a more disciplined approach to ad management.

- **Campaigns were over-managed with frequent pausing of ad sets and ads, causing constant resets of the learning phase and leading to rising CPL despite a monthly spend of around 6,000 to 7,000 USD without reaching 30 leads per day** (14:00)
    - The algorithm needs at least **two weeks** of stability to optimize properly before any major changes.
    - Milan Wagner noted the team was pausing entire campaigns or assets too often, which Nina Belina confirmed disrupts performance.
    - Best practice is to maintain at least **five active ad sets**, adding replacements before pausing any underperforming ones.
    - This approach aims to minimize re-learning periods and improve cost efficiency.

- **AI-generated ad copy introduced errors and outdated references, damaging campaign authenticity, especially for the gym and fitness audience** (19:00)
    - Examples included outdated year references in promotional texts, which were flagged and corrected.
    - Nina recommended stopping AI copy use or strictly reviewing and approving all content before publishing.
    - Milan called this lax oversight "laziness," highlighting the need for human checks to preserve genuine messaging.
    - This quality control is critical given the audience’s preference for authentic human communication.

- **To increase qualified leads from current 12 to the target 30 per day, the budget must nearly double from 2,500 USD to about 4,500 USD monthly, paired with improved campaign management** (27:00)
    - Nina explained that the current spend delivers around 12 leads, but optimized campaigns with stable ad sets and better targeting can hit 30 leads.
    - Milan pointed out prior spend of 6,000–7,000 USD without results was due to poor management resetting learning phases.
    - Colin from Nina’s team is tasked to provide pricing and estimated hours to manage Meta ads properly, with a prompt update expected the same day.
    - This cost versus results analysis drives the decision to possibly switch campaign management to Nina’s team.

- **Campaign structure should diversify traffic paths to test lead quality, not just rely on a single HubSpot lead form** (17:00)
    - Nina suggested using multiple ad sets directing users to different destinations: direct lead forms, website conversion pages, and “Join Now” pages.
    - This multi-path approach helps identify which lead source performs best and extends the customer journey strategically.
    - Milan confirmed current practice funnels all leads to a single HubSpot form, limiting testability.
    - Adjusting this will improve data-driven optimization and lead qualification.

## **Website Engagement and Conversion**

Visitors spend less time than initially thought on the site, with most leaving on the pricing page, indicating potential barriers that need testing and possible lead capture improvements.

- **Actual average session engagement is closer to 30 seconds, not 1.5 minutes, due to Google Analytics audience segmentation, with the pricing page seeing the highest drop-off** (22:00)
    - Nina clarified that longer engagement metrics reflect repeat or engaged users, but average engagement across all visitors is low.
    - Milan raised concerns that the pricing page might be turning visitors away due to perceived high costs.
    - Nina suggested this drop-off might reflect typical gym decision processes rather than outright rejection.
    - Retargeting offers like 20% off the first three months could help pull visitors back.

- **Introducing gating on the pricing page by requiring visitor information before viewing prices could increase lead capture if paired with a compelling offer** (24:00)
    - Nina emphasized the need to give visitors a clear value, such as a discount or a free workout, for surrendering their contact details.
    - Milan proposed alternatives including a strong call to action like scheduling a visit or a free trial to justify gating.
    - This tactic aims to convert curious browsers into engaged leads by providing immediate benefits.
    - Implementation would require UX adjustments and clear communication of incentives.

- **Tracking visitor interactions on key pages is currently insufficient; adding tools like Hotjar for heatmaps and detailed user behavior analysis is recommended** (26:00)
    - Nina highlighted Hotjar’s ability to show click patterns, scrolling, and user focus areas, which Google Analytics alone cannot provide.
    - Milan requested the link to Hotjar to evaluate it for immediate adoption.
    - Better tracking will inform website improvements and help optimize conversion funnels.
    - This complements Meta campaign data to provide a fuller picture of user engagement.

## **HubSpot Integration and Campaign Automation**

The HubSpot platform is being enhanced with new forms and automated SMS/email campaigns to support lead capture and nurture, with content and compliance details still pending finalization.

- **Two new HubSpot lead capture forms are created for Miami and Fort Lauderdale clubs, each with detailed properties to track user responses and interests** (30:00)
    - Nina explained that every user answer is stored as a separate property for precise segmentation.
    - Terms and conditions, including liability waivers and marketing consent, will be mandatory checkboxes on these forms.
    - Milan confirmed that the waiver and marketing communication terms will mirror existing documentation.
    - These forms will integrate with Meta campaign leads to ensure accurate data flow.

- **A trial campaign is being set up to funnel Meta leads into HubSpot lists and trigger automated emails offering complimentary day passes, with Milan writing the email content** (30:00)
    - Campaign setup includes separate forms per club and automated follow-up emails.
    - Nina will send the email drafts for review before launch.
    - No SMS or emails will be sent before final approval to maintain control over messaging.
    - This campaign aims to increase trial participation and move leads down the funnel.

- **HubSpot SMS automation is under development based on text content Milan provided, with full integration pending content confirmation** (29:00)
    - Nina confirmed no further input needed besides finalizing email content.
    - The SMS campaign will complement email outreach to maximize lead touchpoints.
    - Monitoring and review processes will ensure quality before live deployment.
    - This layered communication strategy is designed to boost lead engagement.

## **Budget and Resource Planning**

Decisions on campaign management responsibility and cost implications are pending, with quick turnaround needed to improve lead generation results.

- **Nina’s team can run Meta ads properly if engaged, but exact cost and resource estimates are pending from Colin, with a commitment to respond today** (28:00)
    - Milan requested a clear breakdown of hours and fees to decide on switching campaign management quickly.
    - Robert confirmed willingness to evaluate and proceed based on cost-benefit.
    - The urgency stems from current ineffective spend and the need to reach 30 leads daily.
    - This evaluation will determine whether outsourcing ad management improves outcomes.

- **Current campaign management is not handled by Nina’s team; the audit was to identify flaws and offer better service options** (33:00)
    - Robert initially misunderstood the responsibility but agreed to further discussion after clarification.
    - Nina’s team highlighted that the audit revealed common mistakes their team can avoid.
    - This positions Nina’s team as a strong candidate for managing future campaigns.
    - A final decision depends on pricing and resource allocation details from Colin.

## **Strategic Recommendations and Next Steps**

Implementing disciplined campaign management, enhanced tracking, and integrated lead nurturing will improve lead volume and quality while optimizing budget use.

- **Milan and Nina agreed on key improvements: keep campaigns stable for two weeks, replace ad sets before pausing, diversify traffic paths, and review AI-generated copy carefully** (16:00)
    - These steps address campaign performance and audience expectations.
    - They collectively aim to reduce wasted spend and improve lead quality.
    - Adoption of these practices will require training or oversight of current marketing teams.
    - This disciplined approach forms the foundation for scaling lead generation.

- **Implement website behavior tracking tools like Hotjar and consider gating pricing pages with compelling offers to increase lead capture** (26:00)
    - These changes will complement Meta campaigns by converting more visitors into leads.
    - Tracking user behavior will identify friction points and guide UX improvements.
    - Gating with offers aligns with observed user hesitation and decision-making patterns.
    - Together, these tactics enhance the overall marketing funnel effectiveness.

- **Finalize HubSpot campaign content and forms, ensuring legal compliance and seamless integration with Meta campaigns, before launching automated email and SMS sequences** (31:00)
    - Milan will provide email copy promptly; Nina will prepare the systems accordingly.
    - Mandatory terms checkboxes maintain compliance and protect the business.
    - Automated follow-ups aim to increase conversion from lead to trial.
    - Careful rollout and monitoring are planned to optimize results.

- **Await Colin’s cost proposal for Meta campaign management and evaluate the potential switch to Nina’s team to improve campaign outcomes and budget efficiency** (28:00)
    - This decision point is critical to operationalizing the audit recommendations.
    - Robert and Milan will lead the evaluation based on pricing and expected impact.
    - Quick action is needed given the current underperformance and budget waste.
    - Successful transition could unlock the goal of 30 qualified leads daily.',
  '2026-01-07 16:00:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Write and send email content for the trial campaign''s automated email for review (31:22)","completed":false},{"text":"Review and approve the punch platforms/forms with extra qualifying questions once received (31:50)","completed":false},{"text":"Request and receive Hotjar platform link from Nina for heatmap and behavior tracking (26:40)","completed":false},{"text":"Share detailed meta audit and website audit documents with Milan for review (25:40)","completed":false},{"text":"Confirm terms and conditions for use in lead forms aligned with existing waivers (31:20)","completed":false},{"text":"Get pricing and estimated hours required from Colin for managing Meta ads and communicate to Milan and team by end of day (28:47)","completed":false},{"text":"Send HubSpot SMS campaign email content draft for Milan’s review (32:30)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide Hotjar platform link and setup guidance to Milan (26:40)","completed":false},{"text":"Evaluate decision on whether to have Marketers In Demand manage ad sets after pricing/info is received (34:15)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide cost and hours estimate for ongoing Meta ads management to Nina and Milan promptly (28:47)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
  true
FROM new_meeting;

-- Meeting: Rugged Robotics <> MiD Bi-Weekly (2026-01-07 15:00:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    'db0afec5-85bc-41b0-8c0f-79b368eb3b16',
    '2026-01-07 15:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KE7E9NH2H88W8JMYGNBV7QPQ',
    'Rugged Robotics <> MiD Bi-Weekly',
    '{"Rob Schnitzler","Rob Schnitzler","Tristan Pelligrino"}'::text[],
    1960,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/84801960534?pwd=tq9BFJBUCprJPJ0W7NRoAlJYH7bZXD.1&jst=2',
    '{"id":"01KE7E9NH2H88W8JMYGNBV7QPQ","title":"Rugged Robotics <> MiD Bi-Weekly","summary":{"notes":"## **Website Development and Content Updates**\n\nThe website updates are delayed but set for daily focused work starting immediately to prepare for a staging-to-live rollout.\n\n- **Rob Schnitzler committed to dedicating 1.5 hours daily starting after his upcoming Tuesday meeting to progress website copy and content block updates** (03:43)\n    - He acknowledged competing priorities and personal constraints as the main blockers so far.\n    - The goal is to have substantial progress within the next two weeks to support ABM campaigns.\n    - Tristan Pelligrino confirmed readiness to assist with staging environment setup for new dedicated case study pages.\n    - These pages will replicate existing PDFs into a web format, enabling targeted campaign landing pages aligned with email and ad outreach.\n\n## **LinkedIn Business Manager and Advertising Infrastructure**\n\nResolving LinkedIn Business Manager access issues is critical to enable multi-user ad management and HubSpot integration for ABM campaigns.\n\n- **Rob reported ongoing difficulties with LinkedIn ad account administration and support access, delaying account consolidation and billing admin transfers** (05:10)\n    - LinkedIn’s complex product structure and inconsistent support routing are the main challenges.\n    - Tristan explained the strategic value of LinkedIn Business Manager for multi-user access and native integrations, such as custom webhooks syncing LinkedIn lead gen forms with HubSpot.\n    - Resolving this will enable refined targeting of ABM audiences and streamlined campaign management by the marketing team.\n    - Rob plans to reassign billing admin rights from another user to himself to facilitate troubleshooting and direct support contact.\n\n- **LinkedIn ad campaigns continue running without dedicated custom audiences tied to ABM lists, limiting performance tracking and audience precision** (07:30)\n    - Tristan suggested building out LinkedIn custom audiences once access is resolved to improve campaign targeting.\n    - This aligns with ongoing efforts to integrate email and LinkedIn engagement data for enhanced account-level insights.\n\n## **ABM Data Reporting and Engagement Metrics**\n\nA comprehensive multi-source ABM reporting system is in place, tracking email outreach, website visits, and LinkedIn interactions for 43 engaged accounts since mid-December.\n\n- **Tristan demonstrated the integrated reporting combining Smart Lead email campaigns, HubSpot contacts, and Factors website analytics to track ABM engagement** (11:37)\n    - Email tracking logs first outbound emails but excludes subsequent sequence emails due to platform limitations; unsubscribe and reply events are monitored.\n    - Website visits by targeted accounts are identified anonymously via Factors, enabling account-level activity scoring.\n    - LinkedIn ad views and clicks are also captured and tied to account engagement scoring.\n    - The current ABM list includes **43 accounts** with logged engagement since **December 16th**.\n    - Rob expressed interest in accessing Factors directly to explore website visitor data and understand engagement patterns.\n\n- **Tristan and Rob agreed that providing direct Factors access and customizable reporting views would empower sales and marketing teams to identify promising accounts and tailor outreach** (20:07)\n    - They discussed filtering and segmenting accounts based on activity levels, such as multiple LinkedIn ad views combined with recent website visits within 60 days.\n    - Rob noted that some visitor accounts, particularly certain construction companies, are not current sales targets due to service model constraints but remain relevant for future leasing models.\n    - Electrical contractors working on data centers were flagged as high-value targets aligned with direct outreach efforts.\n    - Tristan highlighted the value of early engagement signals for sales intelligence before formal leads convert.\n\n## **Email Outreach and Reply Handling Automation**\n\nThe email outreach system is fully operational, with warmed-up email domains ready to activate and AI-enhanced reply filtering to optimize response handling.\n\n- **Two new email domains, each with 4 warmed-up addresses, have been ready since December 16th for immediate inclusion in outreach** (25:25)\n    - Rob approved folding these new contacts into the campaign to expand reach.\n    - Replies to outreach emails trigger AI analysis to classify response types, improving prioritization of follow-ups.\n    - Tristan explained that all replies generate Slack notifications and broadcast emails to internal and client channels, currently managed by Tristan but soon expanded to include Connor, Trey, and George.\n    - Notifications include detailed context such as campaign source, contact info, and full reply text, enabling quick, personalized follow-up by sales reps.\n    - The system ensures replies are handled naturally through individual email responses rather than automated sequences.\n\n## **Future Targeting and Lookalike Audience Development**\n\nPlans are underway to enhance targeting via lookalike audiences built from industry-standard contact lists to improve campaign precision and reduce outreach fatigue.\n\n- **Rob outlined a strategy to upload curated contact lists from ENR (Engineering News-Record) for trades like electrical and mechanical firms to Clay for lookalike audience generation** (30:46)\n    - This approach will help identify similar companies and contacts beyond those currently targeted.\n    - The data is already logged in HubSpot, enabling seamless integration with outreach workflows.\n    - Rob emphasized that this will be a future task after exhausting initial contact attempts.\n    - Tristan confirmed the team can support building these lookalike segments and integrate them into LinkedIn custom audiences.\n\n- **The outreach approach combines email and phone calls for multi-channel engagement, with potential for evergreen LinkedIn campaigns targeting these refined audiences** (31:38)\n    - Tristan suggested establishing low-cost, ongoing LinkedIn campaigns to maintain visibility with key trade contacts.\n    - Rob agreed to add this as a non-immediate task to develop a customized audience for sustained outreach efforts.\n\n## **Meeting Cadence and Collaboration Workflow**\n\nThe current biweekly meeting schedule will continue, with flexibility to shift to weekly if urgent progress on ABM or website tasks requires it.\n\n- **Rob prefers maintaining biweekly meetings unless website progress demands otherwise, balancing workload and personal commitments** (04:35)\n    - Tristan agreed to maintain this cadence but remain flexible for ad hoc meetings around campaign needs.\n    - Both parties committed to ongoing communication to resolve LinkedIn access and website updates.\n    - Collaborative workflows include shared Slack channels and email notifications for real-time reply handling and campaign monitoring.","outline":null,"keywords":["ABM","LinkedIn Business Manager","HubSpot Integration","Website Updates","Factors Reporting","Smart Lead Email Outreach"],"overview":"- **Website Progress:** Daily updates to website planned; goal to support ABM campaigns in the next two weeks.\n\n- **LinkedIn Access Issues:** Critical access problems delaying ad management; resolving will enhance audience targeting and campaign efficiency.\n\n- **ABM Engagement Metrics:** Tracking metrics for 43 accounts since December; reveals email, website, and LinkedIn interactions for effective outreach.\n\n- **Email Automation:** New email domains ready; AI reply filtering improves follow-up prioritization and provides context for responses.\n\n- **Future Targeting Plans:** Strategy to develop lookalike audiences from industry contacts to refine targeting; focusing on multi-channel outreach methods.\n\n- **Meeting Schedule:** Biweekly meetings will continue unless urgent issues arise; open to additional meetings as needed for progress.","action_items":"\n**Rob Schnitzler**\nAllocate daily 1.5-hour blocks post-meeting Tuesday to progress on website updates and staging (03:40)\nAttempt to assign billing admin role to self on LinkedIn ad account to resolve access issues (05:20)\nCoordinate with team for case study pages creation and online publishing on staging (08:40)\nProvide feedback on website and LinkedIn issues during bi-weekly meetings (04:40)\nEngage new warming email accounts Trey and George into active outreach (25:40)\nShare targeted trade contact lists with marketing for upload to Clay for lookalike audience development (30:45)\n\n**Tristan Pelligrino**\nContinue monitoring ABM email campaigns and generate on-demand custom reports from HubSpot and Factors (14:00)\nProvide Rob and team with Factors platform login and training on data exploration (20:30)\nBuild dedicated case study web pages in staging reflecting PDF content and design (08:45)\nAdd Rob, Connor, Trey, and George to Smart Lead reply notification Slack channels and emails (27:20)\nAssist in setting up LinkedIn custom audience and evergreen campaigns for long-term sales support (31:55)\nFollow up with LinkedIn support contacts or facilitate troubleshooting to enable account access (06:40)\nEnsure Smart Lead AI reply filtering is correctly configured and notifications routed to relevant sales staff (26:40)\n\n**Natalie Mintjens**\nSupport building case study web pages and assisting with website content deployment (08:40)\n"},"duration":32.65999984741211,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"id":1,"name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"id":2,"name":"Tristan Pelligrino"}],"sentences":[{"text":"One sec.","index":0,"end_time":11.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":10.48,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Trying to align headphones.","index":1,"end_time":15.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":11.28,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"There we go.","index":2,"end_time":16.399,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":15.76,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"I like, I had before I went on paternity leave, I had my computer broke and we like sent it in.","index":3,"end_time":26.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":18.72,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"To Dell and like all that stuff.","index":4,"end_time":28.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":26.12,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"And then I just never went through pain of like when I got it.","index":5,"end_time":31.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":28.32,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Back, they had to do a hard.","index":6,"end_time":33.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":31.78,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Reset and I just never went through the pain.","index":7,"end_time":35.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":33.02,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"So now you gotta reconnect everything and go through all that stuff.","index":8,"end_time":40.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":36.3,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, and it''s like down, you know, download Chrome, get the setup back, and.","index":9,"end_time":46.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":40.7,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"It''S just so painful.","index":10,"end_time":47.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":46.74,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"And then for What?","index":11,"end_time":48.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":47.86,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Very oddly, Office 365 on this computer is not automatically downloaded.","index":12,"end_time":55.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":49.02,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Had to go and find that.","index":13,"end_time":58.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":57.8,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"All right, well, New year, new computer, so I think.","index":14,"end_time":63.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":60.44,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":15,"end_time":65.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":64.68,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Well, well, Happy New Year.","index":16,"end_time":67.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":65.8,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I sent you a note before one to, you know, bring on some additional folks that we have here.","index":17,"end_time":74.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":68.76,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Rob, I don''t know if you saw that, but I wanted to pull in both Bailey and Natalie.","index":18,"end_time":80.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":74.28,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So Bailey''s flying today.","index":19,"end_time":82.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":80.64,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We have our leadership meeting on Thursday, Friday.","index":20,"end_time":85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":82.44,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So she''s in the air right now.","index":21,"end_time":87.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":85.62,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So she couldn''t make today''s meeting, but so she''s one of our account directors and on our leadership team.","index":22,"end_time":94.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":87.54,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then Natalie works on her team and so we have some.","index":23,"end_time":97.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":94.22,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Some other hands on the account.","index":24,"end_time":99.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":97.14,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So that''s what I wanted to.","index":25,"end_time":100.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":99.62,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"To get in place for you.","index":26,"end_time":102.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":100.94,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But I''ll still be be meeting with you and you know, making sure everything keeps going based on some of the new things we.","index":27,"end_time":109.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":102.98,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We''ve pushed forward.","index":28,"end_time":111.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":109.5,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So what I wanted to do today, got a couple slides.","index":29,"end_time":115.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":111.54,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I want to go through some of the ABM stuff that did kick off and show you the reporting that''s in place and what some of the data means based on some of the emails that we did, you know, that we have been sending out.","index":30,"end_time":127.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":115.68,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But there''s still some layers that we want to add.","index":31,"end_time":130.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":127.84,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Obviously.","index":32,"end_time":131.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":130.6,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We''ll talk through the.","index":33,"end_time":132.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":131.2,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"The LinkedIn business manager stuff, adding the new email accounts.","index":34,"end_time":136.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":132.48,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I know you have some new sales folks, so we''ll go through all that and then also want to talk about some of our open items like the website and such.","index":35,"end_time":144.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":136.6,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So.","index":36,"end_time":144.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":144.13,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So how does that sound for you?","index":37,"end_time":145.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":144.53,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Sounds perfect.","index":38,"end_time":147.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":146.37,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"All right, let me share.","index":39,"end_time":150.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":148.29,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right, so nice to meet you, Natalie.","index":40,"end_time":160.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":156.05,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Nice to meet you too.","index":41,"end_time":161.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":160.69,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Yes.","index":42,"end_time":162.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":162.21,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Sorry, I just jumped into this here.","index":43,"end_time":164.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":162.69,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right, so here''s agenda I just went through big thing.","index":44,"end_time":171.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":165.89,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I wanted to go through the outstanding stuff.","index":45,"end_time":173.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":171.03,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I thought we''d start there.","index":46,"end_time":175.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":173.67,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So we got the website.","index":47,"end_time":178.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":176.19,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I know, Rob, you were doing quite a bit on that before the holiday, so I wanted to touch base there I know you were looking to not only adjust copy, there were some content blocks and things like that that you were adjusting as well.","index":48,"end_time":194.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":179.31,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So I just wanted to see how that''s going and.","index":49,"end_time":196.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":194.47,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And what we can do to roll staging to live.","index":50,"end_time":200.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":196.88,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay.","index":51,"end_time":201.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":200.64,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Yeah, I.","index":52,"end_time":202.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":201.6,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Look, I had this big plan to.","index":53,"end_time":205,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":202.4,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Like, do it over the.","index":54,"end_time":206.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":205,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Like, actually go through it when it was calm and stuff like that.","index":55,"end_time":210.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":207.28,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"And then, you know, holidays and the kid, stuff like that.","index":56,"end_time":216.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":210.8,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Just kind of.","index":57,"end_time":217.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":216.84,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":58,"end_time":218.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":218.24,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And Natalie, just so you know, Rob''s a new dad, so he''s.","index":59,"end_time":222.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":218.68,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"He''s not sleeping much.","index":60,"end_time":223.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":222.59,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":61,"end_time":224.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":223.79,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"So.","index":62,"end_time":226.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":225.63,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":63,"end_time":227.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":227.23,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":64,"end_time":228.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":227.83,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"So I have some stuff like, as we kick off the new year that I have to do for meeting Tuesday, but after, like in parallel or after that, like, I''m just gonna put like.","index":65,"end_time":240.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":228.43,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"An hour and a half block in my calendar every day and try to make progress on it.","index":66,"end_time":245.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":240.27,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"So there''s not.","index":67,"end_time":245.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":245.11,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Not a lot of updates that''s completely on me and just kind of competing priorities and stuff like that.","index":68,"end_time":251.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":245.79,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Okay, no worries.","index":69,"end_time":252.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":251.68,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"There is this something.","index":70,"end_time":254.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":252.72,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And this is a question I also had.","index":71,"end_time":256.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":255.04,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Rob, do you want to.","index":72,"end_time":257.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":256.76,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Right now we have bi weekly meetings.","index":73,"end_time":259.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":257.84,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Do you want to shift this to weekly or what?","index":74,"end_time":262.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":260,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"There''s a question I had at the end, but I''ll just ask now because we can touch base on the website stuff, you know, during our weekly meetings.","index":75,"end_time":270.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":262.56,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"What I would say is maybe, but like, let''s do two weeks between.","index":76,"end_time":278.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":275.13,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Unless of the ABM stuff or some of the ads, we need to meet next week because I want to have substantial progress on the website and then maybe.","index":77,"end_time":288.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":279.13,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Then maybe we can meet.","index":78,"end_time":289.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":288.85,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"But I think let''s keep two weeks for now.","index":79,"end_time":292.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":289.85,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Just when I.","index":80,"end_time":293.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":292.33,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Everything I have to do and stuff like that.","index":81,"end_time":295.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":293.53,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"All right, sounds good.","index":82,"end_time":297.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":295.69,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So that helps on the website side.","index":83,"end_time":299.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":297.85,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So LinkedIn business manager, I know you''re.","index":84,"end_time":303.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":299.77,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You''re unable to add your ad account, which is kind of strange, but I wanted to know if you.","index":85,"end_time":307.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":303.43,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Did you get any updates from LinkedIn on that at all?","index":86,"end_time":310.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":307.67,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Well, it''s very weird because then it''s like they''re like contact support, and then their support bot is like, not online.","index":87,"end_time":316.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":310.39,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Or something like that.","index":88,"end_time":317.789,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":316.71,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Or it''s like every time I''ve tried to do it, like some other thing has come in the way.","index":89,"end_time":323.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":317.789,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"I''m gonna maybe try to take billing admin away from Paul and make me.","index":90,"end_time":327.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":323.99,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Or make me a billing admin as.","index":91,"end_time":329.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":327.83,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Well on the ad account.","index":92,"end_time":330.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":329.39,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"It''s weird because it''s like contact LinkedIn and sometimes they, like, want you to talk to a salesperson, and then other.","index":93,"end_time":338.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":333.6,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Times it''s like impossible to find.","index":94,"end_time":340.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":338.8,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Like what to do.","index":95,"end_time":344.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":342.88,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"So I, I will take that as well.","index":96,"end_time":346.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":344.24,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Yeah, you''re right.","index":97,"end_time":347.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":346.56,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"If you, if you have like a $200,000 a month budget, they''ll kick you to sales and then otherwise it''s like, it is quite difficult.","index":98,"end_time":356.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":348.32,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We do see like, like a 24 to 48 hour response should be.","index":99,"end_time":362.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":357.12,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"If you can drop in a note.","index":100,"end_time":364.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":362.48,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":101,"end_time":364.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":364.6,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You should be able to just do like something like it''s trying to present an email.","index":102,"end_time":369.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":364.96,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Like an email or.","index":103,"end_time":370.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":369.68,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, there should be that.","index":104,"end_time":373.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":371.32,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Either there''s a contact form there, it''s like a widget or there, there should be somewhere through LinkedIn you can send that as a message and, and I can, you know, if you have difficulty finding that, let me know.","index":105,"end_time":385.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":373.4,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But yeah, I mean, the business manager Rod.","index":106,"end_time":388.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":385.4,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And this is why I wanted to let you.","index":107,"end_time":389.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":388.06,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I mean, and since we''ve been managing accounts like, I mean, four years ago or whatever, they didn''t have this.","index":108,"end_time":395.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":389.14,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But what this allows us to do is, is you give access to marketers in demand, which is our business manager account, then we can, you know, have multiple paid folks on our side evaluate and jump in and such, which is what I want, versus you just giving, like me and Natalie, you know.","index":109,"end_time":414.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":395.46,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":110,"end_time":414.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":414.67,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Access.","index":111,"end_time":415.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":414.91,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m all for doing it.","index":112,"end_time":417.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":415.63,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"I just.","index":113,"end_time":417.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":417.31,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"The way they piece their products together is incredibly confusing.","index":114,"end_time":421.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":417.95,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Right.","index":115,"end_time":422.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":421.63,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"So I''m all for the end result.","index":116,"end_time":425.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":422.83,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"I just, what I thought would be an easy process of creating hasn''t.","index":117,"end_time":429.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":425.39,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"So yeah, they''re, they''re all pretty bad, to be honest.","index":118,"end_time":434.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":430.11,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Meta''s even worse.","index":119,"end_time":435.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":434.39,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But we won''t, we won''t get into that.","index":120,"end_time":438.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":436.43,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, they, they make it hard.","index":121,"end_time":440.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":439.47,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Well, a lot of these also started as like consumer advertising platforms.","index":122,"end_time":444.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":440.59,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Right.","index":123,"end_time":444.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":444.71,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So they didn''t even have like a team concept or even like an agency business management concept either.","index":124,"end_time":450.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":444.91,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So those things have kind of layered on over the years.","index":125,"end_time":453.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":450.89,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But, but that''ll also allow us to, you know, do custom web hooks and events and tap that into HubSpot.","index":126,"end_time":461.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":453.69,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That''s the big thing.","index":127,"end_time":462.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":461.41,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You know, if we do like LinkedIn lead gen forms, we do need that native integration from LinkedIn.","index":128,"end_time":469.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":462.89,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So it''ll allow our user and HubSpot to approve that back and forth.","index":129,"end_time":473.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":469.17,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We''re good on the HubSpot side.","index":130,"end_time":474.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":473.33,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We just need on, on the LinkedIn side as well.","index":131,"end_time":476.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":474.81,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right, so I know you''re working on that.","index":132,"end_time":481.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":479.05,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We still do have the other paid components running.","index":133,"end_time":485.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":482.65,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We just don''t have the dedicated custom audience to this ABM group.","index":134,"end_time":490.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":485.49,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So I just wanted to, to confirm that.","index":135,"end_time":492.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":490.17,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay.","index":136,"end_time":493.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":492.81,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then we did touch upon this before because I know if we roll out even case study ads and things like that, or even links within emails, if we adjust any of those, it would be helpful to have dedicated case study pages.","index":137,"end_time":510.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":494.97,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I wanted to know if that''s something you want us to get into the workflow.","index":138,"end_time":513.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":510.28,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We could build that in the staging environment as you''re already making updates.","index":139,"end_time":517.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":513.6,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You can see what that looks like.","index":140,"end_time":518.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":517.16,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But I wanted to get your thoughts there.","index":141,"end_time":519.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":518.44,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, let''s do that.","index":142,"end_time":521.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":520,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Okay, so Natalie, we''ll get that piece done because there needs to be a high level design.","index":143,"end_time":526.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":521.76,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We already have the PDFs in place.","index":144,"end_time":528.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":526.68,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We''re just going to replicate that on the web and then we''ll have basically a format that we''ll be able to, to build those out with.","index":145,"end_time":535.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":528.24,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right, so we''ll get that rolling, Rob.","index":146,"end_time":538.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":536.32,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then anything else outstanding for you before I get into how the, the ABM activities are being reported on and such?","index":147,"end_time":548.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":540.48,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"No, I don''t think so.","index":148,"end_time":549.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":548.8,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"It''s.","index":149,"end_time":549.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":549.56,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"I mean I''m the blocker on the way to website.","index":150,"end_time":553.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":549.88,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"All right, makes sense.","index":151,"end_time":555.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":554.27,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Let me.","index":152,"end_time":557.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":557.07,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right, so the next piece I''ll go over, I want to just talk, take a few minutes today and like discuss like where the data is coming from and how like you can even check as well so how like some of the data stitched together so the, the first thing in HubSpot and let me, let me stop sharing.","index":153,"end_time":579.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":558.27,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I''ll actually pull up HubSpot for us.","index":154,"end_time":581.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":579.23,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, so one key driver.","index":155,"end_time":598.069,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":596.63,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right, so.","index":156,"end_time":604.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":603.43,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right, so I have a view here.","index":157,"end_time":610.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":609.52,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I can share this publicly if you like.","index":158,"end_time":613.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":611.76,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But what we have is a custom view and the main driver here, Rob, is a custom source of abm.","index":159,"end_time":626.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":614,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So this is the field that we created to drive basically any.","index":160,"end_time":632.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":626.08,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"When we email in smartly, we automatically pull into HubSpot with this custom source.","index":161,"end_time":638.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":633.37,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So that''s how you''re able to see activities here.","index":162,"end_time":641.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":638.65,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So anytime you want to check that out, custom source will be populated there.","index":163,"end_time":649.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":643.21,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then these are all non marketing contacts which I believe we talked about.","index":164,"end_time":653.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":649.85,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We''re still able to pull Those in the HubSpot, record any type of events to them.","index":165,"end_time":660.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":654.17,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"They''re like any other contact, they just don''t count against your tier of ones that you''re paying for.","index":166,"end_time":666.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":661.69,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Within that we''re also for example the, we do log the email.","index":167,"end_time":676.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":667.69,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So every first email that gets sent, there''s a first email event that gets populated.","index":168,"end_time":687.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":679.21,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And so for example this person here, Turner Construction, got this email here and we logged that.","index":169,"end_time":697.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":687.85,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So this was on December 19th.","index":170,"end_time":700.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":697.29,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And so we''re not logging every email that gets sent in that sequence, just the first one.","index":171,"end_time":706.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":700.65,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We do that.","index":172,"end_time":707.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":706.77,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So we don''t, you know, have all these email events flying by and such.","index":173,"end_time":712.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":707.45,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So this basically tells you when the campaign started.","index":174,"end_time":715.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":712.97,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And we do mentioned the, the campaign in Smart Lead that was used.","index":175,"end_time":721.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":715.57,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So that''s the information that we pull in there.","index":176,"end_time":723.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":721.29,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And so for all of these that you would see in an ABM report, you''ll be able to see like when the, you know, the first email was sent.","index":177,"end_time":732.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":723.61,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So if I pull up another one.","index":178,"end_time":733.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":732.29,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Will we also log like the fifth one to just know we like finished.","index":179,"end_time":740.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":735.85,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"The campaign or we assume that we finished.","index":180,"end_time":743.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":740.65,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"We don''t.","index":181,"end_time":745.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":744.78,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, we, we don''t because I don''t think Smart leads has a concluding event or sequence ended event that they can send.","index":182,"end_time":754.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":745.34,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But anytime someone unsubscribes replies any of those events that effectively stop the sequence, we do get those.","index":183,"end_time":767.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":755.34,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So it''s kind of weird.","index":184,"end_time":768.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":767.82,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Smartly doesn''t give us a conclusion event.","index":185,"end_time":770.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":768.66,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We can assume that those do conclude.","index":186,"end_time":772.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":770.9,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But we do get all the other events that would stop the sequence.","index":187,"end_time":776.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":773.54,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And so we''re able to process the replies.","index":188,"end_time":780.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":777.14,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And that''s where we have Slack notifications.","index":189,"end_time":784.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":780.58,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We''ll also send the email out everything that we documented in that plan.","index":190,"end_time":788.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":784.5,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Those replies get handled that way.","index":191,"end_time":791.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":788.74,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And so right now we''ve had one reply which is an out of office reply, but we actually don''t factor that as a reply because we, we filter that out on our side smartly reports it as a reply because we actually got an email automated reply, but we filter that out.","index":192,"end_time":810.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":792.26,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So that''s, that''s where we are there.","index":193,"end_time":813.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":811.8,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We''re tracking the, the events and that''s probably a good time.","index":194,"end_time":817.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":813.6,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I''ll show you the ABM report and we''ll give this to you.","index":195,"end_time":825.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":817.24,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Rob, you can run this on demand anytime you like as well.","index":196,"end_time":828.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":825.33,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So this is where we''re pulling all the data into a separate database.","index":197,"end_time":836.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":831.65,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So this is outside, if you Remember, outside of HubSpot.","index":198,"end_time":839.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":836.37,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And so a lot of these events we can''t track in HubSpot.","index":199,"end_time":845.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":839.65,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"For example, when an account does go visit because we have factors in place which is able to detect the accounts that do arrive on your website.","index":200,"end_time":854.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":845.01,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We don''t know who that person is per se.","index":201,"end_time":858.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":855.98,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So we can''t like tag a user in HubSpot but we still record an account event, a website view, because factors is able to say, hey, someone at for example Turner Construction did visit the website.","index":202,"end_time":870.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":858.46,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We''ll record that event.","index":203,"end_time":872.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":871.02,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We don''t know who it was.","index":204,"end_time":874.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":872.94,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We do know who we send emails to, because we obviously have their emails, but this is just where we stitch all those events together.","index":205,"end_time":882.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":875.31,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So both the email individual activities are tracked here as well as account level activities.","index":206,"end_time":888.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":882.11,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So right now we''ve got 43 accounts engaged.","index":207,"end_time":894.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":889.31,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then so far in this filters data out by anyone it assume or it requires that we have at least sent an email to this domain.","index":208,"end_time":908.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":896.91,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So this is filtering out basically everyone in our ABM list that we''ve emailed.","index":209,"end_time":913.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":908.77,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So any accounts that you see on here are part of that sequence of events.","index":210,"end_time":919.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":913.73,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And so what we do is we put a scoring system together.","index":211,"end_time":922.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":919.73,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So any event that we record, we give it these values up top and then we summarize those based on the date parameter that we put at the top.","index":212,"end_time":932.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":923.65,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So this is everything from December 16th.","index":213,"end_time":935.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":932.74,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":214,"end_time":936.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":935.62,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And so there are a number I, I, I do want to show you factors.","index":215,"end_time":942.779,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":937.3,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I think that''d be helpful to see because there''s a lot of other potential accounts that are visiting your website.","index":216,"end_time":949.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":942.779,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We are only filtering those that are in the ABM list.","index":217,"end_time":952.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":949.54,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So that''s something important to know.","index":218,"end_time":955.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":954.4,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So we''ve got, is there, is there.","index":219,"end_time":959,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":956.4,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"A factors report in Nan that I.","index":220,"end_time":962.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":959,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Can do on demand too to see.","index":221,"end_time":964.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":962.4,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"That, or that''s kind of something we''ll.","index":222,"end_time":966.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":964.6,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Just have to review.","index":223,"end_time":967.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":966.8,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"We can build that quite easily.","index":224,"end_time":969.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":967.6,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We, we have all the events in the database.","index":225,"end_time":971.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":969.64,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So what we could do is I could either give you Factors access and let me, I''ll just show you a preview of that.","index":226,"end_time":982.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":972.48,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Let me, let me just pull that up.","index":227,"end_time":983.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":982.25,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I had it up earlier.","index":228,"end_time":984.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":983.53,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right, so here''s what factors looks like, Rob.","index":229,"end_time":1017.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1012.82,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And so we do have some views we created on the left and essentially Factors allows us to send events outside, so we pull it into our own database.","index":230,"end_time":1032.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1018.98,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But, you know, like I mentioned, we''re filtering those accounts.","index":231,"end_time":1036.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1032.02,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But it might be helpful for you if you just want to look more broadly speaking, who''s identified and visiting the website.","index":232,"end_time":1044.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1036.42,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That''s what you have in place here.","index":233,"end_time":1046.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1044.78,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"The other nice thing with Factors is it''s plugged into HubSpot.","index":234,"end_time":1052.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1047.66,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So if you ever want to see activities of companies that are both in HubSpot as well as those who have visited the website, this is that, that segment.","index":235,"end_time":1064.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1053.1,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then we also take a peek at those that have engaged on LinkedIn.","index":236,"end_time":1069.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1064.95,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right, so these are accounts that have a LinkedIn event ad view or qlik, and then they''ve also visited the website.","index":237,"end_time":1090.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1074.63,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So there''s a couple different lenses that we look at here as well.","index":238,"end_time":1095.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1090.3,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So this is like outside of the ABM data.","index":239,"end_time":1097.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1095.58,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"This is Globally, Rob.","index":240,"end_time":1099.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1097.78,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So any, you know, we''re not filtering any of those domains.","index":241,"end_time":1102.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1099.14,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"This is pretty much any visitor that is identified shows up in these reports.","index":242,"end_time":1106.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1102.34,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And so there''s a couple other different views that we have here.","index":243,"end_time":1111.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1108.94,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And this might be something for.","index":244,"end_time":1115.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1113.51,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"For us to think through because, you know, ABM is like a cohort.","index":245,"end_time":1119.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1115.47,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But then there also are other companies obviously that are showing signals.","index":246,"end_time":1124.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1119.27,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Either they''ve seen multiple ads and have visited the website.","index":247,"end_time":1128.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1124.63,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"They just haven''t filled out a form yet.","index":248,"end_time":1130.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1129.03,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You know, so that''s what we call kind of like signals early.","index":249,"end_time":1134.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1131.51,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"They haven''t, they haven''t really raised their hand, so to speak, or maybe even replied and become a lead in HubSpot.","index":250,"end_time":1140.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1134.51,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But it might be a good mechanism for some of the new sales folks to maybe get a filtered list or something like that to go through.","index":251,"end_time":1148.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1141.64,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay, yeah, that''s what I was thinking.","index":252,"end_time":1150.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1148.92,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"It''s like.","index":253,"end_time":1151,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1150.44,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Maybe we do do weekly and then there''s some kind of report or something we just can kind of download.","index":254,"end_time":1163,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1153.48,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"And it''s like obviously like rippling and link.","index":255,"end_time":1167.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1163.16,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Link.","index":256,"end_time":1168.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1167.68,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Te or something like that.","index":257,"end_time":1170.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1168.56,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":258,"end_time":1170.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1170.52,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Link tree.","index":259,"end_time":1171.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1170.84,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":260,"end_time":1172.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1171.76,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"So some of these.","index":261,"end_time":1172.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1172.12,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, but like there will be garbage, but.","index":262,"end_time":1178.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1175.6,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And there''s like gcs that we''re kind of interested in, but not really right now, but like the, the electrical one.","index":263,"end_time":1185.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1178.64,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Was I.","index":264,"end_time":1187.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1186.96,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"You know, one of the bigger ones.","index":265,"end_time":1189.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1187.92,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"There''s an electrical one at the bottom.","index":266,"end_time":1190.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1189.12,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Which could be, could be related to their, like this, their direct outreach.","index":267,"end_time":1196.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1191.28,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"So it''s interesting to kind of connect the dots.","index":268,"end_time":1198.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1196.47,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":269,"end_time":1199.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1198.79,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Did you see that?","index":270,"end_time":1199.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1199.11,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Which one was it?","index":271,"end_time":1200.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1199.63,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Hey, electrical.","index":272,"end_time":1201.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1200.23,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"It''s like dub.","index":273,"end_time":1204.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1201.27,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Dub back.","index":274,"end_time":1205.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1204.63,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Electoral or something like that.","index":275,"end_time":1207.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1206.47,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"This one?","index":276,"end_time":1208.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1207.91,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, the, the other.","index":277,"end_time":1211.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1208.87,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay, so this is helpful.","index":278,"end_time":1214.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1211.59,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So they''ve seen.","index":279,"end_time":1218.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1217.35,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":280,"end_time":1221.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1220.89,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Since December, so.","index":281,"end_time":1222.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1221.13,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And I think that''s what''s helpful too.","index":282,"end_time":1225.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1223.53,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And, and we, we like factors because it gives you more of a, you know, like a 360 view of, of the different.","index":283,"end_time":1232.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1225.09,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Stuff.","index":284,"end_time":1234.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1234.25,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"I think given that, like there''s this.","index":285,"end_time":1236.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1234.69,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Detail in here, maybe getting a log.","index":286,"end_time":1237.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1236.13,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we do have clients and, and there are different ways to.","index":287,"end_time":1242.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1238.65,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And you can even think about this, like how you would like to use this information.","index":288,"end_time":1246.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1243.21,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We could definitely process this data in N8N and pull it somewhere else for you.","index":289,"end_time":1253.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1247.96,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Filter it, send you an email.","index":290,"end_time":1255.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1253.8,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We can do that or we can build you segments in here.","index":291,"end_time":1259.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1255.76,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Like, if you have different logic, if you tell us.","index":292,"end_time":1261.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1259.4,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I would love to see someone that has, you know, at least viewed a LinkedIn ad two times they visited the website within the last 60 days.","index":293,"end_time":1271.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1262.12,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Like, you know, that type of stuff.","index":294,"end_time":1272.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1271.36,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You can Build.","index":295,"end_time":1273.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1272.6,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, I think just having a login.","index":296,"end_time":1276.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1274.91,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"And playing around with understanding what''s there.","index":297,"end_time":1279.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1276.75,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Is probably where we''re at right now versus having those defined segments.","index":298,"end_time":1290.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1281.95,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"I just want to see what data.","index":299,"end_time":1292.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1290.67,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Is available, who''s clicking and stuff like that.","index":300,"end_time":1295.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1292.39,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Yeah, and another thing too is, you know, we''ll do this a lot of times.","index":301,"end_time":1301.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1296.03,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We''ll, we''ll down select.","index":302,"end_time":1303.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1301.97,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I think we do have.","index":303,"end_time":1306.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1305.17,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yes, we have like some filters here.","index":304,"end_time":1308.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1306.53,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, we can set this up.","index":305,"end_time":1311.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1309.73,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But so like there''s some scoring we can do within factors itself.","index":306,"end_time":1315.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1311.25,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So we kind of use their events and build that report.","index":307,"end_time":1317.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1315.33,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But then you might want to score things in here like you know, evaluate any accounts that have a certain amount of activity and pull that into a segment so we can do that as well.","index":308,"end_time":1328.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1318.05,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So just like context wise for you all, like some of those construction companies, it''s like both good that there''s interest, but we don''t really have a product for them for like six months.","index":309,"end_time":1341.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1329.55,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"So we''re like the salespeople today are focused on bigger customers that we could.","index":310,"end_time":1348.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1342.99,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Do a lot of direct service.","index":311,"end_time":1349.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1348.23,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"So you go on site for some of those construction companies are definitely visiting us because maybe they''re evaluating hp.","index":312,"end_time":1359,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1349.59,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Hewlett Packer has a product and then Dusty Robotics has a product and maybe they''re evaluating like leasing or buying one.","index":313,"end_time":1367.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1359.24,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Of those and they want to take.","index":314,"end_time":1369.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1367.68,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Take a look at Rugged as well.","index":315,"end_time":1371.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1369.56,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"But the, the issue is right now like we''re not going to go to a random job site in Kansas City.","index":316,"end_time":1377,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1371.4,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"And perform the service for them.","index":317,"end_time":1379.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1377.24,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"So we kind of really have.","index":318,"end_time":1380.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1379.44,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"So there''ll be more things to do as we add kind of the leasing model over time.","index":319,"end_time":1386,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1381.44,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"But it''s still interesting to see like.","index":320,"end_time":1388.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1386.8,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Who, you know, who''s visiting and stuff like that.","index":321,"end_time":1391.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1388.56,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Where the electrical, the electrical one is like somewhat depending on how big they are, is like aligned with who we''re.","index":322,"end_time":1399.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1391.36,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Doing some direct outreach to of electrical.","index":323,"end_time":1402.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1399.48,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Like electrical firms that are working on data centers and could be million dollar.","index":324,"end_time":1407.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1402.4,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Plus accounts for us.","index":325,"end_time":1408.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1407.78,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"So.","index":326,"end_time":1409.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1409.3,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Yeah, and the other thing too, I know Rob, when you were working on board meetings and such, some of this signal data might be helpful to pull together as well before someone fills out a form or you know, call someone at Rugged.","index":327,"end_time":1426.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1409.86,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Right.","index":328,"end_time":1426.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1426.26,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Like you could say like here, here''s kind of some company segment or industry segments.","index":329,"end_time":1431.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1426.5,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Here''s some of the activity that we''re seeing and it gives you some data that''s earlier, you know, before you get those, those conversion events.","index":330,"end_time":1441.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1432.42,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So.","index":331,"end_time":1441.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1441.36,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":332,"end_time":1443.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1441.68,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"All right, let me see.","index":333,"end_time":1446.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1445.44,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right, so want to make sure I hit on everything.","index":334,"end_time":1463.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1459.76,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So review scoring system filtering factors and then.","index":335,"end_time":1468,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1463.24,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, so all the LinkedIn ad view and clicks that you see in the ABM report, that stems from factors.","index":336,"end_time":1476.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1469.28,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All the email activity is from Smart Lead.","index":337,"end_time":1479.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1476.96,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then you have all the.","index":338,"end_time":1481.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1480,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"The folks in HubSpot that we''ve conducted outreach to at least one email using that custom source.","index":339,"end_time":1489.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1481.76,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So that''s kind of where most of the data is connected for you.","index":340,"end_time":1492.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1489.64,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then, you know, with this we.","index":341,"end_time":1496.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1493.36,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We also have two.","index":342,"end_time":1498.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1496.95,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Well, a number of emails I wanted to see if you wanted those have been warmed up.","index":343,"end_time":1506.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1499.55,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Where''s.","index":344,"end_time":1512.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1511.87,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Yeah, we have Trey and George both.","index":345,"end_time":1527.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1525.72,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We have I think four emails each of those domains.","index":346,"end_time":1532.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1527.96,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Those have been warming up Rob since the 16th.","index":347,"end_time":1536.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1532.6,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So they''re pretty much ready to go.","index":348,"end_time":1538.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1536.44,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"If you want us to fold those two folks in as well.","index":349,"end_time":1541.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1538.68,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, we can do that.","index":350,"end_time":1543,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1541.96,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Okay.","index":351,"end_time":1544.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1543.64,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So now we can turn on pretty quickly.","index":352,"end_time":1546.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1544.76,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So if someone replies to them, they get the email.","index":353,"end_time":1553.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1549.39,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Yeah, so let me pull that up quick.","index":354,"end_time":1557.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1554.35,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So many windows open trying to get word.","index":355,"end_time":1595.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1592.6,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right.","index":356,"end_time":1596.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1595.88,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"So.","index":357,"end_time":1596.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1596.24,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So yeah, Rob, so basically I think I showed this to you at some point.","index":358,"end_time":1602.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1596.92,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But what we do is we.","index":359,"end_time":1605.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1603.45,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Any Smart Lead activity that comes by, if there is a reply, we actually use AI to figure out what type of reply it is.","index":360,"end_time":1616.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1606.09,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So Smart Lead has like its own filtering but we bypass that and use our own because sometimes someone will say I''m not, I''m not interested.","index":361,"end_time":1627.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1616.25,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Or here''s another person that, that you should speak to.","index":362,"end_time":1630.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1627.9,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"There''s a little bit more nuance to it.","index":363,"end_time":1632.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1630.82,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So that''s why we use this here.","index":364,"end_time":1634.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1632.66,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But based on the replies that we do get, we are sending a message to Slack Channel and then also an email that comes from Connor''s email.","index":365,"end_time":1648.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1634.58,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And.","index":366,"end_time":1649.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1649.54,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Connor would get an email.","index":367,"end_time":1666.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1665.31,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Yeah, right now it''s just going to me.","index":368,"end_time":1669.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1666.83,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So I need to fix that.","index":369,"end_time":1671.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1669.71,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then the Slack would be like.","index":370,"end_time":1673.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1671.95,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"RMID Slack or something else.","index":371,"end_time":1676.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1673.71,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Yeah, that it''s connected to our Slack channel.","index":372,"end_time":1679.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1676.75,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So the id.","index":373,"end_time":1680.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1679.75,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Slack channel id.","index":374,"end_time":1683.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1682.57,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":375,"end_time":1690.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1690.25,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So we''re sending it to our internal and then also the client.","index":376,"end_time":1694.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1690.65,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So our shared Slack both.","index":377,"end_time":1696.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1694.57,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So at a minimum that that''s.","index":378,"end_time":1698.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1696.97,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That will go through.","index":379,"end_time":1700.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1699.29,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I do need.","index":380,"end_time":1700.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1700.09,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Let me make a note.","index":381,"end_time":1701.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1700.65,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I need to.","index":382,"end_time":1701.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1701.41,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Because for testing purposes I didn''t have you guys on all those emails.","index":383,"end_time":1705.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1701.93,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I need to flip that.","index":384,"end_time":1706.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1705.53,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So I''m going to add you, Connor, Trey and George on those.","index":385,"end_time":1712.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1707.34,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Would they all get the email or.","index":386,"end_time":1715.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1713.66,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Be who it was sent from?","index":387,"end_time":1717.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1715.18,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Right now any reply to anyone in Smartly will go.","index":388,"end_time":1722.979,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1718.3,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Will get a broadcasted email but they will then be able to reply to that Using their own email, and just reply naturally from there.","index":389,"end_time":1732.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1722.979,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay.","index":390,"end_time":1733.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1733.32,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"And it''ll say in the email itself.","index":391,"end_time":1737.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1733.96,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Like, who it came from or something.","index":392,"end_time":1740.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1737.64,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Yeah, exactly.","index":393,"end_time":1741.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1740.84,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So we''re setting a bunch of data, like, here''s the whole thing.","index":394,"end_time":1746.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1741.68,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So you get contact information, who it was, what campaign it came from, what their actual reply was.","index":395,"end_time":1753.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1746.44,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All this is within the response, and then it just says, copy the reply text above and then reply from your regular company email.","index":396,"end_time":1762.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1754.12,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay.","index":397,"end_time":1763.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1762.97,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":398,"end_time":1768.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1767.93,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"All right.","index":399,"end_time":1769.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1768.73,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So that''s the extent of it.","index":400,"end_time":1771.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1769.77,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So I got a few things to take care of on our side.","index":401,"end_time":1773.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1771.09,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then, you know, as you''re working through LinkedIn website stuff, let me know if anything comes up and we''ll touch base.","index":402,"end_time":1781.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1773.53,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"One question I have for you, I.","index":403,"end_time":1784.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1782.01,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Thought of as we doing it.","index":404,"end_time":1785.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1784.17,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"So they''re doing a kind of campaign.","index":405,"end_time":1788.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1786.16,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Where we want to have them kind of like, find the right people at some of these trades.","index":406,"end_time":1796.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1789.36,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"So the electrical, mechanical, et cetera, that are working on data centers, and then.","index":407,"end_time":1802.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1796.8,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"They''Re doing, like, somewhat customized targeted outreach.","index":408,"end_time":1806.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1802.2,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Across channels and that sort of thing.","index":409,"end_time":1809.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1806.6,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"How customized it is, I''m not 100% sure yet.","index":410,"end_time":1814.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1811.37,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"But that''s.","index":411,"end_time":1815.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1814.57,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"The theory is there''s only so many big electrical trades that we want to.","index":412,"end_time":1819.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1815.93,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Talk to that you don''t burn your shot.","index":413,"end_time":1823.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1819.85,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"You reach out to them, customize message.","index":414,"end_time":1826.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1823.41,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"And you gotta find the right level and the right person, stuff like that.","index":415,"end_time":1830.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1826.73,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"If we have those lists, though, can we upload those lists to Clay and then see, like, lookalike people or something that Clay''s doing?","index":416,"end_time":1844.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1833.21,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Or, like.","index":417,"end_time":1845.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1844.32,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Yeah, 100%.","index":418,"end_time":1847.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1846.88,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay.","index":419,"end_time":1849.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1848.4,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"So that''s something we could maybe do over time.","index":420,"end_time":1850.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1849.2,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"So they''re using an enr.","index":421,"end_time":1852.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1850.8,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"ENR is like, the kind of, like, de facto industry standard.","index":422,"end_time":1854.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1852.12,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"They''re using, like, industry list of ENR revenue and kind of, like, top people.","index":423,"end_time":1860.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1854.88,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"So.","index":424,"end_time":1861.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1861.36,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"And that data is all in HubSpot.","index":425,"end_time":1864.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1863.12,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"When they reach out, like, they''re logging.","index":426,"end_time":1866.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1864.88,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"In HubSpot, So not.","index":427,"end_time":1870.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1866.56,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Not immediate, but that''s something we can.","index":428,"end_time":1872.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1870.46,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Do when they''ve kind of exhausted and they say, hey, I''ve reached out to.","index":429,"end_time":1876.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1872.22,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Like, six people at this firm and stuff like that.","index":430,"end_time":1879.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1876.54,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"We can just upload all the contacts and titles and stuff to Clay and.","index":431,"end_time":1884.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1879.38,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"See what Clay produces for, like, lookalike companies and contacts.","index":432,"end_time":1888.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1884.34,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Yeah, 100%.","index":433,"end_time":1889.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1888.62,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And.","index":434,"end_time":1890.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1889.7,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And also, Rob, like, if you want, like, more air cover, they''re doing email.","index":435,"end_time":1896.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1890.3,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Are they.","index":436,"end_time":1896.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1896.52,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Are they dialing as well?","index":437,"end_time":1898.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1896.96,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"They''re calling, like, their message to do a combo.","index":438,"end_time":1901.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1898.68,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":439,"end_time":1901.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1901.36,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Okay.","index":440,"end_time":1902.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1901.8,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":441,"end_time":1902.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1902.32,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I mean, we could do a custom audience in LinkedIn as well, if you want, because you probably have some, you know, some, some ad content.","index":442,"end_time":1910.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1902.64,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You could do that relatively inexpensively and maybe even just have an evergreen campaign that''s always running to those folks just up there.","index":443,"end_time":1922.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1911.24,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":444,"end_time":1922.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1922.13,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Let''s add that as, like, a task for not very immediate, but, like, hey.","index":445,"end_time":1927.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1922.85,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Just like, future task of, like, let''s get the customized audience of that campaign.","index":446,"end_time":1932.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1927.85,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Yep.","index":447,"end_time":1934.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1933.89,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yep.","index":448,"end_time":1934.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1934.37,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We can help you build that out in clay, kind of give you some.","index":449,"end_time":1939.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1934.69,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Some other lookalike companies and.","index":450,"end_time":1940.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1939.01,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And go that direction for sure.","index":451,"end_time":1942.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1940.81,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay.","index":452,"end_time":1943.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1942.85,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":453,"end_time":1944.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1943.73,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"All right.","index":454,"end_time":1945.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1945.09,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Well, good deal, Rob.","index":455,"end_time":1946.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1945.81,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Thanks, man.","index":456,"end_time":1947.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1947.14,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Appreciate you dialing in this morning, and we''ll chat soon.","index":457,"end_time":1950.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1947.54,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":458,"end_time":1951.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1951.22,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":459,"end_time":1952.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1951.74,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":460,"end_time":1953.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1952.66,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Bye.","index":461,"end_time":1953.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1953.14,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"}],"dateString":"2026-01-07T15:00:00.000Z","host_email":"tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/84801960534?pwd=tq9BFJBUCprJPJ0W7NRoAlJYH7bZXD.1&jst=2","participants":["tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com,rob@rugged-robotics.com,baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com,nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com","rob@rugged-robotics.com","baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KE7E9NH2H88W8JMYGNBV7QPQ","organizer_email":"tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Enabled account directors Natalie and Bailey to support Rob; Bailey unavailable due to travel.","Committed to daily website progress; Rob to calendar 1.5-hour work blocks per day.","Launched ABM reporting integrations across HubSpot, SmartLead, and Factors for cross-channel insights.","Agreed to build dedicated case study pages in staging for reuse across campaigns.","Prepared additional sales emails; Rob approved adding Trey and George to SmartLead outreach."],"highlights":[{"quote":"I''m just gonna put like an hour and a half block in my calendar every day and try to make progress on it.","speaker":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"quote":"So this is where we''re pulling all the data into a separate database... event scoring is summarized.","speaker":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"quote":"Yeah, we can do that.","speaker":"Rob Schnitzler"}],"topics":["abm","website","reporting","sales","delivery"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-07T21:42:10Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Website Development and Content Updates**\n\nThe website updates are delayed but set for daily focused work starting immediately to prepare for a staging-to-live rollout.\n\n- **Rob Schnitzler committed to dedicating 1.5 hours daily starting after his upcoming Tuesday meeting to progress website copy and content block updates** (03:43)\n    - He acknowledged competing priorities and personal constraints as the main blockers so far.\n    - The goal is to have substantial progress within the next two weeks to support ABM campaigns.\n    - Tristan Pelligrino confirmed readiness to assist with staging environment setup for new dedicated case study pages.\n    - These pages will replicate existing PDFs into a web format, enabling targeted campaign landing pages aligned with email and ad outreach.\n\n## **LinkedIn Business Manager and Advertising Infrastructure**\n\nResolving LinkedIn Business Manager access issues is critical to enable multi-user ad management and HubSpot integration for ABM campaigns.\n\n- **Rob reported ongoing difficulties with LinkedIn ad account administration and support access, delaying account consolidation and billing admin transfers** (05:10)\n    - LinkedIn’s complex product structure and inconsistent support routing are the main challenges.\n    - Tristan explained the strategic value of LinkedIn Business Manager for multi-user access and native integrations, such as custom webhooks syncing LinkedIn lead gen forms with HubSpot.\n    - Resolving this will enable refined targeting of ABM audiences and streamlined campaign management by the marketing team.\n    - Rob plans to reassign billing admin rights from another user to himself to facilitate troubleshooting and direct support contact.\n\n- **LinkedIn ad campaigns continue running without dedicated custom audiences tied to ABM lists, limiting performance tracking and audience precision** (07:30)\n    - Tristan suggested building out LinkedIn custom audiences once access is resolved to improve campaign targeting.\n    - This aligns with ongoing efforts to integrate email and LinkedIn engagement data for enhanced account-level insights.\n\n## **ABM Data Reporting and Engagement Metrics**\n\nA comprehensive multi-source ABM reporting system is in place, tracking email outreach, website visits, and LinkedIn interactions for 43 engaged accounts since mid-December.\n\n- **Tristan demonstrated the integrated reporting combining Smart Lead email campaigns, HubSpot contacts, and Factors website analytics to track ABM engagement** (11:37)\n    - Email tracking logs first outbound emails but excludes subsequent sequence emails due to platform limitations; unsubscribe and reply events are monitored.\n    - Website visits by targeted accounts are identified anonymously via Factors, enabling account-level activity scoring.\n    - LinkedIn ad views and clicks are also captured and tied to account engagement scoring.\n    - The current ABM list includes **43 accounts** with logged engagement since **December 16th**.\n    - Rob expressed interest in accessing Factors directly to explore website visitor data and understand engagement patterns.\n\n- **Tristan and Rob agreed that providing direct Factors access and customizable reporting views would empower sales and marketing teams to identify promising accounts and tailor outreach** (20:07)\n    - They discussed filtering and segmenting accounts based on activity levels, such as multiple LinkedIn ad views combined with recent website visits within 60 days.\n    - Rob noted that some visitor accounts, particularly certain construction companies, are not current sales targets due to service model constraints but remain relevant for future leasing models.\n    - Electrical contractors working on data centers were flagged as high-value targets aligned with direct outreach efforts.\n    - Tristan highlighted the value of early engagement signals for sales intelligence before formal leads convert.\n\n## **Email Outreach and Reply Handling Automation**\n\nThe email outreach system is fully operational, with warmed-up email domains ready to activate and AI-enhanced reply filtering to optimize response handling.\n\n- **Two new email domains, each with 4 warmed-up addresses, have been ready since December 16th for immediate inclusion in outreach** (25:25)\n    - Rob approved folding these new contacts into the campaign to expand reach.\n    - Replies to outreach emails trigger AI analysis to classify response types, improving prioritization of follow-ups.\n    - Tristan explained that all replies generate Slack notifications and broadcast emails to internal and client channels, currently managed by Tristan but soon expanded to include Connor, Trey, and George.\n    - Notifications include detailed context such as campaign source, contact info, and full reply text, enabling quick, personalized follow-up by sales reps.\n    - The system ensures replies are handled naturally through individual email responses rather than automated sequences.\n\n## **Future Targeting and Lookalike Audience Development**\n\nPlans are underway to enhance targeting via lookalike audiences built from industry-standard contact lists to improve campaign precision and reduce outreach fatigue.\n\n- **Rob outlined a strategy to upload curated contact lists from ENR (Engineering News-Record) for trades like electrical and mechanical firms to Clay for lookalike audience generation** (30:46)\n    - This approach will help identify similar companies and contacts beyond those currently targeted.\n    - The data is already logged in HubSpot, enabling seamless integration with outreach workflows.\n    - Rob emphasized that this will be a future task after exhausting initial contact attempts.\n    - Tristan confirmed the team can support building these lookalike segments and integrate them into LinkedIn custom audiences.\n\n- **The outreach approach combines email and phone calls for multi-channel engagement, with potential for evergreen LinkedIn campaigns targeting these refined audiences** (31:38)\n    - Tristan suggested establishing low-cost, ongoing LinkedIn campaigns to maintain visibility with key trade contacts.\n    - Rob agreed to add this as a non-immediate task to develop a customized audience for sustained outreach efforts.\n\n## **Meeting Cadence and Collaboration Workflow**\n\nThe current biweekly meeting schedule will continue, with flexibility to shift to weekly if urgent progress on ABM or website tasks requires it.\n\n- **Rob prefers maintaining biweekly meetings unless website progress demands otherwise, balancing workload and personal commitments** (04:35)\n    - Tristan agreed to maintain this cadence but remain flexible for ad hoc meetings around campaign needs.\n    - Both parties committed to ongoing communication to resolve LinkedIn access and website updates.\n    - Collaborative workflows include shared Slack channels and email notifications for real-time reply handling and campaign monitoring.","outline":null,"keywords":["ABM","LinkedIn Business Manager","HubSpot Integration","Website Updates","Factors Reporting","Smart Lead Email Outreach"],"overview":"- **Website Progress:** Daily updates to website planned; goal to support ABM campaigns in the next two weeks.\n\n- **LinkedIn Access Issues:** Critical access problems delaying ad management; resolving will enhance audience targeting and campaign efficiency.\n\n- **ABM Engagement Metrics:** Tracking metrics for 43 accounts since December; reveals email, website, and LinkedIn interactions for effective outreach.\n\n- **Email Automation:** New email domains ready; AI reply filtering improves follow-up prioritization and provides context for responses.\n\n- **Future Targeting Plans:** Strategy to develop lookalike audiences from industry contacts to refine targeting; focusing on multi-channel outreach methods.\n\n- **Meeting Schedule:** Biweekly meetings will continue unless urgent issues arise; open to additional meetings as needed for progress.","action_items":"\n**Rob Schnitzler**\nAllocate daily 1.5-hour blocks post-meeting Tuesday to progress on website updates and staging (03:40)\nAttempt to assign billing admin role to self on LinkedIn ad account to resolve access issues (05:20)\nCoordinate with team for case study pages creation and online publishing on staging (08:40)\nProvide feedback on website and LinkedIn issues during bi-weekly meetings (04:40)\nEngage new warming email accounts Trey and George into active outreach (25:40)\nShare targeted trade contact lists with marketing for upload to Clay for lookalike audience development (30:45)\n\n**Tristan Pelligrino**\nContinue monitoring ABM email campaigns and generate on-demand custom reports from HubSpot and Factors (14:00)\nProvide Rob and team with Factors platform login and training on data exploration (20:30)\nBuild dedicated case study web pages in staging reflecting PDF content and design (08:45)\nAdd Rob, Connor, Trey, and George to Smart Lead reply notification Slack channels and emails (27:20)\nAssist in setting up LinkedIn custom audience and evergreen campaigns for long-term sales support (31:55)\nFollow up with LinkedIn support contacts or facilitate troubleshooting to enable account access (06:40)\nEnsure Smart Lead AI reply filtering is correctly configured and notifications routed to relevant sales staff (26:40)\n\n**Natalie Mintjens**\nSupport building case study web pages and assisting with website content deployment (08:40)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"6e380313-3d9d-405e-b968-03d65b24c00d","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
