-- Meeting: New North Techmode meeting (2026-01-06 19:30:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    'b1f3ae44-0316-492e-aef1-bb260b814482',
    '2026-01-06 19:30:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KE7AN235EECZ4Q5XWX18VT9G',
    'New North Techmode meeting',
    '{"Colin Costigan","Christopher Quigley","Matthew Look","Lindsay Hall","Ryan Fisher"}'::text[],
    1990,
    'https://teams.microsoft.com/l/meetup-join/19:meeting_MzQ2YzRjZDItMDkwYy00MzJlLWE1YWMtZWVjNzYxNDRjZGY4@thread.v2/0?context={"Tid":"3801011d-e732-48ee-be2a-e499b1a29ba4","Oid":"e591be63-0f4d-423b-b320-5caca12ffa3b"}',
    '{"id":"01KE7AN235EECZ4Q5XWX18VT9G","title":"New North Techmode meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Website and Landing Page Updates**\n\nThe team finalized key webpage updates and improved internal linking to support upcoming ad campaigns.\n\n- **MSP reseller and virtual IP pages** were updated to include interlinking and an FAQ explaining the **NPS score of 85**, enhancing user guidance and SEO relevance (03:59)\n    - The MSP page now places key info just below the hero section for better visibility\n    - Links were added to boxes directing visitors to relevant articles and landing pages\n    - The “apply and onboard” button now opens the form directly on the page, reducing friction\n    - These changes align with Matthew Look’s feedback and received approval from Lindsay Hall\n\n- A new **campaign landing page focused on Microsoft integrations** was completed to target Bing users searching Microsoft-related terms (05:41)\n    - This page intends to position the product as a strong alternative for Microsoft Teams users\n    - Matthew questioned the narrow targeting of Teams users, noting RingCentral holds significantly larger market share, prompting Colin Costigan to plan additional headline options and send updated content for review\n    - The team agreed to finalize this page and launch ad campaigns once approved\n\n## **SEO Strategy and AI Search Optimization**\n\nThe team aligned on evolving SEO tactics to prepare for AI-driven search behaviors expected by 2026.\n\n- Matthew Look emphasized the need to **shift from generic blog posts to AI-trusted content** focused on competitor comparisons and case studies to improve visibility in AI-powered search results (07:59)\n    - He highlighted that current searchers still use Google or Bing rather than AI chat for product replacement queries, but this will change over the next 3–5 years\n    - Ryan Fisher and Colin supported this view, noting AI tools pull from Google''s organic rankings and user engagement signals\n\n- Based on AI content analysis, the team agreed to add a **navigation section comparing TechMode directly with competitors like RingCentral and Nextiva** to increase inclusion in AI recommendations (12:16)\n    - Colin explained that AI values accurate, detailed feature breakdowns as “source of truth” to recommend products confidently\n    - Matthew plans to meet with his team to develop a phased plan for this content, targeting gradual rollout through 2026 to secure long-term SEO gains\n\n- The team discussed new SEO metrics such as the **AI citation rate**, which tracks how often TechMode appears in AI-generated content, and committed to upgrading their SEO tool to access this data for about **$10/month** (21:38)\n    - Lindsay confirmed the upgrade is affordable and will be pursued to improve AI performance tracking\n\n- Colin clarified that AI crawlers rely on the website’s **sitemap to discover all blog posts**, even those not listed on public pages, ensuring hidden content still contributes to SEO and AI indexing (26:03)\n\n## **Google Ads and Campaign Management**\n\nThe team resolved recent Google Ad issues and prepared to launch new campaigns on Bing.\n\n- The **Google Ads campaigns paused due to website plugin vulnerabilities** were fully resolved, with a clean sweep from Google Search Console confirming no outstanding issues (26:56)\n    - Lindsay investigated logs and identified conflicting optimization plugins installed around October, likely by multiple parties\n    - Colin confirmed removal of the problematic plugins and implementation of a **weekly website maintenance task** covering WordPress core and plugin updates to prevent future problems (29:25)\n    - The team agreed responsibility for ongoing WordPress updates lies with Colin’s agency\n\n- Bing advertising accounts were verified after a challenging document submission process, allowing the team to proceed with planned campaigns targeting Microsoft-related search terms (30:39)\n    - Colin has the campaign fully drafted and will finalize uploading once verification is confirmed\n    - Matthew expressed strong interest in monitoring Bing campaign performance, noting no current agency clients advertise there currently\n\n## **Competitive Positioning and Market Insights**\n\nThe discussion highlighted the importance of competitive content and strategic messaging to improve market share against dominant players.\n\n- Matthew and Colin debated the pros and cons of explicitly naming **RingCentral** in comparison content, with AI tools recommending direct competitor callouts to improve relevance and search association (11:20)\n    - They agreed to cautiously develop comparison pages clearly showing similarities and differences, aiming to position TechMode as a credible alternative\n\n- Market data confirmed **RingCentral’s significantly larger market share compared to Microsoft Teams** in the target space, influencing targeting strategies for paid ads and content focus (07:20)\n    - The team decided to create additional headline options and content to reflect this reality and maximize campaign effectiveness\n\n- Long-term vision includes preparing for rising AI influence in buyer journeys by **building trust through accurate, comprehensive competitor comparisons and case studies** that AI systems can use to recommend the product (20:12)\n    - Matthew framed this as a multi-year strategy to “get ahead of the curve” and capture emerging search trends before competitors do\n\n## **Process Improvements and Operational Controls**\n\nThe meeting concluded with steps to improve operational oversight and prevent future technical disruptions.\n\n- Colin’s team implemented a **comprehensive plugin and WordPress core update schedule**, with weekly checks to avoid vulnerabilities impacting paid search campaigns (29:25)\n    - Lindsay confirmed visibility improvements through a simplified log system to track website changes in real time, aiding troubleshooting\n\n- The team agreed to confirm the recent **geographic targeting adjustment on the PMAX campaign** and communicate the status via email alongside new landing page assets (30:14)\n    - This change supports more precise ad spend and audience targeting, expected to enhance campaign ROI\n\n- Bing Ads account verification was completed, enabling immediate campaign activation once landing pages are finalized (30:45)\n    - Colin will share new headlines and campaign details by end of day to keep momentum on track\n\n- The group committed to ongoing communication and rapid issue escalation to avoid surprises, demonstrating strengthened accountability and operational discipline going forward (29:52)","outline":null,"keywords":["AI SEO strategy","competitor comparison","Google Ads suspension","plugin vulnerabilities","Microsoft Ads campaign","AI citation tracking"],"overview":"- **Website Updates:** Reseller and IP pages updated with new FAQs and links, enhancing SEO and user guidance; NPS score at 85.\n\n- **New Landing Page:** Completed Microsoft integration page to target Bing users; team to finalize and launch ads for approval.\n\n- **SEO Strategy Shift:** Focus on AI-driven content, competitor comparisons, and case studies to improve visibility and engagement over next few years.\n\n- **AI Metrics and Tools:** Introduced AI citation rate; committed to $10/month tool upgrade for better SEO and performance tracking.\n\n- **Google Ads Resolved:** Previous plugin issues fixed; weekly maintenance implemented to prevent future vulnerabilities; Bing ads ready for launch.\n\n- **Competitive Positioning:** Emphasis on comparing with RingCentral to boost relevance; long-term strategy to adapt content for rising AI influence.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nSend updated MSP reseller and Virtual IP pages with added links for review (05:30)\nProvide additional headline options for Microsoft Ads campaign landing page and send related materials for approval (07:40)\nVerify geography fencing status with team and communicate confirmation to Lindsay (30:25)\nOversee weekly WordPress core and plugin updates to prevent future site vulnerabilities (29:30)\nRemove vulnerable website optimization plugins and maintain website security (27:45)\n\n**Matthew Look**\nMeet with team to discuss strategic plan for AI-focused SEO and advertising approach based on Reddit insights and AI content analysis (09:25)\nCoordinate with Colin and Lindsay on incorporating AI trust factors into content strategy for 2026 (19:50)\nReview and approve new Microsoft Ads campaign landing page and headlines upon receipt (31:20)\n\n**Lindsay Hall**\nConfirm if geography fencing was updated on PMAX campaign and report back (30:15)\nUpgrade SEO tool plan to access AI citation tracking feature (21:45)\n\n**All participants**\nMaintain communication regarding campaign progress and any arising issues or updates (32:35)\n"},"duration":33.15999984741211,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":1,"name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"id":2,"name":"Matthew Look"},{"id":3,"name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"id":4,"name":"Ryan Fisher"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hey, Chris.","index":0,"end_time":3.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, Colin.","index":1,"end_time":4.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3.6,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"How you doing?","index":2,"end_time":4.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":4.28,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"Doing all right.","index":3,"end_time":5.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":5.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How about yourself?","index":4,"end_time":6.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":5.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not bad.","index":5,"end_time":7.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":7.28,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"How was your holiday?","index":6,"end_time":8.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":7.76,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"It was good except for the part where the whole family is sick.","index":7,"end_time":12.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":9.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But other than that, guys, how do you manage that?","index":8,"end_time":17.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":12.8,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"You know, I think once you, once you have a kid and then you go to see more kids in your family, it''s just bound that everyone gets sick.","index":9,"end_time":27.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":18.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I heard about that.","index":10,"end_time":29.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":28.01,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"I''m sorry to hear that.","index":11,"end_time":31.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":30.73,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"Hope it didn''t ruin, you know, your holiday and everything, the togetherness and the family and all that.","index":12,"end_time":38.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":31.77,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"Yeah, no, it was fine.","index":13,"end_time":39.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":38.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And luckily things slowed down so, you know, if there, if there is a time to get sick, I guess it''s when things are slow.","index":14,"end_time":46.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":39.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right on.","index":15,"end_time":47.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":46.97,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"We don''t have.","index":16,"end_time":50.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":49.69,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"Well, my girlfriend and I, neither one of us have family here, so we just really took the opportunity to spend the days off that we don''t usually get any days off together.","index":17,"end_time":58.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":51.37,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"So unusual.","index":18,"end_time":60.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":59.4,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"So we just tried to hang out, do some dining locally and hanging out here.","index":19,"end_time":68.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":60.2,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"Did a little cooking on Christmas day.","index":20,"end_time":71.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":68.52,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"We made sea bass and lobster.","index":21,"end_time":74.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":71.76,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"Nice.","index":22,"end_time":75.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":75.32,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"A traditional Christmas.","index":23,"end_time":77.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":76.2,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"Yeah, traditional, yeah.","index":24,"end_time":78.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":77.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So yeah, it was nice to have the time and just, you know, get a lot of rest.","index":25,"end_time":84.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":79,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"Felt good to, you know, do nothing as much as possible.","index":26,"end_time":90.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":85.75,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"I know that is, that''s the funny thing about my daughter''s.","index":27,"end_time":94.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":90.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She''s about to turn one this month and I''m like, man, you just don''t know how good you got it when you don''t have to do anything all day.","index":28,"end_time":100.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":94.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right?","index":29,"end_time":101.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":101.27,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"What''s up gang?","index":30,"end_time":104.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":103.35,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":31,"end_time":105.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":104.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":32,"end_time":106.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":105.91,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"How''s your holiday, Colin?","index":33,"end_time":109.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":108,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"It was good.","index":34,"end_time":110.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":109.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was telling Chris here, my, my whole family got sick, but other than that, everything''s all good.","index":35,"end_time":113.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":110.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, our, our son got sick and we, we threw him up in his room.","index":36,"end_time":118.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":115.12,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"He''s 20, so we threw him up in his room and said basically shove things through a food through a slot if you needed it.","index":37,"end_time":124.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":118.76,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, Quarantine.","index":38,"end_time":125.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":124.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So far we have not caught it.","index":39,"end_time":127.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":125.76,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So lucky you.","index":40,"end_time":129.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":127.32,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"He goes snowboarding all day, hangs out with all those snotty nosed kids.","index":41,"end_time":136.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":131.12,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"They''re still snotty nosed even they''re snotty nose from when they''re 6 to when they''re 25.","index":42,"end_time":141.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":136.51,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":43,"end_time":142.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":142.27,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Comes back sick.","index":44,"end_time":143.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":142.91,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"That''s what happened last year over Christmas again, same thing this year.","index":45,"end_time":148.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":143.91,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Noticing a trend.","index":46,"end_time":150.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":149.789,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, exactly.","index":47,"end_time":152.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":151.71,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":48,"end_time":155.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":154.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m the, I''m the only one not on medicine right now, so hoping that I don''t need it, but we''ll see.","index":49,"end_time":161.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":155.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I would make fun of him for passing the same joint around or something, but I know he doesn''t because he gets drug tested at work all the time.","index":50,"end_time":169.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":162.1,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Government?","index":51,"end_time":171.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":170.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"State.","index":52,"end_time":173.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":172.74,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"State.","index":53,"end_time":174.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":173.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":54,"end_time":176.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":176.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Lindsay, how about you?","index":55,"end_time":177.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":176.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How was your holiday?","index":56,"end_time":178.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":177.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, pretty good.","index":57,"end_time":179.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":178.82,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"My whole family got sick.","index":58,"end_time":181.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":179.7,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"I mean, it''s not funny.","index":59,"end_time":186.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":185.95,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"I''m sorry.","index":60,"end_time":187.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":186.79,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"No, they all got me sick.","index":61,"end_time":189.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":187.55,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"We got the entire wedding party sick.","index":62,"end_time":191.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":189.71,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"So that was a joy.","index":63,"end_time":193.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":192.11,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah, but other than that, it was nice.","index":64,"end_time":196.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":195.23,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"It was fun.","index":65,"end_time":197.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":196.75,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":66,"end_time":198.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":198.03,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Other than the sickness part.","index":67,"end_time":199.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":198.43,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"And then, Ryan, I think you''re there.","index":68,"end_time":202.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":200.749,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How about you?","index":69,"end_time":203.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":203.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, it was great.","index":70,"end_time":206.59,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":205.63,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"Nobody got sick.","index":71,"end_time":208.03,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":207.07,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"Shrub it in.","index":72,"end_time":210.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":209.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Congrats.","index":73,"end_time":211.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":210.75,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Hello, Bar.","index":74,"end_time":212.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":211.92,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"That means two things.","index":75,"end_time":214.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":213.76,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Well, I mean that by the sound of this group, that was.","index":76,"end_time":217.2,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":214.68,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"That meant I had a really, really good holiday.","index":77,"end_time":220.16,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":217.68,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"Yeah, I''d say so.","index":78,"end_time":223.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":221.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":79,"end_time":225.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":225.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Matt, I got your email, so I have those in our slide as well, but I just wanted to go through page updates and make sure that we''re all squared away.","index":80,"end_time":233.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":226.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I got a list which is probably a duplicate of what you already have on yours, so perfect.","index":81,"end_time":238.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":233.92,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"All right, so the MSP reseller page.","index":82,"end_time":241.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":239.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we worked in all of your feedback, including moving this higher into the page so it''s right below.","index":83,"end_time":246.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":241.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So there''s the hero section and then bill for msps and then talks about trusted by MSPS nationwide with the NPS score and everything else.","index":84,"end_time":254.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":246.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Love it.","index":85,"end_time":255.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":255.14,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"And then we also added links to all of these boxes because you made a comment about just having more interlinking throughout the website.","index":86,"end_time":262.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":256.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So some of these are like Premiere Launch tried to find relevant articles or landing pages to what the content in the box is for all of these.","index":87,"end_time":271.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":263.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect and same.","index":88,"end_time":276.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":273.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then down here, if you do click on apply and onboard, it will open up the form right there as well.","index":89,"end_time":282.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":276.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But other than that, all of your.","index":90,"end_time":288.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":287.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, and she''s hot.","index":91,"end_time":289.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":288.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do we know her?","index":92,"end_time":290.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":289.97,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I think that''s AI.","index":93,"end_time":294.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":293.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She''s not real.","index":94,"end_time":295.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":294.02,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"She''s my type.","index":95,"end_time":296.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":295.18,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"And then your comment also.","index":96,"end_time":299.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":296.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or you had a comment on the FAQ of.","index":97,"end_time":301.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":299.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let''s ask, like, what is an NPS score?","index":98,"end_time":303.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":301.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And is an 85 good?","index":99,"end_time":304.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":303.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I added those in here.","index":100,"end_time":305.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":304.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t remember saying that, but all right, sounds good.","index":101,"end_time":308.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":306.06,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I''m not doubting you.","index":102,"end_time":309.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":308.62,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"That just means it''s been a few weeks and I don''t remember.","index":103,"end_time":312.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":309.66,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I gotcha.","index":104,"end_time":313.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":312.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So all of that''s updated.","index":105,"end_time":314.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":313.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And same thing on the virtual IP page.","index":106,"end_time":316.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":314.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Same with adding links to these as well.","index":107,"end_time":319.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":318.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So a lot more links added to these for people to click through.","index":108,"end_time":325.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":320.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I can send these over if you guys want to take any other look.","index":109,"end_time":329.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":326.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But other than that, if they''re good to go, then we can finalize the ad Campaigns to get them flowing there.","index":110,"end_time":334.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":329.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m good with them if you''ve made the changes I requested.","index":111,"end_time":337.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":334.92,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Lindsey, did you have anything else you wanted to add to that?","index":112,"end_time":339.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":337.04,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Nope.","index":113,"end_time":339.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":339.28,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Those look good to me.","index":114,"end_time":340.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":339.72,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"All right, love it.","index":115,"end_time":342.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":341.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we also have the campaign, the landing page we built for the campaign, and Microsoft ads for the 1599.","index":116,"end_time":355.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":345.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So send this over to review.","index":117,"end_time":357.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":355.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Largely similar to the other 1599 page, but a lot more information around Microsoft integrations and different pain points that people feel.","index":118,"end_time":366.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":357.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Did we look at this page yet?","index":119,"end_time":371.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":370.14,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"We just wrapped this up.","index":120,"end_time":373.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":372.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it.","index":121,"end_time":374.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":373.74,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Okay, wait, strip it over.","index":122,"end_time":375.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":374.22,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Let''s take a look at it.","index":123,"end_time":376.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":375.26,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yep.","index":124,"end_time":376.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":376.3,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"But this is.","index":125,"end_time":377.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":376.78,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Is this the primary landing page for everybody who searches on Google or, sorry, searches on Bing?","index":126,"end_time":382.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":377.5,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"That''s what it looks like.","index":127,"end_time":384.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":383.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It is.","index":128,"end_time":384.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":384.06,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So we''re go back up.","index":129,"end_time":388.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":387.34,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So we''re assuming they''re.","index":130,"end_time":390.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":389.26,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"They''re a teams user just because they''re using Bing.","index":131,"end_time":393.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":390.54,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Well, the keywords that we were going to bid on were around Microsoft terms.","index":132,"end_time":399.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":395.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t remember that discussion.","index":133,"end_time":403.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":401.83,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Does anybody?","index":134,"end_time":403.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":403.07,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So we were pulling up metrics, if you remember, around Bing users and what platforms they use, and it''s largely skews to Microsoft users.","index":135,"end_time":415.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":408.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You are correct.","index":136,"end_time":417.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":416.87,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Microsoft and corporations.","index":137,"end_time":421.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":417.99,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yes.","index":138,"end_time":422.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":421.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I. I vaguely remember this conversation from.","index":139,"end_time":425.96,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":423.48,"speaker_name":"Ryan Fisher"},{"text":"I do remember that part, but I don''t remember specifically saying we wanted to combat.","index":140,"end_time":429.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":425.96,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Call out teams, though.","index":141,"end_time":430.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":429.64,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Okay.","index":142,"end_time":433.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":432.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Kick it over and let me look at it.","index":143,"end_time":436.279,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":435,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Let me think about it.","index":144,"end_time":437.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":436.279,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Okay.","index":145,"end_time":437.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":437.24,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"And I can even.","index":146,"end_time":440.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":439.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because I don''t.","index":147,"end_time":440.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":440.36,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I mean, that''s such a narrow.","index":148,"end_time":442.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":440.88,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Because if somebody has teams, they likely don''t have Ring.","index":149,"end_time":446.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":443.32,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Right.","index":150,"end_time":449.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":449.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we know Ring has the biggest market share, significantly more than teams.","index":151,"end_time":455.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":451.43,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yep.","index":152,"end_time":459.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":458.95,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":153,"end_time":459.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":459.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We even have them in our comparison table.","index":154,"end_time":461.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":459.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, yeah