    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.93,"bullets":["Implemented feedback on MSP reseller and virtual IP pages; interlinking and form UX improved.","Colin confirmed Google Ads campaigns are ready pending final approvals on content updates.","Matthew initiated strategy shift to optimize site for AI ranking and citation readiness.","Resolved plugin vulnerabilities that had triggered temporary Google Ads campaign pauses.","Team aligned on building competitor comparison and industry-specific landing pages in 2026."],"highlights":[{"quote":"I think we''re on the same page and it was actually summed up pretty good here.","speaker":"Matthew Look"},{"quote":"I think that the next logical steps are to draft these pages and then build them.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"Let''s get that footing down... as we continue to build the house.","speaker":"Matthew Look"}],"topics":["SEO","ads","AI","risk","delivery"],"model":"openai/gpt-4","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-06T22:41:03Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Website and Landing Page Updates**\n\nThe team finalized key webpage updates and improved internal linking to support upcoming ad campaigns.\n\n- **MSP reseller and virtual IP pages** were updated to include interlinking and an FAQ explaining the **NPS score of 85**, enhancing user guidance and SEO relevance (03:59)\n    - The MSP page now places key info just below the hero section for better visibility\n    - Links were added to boxes directing visitors to relevant articles and landing pages\n    - The “apply and onboard” button now opens the form directly on the page, reducing friction\n    - These changes align with Matthew Look’s feedback and received approval from Lindsay Hall\n\n- A new **campaign landing page focused on Microsoft integrations** was completed to target Bing users searching Microsoft-related terms (05:41)\n    - This page intends to position the product as a strong alternative for Microsoft Teams users\n    - Matthew questioned the narrow targeting of Teams users, noting RingCentral holds significantly larger market share, prompting Colin Costigan to plan additional headline options and send updated content for review\n    - The team agreed to finalize this page and launch ad campaigns once approved\n\n## **SEO Strategy and AI Search Optimization**\n\nThe team aligned on evolving SEO tactics to prepare for AI-driven search behaviors expected by 2026.\n\n- Matthew Look emphasized the need to **shift from generic blog posts to AI-trusted content** focused on competitor comparisons and case studies to improve visibility in AI-powered search results (07:59)\n    - He highlighted that current searchers still use Google or Bing rather than AI chat for product replacement queries, but this will change over the next 3–5 years\n    - Ryan Fisher and Colin supported this view, noting AI tools pull from Google''s organic rankings and user engagement signals\n\n- Based on AI content analysis, the team agreed to add a **navigation section comparing TechMode directly with competitors like RingCentral and Nextiva** to increase inclusion in AI recommendations (12:16)\n    - Colin explained that AI values accurate, detailed feature breakdowns as “source of truth” to recommend products confidently\n    - Matthew plans to meet with his team to develop a phased plan for this content, targeting gradual rollout through 2026 to secure long-term SEO gains\n\n- The team discussed new SEO metrics such as the **AI citation rate**, which tracks how often TechMode appears in AI-generated content, and committed to upgrading their SEO tool to access this data for about **$10/month** (21:38)\n    - Lindsay confirmed the upgrade is affordable and will be pursued to improve AI performance tracking\n\n- Colin clarified that AI crawlers rely on the website’s **sitemap to discover all blog posts**, even those not listed on public pages, ensuring hidden content still contributes to SEO and AI indexing (26:03)\n\n## **Google Ads and Campaign Management**\n\nThe team resolved recent Google Ad issues and prepared to launch new campaigns on Bing.\n\n- The **Google Ads campaigns paused due to website plugin vulnerabilities** were fully resolved, with a clean sweep from Google Search Console confirming no outstanding issues (26:56)\n    - Lindsay investigated logs and identified conflicting optimization plugins installed around October, likely by multiple parties\n    - Colin confirmed removal of the problematic plugins and implementation of a **weekly website maintenance task** covering WordPress core and plugin updates to prevent future problems (29:25)\n    - The team agreed responsibility for ongoing WordPress updates lies with Colin’s agency\n\n- Bing advertising accounts were verified after a challenging document submission process, allowing the team to proceed with planned campaigns targeting Microsoft-related search terms (30:39)\n    - Colin has the campaign fully drafted and will finalize uploading once verification is confirmed\n    - Matthew expressed strong interest in monitoring Bing campaign performance, noting no current agency clients advertise there currently\n\n## **Competitive Positioning and Market Insights**\n\nThe discussion highlighted the importance of competitive content and strategic messaging to improve market share against dominant players.\n\n- Matthew and Colin debated the pros and cons of explicitly naming **RingCentral** in comparison content, with AI tools recommending direct competitor callouts to improve relevance and search association (11:20)\n    - They agreed to cautiously develop comparison pages clearly showing similarities and differences, aiming to position TechMode as a credible alternative\n\n- Market data confirmed **RingCentral’s significantly larger market share compared to Microsoft Teams** in the target space, influencing targeting strategies for paid ads and content focus (07:20)\n    - The team decided to create additional headline options and content to reflect this reality and maximize campaign effectiveness\n\n- Long-term vision includes preparing for rising AI influence in buyer journeys by **building trust through accurate, comprehensive competitor comparisons and case studies** that AI systems can use to recommend the product (20:12)\n    - Matthew framed this as a multi-year strategy to “get ahead of the curve” and capture emerging search trends before competitors do\n\n## **Process Improvements and Operational Controls**\n\nThe meeting concluded with steps to improve operational oversight and prevent future technical disruptions.\n\n- Colin’s team implemented a **comprehensive plugin and WordPress core update schedule**, with weekly checks to avoid vulnerabilities impacting paid search campaigns (29:25)\n    - Lindsay confirmed visibility improvements through a simplified log system to track website changes in real time, aiding troubleshooting\n\n- The team agreed to confirm the recent **geographic targeting adjustment on the PMAX campaign** and communicate the status via email alongside new landing page assets (30:14)\n    - This change supports more precise ad spend and audience targeting, expected to enhance campaign ROI\n\n- Bing Ads account verification was completed, enabling immediate campaign activation once landing pages are finalized (30:45)\n    - Colin will share new headlines and campaign details by end of day to keep momentum on track\n\n- The group committed to ongoing communication and rapid issue escalation to avoid surprises, demonstrating strengthened accountability and operational discipline going forward (29:52)","outline":null,"keywords":["AI SEO strategy","competitor comparison","Google Ads suspension","plugin vulnerabilities","Microsoft Ads campaign","AI citation tracking"],"overview":"- **Website Updates:** Reseller and IP pages updated with new FAQs and links, enhancing SEO and user guidance; NPS score at 85.\n\n- **New Landing Page:** Completed Microsoft integration page to target Bing users; team to finalize and launch ads for approval.\n\n- **SEO Strategy Shift:** Focus on AI-driven content, competitor comparisons, and case studies to improve visibility and engagement over next few years.\n\n- **AI Metrics and Tools:** Introduced AI citation rate; committed to $10/month tool upgrade for better SEO and performance tracking.\n\n- **Google Ads Resolved:** Previous plugin issues fixed; weekly maintenance implemented to prevent future vulnerabilities; Bing ads ready for launch.\n\n- **Competitive Positioning:** Emphasis on comparing with RingCentral to boost relevance; long-term strategy to adapt content for rising AI influence.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nSend updated MSP reseller and Virtual IP pages with added links for review (05:30)\nProvide additional headline options for Microsoft Ads campaign landing page and send related materials for approval (07:40)\nVerify geography fencing status with team and communicate confirmation to Lindsay (30:25)\nOversee weekly WordPress core and plugin updates to prevent future site vulnerabilities (29:30)\nRemove vulnerable website optimization plugins and maintain website security (27:45)\n\n**Matthew Look**\nMeet with team to discuss strategic plan for AI-focused SEO and advertising approach based on Reddit insights and AI content analysis (09:25)\nCoordinate with Colin and Lindsay on incorporating AI trust factors into content strategy for 2026 (19:50)\nReview and approve new Microsoft Ads campaign landing page and headlines upon receipt (31:20)\n\n**Lindsay Hall**\nConfirm if geography fencing was updated on PMAX campaign and report back (30:15)\nUpgrade SEO tool plan to access AI citation tracking feature (21:45)\n\n**All participants**\nMaintain communication regarding campaign progress and any arising issues or updates (32:35)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"d048015c-a1a0-486f-b5e7-ff1dc93afc24","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
