-- Meeting: KTC // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting (2026-01-06 18:00:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '72cdc11e-fd4f-4d90-8688-1fc1484de2b0',
    '2026-01-06 18:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KE5JNQ7VZX5YQ32QKF0JNV3Y',
    'KTC // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting',
    '{"Kristen Baller","Michael Kersten","Colin Costigan","Colin Costigan","Colin Costigan"}'::text[],
    1942,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/83519004309?pwd=JvKSZR6BzSlyNxK5WTgZHYayMsLSKi.1&jst=2',
    '{"id":"01KE5JNQ7VZX5YQ32QKF0JNV3Y","title":"KTC // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Account-Based Marketing (ABM) Strategy and Outreach**\n\nThe team finalized the ABM plan with a focus on multi-channel outreach, emphasizing rapid list building and integrated communications.\n\n- **Michael Kersten committed to providing detailed feedback on the ABM plan by the end of the week** to clarify messaging and outreach priorities (06:07)  \n    - Michael requested help to rewrite and reposition his LinkedIn profile to better align with outreach efforts and reduce confusion caused by outdated affiliations.  \n    - The team agreed to incorporate KTC Search branding into LinkedIn profiles and communications, with plans to add consulting engagements and logos for clearer identity.  \n    - This profile update supports smoother LinkedIn direct messaging, which is a key channel alongside emails and paid ads.  \n    - The goal is to avoid confusion and maximize credibility during the critical first quarter payout period.\n\n- **Outreach communications will be sent from Michael or Kristen’s official domains, and LinkedIn messaging will use real profiles for authenticity** (06:18)  \n    - The team confirmed the use of newly set-up email domains rather than legacy ones like KTCsearch.com to maintain brand consistency.  \n    - LinkedIn outreach will be managed through Michael’s and Kristen’s profiles, requiring profile updates for clarity and brand alignment.  \n    - This dual-domain and channel approach strengthens brand recognition and trust across email and LinkedIn.  \n    - Paula’s strategy team supports backend system execution to ensure smooth multi-channel deployment.\n\n- **Cold emails, LinkedIn messages, and paid ads will launch simultaneously to build awareness and accelerate engagement** (28:32)  \n    - Colin explained that combining cold email, LinkedIn outreach, and paid ads creates top-of-mind brand awareness leading to higher response rates.  \n    - Paid ads will start alongside outreach emails, not delayed until later quarters, to create consistent touchpoints.  \n    - Weekly and monthly analytics will optimize ad spend, shifting budget to higher-performing channels.  \n    - The plan recommends a monthly ad budget between **$2,500 for LinkedIn ads** and **$500 for retargeting ads**, totaling **$3,000 per month** initially (29:41).\n\n## **Website Design, Content, and Platform Migration**\n\nThe website redesign is approved and development will start immediately, with plans to migrate to HubSpot and expand campaign-specific landing pages.\n\n- **Michael approved all website redesigns with no requested changes, allowing immediate development to begin** (10:35)  \n    - The team will proceed with development to maintain momentum and meet project deadlines.  \n    - The new design aims to position the brand to look like a top-tier competitor while maintaining differentiation.  \n    - This refresh supports the strategic focus on retained search services, which drive **78% of revenue**, as emphasized by Michael (11:18).  \n    - Secondary services like contingent and fractional recruiting will be presented but deprioritized on the site to focus on profitability.\n\n- **The team plans a full migration to HubSpot by the end of the month, including website hosting, content management, and campaign landing pages** (27:47)  \n    - The main developer will return from holiday to finalize the HubSpot build by month-end.  \n    - Campaign-specific landing pages will be created within HubSpot to support ABM and paid advertising workflows.  \n    - Michael’s internal content posting will pause once the migration is ready to avoid duplicate or conflicting content.  \n    - The new platform will enable integrated tracking and easier content updates, streamlining marketing operations.\n\n- **A pixel tracking tool via Factors AI will be added to the website once Google Search Console access is granted, enabling de-anonymized traffic data for better lead intake** (08:57)  \n    - Colin will coordinate with Ryan to gain Google Search Console access needed for pixel deployment.  \n    - This tracking supports enhanced data accuracy for ABM campaigns and attribution analysis.  \n    - Pixel data will feed into HubSpot and campaign automation to improve targeting and retargeting.  \n    - Access handoff and coordination with internal IT/Google admin will be critical to avoid delays.\n\n## **Branding and Logo Decisions**\n\nLogo design variations were presented with a focus on blending KTC Search’s identity with the Richie Mae brand for strategic alignment.\n\n- **Michael favored a clean green gradient logo that balances standing out and fitting within the Richie Mae ecosystem** (13:09)  \n    - Colin highlighted that multiple logo versions have been prepared for different backgrounds and use cases to maximize flexibility.  \n    - This branding approach supports clear messaging that the company has full capabilities while benefiting from Richie Mae’s backing.  \n    - The chosen logo will be implemented on the website and Executive Advantage materials, reinforcing brand cohesion.  \n    - Final logo selection will be communicated promptly to keep website development on track.\n\n- **Domain management was clarified with all domains now transferred to GoDaddy, which poses no issues for DNS updates or email rebranding** (14:40)  \n    - Michael confirmed domains like KTCsearch.com are on GoDaddy, and Colin confirmed this registrar is manageable for ongoing updates.  \n    - The team agreed that rebranding email addresses to match the KTC Search domain on Microsoft 365 will reduce friction for prospects (31:09).  \n    - Coordination with Daniel, the Google/IT contact, will ensure smooth email migration and brand consistency.  \n    - This domain and email alignment supports streamlined communications and brand recognition.\n\n## **Data Enrichment and List Building Tools**\n\nThe team evaluated Clay and related platforms for contact enrichment and outreach list management, deciding to implement a flexible, credit-based usage model.\n\n- **Clay will be used as the primary tool for building targeted lists and enriching contact data, integrated into HubSpot workflows** (15:19)  \n    - Colin explained Clay’s capabilities to filter companies by revenue, employee count, and industry, then find relevant contacts by title and location.  \n    - Enrichment includes adding work emails and company data, sometimes supplemented by ZoomInfo or other tools as needed.  \n    - Michael emphasized the need to keep data clean and enriched automatically to avoid manual entry and improve campaign efficiency.  \n    - The team will provide a CSV of contacts from Clay for Michael’s review before outreach.\n\n- **Clay’s credit-based pricing model allows starting at low usage with flexibility to scale, with the agency charging a small fee per 2,000 credits used** (20:01)  \n    - Michael will decide whether to license Clay directly or have the agency manage it and bill accordingly.  \n    - The agency’s partnership with Clay enables them to undercharge, providing cost efficiency.  \n    - This credit system supports cost control and scaling based on actual usage and campaign needs.  \n    - Initial trial with the free tier and small monthly packages is planned to validate fit.\n\n- **Heyreach will automate LinkedIn outreach workflows, including sequential profile views, connection requests, and message follow-ups without manual copy-pasting** (23:44)  \n    - Colin described Heyreach’s ability to send personalized, automated LinkedIn messages with conditional follow-ups based on response behavior.  \n    - Kristen confirmed the tool tracks responses and can centralize message logs for easy management by multiple users.  \n    - Heyreach operates independently from email outreach to avoid system breaks and ensure reliability.  \n    - This automation reduces manual effort and improves outreach consistency.\n\n- **Integration of Clay with HubSpot and use of Heyreach and SmartLead for email and LinkedIn campaigns will streamline multi-channel ABM execution** (25:01)  \n    - Lists created in Clay will feed directly into outreach tools after client review, ensuring accuracy and targeting precision.  \n    - Michael’s internal team will focus on referrals while agency manages outbound campaigns leveraging these tools.  \n    - This division of labor optimizes resource use and campaign scale.  \n    - The agency will provide training and support as needed to maximize platform adoption.\n\n## **Budgeting and Campaign Timelines**\n\nThe team agreed on an initial budget range and aggressive timelines to launch the ABM campaigns and paid ads by early Q2.\n\n- **The recommended ad spend is between $6,000 and $12,000 per quarter, split as $2,500 monthly for LinkedIn ads and $500 monthly for retargeting ads** (29:39)  \n    - Kristen plans to revisit and adjust the budget in upcoming one-on-one meetings to align with overall financial plans.  \n    - Colin emphasized weekly budget optimization based on performance data to maximize ROI.  \n    - Paid ads will start concurrently with email and LinkedIn outreach to generate multi-channel touchpoints.  \n    - This budget supports sustained campaign activity to build brand awareness and lead generation.\n\n- **List building and campaign infrastructure setup will conclude within one week, with development and live launch targeted by the end of the month** (29:09)  \n    - The main developer’s return from holiday enables final HubSpot and website work by month-end.  \n    - N8N automation workflows for campaign triggers will take approximately two days to build.  \n    - Campaign launch timing depends on receipt of ABM plan feedback from Michael and Kristen.  \n    - This timeline ensures readiness for Q2 paid ad activation and outreach acceleration.\n\n- **Michael confirmed readiness to support domain and email rebranding to align with KTC Search as part of the upcoming cutover** (31:07)  \n    - Coordination with internal IT and Google admin will be necessary for smooth transition.  \n    - This rebranding reduces prospect friction and unifies the customer experience.  \n    - Early communication about cutover timing is critical given Michael’s travel schedule the following week.  \n    - The team confirmed the next scheduled meeting remains Tuesday to keep momentum.","outline":null,"keywords":["Account-Based Marketing","LinkedIn Outreach","Website Redesign","HubSpot Migration","Clay Data Enrichment","Paid Advertising Budget"],"overview":"- **ABM Strategy Finalized:** Multi-channel outreach will focus on rapid list building and integrated communications for maximum engagement.  \n- **Email and LinkedIn Outreach:** Communications will use official domains and profiles to enhance authenticity and brand recognition.  \n- **Launch of Paid Ads:** Cold emails, LinkedIn messages, and paid ads will start simultaneously to boost awareness and engagement.  \n- **Website Redesign Approved:** New design aims to enhance brand perception and focus on retained search services, which contribute 78% of revenue.  \n- **HubSpot Migration Planned:** Full migration to HubSpot is set for month-end, enabling improved tracking and content management efficiencies.  \n- **Clay for Contact Enrichment:** Clay will be the primary tool for list building and data enrichment, integrated into automated outreach workflows.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nEmail Ryan to obtain Google Search Console access for website analytics and pixel implementation (09:35)\nSend Executive Vantage logo markup link for Michael’s review and decision on preferred styles (13:08)\nProvide Michael with live ABM plan link for feedback and coordinate list building in Clay for review (25:01)\nSetup campaign infrastructure in N8N tool for ABM campaigns and prepare to go live pending final feedback (29:20)\nSchedule and manage paid ad campaigns budget allocations and weekly/monthly performance optimizations (30:40)\nPrepare to build campaign landing pages and subpages in HubSpot post-development phase (27:58)\nManage LinkedIn and email messaging automation tool integration with Heyreach and Smart Lead (24:51)\n\n**Michael Kersten**\nReview ABM plan thoroughly and provide detailed feedback (06:07)\nCoordinate with David (Google/IT resource) on rebranding email setup in Microsoft 365 to reflect KTC Search domain (31:07)\nProvide LinkedIn access/password for profile adjustments by marketing team (27:13)\nAdvise internal team to pause blog posting when content development by marketing team ramps up (09:50)\nEvaluate Clay pricing/licensing options and decide on subscription or service usage (21:32)\nReview and finalize Executive Vantage logo choice from options shared (13:31)\nMonitor offshore recruiter outreach methods and consider Clay and Heyreach tools for efficiency and better candidate engagement (22:55)\nConfirm next meeting schedule in light of travel plans (32:07)\n\n**Kristen Baller**\nCoordinate with Michael on social content calendar and meeting follow-up to ensure alignment on content and outreach (12:40)\nRevisit and revise paid ads budget aligned with overall marketing budgets based on recent discussion (30:11)\n\n**Paula**\nSupport overall project execution and ensure backend systems alignment alongside Colin and Guille (05:07)\n"},"duration":32.369998931884766,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Kristen Baller"},{"id":1,"name":"Michael Kersten"},{"id":2,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":3,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":4,"name":"Colin Costigan"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hey there.","index":0,"end_time":231.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":231.29,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Here you guys.","index":1,"end_time":272.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":271.78,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Hey, Michael.","index":2,"end_time":274.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":273.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":3,"end_time":275.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":274.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":4,"end_time":275.9,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":275.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How about yourself?","index":5,"end_time":276.5,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":275.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m doing good.","index":6,"end_time":277.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":276.9,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Doing good.","index":7,"end_time":278.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":277.86,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Hang on a second here.","index":8,"end_time":279.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":278.3,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You disappear.","index":9,"end_time":279.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":279.18,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"There you are.","index":10,"end_time":280.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":279.78,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Did you find me?","index":11,"end_time":281.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":281.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes, yes.","index":12,"end_time":283.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":282.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Too many screens going here.","index":13,"end_time":285.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":283.55,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"How was holiday season?","index":14,"end_time":288.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":286.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was okay.","index":15,"end_time":290.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":289.87,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Didn''t get caught up on as much stuff as I wanted to get caught up on, but, you know, I guess it is what it is.","index":16,"end_time":298.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":291.79,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"That''s.","index":17,"end_time":298.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":298.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s how it goes.","index":18,"end_time":299.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":298.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s for sure.","index":19,"end_time":300.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":299.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":20,"end_time":301.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":300.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is Kristen joining us today?","index":21,"end_time":303.47,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":302.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think she was on the call.","index":22,"end_time":305.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":304.11,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We could.","index":23,"end_time":305.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":305.11,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We can go ahead and start.","index":24,"end_time":306.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":305.39,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And when she joined.","index":25,"end_time":307.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":306.15,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"She joined.","index":26,"end_time":307.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":307.11,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"She joins.","index":27,"end_time":307.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":307.51,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So.","index":28,"end_time":308.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":307.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, sounds good.","index":29,"end_time":309.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":308.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I also wanted to introduce.","index":30,"end_time":310.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":309.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Paula, who''s on the call now and Kristen''s joining.","index":31,"end_time":313.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":310.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It looks like Paula is another member of our strategy team.","index":32,"end_time":317.82,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":313.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you''ll see her on some calls and she helps out with me and.","index":33,"end_time":321.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":317.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Guille and all of our team.","index":34,"end_time":322.98,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":321.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just getting everything done and executed in the back end of the systems.","index":35,"end_time":325.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":322.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hi, Michael.","index":36,"end_time":327.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":327.02,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Nice to meet you.","index":37,"end_time":328.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":328.06,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Nice to meet you too.","index":38,"end_time":331.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":330.22,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Sorry about that.","index":39,"end_time":332.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":331.42,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Right.","index":40,"end_time":334.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":334.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, Kristen.","index":41,"end_time":335.6,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":334.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, I''ll jump in.","index":42,"end_time":339.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":337.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":43,"end_time":348.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":347.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so just want to go through some final things on the ABM plan and then updates on the website.","index":44,"end_time":355.28,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":349.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Design and then podcast in the list creation that we''ve been working through.","index":45,"end_time":360.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":355.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So for the ABM plan, have you.","index":46,"end_time":362.72,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":360.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Guys had a chance to review it?","index":47,"end_time":363.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":362.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I haven''t seen any feedback come through on anything.","index":48,"end_time":365.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":363.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ve gone through it, but I have put any feedback and I can definitely take that as an action.","index":49,"end_time":371.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":367.1,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I read it over through the holidays, so I didn''t have like any glaring things.","index":50,"end_time":374.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":371.18,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But I will make some comments for you.","index":51,"end_time":377.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":375.74,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Okay, that would be great.","index":52,"end_time":379.86,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":378.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then my, my one question is.","index":53,"end_time":382.139,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":379.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Who we want to send communication from?","index":54,"end_time":384.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":382.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is that going to be coming from Michael or Kristen?","index":55,"end_time":387.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":384.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"When we say communication, tell me what you mean by that in regards.","index":56,"end_time":391.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":388.06,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, so we.","index":57,"end_time":392.7,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":391.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"One thing is we set up email domains so they''re not going to be like KTC search.com, but I have a few of them outlined in the plan document.","index":58,"end_time":401.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":392.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we would send from either Michael.","index":59,"end_time":403.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":401.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"At whatever domain or Kristen at whatever domain.","index":60,"end_time":405.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":403.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we also have LinkedIn as an.","index":61,"end_time":407.7,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":405.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Aspect of our outreach so that we do communication through direct message where that would have to be connected to your real profile.","index":62,"end_time":414.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":407.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, that''s fine.","index":63,"end_time":415.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":414.46,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You can send them out to me.","index":64,"end_time":416.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":415.14,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Now.","index":65,"end_time":416.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":416.1,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Question for you guys is, you guys obviously have gone to my, my LinkedIn profile, so I need to see.","index":66,"end_time":424.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":416.3,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Can you guys help me maybe reposition some of that stuff?","index":67,"end_time":427.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":424.4,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Maybe just to make it easier for you guys.","index":68,"end_time":429.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":427.68,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I don''t know if we want to change some stuff, I mean you guys can rewrite that or whatever, but maybe so that way we can, you can still send stuff out where it''s, it''s not confusing people if they see ID me on there listically right now I have ID me at the top.","index":69,"end_time":443.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":429.8,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You know, if I need to manipulate that and drop it below, I can do it and you know, whatever.","index":70,"end_time":450.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":444.92,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"If I get caught, I get caught.","index":71,"end_time":451.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":450.04,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I mean the time, you know, by the time they somebody sees that, I''ll be, you know, we''ll be know first quarter be done and I get my payout.","index":72,"end_time":457.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":451.08,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So.","index":73,"end_time":457.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":457.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, that''s actually was my next.","index":74,"end_time":460.54,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":457.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Question because I was reviewing yours and I was also reviewing Kristen''s and I didn''t see KTC on there as the list of in career.","index":75,"end_time":466.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":460.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s definitely one part I wanted to confirm.","index":76,"end_time":468.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":466.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":77,"end_time":469.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":468.78,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Now the one thing that will when you guys redo mine, I won''t, I won''t put it on there yet, but we''ll have to wordsmith or put, you know, you guys, we can, I can add it on there but it will eventually have to put, you know, as you''re rewriting it or if you guys want to rewrite it, we''ll need to put the Richie May stuff in there.","index":78,"end_time":486.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":469.22,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You know, I can drop it on as another line item if you guys want.","index":79,"end_time":490.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":487.29,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Think about it as I can just show it as a consulting engagement maybe under KTC or something like that.","index":80,"end_time":495.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":490.57,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"That way we can drop a logo on there, we can do something.","index":81,"end_time":498.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":496.01,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I mean, you guys talk among yourselves and however you think we can do that really, is this going to be a problem for the next 60 days?","index":82,"end_time":506.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":498.53,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Because like I said, you know, we can, we can eliminate, you know, the ID me stuff will be done before we know it.","index":83,"end_time":512.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":506.57,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So if you want to work, we want to make some changes, I''ll make the changes and you know, I''ll roll with the dice.","index":84,"end_time":518.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":512.17,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So.","index":85,"end_time":518.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":518.39,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, because like I said, the chance of somebody seeing it is probably slim to none.","index":86,"end_time":523.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":518.67,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I still don''t want to throw up a bunch of videos up there myself until that''s done.","index":87,"end_time":527.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":523.99,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But you know, wordsmithing my LinkedIn profile, moving positions and companies around, I''m not so worried about that because I''m not.","index":88,"end_time":534.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":527.27,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I don''t really have a bunch of people hitting my LinkedIn profile, so.","index":89,"end_time":537.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":534.15,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Okay, yeah, that''s great.","index":90,"end_time":538.03,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":537.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll definitely do a rewrite then.","index":91,"end_time":539.43,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":538.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then one other thing I had on here is one pixel that we tend to add to websites through a.","index":92,"end_time":546.13,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":540.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Tool called Factors AI and that is just to de.","index":93,"end_time":548.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":546.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Anonymize website traffic in.","index":94,"end_time":550.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":548.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"In our asset intake.","index":95,"end_time":551.45,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":550.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We actually didn''t get access to your Google search console.","index":96,"end_time":553.61,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":551.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I don''t know if that''s something that maybe Ryan has control of.","index":97,"end_time":556.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":553.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep, just ask Ryan to give that to it and then.","index":98,"end_time":558.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":556.21,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Okay, I didn''t know.","index":99,"end_time":560.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":558.13,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And you guys may have this in the plan, but you know, when.","index":100,"end_time":562.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":560.41,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"When do.","index":101,"end_time":563.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":562.85,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I haven''t said anything to him about we''re moving to anything to wor or I''m sorry, HubSpot.","index":102,"end_time":568.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":563.33,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So, you know, just let me know as we''re getting closer and what you want to, you know, when we''re ready to do that, let me know.","index":103,"end_time":574.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":568.53,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I still have Michael, our internal guy, still writing.","index":104,"end_time":577.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":574.47,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You can probably see he''s posting blogs up there every Wednesday.","index":105,"end_time":579.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":577.31,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Let me know when you want me to nip that.","index":106,"end_time":582.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":580.47,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Because I''m assuming part of what we''ll be doing throughout the year.","index":107,"end_time":584.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":582.35,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You guys are going to start developing content and stuff like that.","index":108,"end_time":587.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":584.99,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And you know, I can tell him to cease and desist.","index":109,"end_time":589.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":587.59,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Like I said, I''ve had him put stuff up there.","index":110,"end_time":592.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":589.83,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But, you know, if you wise one, I can tell him, hey, you don''t need to worry about posting anything going forward.","index":111,"end_time":598.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":594.15,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I just need you guys to give me some directions so I know when to tell him to drop off.","index":112,"end_time":601.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":598.47,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":113,"end_time":602.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":601.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I''ll show up, I''ll pull up.","index":114,"end_time":603.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":602.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All the website design and I want to talk through that as well.","index":115,"end_time":605.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":603.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As far as writing blogs.","index":116,"end_time":608.01,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":606.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes, that is.","index":117,"end_time":608.77,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":608.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s why we.","index":118,"end_time":609.89,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":609.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Another big piece of the Executive Advantage interview series is we can create so much content out of that.","index":119,"end_time":614.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":609.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So not only blogs, but white papers, a bunch of different downloadable content, social content, all sorts of things.","index":120,"end_time":619.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":614.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":121,"end_time":620.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":619.65,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":122,"end_time":620.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":620.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so I will email Ryan.","index":123,"end_time":622.09,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":620.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To get access to Google Search Console and then we can get that added and I''ll pull up.","index":124,"end_time":626.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":622.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re making a lot of progress.","index":125,"end_time":628.5,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":627.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As you can see here, we have all of the pages that we''ve redesigned in here.","index":126,"end_time":633.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":628.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I haven''t seen any feedback come through.","index":127,"end_time":634.62,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":633.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For the designs, so they look good.","index":128,"end_time":637.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":635.34,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I didn''t have any.","index":129,"end_time":638.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":637.82,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I didn''t have any complaints on anything.","index":130,"end_time":640.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":638.54,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So that was my one question when Guiller and Paula and I were talking through.","index":131,"end_time":642.86,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":640.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re going to go ahead and start.","index":132,"end_time":644.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":642.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Typically we would say like, all right.","index":133,"end_time":646.62,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":645.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Here''S all the copy, then here''s all the design and then we develop it.","index":134,"end_time":649.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":646.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"With you guys not really having any, like, negative feedback or any changes or anything.","index":135,"end_time":653.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":649.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re just going to start doing the development phase so that we can create this project along.","index":136,"end_time":656.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":653.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, that''s totally fine.","index":137,"end_time":657.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":656.9,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yep.","index":138,"end_time":658.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":658.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":139,"end_time":659.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":658.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":140,"end_time":660.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":659.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, what you guys have is.","index":141,"end_time":661.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":660.18,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"It looks a lot better and you know, so I, I didn''t have any complaints, so feel free if you want.","index":142,"end_time":666.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":661.3,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"All right, you.","index":143,"end_time":667.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":666.5,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You get the ultimate day.","index":144,"end_time":668.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":667.3,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We''re trying to make ourselves look like the big five.","index":145,"end_time":670.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":668.34,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yep.","index":146,"end_time":670.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":670.42,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But, you know, slightly customized, so.","index":147,"end_time":672.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":671.06,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, exactly.","index":148,"end_time":673.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":672.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":149,"end_time":674.059,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":673.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Still differentiating.","index":150,"end_time":674.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":674.059,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":151,"end_time":675.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":675.06,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":152,"end_time":676.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":675.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I haven''t seen any changes.","index":153,"end_time":678.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":676.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The question I had going back on the thing is in regards to when you guys go to the website, kind of positioning, keep in mind is primary is either retain or we have the contingent stuff and then kind of what I call rpo, fractional or kind of the secondary stuff.","index":154,"end_time":693.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":678.34,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So if you look at where the masses of the revenues being driven.","index":155,"end_time":697.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":693.64,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"88.","index":156,"end_time":699.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":698.92,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Well, 78% of my revenue is coming from retained search and then the other, you know, remainder is going to be, you know, a little bit of fractional and then, you know, contingent.","index":157,"end_time":709.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":699.88,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Because like I said, some of my smaller clients that are startups or stuff like that, you know, I have an exclusive but you know, they''re.","index":158,"end_time":716.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":709.72,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"They pay me at the end once I do it where, you know, my bigger PE clients were running a traditional executive search.","index":159,"end_time":724.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":716.76,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So as you guys highlight or highlight, that would be.","index":160,"end_time":727.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":724.3,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We want to definitely lead with retained search as our primary because that''s where the real money is.","index":161,"end_time":732.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":727.62,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yes.","index":162,"end_time":732.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":732.1,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We can talk about the other things that we do, but retained is what we.","index":163,"end_time":736.219,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":732.46,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We want to use to drive the revenue because there''s high profitability in that.","index":164,"end_time":739.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":736.219,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So.","index":165,"end_time":740.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":739.74,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":166,"end_time":740.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":740.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":167,"end_time":741.22,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":740.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that feeds directly into how we.","index":168,"end_time":742.46,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":741.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Were situating it anyways with PE back being a large portion of the copy as well.","index":169,"end_time":746.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":742.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":170,"end_time":746.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":746.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that.","index":171,"end_time":747.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":746.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That fits perfectly.","index":172,"end_time":748.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":747.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":173,"end_time":750.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":749.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I haven''t seen any changes to the social content calendar that we created.","index":174,"end_time":753.76,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":750.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So one, I want to make sure.","index":175,"end_time":754.88,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":753.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That you guys have been able to get into this.","index":176,"end_time":756.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":754.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Did the links that we share worked, Kristen?","index":177,"end_time":760,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":758.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I just.","index":178,"end_time":761.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":760.64,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"I have it on my one on one with Michael.","index":179,"end_time":764.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":761.84,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"We just weren''t able to meet on Friday.","index":180,"end_time":765.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":764.04,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"I had captured awesome family thing come up.","index":181,"end_time":769.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":765.6,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"All right, well, keep us posted with any questions or anything or any changes.","index":182,"end_time":772.8,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":769.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That you''re making to this.","index":183,"end_time":773.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":772.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"In the meantime, it kind of feeds off the.","index":184,"end_time":776.61,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":773.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The next slide, but we''ll be creating the full package.","index":185,"end_time":779.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":776.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''ll have all the intros and outros and how we''ll basically produce every asset out of the.","index":186,"end_time":785.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":779.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any.","index":187,"end_time":786.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":785.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any interviews that we run.","index":188,"end_time":787.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":786.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":189,"end_time":788.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":788.04,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"With the logos, we''ve created actually a bunch of different variations.","index":190,"end_time":794.16,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":789.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we want to send over this.","index":191,"end_time":795.28,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":794.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Markup link and this just has a bunch of different styles that we''ve created with different ways to use the green gradient.","index":192,"end_time":801.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":795.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we just wanted you to make.","index":193,"end_time":804.39,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":803.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A decision here because that will obviously impact what we put on the website, what we put into the Executive Vantage logo.","index":194,"end_time":811.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":804.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it.","index":195,"end_time":811.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":811.39,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Now let me ask you this, which, that, that one''s pretty cool.","index":196,"end_time":814.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":811.87,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"What of the 30 that you guys have there, what was your guys''s favorites?","index":197,"end_time":818.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":814.67,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So I really like, I think this.","index":198,"end_time":819.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":818.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Gradient is really clean and I think it shows that you are still like standing out as kind of a different piece but definitely blended into.","index":199,"end_time":828.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":819.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I kind of read a little bit into like the emotional side of imagery.","index":200,"end_time":831.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":829.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I think this strikes a nice balance with saying like we are kind.","index":201,"end_time":836.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":831.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Of standalone but we are also in.","index":202,"end_time":837.97,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":836.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The fold of Richie Mae.","index":203,"end_time":838.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":837.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we have our full capabilities but also theirs.","index":204,"end_time":841.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":838.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":205,"end_time":842.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":841.85,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"No, I like that.","index":206,"end_time":843.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":842.41,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, there''s a bunch of different ones in here.","index":207,"end_time":845.93,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":844.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So let us know what you prefer.","index":208,"end_time":847.21,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":845.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we can go with that because we even have like different gradients on the text.","index":209,"end_time":850.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":847.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":210,"end_time":850.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":850.13,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"From a website like that where you''re blending in the different color and stuff like that.","index":211,"end_time":854.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":851.21,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"How does that look from a site standpoint or what''s your guys recommendation on that?","index":212,"end_time":858.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":854.73,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Because then you''re, you know, to this you''re kind of blending in our colors and their colors all into that.","index":213,"end_time":863.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":858.21,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You know, you''re kind of hitting it all into one.","index":214,"end_time":865.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":863.44,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":215,"end_time":866.32,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":865.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So for all of these we created variations so we can have it on.","index":216,"end_time":869,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":866.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A white background, a dark background, colored background, everything like that.","index":217,"end_time":872.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":869,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So as far as like placement on.","index":218,"end_time":874.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":872.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The website or any documents, we are safe.","index":219,"end_time":876.48,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":874.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like we have a version for anything.","index":220,"end_time":877.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":876.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":221,"end_time":878.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":878.08,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So yeah, it''s really just up to personal preference.","index":222,"end_time":880.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":878.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":223,"end_time":881.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":880.88,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then hey, the other thing that I was going to let you know too is and hopefully this doesn''t cause any fricking grief because I gave him.","index":224,"end_time":889.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":881.48,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I didn''t realize he was going to move him to GoDaddy.","index":225,"end_time":892.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":889.57,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But those, the KTC search and stuff, those other domains that I have, Daniel, which was our Google guy that was kind of setting up domain, he transferred those domains all to GoDaddy.","index":226,"end_time":904.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":892.05,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So they''re sitting on GoDaddy''s.","index":227,"end_time":905.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":904.21,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Does that really make it.","index":228,"end_time":906.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":905.65,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"That doesn''t mess.","index":229,"end_time":907.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":906.53,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"No, it''s not a huge.","index":230,"end_time":908.13,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":907.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As long as we get access to.","index":231,"end_time":909.21,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":908.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It, we can update the records.","index":232,"end_time":910.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":909.21,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s fine.","index":233,"end_time":911.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":910.57,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yep.","index":234,"end_time":911.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":911.37,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I was trying to get away from godaddy and then he.","index":235,"end_time":913.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":911.77,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I saw that stuff went through so it is what it is.","index":236,"end_time":915.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":913.65,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But yeah, I mean they''re a cheap registrar so.","index":237,"end_time":918.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":915.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":238,"end_time":918.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":918.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":239,"end_time":918.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":918.33,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":240,"end_time":919.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":918.78,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":241,"end_time":920.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":919.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then one other thing I wanted to follow up on from our last call was I know you were trying to set up a Clay account, so I did talk to a member of.","index":242,"end_time":926.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":920.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Their team over there and they said that the self serve signup is still working.","index":243,"end_time":929.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":926.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I wanted to also have some time maybe if you wanted to share.","index":244,"end_time":932.82,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":929.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Your screen and just see like what issue you''re running into and then I can help you further.","index":245,"end_time":936.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":932.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, what I guess with Clay and we can save it to the end once you go through stuff is I''m used to Zoom info.","index":246,"end_time":942.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":936.14,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So the way Clay sets us up, you know, they got all the different stuff you can, you know, the behind the work diagram and when I signed up and logged in and just did the free one temporarily and it shows the information, but the way it provides the information is totally different than what I''m used to seeing with Zoom.","index":247,"end_time":959.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":942.38,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So I guess I''d like to tell you what I''d like to use it for and then maybe you guys can say, does it make sense to switch to them?","index":248,"end_time":967.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":960.02,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Will they be able to get me that information or not?","index":249,"end_time":969.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":967.06,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Because really all I''m looking for is enrichment.","index":250,"end_time":972.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":969.46,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So when we''re pushing stuff into HubSpot, we''re able to enrich the data in regards to it''s sucking in all the players so we''re not handkey and all this stuff.","index":251,"end_time":981.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":972.46,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And that''s really what I use Zoom for.","index":252,"end_time":983.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":981.76,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I mean at the end of the day when you guys start building the campaigns and stuff, you''re really doing my outreach there.","index":253,"end_time":988.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":983.16,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So I''m not really going to be doing a whole lot other than what you guys drive because I''ll, I''ll keep myself busy with my referrals and then hopefully you guys are bringing us in new clients.","index":254,"end_time":996.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":988.36,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So you''re doing all the outreach.","index":255,"end_time":998.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":996.88,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So I don''t really, I''m not going to be downloading a bunch of friggin list.","index":256,"end_time":1002.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":998.48,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I just wanted to keep my data enriched and clean.","index":257,"end_time":1006,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1002.8,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So that way when we''re doing these searches or we''re, you know, we''re getting people, we''re able to push all that people in there automatically instead of hand keying it.","index":258,"end_time":1013.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1006,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So yeah, you guys, since you guys are a user of Clay and I''m sure you Zoom, I''d love your insight to say hey, based on what you''re trying to do, you know, yeah, this or you do need it.","index":259,"end_time":1024.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1013.28,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So yeah, absolutely.","index":260,"end_time":1025.76,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1024.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So there''s a few things there.","index":261,"end_time":1027.16,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1025.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So one is for pure enrichment, HubSpot.","index":262,"end_time":1030.8,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1027.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Also has Breeze, which is an AI platform that they utilize to Pull, like, company names and information like that based off of email addresses.","index":263,"end_time":1038,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1030.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you''re looking to say, like, hey, I engaged with this company, and I.","index":264,"end_time":1041.54,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1038.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Want to get more people into HubSpot that are, like, these titles from this company.","index":265,"end_time":1045.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1041.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, Clay is a perfect place to do that.","index":266,"end_time":1047.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1045.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":267,"end_time":1047.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1047.34,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So what we can do, and we can even do it from our side.","index":268,"end_time":1050.58,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1048.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is just set up like a connection from your HubSpot account to Clay.","index":269,"end_time":1053.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1050.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Say, whenever a record''s created, find these titles at that company and then add them back to HubSpot.","index":270,"end_time":1060.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1053.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":271,"end_time":1060.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1060.46,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":272,"end_time":1061.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1060.86,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Because what.","index":273,"end_time":1062.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1061.38,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"What I have, the Columbia people, you know, they''ve kind of been building some of the stuff which you guys can probably see.","index":274,"end_time":1066.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1062.38,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"What they''re doing in there is right now everything''s plugged into to Zoom.","index":275,"end_time":1070.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1066.74,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So anytime I sync something or pull, it''s all coming from Zoom.","index":276,"end_time":1073.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1070.48,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"They were waiting on me for the Clay standpoint, but when I was playing with Clay, the way, you know, I couldn''t see the way it generates the names and the numbers.","index":277,"end_time":1082.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1074.24,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You know, I''m just like, from a Zoom, you go in there and it shows the.","index":278,"end_time":1084.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1082.32,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Org charge, it shows the email just seems a little bit cleaner.","index":279,"end_time":1087.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1084.84,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I''m assuming Clay gives you the same stuff, but I couldn''t figure out how to manipulate it to see what I was trying to get.","index":280,"end_time":1093.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1088.16,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, I got you.","index":281,"end_time":1094.72,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1093.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So here''s even, like, a template that.","index":282,"end_time":1096.56,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1094.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have set up.","index":283,"end_time":1097.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1096.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So going.","index":284,"end_time":1097.84,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1097.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The way to start it all is by searching.","index":285,"end_time":1099.83,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1098,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Searching for a company list based on parameters.","index":286,"end_time":1102.58,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1099.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you would say, like, find companies, and then you would enter in information.","index":287,"end_time":1105.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1102.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like revenue levels, employee counts, industries, all that sort of stuff.","index":288,"end_time":1109.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1105.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it would pull your list of companies.","index":289,"end_time":1110.78,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1109.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We automatically put in some enrichments because.","index":290,"end_time":1113.58,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1111.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sometimes, like, the spelling can be off or it''s like a trademark sign that they didn''t put incorrectly.","index":291,"end_time":1118.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1113.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so we clean that up, and.","index":292,"end_time":1120.5,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1119.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then you can just hit find.","index":293,"end_time":1122.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1120.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Find people at these companies, and it''ll open up like, I want these job.","index":294,"end_time":1127.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1124.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Titles, this level of seniority.","index":295,"end_time":1128.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1127.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I want them in these locations.","index":296,"end_time":1130.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1128.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then they''ll automatically populate here, and we can add any enrichment that we need.","index":297,"end_time":1135.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1131.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is basically saying any one of these companies with these specific titles is who we want to pool, and then we can directly add them.","index":298,"end_time":1142.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1136.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Austin.","index":299,"end_time":1152.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1151.55,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":300,"end_time":1153.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1152.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I still have you.","index":301,"end_time":1154.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1153.23,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":302,"end_time":1155.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1155.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Am I back?","index":303,"end_time":1156.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1155.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":304,"end_time":1157.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1156.92,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You''re back.","index":305,"end_time":1157.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1157.12,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yep.","index":306,"end_time":1157.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1157.52,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"All right.","index":307,"end_time":1158.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1157.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry about that.","index":308,"end_time":1158.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1158.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He''s back.","index":309,"end_time":1159.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1158.72,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"So, hey, Colin, quick question for you is when you say it enriches that something that you guys are building on the backside that you''re adding stuff in there.","index":310,"end_time":1165.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1159.56,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So you have to Program it a little bit or no.","index":311,"end_time":1167.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1165.76,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So some information does come like out of the box.","index":312,"end_time":1170.84,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1168.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if I click on like this person.","index":313,"end_time":1172.44,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1170.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So basically these two columns, we didn''t do anything.","index":314,"end_time":1175.96,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1172.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We just said, I want this company and I want these job titles.","index":315,"end_time":1178.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1175.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it pulls that for us out of the box.","index":316,"end_time":1180.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1178.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We get a bunch of information.","index":317,"end_time":1181.32,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1180.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":318,"end_time":1182.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1181.72,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But to find like their work email.","index":319,"end_time":1184.74,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1183.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or anything like that, then we do need to set up an enrichment, which we just run through a bunch of tools to find their work email.","index":320,"end_time":1193.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1186.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We even do like, zoom info sometimes.","index":321,"end_time":1195.46,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1193.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If other tools aren''t finding the information, determine if they''re a fit, and then we can add them directly into our campaigns as well.","index":322,"end_time":1201.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1196.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, okay, got it, got it, got it, got it, got it.","index":323,"end_time":1203.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1201.62,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":324,"end_time":1204.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1203.62,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So from a standpoint of, I guess, Clay, what license would I need to buy to get, you know, so the flexibility.","index":325,"end_time":1212.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1204.5,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So you can pull some of that.","index":326,"end_time":1214.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1212.82,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So we actually.","index":327,"end_time":1218.54,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1214.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So there''s.","index":328,"end_time":1219.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1218.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s a few ways we can go about it.","index":329,"end_time":1220.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1219.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you wanted to start, they actually just have a credits model.","index":330,"end_time":1223.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1220.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you can just say, I want to buy.","index":331,"end_time":1224.54,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1223.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, you could probably start with like, what is their lowest number?","index":332,"end_time":1229.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1225.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think it''s like 10.","index":333,"end_time":1230.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1229.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think they have like a 10,000 credits per month or something.","index":334,"end_time":1232.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1230.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":335,"end_time":1233.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1233.02,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Let me just pull that up really quick.","index":336,"end_time":1237.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1235.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then you can.","index":337,"end_time":1238.86,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1238.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You can change it at any point as well.","index":338,"end_time":1240.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1238.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you could say like, hey, we didn''t use them all.","index":339,"end_time":1242.56,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1240.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And they.","index":340,"end_time":1243,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1242.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They don''t automatically expire.","index":341,"end_time":1244.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1243,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You get like half of the next month or most of the next month before they expire from the last month as well.","index":342,"end_time":1249.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1244.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, yeah, I would start, I mean.","index":343,"end_time":1253.52,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1251.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Even at the free.","index":344,"end_time":1254.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1253.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You get 1200 credits and if you move up to like a starter pack, you know, you can do it per year or you can do per month.","index":345,"end_time":1262.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1254.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I would go per month.","index":346,"end_time":1263.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1262.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":347,"end_time":1264.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1263.56,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And you can just start with like, you know, 3,000 credits a month or if you see.","index":348,"end_time":1270.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1264.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then basically after the first month.","index":349,"end_time":1273.16,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1271.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or two or three, we''ll be able to tell you, like, consistently we''re using these many credits.","index":350,"end_time":1276.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1273.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So here''s what you should change your plan to.","index":351,"end_time":1279.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1277.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it, got it.","index":352,"end_time":1280.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1279.4,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":353,"end_time":1280.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1280.24,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So once.","index":354,"end_time":1282.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1281,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Now with the stuff that I have for you, do you guys do that or would I buy this and then you guys would use my license or whatever.","index":355,"end_time":1289.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1282.44,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I buy it just be used for what I would use myself.","index":356,"end_time":1292.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1289.72,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":357,"end_time":1292.69,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1292.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s.","index":358,"end_time":1293.09,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1292.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s an either or there.","index":359,"end_time":1294.17,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1293.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So most clients don''t like to hop.","index":360,"end_time":1296.05,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1294.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Into these platforms and do anything themselves.","index":361,"end_time":1297.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1296.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So for every 2,000 credits that we.","index":362,"end_time":1300.21,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1297.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Spend, we just charge you one point, as you can see there, a little bit there.","index":363,"end_time":1304.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1300.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We actually undercharge there.","index":364,"end_time":1305.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1304.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":365,"end_time":1306.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1305.85,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Because we have a partnership with them, so.","index":366,"end_time":1308.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1306.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":367,"end_time":1309.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1308.81,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":368,"end_time":1309.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1309.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you want to just do it where anytime we use any, any credits.","index":369,"end_time":1312.69,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1309.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We just charge you the point.","index":370,"end_time":1313.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1312.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then we can do it like that.","index":371,"end_time":1314.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1313.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":372,"end_time":1315.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1314.97,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":373,"end_time":1315.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1315.61,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":374,"end_time":1316.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1315.97,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"All right, I''ll mess with this.","index":375,"end_time":1317.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1316.53,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then the way you guys had that set up, is that stuff set up pretty easy or is it.","index":376,"end_time":1321.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1317.37,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Or is it.","index":377,"end_time":1321.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1321.33,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You have to get somewhat sophistic client.","index":378,"end_time":1324.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1321.85,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Because two things that were that I''m thinking for this is one is.","index":379,"end_time":1328.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1324.51,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Is for the client intake that''s coming in.","index":380,"end_time":1331.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1328.95,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But we have some offshore recruiters that they''re helping us with roles and yes, we have LinkedIn recruiter and you know, but part of the problem that I''ve had with our Indian resources, they don''t use the inmails appropriate.","index":381,"end_time":1345.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1331.67,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"They just blow through them and they''re like gold.","index":382,"end_time":1347.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1345.15,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So I have a couple other platforms where if, you know, they build a plat, they build a list of candidates, we can export them and, you know, generate you names and emails.","index":383,"end_time":1356.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1348.71,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I was also looking to see is, is this tool potentially, you know, could help us with that also, or have you seen Clay more?","index":384,"end_time":1364.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1357.17,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"It''s, you know, you''re not really getting the IC people.","index":385,"end_time":1368.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1365.25,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You''re getting more of what I''d call, you know, your traditional, you know, level one managers and up, you know.","index":386,"end_time":1375.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1368.33,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"No, I mean, this, this utilizes LinkedIn''s.","index":387,"end_time":1377.45,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1375.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Database for a lot of information.","index":388,"end_time":1378.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1377.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then you can also, I mean, if I go over here and hit add column, I mean, there I can search, you know, zoom info.","index":389,"end_time":1384.92,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1378.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can pull direct integrations from there for enrichments.","index":390,"end_time":1388.16,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1385.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, basically the way to think.","index":391,"end_time":1389.96,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1388.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"About Clay is it''s a massive spreadsheet that has integrations built into it.","index":392,"end_time":1394.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1389.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it, got it.","index":393,"end_time":1395.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1394.36,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Now, if you put in, you know, zoom info, you''re driving zoom info.","index":394,"end_time":1398.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1395.68,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I''m assuming you have to have a subscription with zoom info then, right?","index":395,"end_time":1401.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1398.8,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Correct.","index":396,"end_time":1401.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1401.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":397,"end_time":1402.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1401.96,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"If you say zoom info there from actions, you would just put in your credit, your credentials there.","index":398,"end_time":1406.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1402.6,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s already hooked up to our API right here.","index":399,"end_time":1409.16,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1407.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s what this key means.","index":400,"end_time":1410.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1409.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, got it.","index":401,"end_time":1410.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1410.28,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":402,"end_time":1411.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1410.96,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"All right, perfect.","index":403,"end_time":1412.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1411.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But yeah, for any of those purposes.","index":404,"end_time":1414.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1412.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, Clay is great for LinkedIn messages.","index":405,"end_time":1417.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1414.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We use Heyreach.","index":406,"end_time":1417.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1417.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That does in mail as well.","index":407,"end_time":1419.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1417.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If we wanted to utilize that, that is $79 a month per user.","index":408,"end_time":1423.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1419.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":409,"end_time":1424.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1423.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So let me ask you this.","index":410,"end_time":1425.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1424.27,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So it''s called heyreach.","index":411,"end_time":1426.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1425.15,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yes.","index":412,"end_time":1426.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1426.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"H E Y R E A okay, how does that different from, like, a source whale?","index":413,"end_time":1434.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1426.99,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Because we have source mail.","index":414,"end_time":1435.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1434.23,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We also have talent, which is running, running out.","index":415,"end_time":1438.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1435.39,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Is it, you know, like, with source whale, talent works a little better.","index":416,"end_time":1441.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1438.27,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Where if I load up a ca, then I say I want a message, it loads it all up, and boom, boom, boom.","index":417,"end_time":1446.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1441.27,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Source whale, it queues it.","index":418,"end_time":1449.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1446.94,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But you have to copy paste.","index":419,"end_time":1450.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1449.22,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So you have to copy the message out of source whale, drop it into the LinkedIn message subject, and then send.","index":420,"end_time":1455.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1450.5,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Does your Heyreach?","index":421,"end_time":1457.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1455.82,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Does it.","index":422,"end_time":1457.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1457.38,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Is it automated or is it still the same thing?","index":423,"end_time":1459.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1457.86,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"If you''re doing through LinkedIn, you have to copy paste.","index":424,"end_time":1461.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1459.78,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"No, it''s all automated.","index":425,"end_time":1462.78,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1461.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the cool thing about heyreach is you can upload lists in several different ways.","index":426,"end_time":1465.58,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1462.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Typically, we take the exact list that.","index":427,"end_time":1467.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1465.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''Re emailing and upload them as a CSV and then we have personalization for, like, name and company and all that sort of stuff.","index":428,"end_time":1472.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1467.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then it''s just a workflow.","index":429,"end_time":1474.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1473.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we say, like, all right, first I want to view their profile.","index":430,"end_time":1477.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1474.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we send them a notification that you viewed their profile.","index":431,"end_time":1479.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1477.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then three hours later, I want to send a connection request.","index":432,"end_time":1481.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1479.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then based on did they accept it?","index":433,"end_time":1484.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1482.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Did they not?","index":434,"end_time":1485.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1484.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Here''s a message that we''re sending.","index":435,"end_time":1486.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1485.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If they didn''t respond, here''s another message we send a couple days later.","index":436,"end_time":1488.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1486.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s just a full, like, workflow diagram.","index":437,"end_time":1491.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1489.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, got it, got it, got it, got it.","index":438,"end_time":1493.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1491.63,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":439,"end_time":1494.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1493.51,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"All right, check that out.","index":440,"end_time":1495.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1494.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":441,"end_time":1496.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1495.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":442,"end_time":1496.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1496.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we''re going to be setting that up.","index":443,"end_time":1497.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1496.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s what we''re going to utilize for your campaign.","index":444,"end_time":1500.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1497.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":445,"end_time":1501.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1500.84,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So we''ll do heyreach and Smart Lead as the email side of it.","index":446,"end_time":1504.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1501.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":447,"end_time":1504.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1504.2,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":448,"end_time":1505.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1504.96,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yep.","index":449,"end_time":1506.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1505.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But the list that I''ll be sending over for you guys to review will be something that we built in Clay.","index":450,"end_time":1511.12,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1506.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''ll give you a CSV to go through and just make sure all the companies and contacts and job titles and everything that we have are fit.","index":451,"end_time":1516.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1511.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But all of those were also outlined in that ABM document that.","index":452,"end_time":1520.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1516.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That is, like, all of the parameters that we''re pulling to build these lists.","index":453,"end_time":1523.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1520.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":454,"end_time":1524.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1523.52,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Hey, Colin.","index":455,"end_time":1525.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1524.36,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Yeah?","index":456,"end_time":1525.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1525.24,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"With Hay Reach, I don''t know if this is possible.","index":457,"end_time":1528.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1526.05,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"We did it.","index":458,"end_time":1529.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1528.57,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"My team did it at my old organization, but we didn''t use Hay Reach.","index":459,"end_time":1533.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1529.73,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"So we could essentially email the candidate or, you know, the contact or in mail.","index":460,"end_time":1543.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1533.41,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"They.","index":461,"end_time":1544.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1544.29,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"And we would essentially direct them to, like, a link to either apply or to schedule time, but they didn''t have the opportunity to respond essentially to the email.","index":462,"end_time":1554.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1544.93,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Is that something that we''re able to manipulate and do in heyreach or is that something.","index":463,"end_time":1560.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1555.85,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"So, for example, then we would, you know, send.","index":464,"end_time":1564.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1562.33,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"We would partner with I, you know, I may partner with Michael and the message might come from Michael, but then I''m connecting with the.","index":465,"end_time":1571.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1565.21,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"I''m interviewing the candidate.","index":466,"end_time":1573.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1572.17,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Or, you know, Michael may have an executive or email, but then it''s going through Michael.","index":467,"end_time":1581.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1573.65,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":468,"end_time":1582.06,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1581.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So for heyreach, yeah, it does do responses, and it also, like when we.","index":469,"end_time":1585.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1582.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Connect Michael''s profile, Michael will send you a login and then you just log into LinkedIn.","index":470,"end_time":1588.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1585.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Essentially.","index":471,"end_time":1589.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1588.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It tracks and you can say, like, I only want to track conversations started from heyreach or I want all conversations tracked in here.","index":472,"end_time":1595.46,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1589.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And it''ll show, like, the full, like, message log of everything going back and forth.","index":473,"end_time":1598.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1595.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, super helpful.","index":474,"end_time":1600.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1599.26,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":475,"end_time":1601.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1600.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":476,"end_time":1601.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1601.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Heyreach is a really cool tool.","index":477,"end_time":1602.86,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1601.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We originally used tools that combined email.","index":478,"end_time":1606.06,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1603.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And LinkedIn, but they would break a lot because they were so dependent on each other.","index":479,"end_time":1609.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1606.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So now we have these operating kind of at the same time.","index":480,"end_time":1612.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1609.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So they are congruent but not super dependent on each other.","index":481,"end_time":1615.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1612.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":482,"end_time":1615.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1615.17,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"All right.","index":483,"end_time":1618.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1618.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that is everything.","index":484,"end_time":1619.29,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1618.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''ll send over the logos to review.","index":485,"end_time":1621.17,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1619.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let me know any feedback you have on the ABM plan.","index":486,"end_time":1624.05,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1621.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I''ll also email Ryan so we can get Google search console access.","index":487,"end_time":1629.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1624.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then Michael will Write a updated.","index":488,"end_time":1632.13,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1629.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"LinkedIn profile for you as well.","index":489,"end_time":1633.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1632.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":490,"end_time":1634.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1633.81,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And I can give you my password.","index":491,"end_time":1635.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1634.41,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You guys can log in and do whatever you want to do.","index":492,"end_time":1637.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1635.73,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"That''s totally fine.","index":493,"end_time":1638.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1637.7,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So.","index":494,"end_time":1638.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1638.42,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Okay.","index":495,"end_time":1639.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1638.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":496,"end_time":1639.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1639.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":497,"end_time":1641.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1640.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Paula, anything that I was missing, please keep me honest.","index":498,"end_time":1645.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1642.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I two other quick questions I had for you guys.","index":499,"end_time":1646.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1645.18,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So you''re going to start building everything out in HubSpot?","index":500,"end_time":1649.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1646.94,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"When would we.","index":501,"end_time":1650.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1649.5,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"When are you guys thinking we would cut over to.","index":502,"end_time":1654.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1650.26,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"To HubSpot?","index":503,"end_time":1655.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1654.94,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then HubSpot''s, you know, basically the website, you know, site.","index":504,"end_time":1658.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1655.9,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then once we do cut over to HubSpot and you guys have all the content done, do we eventually build sub pages or sub, you know, landing pages for different campaigns within that too?","index":505,"end_time":1667.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1658.7,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":506,"end_time":1668.2,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1667.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":507,"end_time":1668.56,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1668.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''m envisioning art.","index":508,"end_time":1670.08,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1668.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The main developer that''s going to be.","index":509,"end_time":1672.08,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1670.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Running this project is out this week just for holiday, but I. I feel confident that we could have this done by the end of the month.","index":510,"end_time":1678.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1672.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":511,"end_time":1679.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1678.959,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, keep me honest there as well.","index":512,"end_time":1682.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1680.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But yes, to answer your question, any.","index":513,"end_time":1684.24,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1682.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Campaign, landing pages, anything, we build that directly in HubSpot.","index":514,"end_time":1687.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1684.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":515,"end_time":1687.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1687.28,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then because I was putting.","index":516,"end_time":1690.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1687.88,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"When Christian was help building my budget for me, I know you guys Want to use paid ads.","index":517,"end_time":1697.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1690.26,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"When do we think we want to start dropping pay ads?","index":518,"end_time":1699.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1697.62,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Because I think you said you guys wanted what, two to three grand in 2000 or 2000amonth or 3000, whatever.","index":519,"end_time":1704.899,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1699.82,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, what.","index":520,"end_time":1706.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1705.06,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"When were we looking to do that?","index":521,"end_time":1707.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1706.1,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Was that going to be a Q2 start or was that, you know, what, what are you guys envisioning from that?","index":522,"end_time":1711.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1707.54,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So the way that we structure these ABM campaigns and again, it''s all in that plan document.","index":523,"end_time":1716.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1712.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But the best way to get results.","index":524,"end_time":1719.19,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1716.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is by having multiple channels running at the same time.","index":525,"end_time":1721.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1719.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So people will say cold email is dead.","index":526,"end_time":1724.47,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1721.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I fight against that very hard.","index":527,"end_time":1725.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1724.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think cold email is just awareness.","index":528,"end_time":1727.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1725.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think it''s something for us to.","index":529,"end_time":1729.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1727.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Get in front of someone.","index":530,"end_time":1729.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1729.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But then they get a LinkedIn message, then they see an ad, then they go to the landing page, they get hit with another ad, all of a sudden they get a fourth email.","index":531,"end_time":1736.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1729.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They know who the brand is, that''s when they follow up.","index":532,"end_time":1738.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1736.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So typically we do start paid activity.","index":533,"end_time":1741.31,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1738.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As soon as emails start sending and messages start going out.","index":534,"end_time":1744.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1741.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, got it.","index":535,"end_time":1745.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1744.55,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":536,"end_time":1746.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1745.99,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"What was the forecasted date for that to go live?","index":537,"end_time":1749.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1746.35,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"I mean, we''ll have the.","index":538,"end_time":1750.39,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1749.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Since I''m hearing that you might come back with some feedback on the ABM.","index":539,"end_time":1753.63,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1750.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Plan this week, that''s the only thing that would impact it.","index":540,"end_time":1755.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1753.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I mean, we can have the list ready next week, the account set up by next week, and then at that point we''re pretty much we just need to build the infrastructure in N8N which takes about two days and then, and then we can go live.","index":541,"end_time":1767.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1755.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":542,"end_time":1768.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1768.47,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"And Colin, I had just missed obviously earlier conversations.","index":543,"end_time":1772.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1768.99,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"From a payday out standpoint, how much per quarter were you recommending from a.","index":544,"end_time":1779.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1772.62,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Spend stand per quarter?","index":545,"end_time":1780.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1779.06,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Between six and 12 grand.","index":546,"end_time":1782.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1781.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Between six to 12.","index":547,"end_time":1784.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1782.78,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Okay.","index":548,"end_time":1784.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1784.06,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Okay.","index":549,"end_time":1785.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1784.62,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"And then what has been your recommendation when you''re partnering with clients?","index":550,"end_time":1790.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1785.58,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Is it like start high, trend back or start low trend up?","index":551,"end_time":1795.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1790.26,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"So it''s not a blanket answer, but typically.","index":552,"end_time":1799.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1796.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we recommended two to three grand.","index":553,"end_time":1802.09,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1800.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I would like to have 2500 on.","index":554,"end_time":1804.61,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1802.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"LinkedIn ads and 500 on our retargeting Pixel ads.","index":555,"end_time":1807.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1804.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I want to add this to our budgets.","index":556,"end_time":1811.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1809.85,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Right, yeah, of course.","index":557,"end_time":1812.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1811.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And, and we are in the accounts.","index":558,"end_time":1814.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1812.729,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Every week, optimizing for performance and running analytics.","index":559,"end_time":1818.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1814.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so we come up, we come.","index":560,"end_time":1820.21,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1818.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Into these meetings and we say like.","index":561,"end_time":1821.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1820.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, this ad variant isn''t performing very well.","index":562,"end_time":1823.93,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1821.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We want to create a new test.","index":563,"end_time":1825.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1824.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or hey, we''re seeing a lot of return on this channel, but we ran out of budget this month.","index":564,"end_time":1829.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1826.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let''s up the budget here.","index":565,"end_time":1831.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1829.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we make those recommendations to you on a weekly and monthly stance as well.","index":566,"end_time":1834.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1831.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":567,"end_time":1835.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1835.19,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"So you said 2500 LinkedIn and then 500 for.","index":568,"end_time":1839.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1835.67,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"It''s the tool we use is called add roll.","index":569,"end_time":1841.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1839.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":570,"end_time":1841.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1841.51,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"ADROLL Club.","index":571,"end_time":1842.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1841.87,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":572,"end_time":1843.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1842.95,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Yep.","index":573,"end_time":1844.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1843.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Michael.","index":574,"end_time":1847.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1846.79,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"I''ll put it on my.","index":575,"end_time":1847.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1847.23,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Our one on one.","index":576,"end_time":1848.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1847.95,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"We can probably revisit what we had budgeted there.","index":577,"end_time":1851.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1848.71,"speaker_name":"Kristen Baller"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":578,"end_time":1853.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1853.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":579,"end_time":1855.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1855.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Did I answer your two questions, Michael?","index":580,"end_time":1857.67,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1855.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":581,"end_time":1858.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1857.67,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yep, yep, yep.","index":582,"end_time":1859.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1858.07,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then the.","index":583,"end_time":1860.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1859.35,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"The ABM thing, I can still go in through that one email that you sent me.","index":584,"end_time":1864.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1860.23,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So that link is still live then, right?","index":585,"end_time":1865.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1864.07,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, Yep.","index":586,"end_time":1866.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1865.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":587,"end_time":1867.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1866.59,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":588,"end_time":1868.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1867.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, I did have one other quick question for you.","index":589,"end_time":1871.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1869.19,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So when.","index":590,"end_time":1872.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1871.19,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"When we switch everything over to KTC Search, do I need to.","index":591,"end_time":1877.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1872.95,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You know, obviously probably set up different email.","index":592,"end_time":1880.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1877.11,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Do we want to.","index":593,"end_time":1881.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1880.5,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You know, I guess I get with David on our.","index":594,"end_time":1882.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1881.18,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Our Google guy or guy on that.","index":595,"end_time":1886.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1883.62,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Because we want to probably rebrand some of that on 365 or whatever.","index":596,"end_time":1890.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1887.7,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Correct.","index":597,"end_time":1891.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1890.98,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I would say so.","index":598,"end_time":1892.9,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1891.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It just be.","index":599,"end_time":1894.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1893.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It would be less friction for a prospect to go through if they land.","index":600,"end_time":1898.42,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1895.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"On KTC search.com and they''re emailing someone at KTC Search.","index":601,"end_time":1902.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1898.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it.","index":602,"end_time":1902.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1902.02,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":603,"end_time":1902.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1902.5,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"No, that''s fine.","index":604,"end_time":1903.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1902.94,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":605,"end_time":1904.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1903.62,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":606,"end_time":1907.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1906.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":607,"end_time":1908.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1907.57,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Sounds like a plan.","index":608,"end_time":1908.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1908.01,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"All right, quick question for you because I think we have.","index":609,"end_time":1912.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1909.17,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"It is.","index":610,"end_time":1913.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1912.77,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We might need to.","index":611,"end_time":1914.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1913.25,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And maybe.","index":612,"end_time":1914.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1914.13,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I think we are.","index":613,"end_time":1915.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1914.49,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We might have already done it.","index":614,"end_time":1915.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1915.01,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Did we move next week?","index":615,"end_time":1918.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1915.85,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I got done traveling, so.","index":616,"end_time":1920.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1918.25,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":617,"end_time":1920.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1920.09,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We''re on Tuesday.","index":618,"end_time":1921.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1920.61,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I just want to make sure.","index":619,"end_time":1921.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1921.01,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Because I''m traveling Wednesday, Thursday, Friday next week.","index":620,"end_time":1923.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1921.69,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, make sure we.","index":621,"end_time":1924.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1923.85,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I couldn''t remember if we had moved that so cool.","index":622,"end_time":1927.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1924.89,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, I think we chatted about that last time.","index":623,"end_time":1929.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1927.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":624,"end_time":1929.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1929.09,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":625,"end_time":1930.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1929.77,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"It.","index":626,"end_time":1930.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1930.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":627,"end_time":1930.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1930.33,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Sounds like a plan.","index":628,"end_time":1931.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1930.73,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I appreciate it.","index":629,"end_time":1931.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1931.37,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":630,"end_time":1932.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1931.97,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":631,"end_time":1933.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1932.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, great stuff, guys.","index":632,"end_time":1934.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1933.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great to see you again.","index":633,"end_time":1935.29,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1934.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":634,"end_time":1935.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1935.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Bye.","index":635,"end_time":1936.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1935.85,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"}],"dateString":"2026-01-06T18:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/83519004309?pwd=JvKSZR6BzSlyNxK5WTgZHYayMsLSKi