-- Meeting: PTO Exchange Weekly (2026-01-05 20:30:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '3f032f15-833e-4d7d-9347-381febf6d953',
    '2026-01-05 20:30:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KDP8J3EPPMM9BTF89SKDWFA0',
    'PTO Exchange Weekly',
    '{"Josh Reinhard","Colin Costigan"}'::text[],
    1680,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/86093865913?pwd=ajXSuerDGmcROjfezSWYYGsa7iPOWd.1',
    '{"id":"01KDP8J3EPPMM9BTF89SKDWFA0","title":"PTO Exchange Weekly","summary":{"notes":"## **Resource Planning and Role Transition**\n\nThe team plans to hire a replacement for **Sam’s role** within the next week to stabilize marketing operations and ensure continuity (06:14).  \n- **Josh Reinhard** and **Rob** interviewed a candidate who might fill Sam’s position, with a decision expected soon.  \n- An interim period may require **Colin Costigan’s team** to support transition work until the new hire is fully up to speed or for a longer term if hiring is paused.  \n- **Colin** proposed discussing with **Justin and Tristan** about securing additional points for the next **three months** to cover this transition workload.  \n- The contract rate is set to revert back on **February 1st**, and the exact timeline will be confirmed to align budgeting with resource needs.  \n\nJosh also confirmed plans to hire a **Chief Marketing Officer (CMO)** to lead strategic efforts, which was positively received in early CMO interviews (08:19).  \n- The CMO’s role will focus on overseeing marketing strategy and coordination, addressing past gaps where no clear “conductor” existed.  \n- This hire aims to improve strategic direction and unify efforts across marketing and sales functions.  \n- Josh expects to finalize the hiring approach after discussions with Rob and will update Colin’s team by the next meeting on Monday.  \n\n## **HubSpot System Overhaul and Marketing Operations**\n\nThe current **HubSpot setup is fragmented and cluttered**, requiring both cleanup and strategic restructuring to improve efficiency and reporting (10:41).  \n- The candidate for Sam’s role is expected to make significant changes in how HubSpot tracks leads, contact properties, and campaign success metrics.  \n- Colin’s team can support either by implementing best practices or adapting to the new hire’s preferred setup, ensuring smooth collaboration.  \n- Josh emphasized that prior efforts to patch HubSpot created a “Frankenstein” system that is hard to maintain or undo (12:29).  \n- The team identified redundant and outdated workflows, such as lists tied to former team members, indicating a need for thorough audit and pruning (20:30).  \n- Colin suggested reviewing each workflow’s purpose and whether associated contacts are actively engaged or targeted, which could unlock valuable audiences for LinkedIn campaigns.  \n\nThere was a discussion about whether to retain some of Sam’s scoring and segmentation ideas or scrap and rebuild from scratch (22:12).  \n- Colin favors a fresh start focused on current needs rather than trying to untangle past efforts.  \n- Josh acknowledged potential value in Sam’s concepts but leans toward rebuilding with clearer goals and better execution.  \n- A short call with Sam to clarify key questions and intent behind existing setups was proposed to decide what to salvage or discard.  \n\n## **Design and Marketing Collateral Management**\n\nJosh highlighted issues around the **FIGMA asset catalog**, noting the lack of clear organization and ease of use for duplicating or modifying marketing materials (13:04).  \n- This disorganization impacts efficiency when the new hire or Colin’s team needs to work with design files.  \n- The plan is to clean up and tighten control over FIGMA assets to streamline campaign development and reduce duplication effort.  \n- Colin’s team will either assist the new hire in managing these assets or update them independently once the new structure is in place (13:46).  \n\n## **Channel Partner Collaboration and Campaign Alignment**\n\nJosh stressed the importance of improving collaboration between **marketing and the channel team**, especially between the marketing function and **Dave**, the channel lead (14:11).  \n- Past setup discouraged support for channel-driven meetings due to conflicting incentives between Sam and Dave.  \n- Josh wants the new marketing hire to adopt a mindset that fully supports channel initiatives and fosters cross-team cooperation.  \n- Invitations will be extended to **Dan, Steph, and Dave** to join marketing meetings for better alignment and shared visibility.  \n- Colin confirmed **Steph** is actively using Outreach and beginning to handle inbound leads, with ongoing support from Colin’s team as needed (15:54).  \n\nThe team agreed that any channel-related marketing work will involve Dave directly, with advance notice to ensure his participation when relevant.  \n\n## **Lead Management and CRM Hygiene**\n\nA specific case was discussed where **Steph encountered duplicate contact records** in HubSpot, highlighting ongoing CRM hygiene challenges (16:10).  \n- Colin’s team is ready to merge duplicates and troubleshoot lead workflow issues to prevent confusion and data fragmentation.  \n- They advised that any HubSpot or website-related questions go through the new North Slack channel for quick resolution.  \n- Josh will encourage the sales team to escalate issues via Slack and keep him copied for awareness and intervention if needed (17:31).  \n\nThis case exemplifies broader challenges with contact lifecycle management and the need for clearer, simplified workflows.  \n\n## **Operational Meetings and Quarterly Planning**\n\nColin’s team will be out of the office on **Thursday and Friday** for an onsite quarterly planning meeting with leadership at **Dominion Club in Richmond** (24:59).  \n- This session includes Colin, Tristan, Justin, and another team member working on quarterly goals and resource alignment.  \n- Josh and Colin agreed to pause their regular Thursday call and reconvene the following Monday with a clearer picture of hiring and ongoing priorities.  \n- Invitations to include Dan, Steph, and Dave in Monday meetings have already been sent by Colin to ensure all key stakeholders are engaged going forward.","outline":null,"keywords":["HubSpot","Marketing Strategy","Lead Management","Workflow Cleanup","Hiring Process","Channel Support"],"overview":"- **Resource Planning:** Hiring a replacement for Sam''s role is underway to stabilize marketing operations within the week.  \n- **CMO Hiring:** Plans to hire a Chief Marketing Officer will enhance strategic direction across marketing and sales functions.  \n- **HubSpot Redesign:** Current HubSpot system needs significant cleanup for better tracking of leads and campaign success metrics.  \n- **FIGMA Organization:** Improve FIGMA asset catalog to streamline design processes and reduce duplication for the upcoming new hire.  \n- **Channel Collaboration:** Enhance synergy between marketing and channel team to support joint initiatives and address past conflicts.  \n- **CRM Hygiene Issues:** Ongoing challenges with duplicate records and lead management necessitate clearer workflows and CRM maintenance.","action_items":"\n**Josh Reinhard**\nDiscuss hiring decisions for Sam’s replacement and CMO with Rob; finalize approach before next Monday meeting (08:18)\nInform Dan, Steph, and Dave about their inclusion in Monday meetings and clarify when Dave’s presence is necessary (15:41)\nCommunicate with Steph and Dan to direct any HubSpot/query issues through new North Slack channel for resolution (19:19)\nShare questions or needed clarifications with Sam about HubSpot workflows to inform cleanup or redevelopment (22:43)\nCoordinate with Colin’s team to integrate support for new hire and maintain marketing operations during transition (13:57)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nReview contract and point allocation with Justin and Tristan to cover interim work and possibly extend support beyond original contract (07:17)\nMonitor and support HubSpot workflow cleanups, including audits of lists, segmentation, and lead scoring (20:22)\nAssist in managing inbound lead/contact merges and provide quick-turnaround support via new North Slack channel (17:03)\nAccept invitations for Monday meetings and participate in strategic discussions moving forward (15:54)\nPrepare to support new marketing hires with system setup, structure changes, and ongoing campaign management (11:52)\nPlan to have follow-up dialogue with Sam regarding existing HubSpot automation for insights before potential rebuild (23:29)\nCancel Thursday meeting and proceed with revised scheduling around team availability (13:59)\n"},"duration":28,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"id":1,"name":"Colin Costigan"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hey, what''s up, Colin?","index":0,"end_time":259.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":258.34,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Hey, Josh.","index":1,"end_time":259.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":259.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":2,"end_time":260.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":259.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":3,"end_time":260.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":260.66,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"How you doing?","index":4,"end_time":261.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":260.98,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Doing all right.","index":5,"end_time":262.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":261.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How was family coming in?","index":6,"end_time":264.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":262.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was good.","index":7,"end_time":265.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":265.22,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It was fun and chaotic and all that.","index":8,"end_time":269.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":266.02,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So awesome.","index":9,"end_time":270.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":269.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All the good things.","index":10,"end_time":271.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":270.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Took him.","index":11,"end_time":272.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":272.02,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Took my brother and his family to the airport this morning, and they''re on their way back to Philadelphia, and good times were had.","index":12,"end_time":278.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":272.58,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That''s awesome.","index":13,"end_time":280.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":279.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":14,"end_time":280.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":280.1,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Glad to hear.","index":15,"end_time":281.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":280.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":16,"end_time":281.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":281.65,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"How''s your New Year''s?","index":17,"end_time":283.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":281.93,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It was good.","index":18,"end_time":284.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":283.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Still just battling back from my whole family got wiped out by whatever''s going around, so.","index":19,"end_time":290.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":285.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":20,"end_time":291.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":290.53,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But it happens.","index":21,"end_time":293.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":291.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We had made a huge party on Saturday night for the Seahawks game here.","index":22,"end_time":298.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":293.33,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We were gonna have a party, and then our.","index":23,"end_time":301.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":300.13,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And our neighbors were gonna have a party, and then we just combined the two.","index":24,"end_time":304.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":301.85,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We had, like, probably like, 45 people over, like, on Saturday night, and.","index":25,"end_time":309.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":304.77,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And started getting text on Sunday of like, this kid''s got a stomach bug, and this kid''s got a stomach bug, and this adult is either massively hungover or has a stomach bug.","index":26,"end_time":319.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":309.12,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And it was like, oh, man.","index":27,"end_time":320.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":319.6,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I just hope this doesn''t hit either my family or my brother''s family.","index":28,"end_time":324.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":320.92,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And we escaped, so that''s good.","index":29,"end_time":326.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":324.6,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":30,"end_time":327.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":327.04,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"My brother had one wave of nausea yesterday, but then he was fine, so.","index":31,"end_time":333.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":327.52,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Oh, no, here it comes.","index":32,"end_time":334.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":333.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think it was like, yeah.","index":33,"end_time":335.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":334.48,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Trickling around, but we were all.","index":34,"end_time":337.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":336.44,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"All escaped unscathed.","index":35,"end_time":339.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":337.88,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Well, that''s good.","index":36,"end_time":340.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":339.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":37,"end_time":340.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":340.44,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So I don''t have too much to share.","index":38,"end_time":346.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":343.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I really just want to have a conversation around.","index":39,"end_time":349.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":346.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know holidays and everything just happened.","index":40,"end_time":351.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":349.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But where you and Rob are with the search and HubSpot work and just, you know, to be point blank, I mean, out of everything that you guys have listed and everything that Sam listed that he was doing, definitely more than happy.","index":41,"end_time":366.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":351.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Happy and capable to do that work, because obviously that''s, you know, anything that we haven''t been asked isn''t happening as of now.","index":42,"end_time":374.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":366.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":43,"end_time":374.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":374.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, yeah, we''re still trying to figure that out.","index":44,"end_time":379.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":374.47,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So we''re.","index":45,"end_time":380.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":379.27,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Rob and I both interviewed a guy that we think we might hire to take on Sam''s role, and we''re probably going to be deciding that in the next week or so.","index":46,"end_time":393.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":382.19,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So we may have some kind of interim period where we need you guys to help bridge so that guy is.","index":47,"end_time":401,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":394.6,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Is up and running and, like, fully functional, or if we ultimately decide that we don''t want to hire this guy, then we would need you for a more of an extended period to do some of the stuff.","index":48,"end_time":411.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":401.24,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But, like, you know, everything dies down so much for us over the holidays that we didn''t have to do too much right now.","index":49,"end_time":417.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":411.96,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So we don''t have like a definitive kind of a plan.","index":50,"end_time":420.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":417.96,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Right.","index":51,"end_time":421.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":420.89,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But I also think we just have.","index":52,"end_time":427.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":421.69,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We just have a lot that we need to figure out.","index":53,"end_time":429.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":427.37,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But I. I do think that even if we hire this other person, there is some stuff that maybe Sam was doing that we should just have you guys be doing.","index":54,"end_time":436.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":429.05,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like, I would agree with that.","index":55,"end_time":438.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":437.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And also I''d be more than happy to talk to Justin and Tristan about just so it doesn''t impact like, your point and everything that we''re able to do.","index":56,"end_time":446.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":438.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll see if we can gift you guys some points maybe for the next three months just so we can cover all of this stuff, whether it''s interim and, you know, and then we keep talking and see if it goes more long term and what we do there.","index":57,"end_time":456.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":446.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":58,"end_time":457.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":457.02,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And we''re back up to the old rate, correct?","index":59,"end_time":461.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":458.94,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We had like a lower rate.","index":60,"end_time":463.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":461.98,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":61,"end_time":464.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":464.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''d have to check with them exactly the timeline of that contract.","index":62,"end_time":468.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":464.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think it was for like three months, if I remember correctly.","index":63,"end_time":470.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":468.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Trying to remember also.","index":64,"end_time":471.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":470.62,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So it might be.","index":65,"end_time":474.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":472.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You might be back.","index":66,"end_time":475.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":474.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Back up.","index":67,"end_time":476.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":475.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or maybe that''s next month.","index":68,"end_time":477.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":476.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll have to check.","index":69,"end_time":478.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":477.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":70,"end_time":478.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":478.66,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Trying to see if I can check while we''re on the phone.","index":71,"end_time":481.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":479.14,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But.","index":72,"end_time":481.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":481.14,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But that would be good for us just to know.","index":73,"end_time":483.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":481.38,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":74,"end_time":489.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":489.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"See if we can pull that up right now, actually.","index":75,"end_time":492.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":490.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"February 1st.","index":76,"end_time":497.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":496.5,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So we have the rest of this month on it.","index":77,"end_time":498.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":497.18,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yes.","index":78,"end_time":499.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":498.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"February 1st goes back to the other thing.","index":79,"end_time":501.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":499.42,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So let''s.","index":80,"end_time":503.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":503.06,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Let.","index":81,"end_time":503.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":503.7,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Let me.","index":82,"end_time":504.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":503.98,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Let me talk to Rob.","index":83,"end_time":505.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":504.88,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I mean, we''re talking about all this stuff now, but, like, I think we are going to go the route.","index":84,"end_time":510.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":505.64,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We''re going to hire someone.","index":85,"end_time":511.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":510.76,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I think.","index":86,"end_time":512.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":511.64,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I think we''re also going to hire a cmo.","index":87,"end_time":514.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":512.24,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Okay.","index":88,"end_time":515.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":515.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I told the cmo, like, what we do with you guys because I interviewed a couple of them already.","index":89,"end_time":522.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":515.72,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"She was like that.","index":90,"end_time":524.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":523.6,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"The way that you''re approaching this sounds great.","index":91,"end_time":526.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":524.72,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"You just need to have like, someone to be in charge of the strategy of the way that this is going to go.","index":92,"end_time":530.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":526.36,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And it seems like you guys have been like, putting the right structure in place, but didn''t have somebody in here that was like the conductor, which.","index":93,"end_time":541.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":530.84,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Which I agree with.","index":94,"end_time":541.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":541.07,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So I do think that''s the route that we''re gonna go, whether it''s these two people that we think we''re gonna hire or not.","index":95,"end_time":546.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":541.91,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I. I think probably yes, but I don''t know for sure.","index":96,"end_time":550.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":547.67,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":97,"end_time":551.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":550.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll.","index":98,"end_time":551.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":551.43,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So I''ll get with Rob this week because you said you''re not going to Be here on Thursday.","index":99,"end_time":555.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":552.47,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So, yeah, Thursday and Friday, I''m out.","index":100,"end_time":558.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":556.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I think by the time we meet again next Monday, I''ll have a much better handle on, like, the direction that we''re going.","index":101,"end_time":564.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":559.06,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But.","index":102,"end_time":565.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":564.98,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But all that said, I do think I. I do think it probably makes sense to get you guys doing some of the stuff that Sam was doing.","index":103,"end_time":574.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":565.38,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And if you have opinions on, like, based on what you heard from Sam, what is, like, easy to just, like, fold into you guys, that would be a good thing for.","index":104,"end_time":583.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":574.7,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"For me to know.","index":105,"end_time":584.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":583.42,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":106,"end_time":584.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":584.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":107,"end_time":584.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":584.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, off the top of my head, it''s like there''s a few different categories, right?","index":108,"end_time":588.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":584.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if it''s like HubSpot, like, hey, this isn''t showing, like, it needs to boom, easy.","index":109,"end_time":593.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":588.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, we''ll go in, we''ll audit the workflows, whatever we need to do there.","index":110,"end_time":595.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":593.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We need to set up new properties.","index":111,"end_time":597.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":595.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The other stuff is like, Sam mentioned the sales guys would say, like, hey, I have a meeting tomorrow and I need a deck that does X, Y and Z.","index":112,"end_time":605.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":598.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or we need a white paper for this.","index":113,"end_time":607.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":605.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We would just need to get that request.","index":114,"end_time":609.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":607.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But you''ve seen our design work and everything.","index":115,"end_time":611.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":609.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can do that no problem.","index":116,"end_time":612.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":611.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s really just like, making sure that you guys are keeping the lights on the way that you want to.","index":117,"end_time":618.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":613.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know there was nurture campaigns and he was writing a lot of emails.","index":118,"end_time":622.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":618.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ve kind of already taken over on the website side of things, so it''s really just like, what do we want to do?","index":119,"end_time":629.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":623.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is it a weekly nurture email that we need to go in and build a list and send out to.","index":120,"end_time":633.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":629.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you guys need help on any other outreach?","index":121,"end_time":635.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":633.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, as far as HubSpot capabilities, we''re more than able to jump in and really help anywhere.","index":122,"end_time":641.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":635.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":123,"end_time":642.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":641.85,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"My initial impression of the guy that I interviewed that I think that we might hire to backfill for Sam''s role is like, he''s a little bit more.","index":124,"end_time":652.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":642.29,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s the right word.","index":125,"end_time":655.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":654.49,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Almost like.","index":126,"end_time":657.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":656.57,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like technical a little bit.","index":127,"end_time":658.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":657.17,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But not like.","index":128,"end_time":659.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":658.57,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Not like it technical, but like the way that he views marketing funnel.","index":129,"end_time":666.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":661.53,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And I think, like, he''s done this before, so I think that he might make some fairly radical changes to the way that our HubSpot is structured, how we''re labeling contacts and how we''re measuring the success of a conversion from a marketing qualified lead to a sales qualified lead to like.","index":130,"end_time":686.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":666.58,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like, I think he''s going to want to.","index":131,"end_time":687.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":686.5,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"He''ll look into this and be like, this is not the way that I would set it up.","index":132,"end_time":692.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":688.58,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And my perspective, like, if he''s our internal guy, then it''s like, then set it up the way that you want.","index":133,"end_time":697.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":692.71,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So I would think that if he can.","index":134,"end_time":700.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":697.31,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"If you can support him so he can do stuff like that and make sure you guys are all on the same page so that whatever kind of output he needs to quantify the success of our marketing department would be helpful.","index":135,"end_time":712.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":701.31,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":136,"end_time":712.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":712.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we could absolutely do that.","index":137,"end_time":714.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":713.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ve handled it from both sides.","index":138,"end_time":716.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":714.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Whether it''s us, like, writing best practices and saying, this is how we''ll do it and then build it, or if someone else comes in and says, this is how I want it, and then we build it.","index":139,"end_time":723.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":716.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I agree.","index":140,"end_time":725.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":724.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, even if you just open up any contact record in your HubSpot account, you''ll see 50 activities of different workflows they went through that could probably be consolidated.","index":141,"end_time":734.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":725.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you even need all those fields?","index":142,"end_time":736.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":734.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What''s.","index":143,"end_time":737.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":736.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, is.","index":144,"end_time":738.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":737.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is deal first meeting really the best way to track success of a campaign?","index":145,"end_time":742.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":738.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or are there other ways that we can track, you know, signals that are showing success?","index":146,"end_time":746.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":742.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, there''s a few different things that we can approach there.","index":147,"end_time":749.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":746.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":148,"end_time":750.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":749.87,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And that''s a lot of what it''s been.","index":149,"end_time":753.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":752.43,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s been like, patchwork.","index":150,"end_time":754.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":753.79,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like, we need this.","index":151,"end_time":755.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":754.99,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":152,"end_time":756.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":755.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We build this.","index":153,"end_time":756.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":756.03,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"These contacts don''t have anything in this property because we didn''t have that property when they came through.","index":154,"end_time":763.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":757.71,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So it is, like, a little bit of a mess.","index":155,"end_time":764.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":763.35,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And I think, you know, to Sam''s credit, he was, like, working to fix some of that stuff.","index":156,"end_time":770.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":764.99,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But I. I also think anytime you''re just, like, bolting stuff on, then all of a sudden, it becomes Frankenstein.","index":157,"end_time":777.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":770.79,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":158,"end_time":777.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":777.24,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And almost to the point where it''s, like, hard to undo, and it wasn''t worth him going back and doing it, so.","index":159,"end_time":782.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":777.6,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yep, that makes total sense.","index":160,"end_time":784.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":782.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But the other part where I think we have trouble is, like, the.","index":161,"end_time":792.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":784.12,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like, the FIGMA stuff that you guys got access to, like, we don''t have a catalog of where all that stuff is or how easy it is to, like, duplicate something and then manipulate it.","index":162,"end_time":804.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":795.88,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And it''s like, we should have that tightened up a little bit better.","index":163,"end_time":808.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":804.52,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So that''s the kind of stuff, like, when this guy comes in, I want to be like, okay, like, unfortunately, here''s.","index":164,"end_time":813.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":808.44,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Here''s the mess.","index":165,"end_time":813.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":813.16,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Make it so that it''s in a way that you feel comfortable with.","index":166,"end_time":818.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":815.4,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And as much as he uses you guys or leverages you guys or whatever, however he decides to do, does feel like you can help a lot with that.","index":167,"end_time":826.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":818.72,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":168,"end_time":826.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":826.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or if he doesn''t need the help.","index":169,"end_time":828.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":826.76,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"He can just do his own thing and tell you what he did.","index":170,"end_time":830.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":828.44,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And then.","index":171,"end_time":831.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":830.92,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And then we just update and run other campaigns.","index":172,"end_time":834.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":832.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":173,"end_time":834.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":834.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we got a little bit of thinking to do on our side.","index":174,"end_time":839.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":837.12,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, totally hear you.","index":175,"end_time":840.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":839.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it sounds like I''ll cancel the call for Thursday then.","index":176,"end_time":843.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":841.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":177,"end_time":844.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":843.84,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And then I''m going to.","index":178,"end_time":846.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":844.8,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I think I mentioned this too, but I want to invite.","index":179,"end_time":849.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":847.04,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Dan and Steph.","index":180,"end_time":852.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":851.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Steph and Dave also.","index":181,"end_time":854.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":852.52,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, I do think that there''s stuff that you all can do to support Dave.","index":182,"end_time":861.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":854.48,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So I always.","index":183,"end_time":864.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":862.32,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I had always felt like Sam and Dave had this, like, almost like, slightly adversarial relationship, because it was.","index":184,"end_time":875.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":864.88,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And it was like, not that they didn''t get along, but it was like the way that we set it up was like, Sam''s in charge of getting a certain amount of first meetings generated through marketing efforts, and Dave''s in charge of getting first number of first meetings for channel.","index":185,"end_time":886.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":875.08,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So Sam wasn''t really incentivized to support Dave because then they can count as channel meetings if they came through Dave.","index":186,"end_time":893.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":887.09,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But our marketing department needs to.","index":187,"end_time":895.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":893.33,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Needs to support our channel team.","index":188,"end_time":898.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":895.85,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So there''s gonna be a lot of stuff that Dave would hear on calls like this that have nothing to do with him.","index":189,"end_time":905.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":898.53,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But I also think that there are campaigns that you guys could help with that are targeted towards channel partners that Dave could really benefit from.","index":190,"end_time":911.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":905.05,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And I also want whoever''s a new person that comes in to just, like, have a totally different.","index":191,"end_time":915.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":912.3,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I want them to have a totally different mindset about each other.","index":192,"end_time":918.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":915.82,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So I do want to get him involved in some of this stuff.","index":193,"end_time":922.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":919.82,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And he may join a bunch of meetings and be like, you know what?","index":194,"end_time":924.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":922.62,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s not even like, I don''t need to be on these unless we''re going to cover a topic that has something to do with him.","index":195,"end_time":930.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":924.5,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And so if, like, that''s what ends up happening.","index":196,"end_time":932.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":930.22,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"If you can let me know ahead of time if we start working on some channel is important for Dave to be there.","index":197,"end_time":937.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":932.86,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But I am going to extend the invitation to all of those guys for our.","index":198,"end_time":940.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":937.58,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, Is it Dave at PTO Exchange?","index":199,"end_time":943.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":941.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"His is David S. So we already had a Dave when he joined, so he''s David S. Ptoexchange.com and then.","index":200,"end_time":950.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":943.62,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And then I got.","index":201,"end_time":951.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":950.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, Dan and Steph.","index":202,"end_time":954.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":952.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":203,"end_time":954.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":954.26,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":204,"end_time":957.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":956.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":205,"end_time":958.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":958.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":206,"end_time":959.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":959.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I invited them to our Mondays rolling forward.","index":207,"end_time":961.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":959.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":208,"end_time":964.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":963.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Steph is live in outreach and everything, so we''re all set there.","index":209,"end_time":970.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":965.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s what she said.","index":210,"end_time":971.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":970.77,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"She''s starting to get some.","index":211,"end_time":972.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":971.33,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Some stuff today.","index":212,"end_time":973.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":972.33,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":213,"end_time":973.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":973.49,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So she had an issue today.","index":214,"end_time":977.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":975.57,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Not an issue, but she had something come up today where, like, she got an inbound lead, I think from something that you guys did when the contact came over to her similar to what happened last time.","index":215,"end_time":989.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":977.89,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It was like the personal email address, but also the.","index":216,"end_time":995.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":989.09,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"The.","index":217,"end_time":1000.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1000.14,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"The contact was already in our system because of something else that she had done.","index":218,"end_time":1005.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1000.62,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But then the lead came through for Steph and now it''s like sharonda@whatever hospital.org or sharonda123ahoo.com but it''s.","index":219,"end_time":1020.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1007.1,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s the same person.","index":220,"end_time":1021.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1020.46,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, we can merge those.","index":221,"end_time":1023.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1021.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So she was.","index":222,"end_time":1024.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1023.43,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So she was merging them and then I basically said to her, like, you take over this contact because I shouldn''t be on there.","index":223,"end_time":1031.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1024.15,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like, this should be you now that you''re up and running, blah, blah, whatever.","index":224,"end_time":1034.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1031.71,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But she reached out to Sam on Slack and said, hey, what should I do with this?","index":225,"end_time":1040.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1035.11,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like, she used to Salesforce and she knows sometimes when you merge contacts, it can just like blow it up.","index":226,"end_time":1046.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1041.11,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, but is that the kind of thing should she go into, like, the new North Slack and.","index":227,"end_time":1050.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1046.63,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":228,"end_time":1051.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1050.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":229,"end_time":1052.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1051.92,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Any question she has, HubSpot, anything related, website, anything, definitely let us know right away because I want to determine if that''s like, what I assume happened is maybe she manually created a lead when she saw a message and then the workflow went through and created the same person.","index":230,"end_time":1068.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1052.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":231,"end_time":1072.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1072,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But yeah, if she lets us know, then we can track and figure out exactly, like, what happened and fix it.","index":232,"end_time":1077.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1072.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":233,"end_time":1078.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1078.46,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"If it was anything wrong with the workflow.","index":234,"end_time":1080.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1079.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you remember the name?","index":235,"end_time":1081.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1080.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think her name is Sharonda Williams.","index":236,"end_time":1084.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1082.3,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"She was from University Hospital.","index":237,"end_time":1086.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1084.62,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"All right, How do you spell sharonda?","index":238,"end_time":1094.019,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1087.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think it''s s h e r r o n d a, I believe.","index":239,"end_time":1098.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1094.019,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Okay.","index":240,"end_time":1103.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1102.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, see right here.","index":241,"end_time":1106.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1105.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it looks like she merged her successfully.","index":242,"end_time":1108.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1106.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She submitted a demo form.","index":243,"end_time":1118.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1116.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You had a task to reach out.","index":244,"end_time":1123.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1122.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She submitted another form.","index":245,"end_time":1125.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1123.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Submitted another form.","index":246,"end_time":1130.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1128.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This person''s really interested in PTO exchange.","index":247,"end_time":1135.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1133.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Dismantled like 4 forms and looks like she followed up today.","index":248,"end_time":1142.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1137.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so it looks like this is all good now, But yeah, anything like that, just please tell her to tell Seth to let us know.","index":249,"end_time":1154.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1142.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can see the task that was assigned to her and it got updated correctly, it looks like.","index":250,"end_time":1159.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1154.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And if she puts something into that Slack and it like, has nothing to do with you guys, I''ll just let you know.","index":251,"end_time":1166.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1159.62,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Just.","index":252,"end_time":1167.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1166.98,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And then just let me know in that Slack channel.","index":253,"end_time":1169.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1167.34,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, like you mention me so that I can then figure it out.","index":254,"end_time":1173.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1169.5,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Or if I have to reach out to Sam''s, figure it out.","index":255,"end_time":1175.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1173.5,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But Then they''re also seeing that it''s getting resolved in this resolution for it.","index":256,"end_time":1181.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1175.42,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":257,"end_time":1181.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1181.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll picture her and Dan know that that should be, like, their initial thing.","index":258,"end_time":1185.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1181.82,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"They have questions, and then we''ll take it from there.","index":259,"end_time":1187.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1185.43,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yep.","index":260,"end_time":1188.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1188.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And this was what I was referring to.","index":261,"end_time":1190.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1188.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m not knocking Sam in any way.","index":262,"end_time":1191.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1190.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just if we''re all.","index":263,"end_time":1192.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1191.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s why I''m saying stuff.","index":264,"end_time":1194.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1192.79,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I''m like, yeah, but like, I mean.","index":265,"end_time":1196.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1194.23,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Look how many different activities someone is going through just when they fill something out.","index":266,"end_time":1200.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1196.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, this just seems.","index":267,"end_time":1202.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1200.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It seems like a lot of things that happen separately without thinking of them all together.","index":268,"end_time":1207.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1203.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And this is just adding them to different lists.","index":269,"end_time":1211.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1209.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, this goes on for like, a mile.","index":270,"end_time":1216.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1214.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s just the type of stuff that I''m looking at that I''ve always thought could use some cleanup.","index":271,"end_time":1220.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1216.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what would.","index":272,"end_time":1223.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1222.38,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I mean, there needs to.","index":273,"end_time":1226.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1225.34,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"There''s got to be a reason that she''s added to all those segments, right?","index":274,"end_time":1230.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1226.38,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":275,"end_time":1230.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1230.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So she''s meeting some sort of criteria.","index":276,"end_time":1232.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1230.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But is John Randall even on the team anymore?","index":277,"end_time":1237.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1232.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No.","index":278,"end_time":1237.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1237.18,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":279,"end_time":1238.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1238.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, like, there''s old stuff like that.","index":280,"end_time":1239.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1238.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Where she.","index":281,"end_time":1243.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1242.45,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I think if.","index":282,"end_time":1244.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1243.25,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Whatever list it should.","index":283,"end_time":1245.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1244.21,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"There should be one that''s for Stephanie Lucchese, and if that''s really a list that she needs to be added for, there should be a Stephanie Lucchese list.","index":284,"end_time":1253.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1245.25,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":285,"end_time":1253.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1253.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And it looks like that''s.","index":286,"end_time":1255.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1254.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That type of work didn''t happen.","index":287,"end_time":1256.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1255.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It looks like.","index":288,"end_time":1257.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1256.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, John Randall territory is 2024.","index":289,"end_time":1259.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1257.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re in 2026.","index":290,"end_time":1260.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1259.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I would think Sam probably created that in 2024.","index":291,"end_time":1268.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1265.1,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Nothing changed because John''s territory changed, and neither John nor Dan left.","index":292,"end_time":1271.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1268.1,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So it''s like it just stayed the same since 2024.","index":293,"end_time":1273.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1271.46,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But, yeah, contacts added since March, since February.","index":294,"end_time":1277.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1273.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":295,"end_time":1278.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1277.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s just a lot of random things in here that, like, I would.","index":296,"end_time":1281.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1278.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just the way that I would always approach this, like, if I were the person that you were talking to and they said they want to do some cleanup, like, I''m diving into all these workflows and being like, what is the purpose of this list?","index":297,"end_time":1290.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1281.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are we emailing these people?","index":298,"end_time":1292.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1290.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is it a different message they get?","index":299,"end_time":1293.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1292.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What are we even doing with it?","index":300,"end_time":1294.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1293.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":301,"end_time":1295.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1294.9,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So, yeah, more than happy to talk to anyone.","index":302,"end_time":1298.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1295.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s, like, the thing that a newer person needs to figure out is, like, 1.","index":303,"end_time":1305.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1298.66,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Are all these lists necessary?","index":304,"end_time":1307.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1305.94,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Necessary.","index":305,"end_time":1308.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1307.9,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Are these lists even, like, part of some automated.","index":306,"end_time":1311.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1308.42,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Right.","index":307,"end_time":1312.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1311.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":308,"end_time":1312.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1312.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is that.","index":309,"end_time":1313.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1312.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is anyone even doing anything with these?","index":310,"end_time":1315.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1313.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":311,"end_time":1315.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1315.38,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"You know, we''re.","index":312,"end_time":1317.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1316.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re probably sitting on some.","index":313,"end_time":1318.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1317.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, if we dust off some data in here.","index":314,"end_time":1320.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1318.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, we''re probably sitting on some audiences we could just upload into LinkedIn for really specified targeting and where, if they''re tagged correctly, then then we know, like, oh, they, they did X, Y and Z, they''re interested.","index":315,"end_time":1331.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1320.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":316,"end_time":1332.669,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1332.19,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And Sam was trying to create some kind of, like, scoring system where, like, if they clicked on a bunch of stuff or if they had this kind of.","index":317,"end_time":1339.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1332.669,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"They were from this kind of industry, like, that they had a different kind of a score.","index":318,"end_time":1342.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1339.63,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But I also was like, very hands off with that.","index":319,"end_time":1346.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1343.59,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And I don''t know what he was doing with the ones that have a certain score, but, like, either we should get on a call with Sam and figure out like five to 10 pressing questions that we should ask him about the way that he tried to set things up, or just like scrap that and start fresh and go forward.","index":320,"end_time":1363.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1347.35,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"My experience is towards the latter.","index":321,"end_time":1365.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1363.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think, I think it actually oftentimes hinders more than helps trying to understand what they were going for instead of just, here''s what we need to do, build it.","index":322,"end_time":1376.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1366.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"My only hesitation with that is like, if he had some good ideas and we just didn''t like, execute on them, great.","index":323,"end_time":1384.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1378.01,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And.","index":324,"end_time":1385.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1385.13,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But the idea is still good.","index":325,"end_time":1386.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1385.45,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Maybe we do it in a different way, but it was like, oh, I see where you were going with this.","index":326,"end_time":1389.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1386.57,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And he''s got all this knowledge of data that we have been collecting over the years that he would know.","index":327,"end_time":1395.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1389.93,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like, if you do it this way, that would be good.","index":328,"end_time":1397.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1395.29,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But I also can see the, you know, upside of just being like, yeah.","index":329,"end_time":1402.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1397.13,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I mean, you know, 20, 30 minutes can''t hurt, right, if we just hop on and talk with them.","index":330,"end_time":1406.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1402.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, yeah, just let me know if that''s something.","index":331,"end_time":1408.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1406.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What are the questions to even ask?","index":332,"end_time":1410.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1409.35,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"You know, like.","index":333,"end_time":1411.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1411.03,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, because it would really just be.","index":334,"end_time":1413.789,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1412.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It might not even require an email.","index":335,"end_time":1415.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1413.789,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just like, hey, was there anything that you were, like, trying to bring to life that, like, just didn''t work out correctly or.","index":336,"end_time":1422.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1415.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we noticed that this, this and this happens.","index":337,"end_time":1426.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1423.65,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":338,"end_time":1426.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1426.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What, what was the, what was the thought behind that?","index":339,"end_time":1430.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1427.41,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, exactly.","index":340,"end_time":1432.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1430.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":341,"end_time":1434.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1432.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But yeah, Steph''s got a bunch of leads to follow up on from the last two weeks, so, yeah, very exciting.","index":342,"end_time":1439.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1434.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m still getting stuff trickled in, so there''s definitely people that are, like, seeing the things that I sent LinkedIn three weeks ago and now responding to it.","index":343,"end_time":1448.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1439.13,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So that does feel like there''s a little bit of runout that''s going to happen with that, which is great.","index":344,"end_time":1452.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1448.61,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"There''s no issue with that.","index":345,"end_time":1453.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1452.01,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But It''ll just get less and less and less as it goes.","index":346,"end_time":1455.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1453.17,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":347,"end_time":1455.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1455.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But yeah, definitely shoot a slack over if anything.","index":348,"end_time":1459.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1456.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If anyone has any questions on anything.","index":349,"end_time":1460.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1459.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":350,"end_time":1461.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1460.94,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":351,"end_time":1462.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1461.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, thank you very much, Josh.","index":352,"end_time":1464.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1462.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And.","index":353,"end_time":1464.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1464.02,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And, you know, didn''t give me any about your Redskins ruining my number two seed.","index":354,"end_time":1468.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1464.34,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"You know, what a kind, kind guy.","index":355,"end_time":1470.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1468.66,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I. I was actually mad that we lost or that we won.","index":356,"end_time":1474.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1471.019,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was like, these losers don''t even know how to lose.","index":357,"end_time":1475.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1474.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re trying to get a better draft.","index":358,"end_time":1477.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1476.14,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"They''re not as bad as the Giants at it.","index":359,"end_time":1479.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1477.9,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Giants are the worst at it.","index":360,"end_time":1480.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1479.38,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, we were dying yesterday.","index":361,"end_time":1482.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1480.87,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Every single year.","index":362,"end_time":1483.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1482.71,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"They just, like, moved down, like, three spots like in the last week of the season, like, oh, good thing we went 5 and 12 instead of 4 and 13.","index":363,"end_time":1491.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1483.63,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like.","index":364,"end_time":1492.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1492.07,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, exactly.","index":365,"end_time":1494.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1492.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But.","index":366,"end_time":1495.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1495.19,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"All right, cool.","index":367,"end_time":1496.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1495.75,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We''ll hope you feel better.","index":368,"end_time":1497.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1496.67,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Appreciate it.","index":369,"end_time":1498.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1498.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Where are you going on Thursday?","index":370,"end_time":1499.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1498.87,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Friday we have an on site meeting for leadership in Virginia.","index":371,"end_time":1504.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1499.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So me, Tristan, Justin, and another member of our team are meeting to go through all of our quarterly planning.","index":372,"end_time":1510.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1505.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nice.","index":373,"end_time":1511.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1511.45,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Where do you guys go to?","index":374,"end_time":1512.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1511.85,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s.","index":375,"end_time":1513.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1513.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s a country club called Dominion Club.","index":376,"end_time":1517.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1513.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":377,"end_time":1520.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1519.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right in Richmond.","index":378,"end_time":1521.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1520.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So do you get to actually play any golf or you just go and use the boardrooms?","index":379,"end_time":1524.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1521.45,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We have not played any golf there yet.","index":380,"end_time":1527.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1525.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They have.","index":381,"end_time":1527.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1527.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"One year before I joined, we played some putt putt last time.","index":382,"end_time":1531.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1527.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That was pretty fun.","index":383,"end_time":1532.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1531.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nice.","index":384,"end_time":1532.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1532.49,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":385,"end_time":1533.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1532.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then went to a nice steakhouse.","index":386,"end_time":1534.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1533.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, yeah, this.","index":387,"end_time":1535.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1534.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I went on the first.","index":388,"end_time":1538.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1535.63,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Actually.","index":389,"end_time":1539.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1539.15,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We woke up with my brother and both of our boys and we went up to the club that I belong to because we have these indoor, like, trackman.","index":390,"end_time":1548.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1539.71,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Nice.","index":391,"end_time":1549.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1549.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, hitting bass.","index":392,"end_time":1550.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1549.71,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But you.","index":393,"end_time":1551.549,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1551.07,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But they have these games that kids can play.","index":394,"end_time":1553.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1551.549,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":395,"end_time":1554.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1553.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And they''re like, hit the ball onto the screen and there''s like.","index":396,"end_time":1557.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1554.11,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s almost like Angry Birds where it like bounces all around and it hits all this stuff.","index":397,"end_time":1562.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1558.43,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So we had our boys doing that because I broke my pinky in October and I haven''t been able to play golf since then.","index":398,"end_time":1571.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1562.94,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And then I went and I realized that actually, like, where I''m at right now that how inconsequential your left pinky is to your grip that I actually can play.","index":399,"end_time":1579.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1571.82,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So now I''m like, oh, this is great.","index":400,"end_time":1581.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1579.78,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I thought I was gonna have another couple months before I could be able to play, but just going up there with the kids, I was like, oh, this is great.","index":401,"end_time":1586.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1581.06,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":402,"end_time":1586.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1586.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Back.","index":403,"end_time":1587.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1587.02,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That''s awesome.","index":404,"end_time":1588.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1587.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":405,"end_time":1588.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1588.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"My wife got me a.","index":406,"end_time":1589.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1588.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like a.","index":407,"end_time":1590.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1590.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A phone mount that''s like a magnet for the golf cart.","index":408,"end_time":1594.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1591.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I''m like, since having this kid, when have I gone out to the golf course?","index":409,"end_time":1597.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1594.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But you gotta get, you gotta get those like golf cart car seats.","index":410,"end_time":1603.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1599.67,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yes.","index":411,"end_time":1604.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1604.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re probably gonna do that this.","index":412,"end_time":1606.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1604.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re gonna do that this year, I''m sure, because my wife golfs too, so.","index":413,"end_time":1611.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1607.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, nice.","index":414,"end_time":1612.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1611.59,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, we gotta figure that out.","index":415,"end_time":1613.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1612.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"My.","index":416,"end_time":1614.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1614.39,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I really was hoping my daughter was going to be in.","index":417,"end_time":1616.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1614.63,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"My wife could not care less.","index":418,"end_time":1618.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1616.87,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I was hoping my daughter was going to be into it.","index":419,"end_time":1620.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1619.03,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"She just doesn''t.","index":420,"end_time":1621.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1620.95,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Doesn''t care that much.","index":421,"end_time":1622.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1621.75,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But my 8 year old son''s into it.","index":422,"end_time":1625.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1622.71,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We played a bunch this summer and my 4 year old will definitely be into it when he''s old enough to hit the back.","index":423,"end_time":1632.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1626.07,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That''s awesome.","index":424,"end_time":1633.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1632.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re going to get some plastic clubs for my daughter at some point.","index":425,"end_time":1635.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1633.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nice.","index":426,"end_time":1636.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1635.75,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":427,"end_time":1636.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1636.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Although I say my four year old son won one of the contests this weekend against his brother and his cousins in that simulator game.","index":428,"end_time":1643.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1636.67,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That''s awesome.","index":429,"end_time":1644.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1643.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He''s proud of you.","index":430,"end_time":1645.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1644.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":431,"end_time":1645.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1645.36,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We took some of my wife''s grandfather''s clubs and cut them down so that my 4 year old had some that are appropriate size and he actually hits it.","index":432,"end_time":1653.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1645.84,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"All right.","index":433,"end_time":1654.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1653.8,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That''s awesome.","index":434,"end_time":1655.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1654.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Making the next Tiger.","index":435,"end_time":1656.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1655.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":436,"end_time":1657.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1656.64,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Not quite there, but.","index":437,"end_time":1658.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1657.04,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"All right, man.","index":438,"end_time":1660.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1659.68,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Well, tell, tell your team we say hello when you''re down there on Thursday and we''ll come up with a plan or do our best to figure out as much of a plan as we can before we meet again Monday.","index":439,"end_time":1668.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1660.28,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":440,"end_time":1668.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1668.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":441,"end_time":1669.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1668.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And you''re sending the invite to the other three?","index":442,"end_time":1671.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1669.2,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Already done.","index":443,"end_time":1671.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1671.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":444,"end_time":1672.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1672,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":445,"end_time":1673.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1672.92,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"}],"dateString":"2026-01-05T20:30:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/86093865913?pwd=ajXSuerDGmcROjfezSWYYGsa7iPOWd.1","participants":["josh@ptoexchange.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,sam@ptoexchange.com","josh@ptoexchange.com","sam@ptoexchange.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KDP8J3EPPMM9BTF89SKDWFA0","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.89,"bullets":["Confirmed likely hire to backfill Sam''s role; decision expected within a week.","Colin offered to allocate additional support points for interim or long‑term coverage.","Josh plans to restructure HubSpot and involve new hire in foundational cleanup.","Steph is now live in outreach and actively following up on inbound leads.","Planned to loop in Dan, Steph, and Dave to support broader channel marketing."],"highlights":[{"quote":"I do think it probably makes sense to get you guys doing some of the stuff that Sam was doing.","speaker":"Josh Reinhard"},{"quote":"We could absolutely do that... we’ve handled it from both sides.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"}],"topics":["hiring","handoff","hubspot","delivery"],"model":"openai/gpt-4","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-05T21:28:06Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Resource Planning and Role Transition**\n\nThe team plans to hire a replacement for **Sam’s role** within the next week to stabilize marketing operations and ensure continuity (06:14).  \n- **Josh Reinhard** and **Rob** interviewed a candidate who might fill Sam’s position, with a decision expected soon.  \n- An interim period may require **Colin Costigan’s team** to support transition work until the new hire is fully up to speed or for a longer term if hiring is paused.  \n- **Colin** proposed discussing with **Justin and Tristan** about securing additional points for the next **three months** to cover this transition workload.  \n- The contract rate is set to revert back on **February 1st**, and the exact timeline will be confirmed to align budgeting with resource needs.  \n\nJosh also confirmed plans to hire a **Chief Marketing Officer (CMO)** to lead strategic efforts, which was positively received in early CMO interviews (08:19).  \n- The CMO’s role will focus on overseeing marketing strategy and coordination, addressing past gaps where no clear “conductor” existed.  \n- This hire aims to improve strategic direction and unify efforts across marketing and sales functions.  \n- Josh expects to finalize the hiring approach after discussions with Rob and will update Colin’s team by the next meeting on Monday.  \n\n## **HubSpot System Overhaul and Marketing Operations**\n\nThe current **HubSpot setup is fragmented and cluttered**, requiring both cleanup and strategic restructuring to improve efficiency and reporting (10:41).  \n- The candidate for Sam’s role is expected to make significant changes in how HubSpot tracks leads, contact properties, and campaign success metrics.  \n- Colin’s team can support either by implementing best practices or adapting to the new hire’s preferred setup, ensuring smooth collaboration.  \n- Josh emphasized that prior efforts to patch HubSpot created a “Frankenstein” system that is hard to maintain or undo (12:29).  \n- The team identified redundant and outdated workflows, such as lists tied to former team members, indicating a need for thorough audit and pruning (20:30).  \n- Colin suggested reviewing each workflow’s purpose and whether associated contacts are actively engaged or targeted, which could unlock valuable audiences for LinkedIn campaigns.  \n\nThere was a discussion about whether to retain some of Sam’s scoring and segmentation ideas or scrap and rebuild from scratch (22:12).  \n- Colin favors a fresh start focused on current needs rather than trying to untangle past efforts.  \n- Josh acknowledged potential value in Sam’s concepts but leans toward rebuilding with clearer goals and better execution.  \n- A short call with Sam to clarify key questions and intent behind existing setups was proposed to decide what to salvage or discard.  \n\n## **Design and Marketing Collateral Management**\n\nJosh highlighted issues around the **FIGMA asset catalog**, noting the lack of clear organization and ease of use for duplicating or modifying marketing materials (13:04).  \n- This disorganization impacts efficiency when the new hire or Colin’s team needs to work with design files.  \n- The plan is to clean up and tighten control over FIGMA assets to streamline campaign development and reduce duplication effort.  \n- Colin’s team will either assist the new hire in managing these assets or update them independently once the new structure is in place (13:46).  \n\n## **Channel Partner Collaboration and Campaign Alignment**\n\nJosh stressed the importance of improving collaboration between **marketing and the channel team**, especially between the marketing function and **Dave**, the channel lead (14:11).  \n- Past setup discouraged support for channel-driven meetings due to conflicting incentives between Sam and Dave.  \n- Josh wants the new marketing hire to adopt a mindset that fully supports channel initiatives and fosters cross-team cooperation.  \n- Invitations will be extended to **Dan, Steph, and Dave** to join marketing meetings for better alignment and shared visibility.  \n- Colin confirmed **Steph** is actively using Outreach and beginning to handle inbound leads, with ongoing support from Colin’s team as needed (15:54).  \n\nThe team agreed that any channel-related marketing work will involve Dave directly, with advance notice to ensure his participation when relevant.  \n\n## **Lead Management and CRM Hygiene**\n\nA specific case was discussed where **Steph encountered duplicate contact records** in HubSpot, highlighting ongoing CRM hygiene challenges (16:10).  \n- Colin’s team is ready to merge duplicates and troubleshoot lead workflow issues to prevent confusion and data fragmentation.  \n- They advised that any HubSpot or website-related questions go through the new North Slack channel for quick resolution.  \n- Josh will encourage the sales team to escalate issues via Slack and keep him copied for awareness and intervention if needed (17:31).  \n\nThis case exemplifies broader challenges with contact lifecycle management and the need for clearer, simplified workflows.  \n\n## **Operational Meetings and Quarterly Planning**\n\nColin’s team will be out of the office on **Thursday and Friday** for an onsite quarterly planning meeting with leadership at **Dominion Club in Richmond** (24:59).  \n- This session includes Colin, Tristan, Justin, and another team member working on quarterly goals and resource alignment.  \n- Josh and Colin agreed to pause their regular Thursday call and reconvene the following Monday with a clearer picture of hiring and ongoing priorities.  \n- Invitations to include Dan, Steph, and Dave in Monday meetings have already been sent by Colin to ensure all key stakeholders are engaged going forward.","outline":null,"keywords":["HubSpot","Marketing Strategy","Lead Management","Workflow Cleanup","Hiring Process","Channel Support"],"overview":"- **Resource Planning:** Hiring a replacement for Sam''s role is underway to stabilize marketing operations within the week.  \n- **CMO Hiring:** Plans to hire a Chief Marketing Officer will enhance strategic direction across marketing and sales functions.  \n- **HubSpot Redesign:** Current HubSpot system needs significant cleanup for better tracking of leads and campaign success metrics.  \n- **FIGMA Organization:** Improve FIGMA asset catalog to streamline design processes and reduce duplication for the upcoming new hire.  \n- **Channel Collaboration:** Enhance synergy between marketing and channel team to support joint initiatives and address past conflicts.  \n- **CRM Hygiene Issues:** Ongoing challenges with duplicate records and lead management necessitate clearer workflows and CRM maintenance.","action_items":"\n**Josh Reinhard**\nDiscuss hiring decisions for Sam’s replacement and CMO with Rob; finalize approach before next Monday meeting (08:18)\nInform Dan, Steph, and Dave about their inclusion in Monday meetings and clarify when Dave’s presence is necessary (15:41)\nCommunicate with Steph and Dan to direct any HubSpot/query issues through new North Slack channel for resolution (19:19)\nShare questions or needed clarifications with Sam about HubSpot workflows to inform cleanup or redevelopment (22:43)\nCoordinate with Colin’s team to integrate support for new hire and maintain marketing operations during transition (13:57)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nReview contract and point allocation with Justin and Tristan to cover interim work and possibly extend support beyond original contract (07:17)\nMonitor and support HubSpot workflow cleanups, including audits of lists, segmentation, and lead scoring (20:22)\nAssist in managing inbound lead/contact merges and provide quick-turnaround support via new North Slack channel (17:03)\nAccept invitations for Monday meetings and participate in strategic discussions moving forward (15:54)\nPrepare to support new marketing hires with system setup, structure changes, and ongoing campaign management (11:52)\nPlan to have follow-up dialogue with Sam regarding existing HubSpot automation for insights before potential rebuild (23:29)\nCancel Thursday meeting and proceed with revised scheduling around team availability (13:59)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"8652c3b5-7b68-4b10-a2df-39c348e8f44f","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
