INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: PTO Exchange Weekly',
  '## **Resource Planning and Role Transition**

The team plans to hire a replacement for **Sam’s role** within the next week to stabilize marketing operations and ensure continuity (06:14).  
- **Josh Reinhard** and **Rob** interviewed a candidate who might fill Sam’s position, with a decision expected soon.  
- An interim period may require **Colin Costigan’s team** to support transition work until the new hire is fully up to speed or for a longer term if hiring is paused.  
- **Colin** proposed discussing with **Justin and Tristan** about securing additional points for the next **three months** to cover this transition workload.  
- The contract rate is set to revert back on **February 1st**, and the exact timeline will be confirmed to align budgeting with resource needs.  

Josh also confirmed plans to hire a **Chief Marketing Officer (CMO)** to lead strategic efforts, which was positively received in early CMO interviews (08:19).  
- The CMO’s role will focus on overseeing marketing strategy and coordination, addressing past gaps where no clear “conductor” existed.  
- This hire aims to improve strategic direction and unify efforts across marketing and sales functions.  
- Josh expects to finalize the hiring approach after discussions with Rob and will update Colin’s team by the next meeting on Monday.  

## **HubSpot System Overhaul and Marketing Operations**

The current **HubSpot setup is fragmented and cluttered**, requiring both cleanup and strategic restructuring to improve efficiency and reporting (10:41).  
- The candidate for Sam’s role is expected to make significant changes in how HubSpot tracks leads, contact properties, and campaign success metrics.  
- Colin’s team can support either by implementing best practices or adapting to the new hire’s preferred setup, ensuring smooth collaboration.  
- Josh emphasized that prior efforts to patch HubSpot created a “Frankenstein” system that is hard to maintain or undo (12:29).  
- The team identified redundant and outdated workflows, such as lists tied to former team members, indicating a need for thorough audit and pruning (20:30).  
- Colin suggested reviewing each workflow’s purpose and whether associated contacts are actively engaged or targeted, which could unlock valuable audiences for LinkedIn campaigns.  

There was a discussion about whether to retain some of Sam’s scoring and segmentation ideas or scrap and rebuild from scratch (22:12).  
- Colin favors a fresh start focused on current needs rather than trying to untangle past efforts.  
- Josh acknowledged potential value in Sam’s concepts but leans toward rebuilding with clearer goals and better execution.  
- A short call with Sam to clarify key questions and intent behind existing setups was proposed to decide what to salvage or discard.  

## **Design and Marketing Collateral Management**

Josh highlighted issues around the **FIGMA asset catalog**, noting the lack of clear organization and ease of use for duplicating or modifying marketing materials (13:04).  
- This disorganization impacts efficiency when the new hire or Colin’s team needs to work with design files.  
- The plan is to clean up and tighten control over FIGMA assets to streamline campaign development and reduce duplication effort.  
- Colin’s team will either assist the new hire in managing these assets or update them independently once the new structure is in place (13:46).  

## **Channel Partner Collaboration and Campaign Alignment**

Josh stressed the importance of improving collaboration between **marketing and the channel team**, especially between the marketing function and **Dave**, the channel lead (14:11).  
- Past setup discouraged support for channel-driven meetings due to conflicting incentives between Sam and Dave.  
- Josh wants the new marketing hire to adopt a mindset that fully supports channel initiatives and fosters cross-team cooperation.  
- Invitations will be extended to **Dan, Steph, and Dave** to join marketing meetings for better alignment and shared visibility.  
- Colin confirmed **Steph** is actively using Outreach and beginning to handle inbound leads, with ongoing support from Colin’s team as needed (15:54).  

The team agreed that any channel-related marketing work will involve Dave directly, with advance notice to ensure his participation when relevant.  

## **Lead Management and CRM Hygiene**

A specific case was discussed where **Steph encountered duplicate contact records** in HubSpot, highlighting ongoing CRM hygiene challenges (16:10).  
- Colin’s team is ready to merge duplicates and troubleshoot lead workflow issues to prevent confusion and data fragmentation.  
- They advised that any HubSpot or website-related questions go through the new North Slack channel for quick resolution.  
- Josh will encourage the sales team to escalate issues via Slack and keep him copied for awareness and intervention if needed (17:31).  

This case exemplifies broader challenges with contact lifecycle management and the need for clearer, simplified workflows.  

## **Operational Meetings and Quarterly Planning**

Colin’s team will be out of the office on **Thursday and Friday** for an onsite quarterly planning meeting with leadership at **Dominion Club in Richmond** (24:59).  
- This session includes Colin, Tristan, Justin, and another team member working on quarterly goals and resource alignment.  
- Josh and Colin agreed to pause their regular Thursday call and reconvene the following Monday with a clearer picture of hiring and ongoing priorities.  
- Invitations to include Dan, Steph, and Dave in Monday meetings have already been sent by Colin to ensure all key stakeholders are engaged going forward.',
  '2026-01-05 20:30:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Discuss hiring decisions for Sam’s replacement and CMO with Rob; finalize approach before next Monday meeting (08:18)","completed":false},{"text":"Inform Dan, Steph, and Dave about their inclusion in Monday meetings and clarify when Dave’s presence is necessary (15:41)","completed":false},{"text":"Communicate with Steph and Dan to direct any HubSpot/query issues through new North Slack channel for resolution (19:19)","completed":false},{"text":"Share questions or needed clarifications with Sam about HubSpot workflows to inform cleanup or redevelopment (22:43)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate with Colin’s team to integrate support for new hire and maintain marketing operations during transition (13:57)","completed":false},{"text":"Review contract and point allocation with Justin and Tristan to cover interim work and possibly extend support beyond original contract (07:17)","completed":false},{"text":"Monitor and support HubSpot workflow cleanups, including audits of lists, segmentation, and lead scoring (20:22)","completed":false},{"text":"Assist in managing inbound lead/contact merges and provide quick-turnaround support via new North Slack channel (17:03)","completed":false},{"text":"Accept invitations for Monday meetings and participate in strategic discussions moving forward (15:54)","completed":false},{"text":"Prepare to support new marketing hires with system setup, structure changes, and ongoing campaign management (11:52)","completed":false},{"text":"Plan to have follow-up dialogue with Sam regarding existing HubSpot automation for insights before potential rebuild (23:29)","completed":false},{"text":"Cancel Thursday meeting and proceed with revised scheduling around team availability (13:59)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
  true
FROM new_meeting;

-- Meeting: Gallagher & Mohan//MiD: Marketing Kickoff (2026-01-05 18:30:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '1194e57c-a4a6-4e1e-bac3-83c4ff3c4ad7',
    '2026-01-05 18:30:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KD8BWP3RB8Y7F8PNY4JRDEYQ',
    'Gallagher & Mohan//MiD: Marketing Kickoff',
    '{"Doug","Colin Costigan"}'::text[],
    907,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/89164916386?pwd=JcDbx9Vnbgy5JWH3DnYAcwehpATil1.1',
    '{"id":"01KD8BWP3RB8Y7F8PNY4JRDEYQ","title":"Gallagher & Mohan//MiD: Marketing Kickoff","summary":{"notes":"## **ABM Campaign Strategy and Execution**\n\nThe team agreed on a focused ABM campaign targeting specific real estate-related industries to drive highly personalized outreach.\n\n- **Target industries include real estate, private equity, multi-family operators, affordable housing owners, and retail, industrial, and logistics investors within real estate investment** as confirmed by Doug and Colin (03:00)  \n    - The campaign will use a formal ABM plan outlining target roles, messaging, timelines, offers, and segmented communication strategies.  \n    - Personalization will tailor messages to roles, such as finance professionals in private equity versus affordable housing.  \n    - Outreach will combine email and LinkedIn, with emails sent from custom domains like “Doug@g&h.com” to avoid spam issues.  \n    - LinkedIn outreach will use Doug’s personal profile for consistency, reducing recipient confusion and anxiety over sales handoffs.\n\n- **Doug emphasized a two-tier sales outreach model using fake email personas routed to India-based sales assistants for rapid response** (05:30)  \n    - This setup enables replies to be handled within 10–20 minutes, improving engagement speed.  \n    - Colin confirmed the email system can replicate this approach, though LinkedIn outreach will remain under Doug’s personal profile for clarity.  \n    - Doug will manually vet lists to avoid contacting existing clients, supported by CRM integration for negative-list filtering.\n\n- **The campaign scope will focus on a controlled, specific list of targeted companies rather than mass outreach** (07:00)  \n    - Doug will stop any overlapping outreach to the same targets to avoid duplication.  \n    - Colin confirmed the process includes list sharing, enrichment, vetting, and then coordinated messaging launch.  \n    - Doug highlighted the need to adjust AUM revenue ranges from “50 million to 1 billion” to a broader scale of “one to hundreds of billions” for accuracy, and Colin committed to updating this (08:20).  \n    - No plans currently exist to activate outreach on the larger existing database of tens to hundreds of thousands of leads, keeping the focus tightly on targeted accounts.\n\n## **Content Engine and Thought Leadership Framework**\n\nThe team plans to develop an internal video series and related content to support ABM campaigns and thought leadership.\n\n- **Colin proposed using a video interview format via the Riverside platform to generate multi-format content for social media, blogs, web pages, and ABM outreach** (10:15)  \n    - This includes one-sided camera interviews with rotating company employees or prospects to showcase expertise.  \n    - Content frequency options include monthly or bi-monthly episodes featuring Doug, senior team members, or other employees.  \n    - The framework will be informed by research on industry trends and prospect interests to ensure relevance.  \n    - This approach aims to build credibility and provide reusable content assets across channels.\n\n- **Doug expressed openness to involving himself, a senior real estate expert, or other employees but requested further internal discussion before finalizing hosts** (10:45)  \n    - Colin committed to drafting the framework to guide scheduling and participant roles as the next step.\n\n## **Technical Setup and Communication Workflow**\n\nThe meeting clarified technical details to ensure smooth campaign execution and protection of Doug’s personal email reputation.\n\n- **Email outreach will use separate domains distinct from Doug’s main “gallagher and mohan.com” domain to avoid spam flags and preserve reputation** (11:50)  \n    - Replies to outreach emails will be routed via sentiment analysis tools to notify Doug only of interested contacts, limiting inbox overload.  \n    - The fake persona email system will be integrated to forward responses directly to Indian sales assistants for timely follow-up, preserving the rapid response model Doug favors.\n\n- **LinkedIn outreach will be connected to Doug’s personal profile, maintaining message consistency and recipient trust** (06:00)  \n    - This reduces confusion caused by handoffs from one communicator to another during the sales process.\n\n- **Colin will send an asset intake document requiring email access and other tool permissions to enable campaign setup** (11:20)  \n    - Doug will provide necessary access credentials and assist in reviewing contact lists to exclude current customers.\n\n## **Project Management and Collaboration Tools**\n\nA shared project portal will provide real-time visibility into campaign progress, deliverables, and outstanding client tasks.\n\n- **Colin introduced a client portal updated every 15 minutes to track goals, documents, tasks, and final deliverables** (12:40)  \n    - Doug will receive a single sign-on invite to access this portal for ongoing transparency and easy retrieval of materials like white papers.  \n    - This portal also highlights any outstanding action items requiring Doug’s input, streamlining communication.\n\n- **Weekly meetings will be scheduled on Mondays at 1:00 PM Eastern to maintain alignment and progress tracking** (14:00)  \n    - Flexibility was agreed upon to reschedule as needed, ensuring continuous collaboration without disruption.\n\n- **Doug confirmed understanding of next steps, including receiving documents to fill out and initiating campaign build after his review** (14:40)  \n    - Colin will send the portal invite, asset intake document, and meeting invite immediately following this call.\n\n## **Strategic Alignment and Market Positioning**\n\nThe campaign’s precision targeting and content strategy aim to position Doug’s company strongly in competitive real estate investment markets.\n\n- **Prioritizing personalization and role-specific messaging reflects a strategic shift toward meaningful engagement over broad outreach** (02:00)  \n    - This addresses market concerns about generic sales approaches that reduce response rates and increase prospect anxiety.  \n    - Doug’s feedback on AUM ranges and list selection shows a focus on quality targeting aligned with true market sizes.\n\n- **Content production as a thought leadership tool supports brand differentiation in a crowded market by showcasing expertise and insights** (10:00)  \n    - Leveraging internal experts and prospective voices enhances credibility and signals deep industry knowledge, helping win trust.\n\n- **Protecting email domain reputation and using sentiment analysis for reply management highlights a sophisticated approach to maintaining outreach efficacy** (11:00)  \n    - This technical care underpins long-term deliverability and engagement success.\n\n- **The combined approach of targeted ABM, content marketing, and streamlined follow-up workflows reflects a holistic sales transformation designed to accelerate pipeline growth and improve conversion** (05:00)  \n    - Doug’s role as both CEO and frontline sales leader integrates strategic oversight with hands-on execution, maximizing impact.","outline":null,"keywords":["Account-Based Marketing","ABM Campaign","Outreach Strategy","Content Engine","LinkedIn Outreach","Prospect List Management"],"overview":"- **ABM Campaign Focus:** Target real estate and investment sectors with personalized outreach strategies for better engagement.\n\n- **Two-Tier Outreach Model:** Use fake email personas for quick replies, routed to sales assistants for faster response times.\n\n- **Targeted Approach:** Restrict outreach to a curated list of companies and increase AUM range for accurate targeting metrics.\n\n- **Content Creation:** Develop internal video series for multiple channels, showcasing expertise and aligning with industry trends.\n\n- **Technical Setup:** Utilize separate email domains for outreach to maintain reputation and filter responses effectively through tools.\n\n- **Project Tracking:** Implement a client portal updated frequently, with weekly meetings to monitor progress and ensure collaboration.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nSend asset intake document to Doug for sharing email addresses and tool access (11:45)\nProvide invitation and access to project management portal with real-time updates (12:40)\nSchedule and send invite for weekly meetings Mondays at 1 PM Eastern starting next week (13:16)\nUpdate ABM campaign target criteria to reflect corrected AUM ranges (08:25)\nPrepare ABM plan document including list segmentation, messaging, landing pages, and outreach strategy for Doug’s review (02:30)\nCoordinate list building and exclusion of current clients via CRM data and manual review by Doug (06:37)\nBegin framework development for internal video content series and interview approach (09:50)\n\n**Doug Gallagher**\nReview and provide feedback on ABM target company list to ensure overlap with own outreach campaigns is avoided (07:55)\nManually review and approve prospect lists to avoid contacting current clients (06:50)\nConsider and decide internally on suitable personnel for hosting the content engine video series or interviews (10:39)\nComplete and return asset intake document shared by Colin (14:41)\n"},"duration":15.109999656677246,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Doug"},{"id":1,"name":"Colin Costigan"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Can you guys hear me?","index":0,"end_time":36.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":36.09,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yes.","index":1,"end_time":37.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":36.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":2,"end_time":39.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":38.17,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"How are you doing today?","index":3,"end_time":41.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":40.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good, good.","index":4,"end_time":42.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":41.77,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":5,"end_time":43.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":42.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":6,"end_time":43.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":43.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s great to, to meet you.","index":7,"end_time":46.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":43.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, definitely.","index":8,"end_time":48.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":47.85,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah, nice to meet you guys too.","index":9,"end_time":50.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":48.73,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Where are you guys based out of?","index":10,"end_time":51.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":50.01,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I''m in Maryland.","index":11,"end_time":52.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":51.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Natalie is in Chicago.","index":12,"end_time":56.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":53.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":13,"end_time":57.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":56.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":14,"end_time":57.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":57.17,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Where in Maryland?","index":15,"end_time":60.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":58.53,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I''m in Frederick.","index":16,"end_time":61.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":60.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, nice.","index":17,"end_time":63.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":62.13,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Not sure if you''re familiar with the.","index":18,"end_time":64.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":63.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":19,"end_time":65.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":65.49,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Stuff happening out here.","index":20,"end_time":67.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":66.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Fairfax, Virginia.","index":21,"end_time":69.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":67.889,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"So I know that.","index":22,"end_time":69.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":69.09,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":23,"end_time":71.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":71.01,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":24,"end_time":72.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":71.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nice.","index":25,"end_time":72.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":72.21,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"All right, well, thank you for taking the time to meet with us today.","index":26,"end_time":75.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":72.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know that your time is very valuable.","index":27,"end_time":77.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":75.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I want to make the most of everything and today is not a super in depth agenda, but definitely an important one.","index":28,"end_time":85.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":77.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re going to go through the framework of what we''re going to do for putting together an ABM campaign, talk a little bit about the content engine that you and Tristan and Justin talked about as well, and then some housekeeping items like assets.","index":29,"end_time":97.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":85.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I just have a few questions also before we get started though.","index":30,"end_time":101.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":97.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are there any questions that you have?","index":31,"end_time":102.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":101.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No.","index":32,"end_time":104.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":103.79,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":33,"end_time":105.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":104.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so for the ABM campaign, conversation of all of the conversations that you and Tristan and Justin had in the framework and everything that we put together together, just want to make sure.","index":34,"end_time":116.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":106.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I can even send this over to you as a final review that nothing has changed since those conversations.","index":35,"end_time":121.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":116.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So as far as main industries that we''re looking to target, it''s going to be real estate, private equity, multi family operators, affordable housing owners, and then retail, industrial and logistics investors.","index":36,"end_time":130.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":121.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, basically all within, like the one thing I''ll say is just, just so you understand, like the retail, industrial and logistics.","index":37,"end_time":140.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":135.05,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Like I, I mean that within like the real estate world.","index":38,"end_time":143.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":140.93,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah, right.","index":39,"end_time":143.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":143.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Real estate investment.","index":40,"end_time":144.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":144.01,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":41,"end_time":149.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":144.97,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Looks all.","index":42,"end_time":149.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":149.16,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Looks all right.","index":43,"end_time":150.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":149.72,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":44,"end_time":151.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":150.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":45,"end_time":152.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":151.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so what we do with this is we come up with a.","index":46,"end_time":154.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":152.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s a, it''s a formal document, but in our effort to always be transparent, it outlines who we''re talking to, how we''re talking to them, who we''re sending communications from, timelines, landing pages.","index":47,"end_time":166.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":154.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Everything that we are running in this campaign will be put together in what we call an ABM plan.","index":48,"end_time":171.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":167.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that will be, you know, what is the offer, how are we enticing them to convert?","index":49,"end_time":175.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":171.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What is our messaging approach?","index":50,"end_time":176.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":175.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How are we segmenting these lists?","index":51,"end_time":178.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":177.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, do we need to say something a little different to someone in a finance role at a private equity firm than we would with someone in a finance role at affordable housing?","index":52,"end_time":188.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":178.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, things like that.","index":53,"end_time":189.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":188.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So everyone needs a little bit of personalization.","index":54,"end_time":191.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":189.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that will all be baked into the communication that we write well, then design a few landing pages based around that and then we''ll set up the technical infrastructure.","index":55,"end_time":201.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":191.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have a lot of different tools that we use to compile signals as well as contact enrichment and email communication and LinkedIn communication.","index":56,"end_time":209.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":201.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we''ll get into launching that.","index":57,"end_time":212.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":210.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"My one question that I want to confirm is who will be utilizing for outreach?","index":58,"end_time":217.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":212.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is that going to come from your profile?","index":59,"end_time":219.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":217.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is there a team of SDRs that.","index":60,"end_time":221.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":219.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You would like involved in terms of what exactly which.","index":61,"end_time":226.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":221.8,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Which platform?","index":62,"end_time":227.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":226.28,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"So we would be sending.","index":63,"end_time":228.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":227.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We would create email domains that we would send on your behalf.","index":64,"end_time":231.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":228.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it could be like Doug at.","index":65,"end_time":233.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":231.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll just say g&h.com.","index":66,"end_time":236.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":234.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"you know, we.","index":67,"end_time":236.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":236.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We set up different domains to send from, but we also do LinkedIn.","index":68,"end_time":240.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":236.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we would connect your personal profile to a tool we use called heyreach and then send communications through a workflow from there.","index":69,"end_time":246.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":240.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":70,"end_time":248.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":247.55,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"And then the email does it like auto forward to my inbox or so.","index":71,"end_time":253.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":248.99,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah, we set up on replies that it would.","index":72,"end_time":255.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":253.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You would get a notification of a reply.","index":73,"end_time":258.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":255.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Other than that, I mean, we''re sending out like hundreds to thousands of emails a week, so you don''t want all of those going to your inbox.","index":74,"end_time":264.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":258.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we have it run through sentiment analysis.","index":75,"end_time":267.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":265.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Understand if someone is showing interest, then we let you know right away.","index":76,"end_time":271.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":267.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I, so I have like a.","index":77,"end_time":273.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":271.11,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"You know, we have.","index":78,"end_time":273.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":273.11,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I have like basically two tiers, right?","index":79,"end_time":275.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":273.83,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Like I''m the CEO, but I also run the sales team essentially, right?","index":80,"end_time":279.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":275.71,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"So I am on the top, like on the front line of sales and like email and stuff like that.","index":81,"end_time":283.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":279.03,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Then also behind me I have like my USA salespeople, right?","index":82,"end_time":287.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":283.83,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"And then behind that I have like my Indian based, like basic sales assistants, right?","index":83,"end_time":292.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":288.33,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Type of thing.","index":84,"end_time":293.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":292.57,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"And so one thing that we''ve done in the past that works pretty well actually is like I''ve created like fake email name, like email names, right?","index":85,"end_time":300.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":293.17,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"So we have a guy named like Tom Snell who''s like, not in existence, right?","index":86,"end_time":303.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":300.25,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"You know, and so like he emails a lot of people, right?","index":87,"end_time":307.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":303.93,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"And.","index":88,"end_time":308.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":307.77,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"But when he replies it, auto goes to one of my Indian sales assistants, right, who like lets our group know.","index":89,"end_time":314.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":308.33,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"And they''re really good because they like, they see it like instantly, you know what I mean?","index":90,"end_time":318.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":315.13,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Like we.","index":91,"end_time":319.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":318.57,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"And so we like I think I was telling the team before, it''s like when we get a response, we can respond like we respond like within like, you know, 20 minutes, 10 minutes, you know, that type of thing.","index":92,"end_time":330.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":319.45,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"So it''s like that formula is good.","index":93,"end_time":331.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":330.25,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"So like, is that Possible for us to replicate something like that, where it''s like it, you know, it is.","index":94,"end_time":336.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":331.89,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Sorry, it''s a fake name.","index":95,"end_time":341.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":338.73,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"That''s not me necessarily.","index":96,"end_time":343.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":341.78,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"And it auto goes to one of our guys in India who I know is gonna be on top of it.","index":97,"end_time":348.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":343.54,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"So that is something that we can set up.","index":98,"end_time":350.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":348.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The one part that kind of makes that a bit more difficult is the LinkedIn side of things.","index":99,"end_time":353.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":350.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, LinkedIn, I can do mine.","index":100,"end_time":355.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":353.94,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah, unless you want.","index":101,"end_time":356.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":355.3,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"You want.","index":102,"end_time":356.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":356.259,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I mean, LinkedIn could be mine.","index":103,"end_time":358.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":356.98,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Do you want the person, like, in an ideal situation, is the person, like, both, ideally?","index":104,"end_time":363.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":358.34,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Because then they''re seeing communication from the same person and that makes like their.","index":105,"end_time":367.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":363.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We see oftentimes in the market what can almost be like, anxiety of like, okay, well, I was talking to this guy the whole time, and then as soon as I said I was interested, now they just passed me off to this person.","index":106,"end_time":377.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":367.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s what we tried.","index":107,"end_time":378.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":377.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Would I be the best person?","index":108,"end_time":380.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":378.94,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Like, bang for your buck?","index":109,"end_time":381.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":380.14,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Like, that''s who I would default.","index":110,"end_time":383.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":381.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, you are who I would default to.","index":111,"end_time":384.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":383.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But, you know, just given what you were mentioning with the sales team, and I know in the earlier conversations you talked about them as well.","index":112,"end_time":389.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":384.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you wanted, you know, a top.","index":113,"end_time":391.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":389.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sales team, we can do me then.","index":114,"end_time":393.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":391.42,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Okay.","index":115,"end_time":394.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":393.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He''s got to be really careful we don''t do it to one of my clients or something.","index":116,"end_time":397.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":394.46,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Obviously.","index":117,"end_time":397.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":397.06,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":118,"end_time":397.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":397.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we''ll.","index":119,"end_time":398.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":397.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As part of building the list, will.","index":120,"end_time":400.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":398.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And the assets and everything, too.","index":121,"end_time":402.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":400.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll get.","index":122,"end_time":402.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":402.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you are willing to share access with your CRM so that we can use that to extract and run a negative list so that we don''t talk to any current customers.","index":123,"end_time":409.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":403.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":124,"end_time":411.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":410.73,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"And I can.","index":125,"end_time":411.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":411.09,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I can also just like, manually look through the list too.","index":126,"end_time":413.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":411.45,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":127,"end_time":414.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":413.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we''ll share that with you so that you can go through it.","index":128,"end_time":416.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":414.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":129,"end_time":418.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":417.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I know that you are currently doing some outreach components as well, or you did mention that in the previous calls.","index":130,"end_time":425.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":418.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are you looking for this to operate in tandem?","index":131,"end_time":428.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":426.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Would that take a different focus?","index":132,"end_time":430.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":428.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we take a different focus?","index":133,"end_time":431.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":430.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are we taking it over completely?","index":134,"end_time":433.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":431.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So from my understanding.","index":135,"end_time":436.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":435.8,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Right.","index":136,"end_time":437.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":437.4,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Correct me if I''m wrong.","index":137,"end_time":438.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":437.88,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"It''s like what we''re doing is we''re going after a specific list.","index":138,"end_time":442.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":438.88,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Right.","index":139,"end_time":443.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":442.76,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"And I go after a lot of different.","index":140,"end_time":447.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":444.12,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"And we''re going to work together on which companies we''re targeting and whatnot, right?","index":141,"end_time":451.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":448.28,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yep.","index":142,"end_time":451.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":451.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But it''s not like an endless amount.","index":143,"end_time":455.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":453.4,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Right.","index":144,"end_time":455.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":455.08,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"We''re kind of keeping it in control.","index":145,"end_time":458.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":457.08,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Right.","index":146,"end_time":459.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":458.76,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I mean, correct me if I''m wrong, but it''s like, so what I''M thinking is like, I think we talked before.","index":147,"end_time":464.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":459.16,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Like, anyone that''s in that list, I''ll do like my best effort to try to stop my own campaigns.","index":148,"end_time":470.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":464.57,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Right.","index":149,"end_time":470.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":470.09,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"But if they''re.","index":150,"end_time":471.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":470.85,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"If that''s not like affiliated to list, then I''ll just keep doing my thing.","index":151,"end_time":474.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":471.57,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":152,"end_time":475.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":475.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, that makes sense.","index":153,"end_time":477.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":475.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":154,"end_time":477.529,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":477.17,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"And the process that we go is we share the list of companies and then from there we enrich to find the people that we would reach out to.","index":155,"end_time":483.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":477.529,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then you would go through those, make sure we''re all good, and then we would start with the communication.","index":156,"end_time":488.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":484.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that.","index":157,"end_time":489.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":488.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That looks good.","index":158,"end_time":489.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":489.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":159,"end_time":491.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":491.24,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"One thing I''ll just say too, like, I''m looking at your list, so 50 million to 1 billion revenue is a lot of money.","index":160,"end_time":500.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":491.44,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"But Aum, that''s like not a lot actually.","index":161,"end_time":503.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":500.92,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Right, right.","index":162,"end_time":504.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":504.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":163,"end_time":505.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":504.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So like, Aum would be like one to like hundreds of billions of dollars, you know?","index":164,"end_time":510.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":505.16,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":165,"end_time":511.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":510.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, I''ll get that updated.","index":166,"end_time":513.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":512.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m just going to leave a note for myself.","index":167,"end_time":514.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":513.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s great feedback.","index":168,"end_time":519.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":519.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I know also just from listening to the calls that you have a pipeline with, I mean, tens of thousands of lead, I mean, maybe hundreds of thousands might be underselling that.","index":169,"end_time":529.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":520.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is there anything that you would want us to do with that list of prospects as well?","index":170,"end_time":533.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":530.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like my entire database?","index":171,"end_time":536.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":535.33,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":172,"end_time":537.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":537.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, if we want to set a rule of like, hey, this person hasn''t.","index":173,"end_time":540.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":537.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s been no communication with this person in a year or, you know, they filled this out in 2022.","index":174,"end_time":546.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":540.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"From 2022 to 2023, we take that list of contacts and do communication.","index":175,"end_time":551.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":547.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is there anything from a campaign perspective that you''re looking to do with that list?","index":176,"end_time":554.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":551.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":177,"end_time":560.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":560.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I haven''t really thought about it.","index":178,"end_time":561.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":560.43,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I thought the sole, the sole thing we were doing now was just like the targeted companies.","index":179,"end_time":565.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":561.35,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"It is.","index":180,"end_time":566.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":565.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":181,"end_time":566.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":566.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I just, I like to be holistic in my approach and just ask if there was anything that you had in mind with those.","index":182,"end_time":570.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":566.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":183,"end_time":571.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":571.31,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Not currently, I guess.","index":184,"end_time":573.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":571.95,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Okay.","index":185,"end_time":573.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":573.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, good to know.","index":186,"end_time":574.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":573.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, then we''ll take the very targeted approach and start putting that together then.","index":187,"end_time":578.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":574.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know there was a lot of questions also around like the content engine and what we can do with it.","index":188,"end_time":584.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":580.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And what we were really thinking was an internal video series.","index":189,"end_time":587.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":584.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And there''s a bunch of different ways that we can mix and match this up.","index":190,"end_time":590.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":587.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I know one of your questions was, does it have to be me?","index":191,"end_time":593.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":591.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can it be someone else on the team and to give some other ideas?","index":192,"end_time":597.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":593.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oftentimes with clients, we''ll even hop on and do an interview, and then we just show the one side of the camera in all of the assets that we produce.","index":193,"end_time":603.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":597.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But basically, having a conversation or an interview in a tool that we use called Riverside is a great way to get content for social media, for web pages, for ABM outreach, to just show thought leadership.","index":194,"end_time":616.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":604.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And also we can create a lot of blogs and downloadable content from those as well.","index":195,"end_time":622.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":616.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I don''t know if you''ve thought about this anymore since your conversations with Justin and Tristan about if you would like to be a person on the show or someone else on your team or if it would just be like a.","index":196,"end_time":632.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":622.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Where interviewing a rotating list of employees and possible prospects.","index":197,"end_time":637.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":633.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I haven''t really thought about it much further from the last time we spoke about it, to be honest.","index":198,"end_time":643.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":639.44,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"There''s a.","index":199,"end_time":644.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":644.16,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"There''s a couple of ideas that we could do, you know, where it''s like, yeah, either me or, you know, I. I do have a senior guy who knows real estate really well, too.","index":200,"end_time":654.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":644.68,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Or, you know, our employees, if we want to show off our talent.","index":201,"end_time":657.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":654.6,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I don''t really know.","index":202,"end_time":658.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":657.6,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"We''d have to talk through that, I think.","index":203,"end_time":659.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":658.16,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":204,"end_time":660.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":659.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, I got you.","index":205,"end_time":661.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":660.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, we''ll start to put together a framework for it then.","index":206,"end_time":663.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":661.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''s basically compiling research on industry trends and topics and what we feel your industry prospects would be interested in hearing about.","index":207,"end_time":671.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":663.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then from there, that can give you a little bit inform more information of like, okay, maybe I host one every month or every couple of months, and then this person does it.","index":208,"end_time":679.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":671.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, flip back and forth.","index":209,"end_time":680.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":679.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can take a few different approaches.","index":210,"end_time":682.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":680.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":211,"end_time":682.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":682.52,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":212,"end_time":684.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":683.8,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"All right.","index":213,"end_time":686.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":685.89,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"And then the last thing.","index":214,"end_time":687.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":686.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, two more things that I want to show is we''ll send over this asset intake document, and this just goes through sharing what email address we need you to share, just some different access with for different tools.","index":215,"end_time":698.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":688.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll send this over to you.","index":216,"end_time":702.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":701.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":217,"end_time":706.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":705.65,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"And for my email, do you guys have a way of, like, protecting my email from being like, spams or something like that?","index":218,"end_time":711.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":706.37,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Protecting, like, the emails that we''re sending out for the ABM campaign.","index":219,"end_time":715.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":712.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, I don''t want my, like, individual email to get, like, flagged.","index":220,"end_time":718.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":715.85,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I don''t know if that''s even possible.","index":221,"end_time":719.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":718.61,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Oh, because of the ABM outreach?","index":222,"end_time":721.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":720.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":223,"end_time":723.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":722.57,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"That''s why we set up different domains that we''re sending from, so it won''t be from anything at gallagher and mohan.com.","index":224,"end_time":728.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":723.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":225,"end_time":729.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":728.81,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"That''s how we protect.","index":226,"end_time":730.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":729.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, got it.","index":227,"end_time":732.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":730.97,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Okay.","index":228,"end_time":733.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":733.13,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"And then the last thing that I''ll show is we''ll also give you an invite.","index":229,"end_time":737.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":734.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is your portal into everything that we are doing.","index":230,"end_time":740.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":737.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this will be updated every 15 minutes from our project management system.","index":231,"end_time":744.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":740.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have our goal in here that was outlined in the strategic document.","index":232,"end_time":749.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":744.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The only item we''re waiting on you.","index":233,"end_time":750.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":749.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you click on review, it will open up the document we were just looking at.","index":234,"end_time":754.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":750.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then if I go back to Safari, then it''ll just also show any tasks that we have coming up.","index":235,"end_time":762.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":756.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll be designing some web pages, the ABM plan document, et cetera.","index":236,"end_time":766.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":763.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And if you ever need to know anything that we''re waiting on you for, obviously you can send us an email or go to to DOS and waiting on client.","index":237,"end_time":772.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":766.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any work that we do throughout our entire engagement will live in final deliverables as well.","index":238,"end_time":779.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":775.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you can always say like, where is that white paper that we made or something.","index":239,"end_time":783.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":779.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You can go here and download it.","index":240,"end_time":784.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":783.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it.","index":241,"end_time":785.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":784.98,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Okay.","index":242,"end_time":787.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":786.82,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"And this is you''re going to send me this link?","index":243,"end_time":789.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":787.62,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":244,"end_time":790.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":790.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''ll.","index":245,"end_time":790.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":790.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You''ll get an email with an invite and it''s just a single sign on.","index":246,"end_time":793.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":790.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, got it.","index":247,"end_time":795.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":794.79,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":248,"end_time":797.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":796.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Other than that, that is really all I wanted to to go through.","index":249,"end_time":800.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":797.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the one action item left is I want to figure out a time that works for you on a weekly basis that we can meet starting next week.","index":250,"end_time":809.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":801.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is there a day that''s better for you?","index":251,"end_time":811.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":809.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not really.","index":252,"end_time":814.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":814.07,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I mean this time is probably overall solid.","index":253,"end_time":817.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":814.63,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Okay, so Mondays at 1:30.","index":254,"end_time":820.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":818.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let''s do it actually next week let''s do it like, can you do it like 2:30?","index":255,"end_time":827.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":821.76,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Is that better?","index":256,"end_time":827.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":827.16,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"2:30 Eastern?","index":257,"end_time":830.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":829.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I cannot on Mondays.","index":258,"end_time":832.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":830.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":259,"end_time":834.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":833.6,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"1:30 is actually generally not good.","index":260,"end_time":835.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":834.319,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I made a mistake.","index":261,"end_time":836.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":835.96,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"What other times around that general time work for you, do you think?","index":262,"end_time":839.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":836.64,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I could do 4pm Eastern or anytime between 12 and 2 Eastern on Mondays or earlier in the morning?","index":263,"end_time":849.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":840.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I could do one o'' clock Eastern.","index":264,"end_time":853.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":852.1,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"One o''.","index":265,"end_time":854.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":853.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Clock.","index":266,"end_time":854.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":854.46,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"All right, let''s do that.","index":267,"end_time":856.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":855.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And if any time you know, you''re like, hey, it''s not going to work this week, just let us know and we''ll move it.","index":268,"end_time":860.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":856.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, sounds good.","index":269,"end_time":861.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":860.58,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":270,"end_time":862.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":861.94,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"All right, well, I''ll send over your pulse access and the asset intake document and as well as the meeting invite for next week.","index":271,"end_time":869.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":862.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we''ll start working on some documentation behind the scenes.","index":272,"end_time":872.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":869.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, that works for me.","index":273,"end_time":875.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":873.99,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Appreciate it.","index":274,"end_time":876.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":875.27,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Any questions that you had that we didn''t cover today?","index":275,"end_time":878.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":876.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not really.","index":276,"end_time":882.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":881.51,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"So we.","index":277,"end_time":882.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":882.15,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"So we''re meeting next week.","index":278,"end_time":883.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":882.63,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"You''re gonna send me some stuff and you want me to fill out that one thing, right?","index":279,"end_time":886.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":883.63,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yep.","index":280,"end_time":887.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":886.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then, then we''ll go from there.","index":281,"end_time":889.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":887.27,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Exactly okay.","index":282,"end_time":891.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":889.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":283,"end_time":892.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":891.99,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":284,"end_time":892.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":892.35,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":285,"end_time":893.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":892.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, I hope you had a great holiday break and very excited to work with you.","index":286,"end_time":897.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":893.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, you, too.","index":287,"end_time":898.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":898.07,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":288,"end_time":899.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":898.79,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":289,"end_time":899.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":899.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, see you.","index":290,"end_time":900.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":899.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, see you.","index":291,"end_time":901.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":900.63,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Bye.","index":292,"end_time":901.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":901.23,"speaker_name":"Doug"}],"dateString":"2026-01-05T18:30:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/89164916386?pwd=JcDbx9Vnbgy5JWH3DnYAcwehpATil1.1","participants":["colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,dougg@gallaghermohan.com,nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com","dougg@gallaghermohan.com","nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KD8BWP3RB8Y7F8PNY4JRDEYQ","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.91,"bullets":["Confirmed ABM campaign will target real estate-related segments using Colin’s formal communication plan.","Doug agreed to use his LinkedIn profile while outreach emails will use domain-managed aliases.","Team aligned on excluding current clients via CRM checks and manual list review by Doug.","Content engine will focus on thought leadership videos; format and host still under discussion.","Client portal access and asset intake process to be shared; weekly syncs to start next Monday."],"highlights":[{"quote":"Sales team, we can do me then.","speaker":"Doug"},{"quote":"Everything that we are running in this campaign will be put together in what we call an ABM plan.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"So the one action item left is I want to figure out a time that works for you on a weekly basis.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"}],"topics":["launch","scope","delivery"],"model":"openai/gpt-4","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-05T21:31:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **ABM Campaign Strategy and Execution**\n\nThe team agreed on a focused ABM campaign targeting specific real estate-related industries to drive highly personalized outreach.\n\n- **Target industries include real estate, private equity, multi-family operators, affordable housing owners, and retail, industrial, and logistics investors within real estate investment** as confirmed by Doug and Colin (03:00)  \n    - The campaign will use a formal ABM plan outlining target roles, messaging, timelines, offers, and segmented communication strategies.  \n    - Personalization will tailor messages to roles, such as finance professionals in private equity versus affordable housing.  \n    - Outreach will combine email and LinkedIn, with emails sent from custom domains like “Doug@g&h.com” to avoid spam issues.  \n    - LinkedIn outreach will use Doug’s personal profile for consistency, reducing recipient confusion and anxiety over sales handoffs.\n\n- **Doug emphasized a two-tier sales outreach model using fake email personas routed to India-based sales assistants for rapid response** (05:30)  \n    - This setup enables replies to be handled within 10–20 minutes, improving engagement speed.  \n    - Colin confirmed the email system can replicate this approach, though LinkedIn outreach will remain under Doug’s personal profile for clarity.  \n    - Doug will manually vet lists to avoid contacting existing clients, supported by CRM integration for negative-list filtering.\n\n- **The campaign scope will focus on a controlled, specific list of targeted companies rather than mass outreach** (07:00)  \n    - Doug will stop any overlapping outreach to the same targets to avoid duplication.  \n    - Colin confirmed the process includes list sharing, enrichment, vetting, and then coordinated messaging launch.  \n    - Doug highlighted the need to adjust AUM revenue ranges from “50 million to 1 billion” to a broader scale of “one to hundreds of billions” for accuracy, and Colin committed to updating this (08:20).  \n    - No plans currently exist to activate outreach on the larger existing database of tens to hundreds of thousands of leads, keeping the focus tightly on targeted accounts.\n\n## **Content Engine and Thought Leadership Framework**\n\nThe team plans to develop an internal video series and related content to support ABM campaigns and thought leadership.\n\n- **Colin proposed using a video interview format via the Riverside platform to generate multi-format content for social media, blogs, web pages, and ABM outreach** (10:15)  \n    - This includes one-sided camera interviews with rotating company employees or prospects to showcase expertise.  \n    - Content frequency options include monthly or bi-monthly episodes featuring Doug, senior team members, or other employees.  \n    - The framework will be informed by research on industry trends and prospect interests to ensure relevance.  \n    - This approach aims to build credibility and provide reusable content assets across channels.\n\n- **Doug expressed openness to involving himself, a senior real estate expert, or other employees but requested further internal discussion before finalizing hosts** (10:45)  \n    - Colin committed to drafting the framework to guide scheduling and participant roles as the next step.\n\n## **Technical Setup and Communication Workflow**\n\nThe meeting clarified technical details to ensure smooth campaign execution and protection of Doug’s personal email reputation.\n\n- **Email outreach will use separate domains distinct from Doug’s main “gallagher and mohan.com” domain to avoid spam flags and preserve reputation** (11:50)  \n    - Replies to outreach emails will be routed via sentiment analysis tools to notify Doug only of interested contacts, limiting inbox overload.  \n    - The fake persona email system will be integrated to forward responses directly to Indian sales assistants for timely follow-up, preserving the rapid response model Doug favors.\n\n- **LinkedIn outreach will be connected to Doug’s personal profile, maintaining message consistency and recipient trust** (06:00)  \n    - This reduces confusion caused by handoffs from one communicator to another during the sales process.\n\n- **Colin will send an asset intake document requiring email access and other tool permissions to enable campaign setup** (11:20)  \n    - Doug will provide necessary access credentials and assist in reviewing contact lists to exclude current customers.\n\n## **Project Management and Collaboration Tools**\n\nA shared project portal will provide real-time visibility into campaign progress, deliverables, and outstanding client tasks.\n\n- **Colin introduced a client portal updated every 15 minutes to track goals, documents, tasks, and final deliverables** (12:40)  \n    - Doug will receive a single sign-on invite to access this portal for ongoing transparency and easy retrieval of materials like white papers.  \n    - This portal also highlights any outstanding action items requiring Doug’s input, streamlining communication.\n\n- **Weekly meetings will be scheduled on Mondays at 1:00 PM Eastern to maintain alignment and progress tracking** (14:00)  \n    - Flexibility was agreed upon to reschedule as needed, ensuring continuous collaboration without disruption.\n\n- **Doug confirmed understanding of next steps, including receiving documents to fill out and initiating campaign build after his review** (14:40)  \n    - Colin will send the portal invite, asset intake document, and meeting invite immediately following this call.\n\n## **Strategic Alignment and Market Positioning**\n\nThe campaign’s precision targeting and content strategy aim to position Doug’s company strongly in competitive real estate investment markets.\n\n- **Prioritizing personalization and role-specific messaging reflects a strategic shift toward meaningful engagement over broad outreach** (02:00)  \n    - This addresses market concerns about generic sales approaches that reduce response rates and increase prospect anxiety.  \n    - Doug’s feedback on AUM ranges and list selection shows a focus on quality targeting aligned with true market sizes.\n\n- **Content production as a thought leadership tool supports brand differentiation in a crowded market by showcasing expertise and insights** (10:00)  \n    - Leveraging internal experts and prospective voices enhances credibility and signals deep industry knowledge, helping win trust.\n\n- **Protecting email domain reputation and using sentiment analysis for reply management highlights a sophisticated approach to maintaining outreach efficacy** (11:00)  \n    - This technical care underpins long-term deliverability and engagement success.\n\n- **The combined approach of targeted ABM, content marketing, and streamlined follow-up workflows reflects a holistic sales transformation designed to accelerate pipeline growth and improve conversion** (05:00)  \n    - Doug’s role as both CEO and frontline sales leader integrates strategic oversight with hands-on execution, maximizing impact.","outline":null,"keywords":["Account-Based Marketing","ABM Campaign","Outreach Strategy","Content Engine","LinkedIn Outreach","Prospect List Management"],"overview":"- **ABM Campaign Focus:** Target real estate and investment sectors with personalized outreach strategies for better engagement.\n\n- **Two-Tier Outreach Model:** Use fake email personas for quick replies, routed to sales assistants for faster response times.\n\n- **Targeted Approach:** Restrict outreach to a curated list of companies and increase AUM range for accurate targeting metrics.\n\n- **Content Creation:** Develop internal video series for multiple channels, showcasing expertise and aligning with industry trends.\n\n- **Technical Setup:** Utilize separate email domains for outreach to maintain reputation and filter responses effectively through tools.\n\n- **Project Tracking:** Implement a client portal updated frequently, with weekly meetings to monitor progress and ensure collaboration.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nSend asset intake document to Doug for sharing email addresses and tool access (11:45)\nProvide invitation and access to project management portal with real-time updates (12:40)\nSchedule and send invite for weekly meetings Mondays at 1 PM Eastern starting next week (13:16)\nUpdate ABM campaign target criteria to reflect corrected AUM ranges (08:25)\nPrepare ABM plan document including list segmentation, messaging, landing pages, and outreach strategy for Doug’s review (02:30)\nCoordinate list building and exclusion of current clients via CRM data and manual review by Doug (06:37)\nBegin framework development for internal video content series and interview approach (09:50)\n\n**Doug Gallagher**\nReview and provide feedback on ABM target company list to ensure overlap with own outreach campaigns is avoided (07:55)\nManually review and approve prospect lists to avoid contacting current clients (06:50)\nConsider and decide internally on suitable personnel for hosting the content engine video series or interviews (10:39)\nComplete and return asset intake document shared by Colin (14:41)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"fd4c57d0-ae25-42c0-9a2a-2e4480a4e972","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
