INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Gallagher & Mohan//MiD: Marketing Kickoff',
  '## **ABM Campaign Strategy and Execution**

The team agreed on a focused ABM campaign targeting specific real estate-related industries to drive highly personalized outreach.

- **Target industries include real estate, private equity, multi-family operators, affordable housing owners, and retail, industrial, and logistics investors within real estate investment** as confirmed by Doug and Colin (03:00)  
    - The campaign will use a formal ABM plan outlining target roles, messaging, timelines, offers, and segmented communication strategies.  
    - Personalization will tailor messages to roles, such as finance professionals in private equity versus affordable housing.  
    - Outreach will combine email and LinkedIn, with emails sent from custom domains like “Doug@g&h.com” to avoid spam issues.  
    - LinkedIn outreach will use Doug’s personal profile for consistency, reducing recipient confusion and anxiety over sales handoffs.

- **Doug emphasized a two-tier sales outreach model using fake email personas routed to India-based sales assistants for rapid response** (05:30)  
    - This setup enables replies to be handled within 10–20 minutes, improving engagement speed.  
    - Colin confirmed the email system can replicate this approach, though LinkedIn outreach will remain under Doug’s personal profile for clarity.  
    - Doug will manually vet lists to avoid contacting existing clients, supported by CRM integration for negative-list filtering.

- **The campaign scope will focus on a controlled, specific list of targeted companies rather than mass outreach** (07:00)  
    - Doug will stop any overlapping outreach to the same targets to avoid duplication.  
    - Colin confirmed the process includes list sharing, enrichment, vetting, and then coordinated messaging launch.  
    - Doug highlighted the need to adjust AUM revenue ranges from “50 million to 1 billion” to a broader scale of “one to hundreds of billions” for accuracy, and Colin committed to updating this (08:20).  
    - No plans currently exist to activate outreach on the larger existing database of tens to hundreds of thousands of leads, keeping the focus tightly on targeted accounts.

## **Content Engine and Thought Leadership Framework**

The team plans to develop an internal video series and related content to support ABM campaigns and thought leadership.

- **Colin proposed using a video interview format via the Riverside platform to generate multi-format content for social media, blogs, web pages, and ABM outreach** (10:15)  
    - This includes one-sided camera interviews with rotating company employees or prospects to showcase expertise.  
    - Content frequency options include monthly or bi-monthly episodes featuring Doug, senior team members, or other employees.  
    - The framework will be informed by research on industry trends and prospect interests to ensure relevance.  
    - This approach aims to build credibility and provide reusable content assets across channels.

- **Doug expressed openness to involving himself, a senior real estate expert, or other employees but requested further internal discussion before finalizing hosts** (10:45)  
    - Colin committed to drafting the framework to guide scheduling and participant roles as the next step.

## **Technical Setup and Communication Workflow**

The meeting clarified technical details to ensure smooth campaign execution and protection of Doug’s personal email reputation.

- **Email outreach will use separate domains distinct from Doug’s main “gallagher and mohan.com” domain to avoid spam flags and preserve reputation** (11:50)  
    - Replies to outreach emails will be routed via sentiment analysis tools to notify Doug only of interested contacts, limiting inbox overload.  
    - The fake persona email system will be integrated to forward responses directly to Indian sales assistants for timely follow-up, preserving the rapid response model Doug favors.

- **LinkedIn outreach will be connected to Doug’s personal profile, maintaining message consistency and recipient trust** (06:00)  
    - This reduces confusion caused by handoffs from one communicator to another during the sales process.

- **Colin will send an asset intake document requiring email access and other tool permissions to enable campaign setup** (11:20)  
    - Doug will provide necessary access credentials and assist in reviewing contact lists to exclude current customers.

## **Project Management and Collaboration Tools**

A shared project portal will provide real-time visibility into campaign progress, deliverables, and outstanding client tasks.

- **Colin introduced a client portal updated every 15 minutes to track goals, documents, tasks, and final deliverables** (12:40)  
    - Doug will receive a single sign-on invite to access this portal for ongoing transparency and easy retrieval of materials like white papers.  
    - This portal also highlights any outstanding action items requiring Doug’s input, streamlining communication.

- **Weekly meetings will be scheduled on Mondays at 1:00 PM Eastern to maintain alignment and progress tracking** (14:00)  
    - Flexibility was agreed upon to reschedule as needed, ensuring continuous collaboration without disruption.

- **Doug confirmed understanding of next steps, including receiving documents to fill out and initiating campaign build after his review** (14:40)  
    - Colin will send the portal invite, asset intake document, and meeting invite immediately following this call.

## **Strategic Alignment and Market Positioning**

The campaign’s precision targeting and content strategy aim to position Doug’s company strongly in competitive real estate investment markets.

- **Prioritizing personalization and role-specific messaging reflects a strategic shift toward meaningful engagement over broad outreach** (02:00)  
    - This addresses market concerns about generic sales approaches that reduce response rates and increase prospect anxiety.  
    - Doug’s feedback on AUM ranges and list selection shows a focus on quality targeting aligned with true market sizes.

- **Content production as a thought leadership tool supports brand differentiation in a crowded market by showcasing expertise and insights** (10:00)  
    - Leveraging internal experts and prospective voices enhances credibility and signals deep industry knowledge, helping win trust.

- **Protecting email domain reputation and using sentiment analysis for reply management highlights a sophisticated approach to maintaining outreach efficacy** (11:00)  
    - This technical care underpins long-term deliverability and engagement success.

- **The combined approach of targeted ABM, content marketing, and streamlined follow-up workflows reflects a holistic sales transformation designed to accelerate pipeline growth and improve conversion** (05:00)  
    - Doug’s role as both CEO and frontline sales leader integrates strategic oversight with hands-on execution, maximizing impact.',
  '2026-01-05 18:30:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Send asset intake document to Doug for sharing email addresses and tool access (11:45)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide invitation and access to project management portal with real-time updates (12:40)","completed":false},{"text":"Schedule and send invite for weekly meetings Mondays at 1 PM Eastern starting next week (13:16)","completed":false},{"text":"Update ABM campaign target criteria to reflect corrected AUM ranges (08:25)","completed":false},{"text":"Prepare ABM plan document including list segmentation, messaging, landing pages, and outreach strategy for Doug’s review (02:30)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate list building and exclusion of current clients via CRM data and manual review by Doug (06:37)","completed":false},{"text":"Begin framework development for internal video content series and interview approach (09:50)","completed":false},{"text":"Review and provide feedback on ABM target company list to ensure overlap with own outreach campaigns is avoided (07:55)","completed":false},{"text":"Manually review and approve prospect lists to avoid contacting current clients (06:50)","completed":false},{"text":"Consider and decide internally on suitable personnel for hosting the content engine video series or interviews (10:39)","completed":false},{"text":"Complete and return asset intake document shared by Colin (14:41)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
  true
