-- Meeting: Ponce Bank // MiD: HubSpot Sync (2026-01-05 18:00:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '059db008-bde9-43e2-b5ea-2d8080194a92',
    '2026-01-05 18:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KDTBY36A9KAHAC25284Q3YX1',
    'Ponce Bank // MiD: HubSpot Sync',
    '{"christinazanca","Colin Costigan","gabrielbencosme","Colin Costigan","Ashlie Taska"}'::text[],
    1959,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/81691347767?pwd=ZRzKZk4Rc2WjKaDAPIqRE5enPc8KD9.1',
    '{"id":"01KDTBY36A9KAHAC25284Q3YX1","title":"Ponce Bank // MiD: HubSpot Sync","summary":{"notes":"## **Data Integration and Field Mapping**\n\nThe team agreed on the critical need to break down the data fields into phased priorities for a smooth HubSpot implementation.\n\n- **Colin Costigan committed to delivering a phased breakdown of the Encompass field mappings and HubSpot properties within one week** to clarify scope and priorities (32:13)  \n    - This phased approach will categorize fields into A, B, and C priority levels, helping to define what must be ready by day one and what can come later  \n    - Christina Zanca emphasized that finalizing field naming conventions early is important to avoid costly reprogramming later  \n    - The phased list will also include preferred sync frequencies to balance real-time needs with system capacity  \n    - The goal is to align marketing and technical teams on what data flows are essential for each phase to prevent scope creep and delays\n\n- **Gabriel Bencosme highlighted the importance of modular, incremental system design** where data flows are built piece by piece rather than one large chunk to ease management and future changes (13:14)  \n    - He clarified that HubSpot can handle complex data but starting with core processes and expanding later reduces risk  \n    - Gabriel underscored that the flow begins on the website, moves through HubSpot, and then passes leads to Salesforce when criteria are met  \n    - This staged flow supports marketing automation without overwhelming sales teams prematurely  \n    - He noted Encompass currently supports only one-way data sync into Salesforce, limiting direct updates back to Encompass\n\n## **Project Scope and Timeline Alignment**\n\nThe team identified the lack of clarity on project phases and scope as a key risk to meeting the tight **19-business-day timeline**.\n\n- **Ashley Taska and Christina Zanca agreed that narrowing down the initial scope for go-live is critical to meet the deadline** without overloading technical and marketing teams (08:34, 27:16)  \n    - Ashley emphasized uncertainty about the final build complexity makes committing to the timeline risky  \n    - Christina proposed a priority-based phased rollout that includes must-have fields for day one and secondary and tertiary features post-launch  \n    - Christina pointed out the contract expiration with Webflow creates a hard launch deadline to avoid a **$100,000 renewal fee** (27:16)  \n    - They agreed ongoing communication about bandwidth and priorities with senior stakeholders Betty and Louie is essential to prevent bottlenecks\n\n- **Colin noted that sharing the detailed HubSpot implementation plan document with Ashley and Gabriel will help clarify expectations and questions** (29:40)  \n    - This document includes lead scoring, data flow logic, and property definitions to guide development  \n    - Colin urged open communication to avoid surprises and ensure alignment  \n    - Ashley requested the document to better understand the scope and prepare questions for upcoming discussions\n\n## **Real-Time Data Sync and System Capabilities**\n\nThe group addressed the challenge of balancing real-time updates with system performance limits.\n\n- **Christina expressed a strong preference for real-time or near real-time sync for critical data like account openings or closures** to enable timely marketing actions such as surveys or abandonment emails (21:51, 25:11)  \n    - Colin confirmed HubSpot and Salesforce can support variable sync frequencies, including real-time triggers or batch updates based on data type (23:17)  \n    - Gabriel described the current core system performs a full daily update (a \"blanket update\") of contact data, which could cause API bottlenecks if replicated in real time (24:30)  \n    - The team recognized the need to carefully select which data points require real-time sync versus daily batch to avoid freezing the system (24:56)  \n    - Christina suggested assigning sync frequency per data type in the A/B/C phased list to optimize performance and responsiveness\n\n- **Gabriel confirmed HubSpot supports manual triggers for marketing teams to promote leads to Salesforce when deemed hot**, aligning with Christina’s requirement to control lead flow actively (23:29)  \n    - This trigger-based sync will help avoid flooding Salesforce with unqualified leads  \n    - The approach balances automation with human oversight for lead management  \n    - Testing and configuration of these triggers will be necessary to ensure reliability\n\n## **Platform Roles and User Access**\n\nThe team clarified the distinct roles of HubSpot and Salesforce and their user bases.\n\n- **Christina confirmed HubSpot will be used exclusively by the marketing team for campaign management and customer communications, not by sales branches** (29:54)  \n    - Branches will continue using Salesforce for account opening and sales processes  \n    - HubSpot will manage marketing data, campaign research, and lead nurturing without overlapping Salesforce functionality  \n    - Only one or two HubSpot licenses remain available, minimizing the need for broad user access setup (30:14)  \n    - This separation simplifies integration and reduces complexity for data syncing and user management\n\n- **Ashley verified that HubSpot users will not update customer contact data; changes like address updates remain in Salesforce or call center systems** (30:39)  \n    - The only exception is the opt-out flag for marketing emails, which HubSpot will manage and sync back to source systems  \n    - This maintains a single source of truth for customer data and reduces data conflicts  \n    - It also ensures compliance with marketing consent regulations\n\n## **Strategic Marketing Data Usage**\n\nThe team framed the broader business rationale behind the data integration and campaign management strategy.\n\n- **Christina emphasized the goal is to build a marketing system that enables campaign measurement, customer segmentation, and targeted communications based on integrated data** (10:57)  \n    - The system will allow marketers to analyze customer behaviors, like website engagement, to tailor campaigns more effectively  \n    - Integrating loan and account data supports understanding product utilization and campaign ROI  \n    - This data-driven approach aims to improve marketing investment efficiency and customer experience  \n    - The marketing team needs a reliable source of truth combining Encompass, Salesforce, and HubSpot data for analysis\n\n- **Christina outlined three main data flows to support marketing goals: customer communications, research insights, and lead management** (14:40)  \n    - Customer communications will rely on basic contact and product data in HubSpot for email and survey automation  \n    - Research will use additional data points to build behavioral profiles and optimize campaigns  \n    - Lead management will gate leads through HubSpot before passing qualified ones to Salesforce for sales follow-up  \n    - This segmentation supports focused workflows and clearer responsibility separation across teams\n\n- **The marketing team’s ability to act rapidly on fresh data was highlighted as a key competitive advantage**, given modern customers expect immediate, relevant engagement (21:51)  \n    - Delays in data sync risk missed opportunities and reduced customer satisfaction  \n    - Real-time triggers and automated workflows will help keep marketing timely and personalized  \n    - The system design must balance performance constraints with these business needs\n\n","outline":null,"keywords":["HubSpot integration","Salesforce sync","Encompass API","lead management","marketing automation","phased implementation"],"overview":"- **Data Integration Phased Approach:** Breakdown of Encompass field mappings into A, B, and C priorities for HubSpot implementation is essential.\n\n- **Project Timeline Risks:** Narrow initial scope for go-live is crucial to meet the tight 19-business-day timeline without overloading teams.\n\n- **Real-Time Data Sync Needs:** Emphasis on critical data sync in real-time to enhance timely marketing actions while managing system performance limits.\n\n- **Distinct Platform Roles:** HubSpot will be used solely by marketing for campaign management; Salesforce remains for sales processes.\n\n- **Strategic Data Usage:** Goal is to build a reliable marketing system for targeted communication using integrated data from Encompass, Salesforce, and HubSpot.  \n\n- **Rapid Data Actions:** Ability to act on fresh data is key for maintaining competitive edge and improving customer satisfaction.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nSend Ashley and Gabe the detailed HubSpot implementation plan document for review (29:41)\nExtract data field lists and organize into phased priority spreadsheets with preferred sync frequencies for internal and client review this week (20:57)\nRespond promptly to questions from Ashley and Gabe post-meeting to maintain transparency (32:01)\n\n**Gabriel Bencosme**\nCollaborate with Colin to define phased approach and technical feasibility based on system capabilities and integration complexities (00:00)\n\n**Ashley Taska**\nProvide feedback on phased field prioritization and proposed timelines once the plan document and spreadsheet are received (29:41)\nCoordinate internally to review project bandwidth and communicate priority adjustments needed with leadership (27:00)\n\n**Christina Zanca**\nLiaise with leadership (Betty and Louie) and marketing teams to align project priorities and escalate resourcing needs or deadline risks (27:00)\nMake note for Victor and Colin to include Encompass API in upcoming integration discussions given SBA and HR portal considerations (20:08)\n"},"duration":32.650001525878906,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"christinazanca"},{"id":1,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":2,"name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"id":3,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":4,"name":"Ashlie Taska"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hi, Colleen.","index":0,"end_time":8.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":7.36,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Hey.","index":1,"end_time":9.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":8.56,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''m looking into the rotate contact owner workflow that used to be free, like.","index":2,"end_time":19.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":10.64,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, I think it''s just a weird billing issue or something.","index":3,"end_time":23.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":20.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":4,"end_time":24.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":23.68,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":5,"end_time":26.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":26.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ve never seen it pop up like that either.","index":6,"end_time":28.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":26.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And they''re core users, so I don''t know.","index":7,"end_time":30.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":28.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good morning, everybody.","index":8,"end_time":70.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":69.3,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"And good afternoon.","index":9,"end_time":70.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":70.06,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Good afternoon.","index":10,"end_time":72.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":71.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you prefer Gabe or Gabriel?","index":11,"end_time":77.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":75.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m fine with both.","index":12,"end_time":79.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":78.42,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":13,"end_time":80.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":79.38,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Happy New Year, though.","index":14,"end_time":82.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":81.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Happy New Year.","index":15,"end_time":83.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":82.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How was the celebration?","index":16,"end_time":88.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":86.82,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"It was good.","index":17,"end_time":89.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":88.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just trying to keep the.","index":18,"end_time":90.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":89.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The family not sick.","index":19,"end_time":92.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":91.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, I heard this little virus going around there is.","index":20,"end_time":96.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":93.299,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":21,"end_time":96.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":96.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know if it''s the flu or what''s going around, but.","index":22,"end_time":99.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":96.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":23,"end_time":99.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":99.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How about for you?","index":24,"end_time":101.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":100.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was all right.","index":25,"end_time":102.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":102.02,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Can''t complain.","index":26,"end_time":103.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":102.9,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Which December was another week long, but.","index":27,"end_time":114.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":111.57,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"It''S not always, that''s for sure.","index":28,"end_time":117.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":114.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":29,"end_time":121.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":121.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hello.","index":30,"end_time":122.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":121.89,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Hello, everyone.","index":31,"end_time":123.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":122.29,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Hi, Christina.","index":32,"end_time":123.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":123.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry, just wrapping up another call.","index":33,"end_time":125.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":123.97,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Just waiting for my team to.","index":34,"end_time":127.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":125.81,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I wonder just where''s your m. Oh, yeah, that''s fine.","index":35,"end_time":133.129,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":130.249,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":36,"end_time":135.849,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":134.889,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then we''re just going to give it a minute for Betty to join it.","index":37,"end_time":139.489,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":136.489,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And I believe.","index":38,"end_time":140.329,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":139.489,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Did you.","index":39,"end_time":141.209,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":140.569,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, but he.","index":40,"end_time":142.929,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":142.409,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think he might be out today.","index":41,"end_time":144.409,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":142.929,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So we just have the, like the senior stakeholders.","index":42,"end_time":151.609,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":146.809,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So.","index":43,"end_time":151.929,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":151.609,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So Louie and Betty on these.","index":44,"end_time":154.489,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":151.929,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"These meetings and some of the other meetings that we''re going to start to set up that are going to be kind of like, you know, key decisions and just for alignment and support too, you know, just makes it an easier transition.","index":45,"end_time":169.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":154.489,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So, for example, like when Ashley and Gabe go back, you know, with.","index":46,"end_time":172.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":169.24,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"To have conversations on work that they''re doing with their, you know, executive, you know, leader, it makes it, you know, easy for them to be in the, you know, in the loop and give them the support that they need.","index":47,"end_time":183.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":172.6,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And the same reason why Betty is on.","index":48,"end_time":185.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":183.96,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So, like, if I have questions or, you know, her to move things forward.","index":49,"end_time":190.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":185.92,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So we''ll just give it a minute.","index":50,"end_time":191.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":190.1,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But I think he''s out, Louie.","index":51,"end_time":195.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":191.94,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So just Betty, because I know this time didn''t really necessarily work for Betty.","index":52,"end_time":202.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":195.42,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So we may have to move it down the line to Fridays like around 9:30 ish.","index":53,"end_time":208.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":202.9,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I don''t know if that works for everybody, but I''ll.","index":54,"end_time":211.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":208.74,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''ll let you know.","index":55,"end_time":211.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":211.02,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I know Betty''s after this week.","index":56,"end_time":213.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":212.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That actually does work for me and Guillermo.","index":57,"end_time":216.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":213.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":58,"end_time":217.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":216.82,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Okay.","index":59,"end_time":217.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":217.49,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Ashley, Gabe, are you guys, if we were to move this to like a Friday, like 9:30, would that work for you guys?","index":60,"end_time":224.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":217.97,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because I think Betty had a conflict with the one clock.","index":61,"end_time":227.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":224.53,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We have meetings every other Friday at that time.","index":62,"end_time":232.69,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":229.49,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Okay.","index":63,"end_time":233.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":232.93,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Is there another time that maybe On Fridays?","index":64,"end_time":237.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":233.97,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":65,"end_time":238.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":237.57,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Think Betty said her concern was that sometimes what happens is on Mondays is the exact meeting goes, you know, way over and then her meetings just get pushed back and so that''s why Mondays are, are hard for her.","index":66,"end_time":253.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":240.37,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then she said Tuesdays are no good.","index":67,"end_time":255.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":254.09,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So she had suggested Fridays.","index":68,"end_time":258.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":256.17,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But obviously you know, you guys are, are the, the key people that we need to work around.","index":69,"end_time":262.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":258.17,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So just, you know, you guys let me know.","index":70,"end_time":265.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":262.97,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And we don''t have to decide it now.","index":71,"end_time":272.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":271.13,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay, you can let me know.","index":72,"end_time":274.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":272.33,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Um, Betty said, you know, she''ll join if, if she could.","index":73,"end_time":278.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":274.58,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So you know, given that it''s 104, I think we could just get started.","index":74,"end_time":280.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":278.1,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Probably have a lot to, to cover.","index":75,"end_time":282.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":281.22,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''ll turn it over to you Colin and kick it off.","index":76,"end_time":285.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":282.54,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":77,"end_time":286.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":285.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So first off, thank you for sending everything over.","index":78,"end_time":289.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":287.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Apologies.","index":79,"end_time":290.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":289.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know I was like, hey, we respond quickly.","index":80,"end_time":292.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":290.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I was out of office.","index":81,"end_time":293.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":292.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For a few days.","index":82,"end_time":293.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":293.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s why, why you saw some like 6pm emails coming over and things like that.","index":83,"end_time":298.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":293.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But now that we''re all back in the flow, you''ll see much faster responses.","index":84,"end_time":302.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":299.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So thank you for sending this over.","index":85,"end_time":303.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":302.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We got the Encompass field mapping as well as the test accounts and Gabe, Ashley, I kind of wanted to just start by giving you an opportunity for any additional context or narration or narrative to these lists.","index":86,"end_time":315.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":303.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, I''m sorry guys, can you, can you repeat that?","index":87,"end_time":323.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":321.47,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Colin?","index":88,"end_time":323.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":323.19,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":89,"end_time":324.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":323.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I was just thanking you for sending this over and I just wanted to give you a few minutes if there was any additional narrative you wanted to share about this list, anything specifically we should be on the lookout for if there''s anything that we need to verify or make a decision on before we build the HubSpot version of the fields that are outlined here.","index":90,"end_time":341.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":324.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, that''s the encompass field, so that is basically what''s being.","index":91,"end_time":345.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":341.69,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"That''s what was coming over from the encompass side of the house.","index":92,"end_time":348.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":345.33,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Just, I mean, I don''t know if we''re going to be able to use this at the beginning of the implementation, but yeah, we can review this, you know, is there in case we need it.","index":93,"end_time":358.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":349.77,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"But I don''t have additional context or anything specific here, so.","index":94,"end_time":361.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":358.45,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Okay.","index":95,"end_time":362.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":362.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay Colin, the only thing I would say is that I think it''s important for both sides of, of the the house.","index":96,"end_time":370.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":362.79,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So, so Gabe and Ashley, for you guys to understand kind of how your work impacts mids and vice versa.","index":97,"end_time":379.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":370.67,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":98,"end_time":379.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":379.15,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So like essentially what MID is going to start to need to do is build out the infrastructure in HubSpot to be able to accept the data that you''re going to send in to the system.","index":99,"end_time":391.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":379.39,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":100,"end_time":391.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":391.39,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so the reason he''s asking for the alignment is because they need to match in order for the success of the, the data, you know, both ways.","index":101,"end_time":401.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":391.71,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":102,"end_time":402.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":401.77,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so at some point we''re going to have to say if it''s on the sheet, we''re going to have to kind of be comfortable with it because I don''t want to have to go back and have anything need to be, you know, reprogrammed, renamed or whatever, because at some point then that''ll incur additional time and expense.","index":103,"end_time":421.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":402.37,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So when can we, I guess say.","index":104,"end_time":429.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":421.81,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because I''m sure you guys may need more time to, to look at it, look at all the, the HubSpot documentation and all that kind of stuff.","index":105,"end_time":435.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":429.01,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But at some point, when can we say that we''re gonna kind of collectively be comfortable with the naming conventions, all of the fields that we''re building towards and like, say they''re almost approved because Encompass2 will need to be improved because we''re gonna, that''s what, that''s where we''re gonna get the loan data.","index":106,"end_time":454.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":435.53,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":107,"end_time":454.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":454.6,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"More specifically, the loan data from Encompass.","index":108,"end_time":460.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":458.48,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"This would be, I guess, the fields that we would need.","index":109,"end_time":463.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":460.96,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I''m not entirely sure if, if there''s a plan, workflow or.","index":110,"end_time":472.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":465.68,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I guess the essential question for me is in this part of, you know, since you bring this up, what is initial, what is the baseline configuration?","index":111,"end_time":480.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":472.04,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"What are, what is the initial aspect or scope of the project?","index":112,"end_time":484.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":480.85,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Essentially, what are we.","index":113,"end_time":486.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":484.93,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"What is the main purpose of the project initially?","index":114,"end_time":489.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":486.13,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Right.","index":115,"end_time":489.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":489.61,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"We understand that we want to move data between both system, but what exactly which objects are we specific talking about that we initially want to have?","index":116,"end_time":498.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":490.21,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Like this is the kind of information that, that we also don''t have right now at this point.","index":117,"end_time":502.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":498.53,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So, yeah, I''m sending the data over for Encompass, but I''m not sure if this is something that we''re going to have at the initial stage of the Go live or maybe something that''s going to be in phase one, two, three, or something that''s going to be implemented later on.","index":118,"end_time":514.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":502.87,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So.","index":119,"end_time":514.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":514.39,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Okay, I wanted to add on to that little bit and that kind of ties back to the concerns expressed with the timeline then, because as of today that''s just 19 business days.","index":120,"end_time":526.59,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":514.91,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"But we don''t have a clear understanding of, I guess if there''s phases.","index":121,"end_time":534.36,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":527.12,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"I mean, I had a conversation with Victor and it doesn''t seem like there were phases discussed, but from these conversations and these meetings we''re hearing a lot of kinds of Like a plan or what needs to happen.","index":122,"end_time":546.72,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":534.36,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"And that''s kind of why we were just like, 19 days is not enough for everything that we''re hearing in these meetings.","index":123,"end_time":555.68,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":548.48,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"So we kind of want to narrow down on what exactly is the expectation for.","index":124,"end_time":562.72,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":556.08,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"For day one, go live.","index":125,"end_time":565.52,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":563.28,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Okay.","index":126,"end_time":566.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":565.84,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"No, that.","index":127,"end_time":567.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":566.4,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That''s fair.","index":128,"end_time":567.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":567.12,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And is that.","index":129,"end_time":568.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":567.6,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And I guess that actually that''s probably what you meant by.","index":130,"end_time":570.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":568.24,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"By workflows.","index":131,"end_time":571.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":570.16,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So, so let me just say this.","index":132,"end_time":574.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":571.92,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"What.","index":133,"end_time":574.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":574.32,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"What ideally we want to happen is anything that''s on this Excel document, whether it be day one or, you know, six months down the line, it''ll.","index":134,"end_time":585.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":574.88,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It''ll be something that we need to program for and get into.","index":135,"end_time":588.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":585.31,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Into HubSpot and have directional data go back, back and forth.","index":136,"end_time":592.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":588.51,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"What we could do is, Colin, based off of the understanding of what our goals are, what I would suggest is let''s just help the team by putting in a priority level to each level of.","index":137,"end_time":610.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":592.43,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Or each field, right.","index":138,"end_time":612.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":610.75,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"To say, okay, this is their first priority.","index":139,"end_time":615.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":612.03,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And that''s going to be the fields that are going to be due in, you know, round one for, for example.","index":140,"end_time":620.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":615.87,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":141,"end_time":620.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":620.51,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Ashley and Gabe, what we''re looking to do is two things.","index":142,"end_time":625.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":622.59,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We''re looking to manage marketing campaigns with the system.","index":143,"end_time":628.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":626.27,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":144,"end_time":629.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":629.15,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so that''ll have, you know, the.","index":145,"end_time":631.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":629.47,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The standard basic data about our customer, you know, product utilization, their name, their contact information, their branch, all that kind of stuff.","index":146,"end_time":640.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":631.91,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":147,"end_time":640.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":640.07,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The reason why we''re incorporating other data that''s not necessarily going to be connected to a campaign is because what we want to do is have a source of truth for us to be able to run concept analysis.","index":148,"end_time":657.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":641.03,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So one of the things that is important for marketers is to understand whether the campaign and investment is valuable.","index":149,"end_time":662.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":657.35,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":150,"end_time":663.27,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":662.91,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"And so a lot of the times we struggle right now is because we don''t necessarily have that access.","index":151,"end_time":669.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":663.59,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"There was a little bit of back and forth about us not being able to get vi.","index":152,"end_time":672.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":670.01,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We''re going to try to get that as well.","index":153,"end_time":674.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":672.97,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But what we want to do is be able to say, based off of a lot of customers clicking on this certain field, go into HubSpot and run sort of like a little bit of a test analysis to say, like, there''s 500 customers that, you know, don''t have this account, or there''s 500 customers that do have the account.","index":154,"end_time":694.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":675.29,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so that''s why there''s those extra fields that are being, you know, looked at, because it''ll help us to, you know, use the data to make better campaign decisions.","index":155,"end_time":703.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":694.73,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So hopefully that kind of helps you understand some of the why?","index":156,"end_time":707.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":704.17,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But I definitely agree like Colin, if you and Guille could take that, you know, first step past that, identifying what''s going to be the priority and then what''s going to be the secondary.","index":157,"end_time":720.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":708.17,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We can even throw in a two part post, post website launch and then a part three, which is like nice to have like after because we realistically, we know we''re not going to necessarily, you know, be able to get to all of the campaigns.","index":158,"end_time":741.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":721.53,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Day one.","index":159,"end_time":741.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":741.33,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"In my mind, I just, I, and correct me if I''m wrong to assume working through this implementation at mcu, the feedback that their teams had given me was that it was like easier for them to kind of program it all at once versus kind of consistently like adding new things.","index":160,"end_time":762.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":743.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But if that''s not the case for you guys and you want to do that phase approach, we can, we can do that too.","index":161,"end_time":767.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":762.89,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Well, well that depends on the sign, right?","index":162,"end_time":772.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":769.05,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"If we build something that is constructed in pieces, then we can add on.","index":163,"end_time":776.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":772.45,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Typically if they construct something that is basically one huge flow and one piece of, I don''t know, let''s, let''s, I guess let''s call it one big chunk of processes jumbled together, then yeah, that''s kind of hard to manage.","index":164,"end_time":794.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":778.05,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":165,"end_time":795.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":794.61,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"If our intent is to get data points and information from different objects, specifically from Salesforce and they''re going to go into different places as well in HubSpot, I don''t, I don''t, I don''t mind.","index":166,"end_time":806.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":795.25,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I wouldn''t specifically say that is a, an issue because of course this is going to be an environment that is going to constantly change.","index":167,"end_time":813.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":806.38,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"We understand that the process, Salesforce and Hotspot, from my understanding, I''ve been looking at the Hotspot documentation.","index":168,"end_time":819.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":813.62,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"It''s very, it''s a pretty big, you know, system itself.","index":169,"end_time":823.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":819.82,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So it can handle a lot of data.","index":170,"end_time":825.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":823.74,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"And yeah, things are going to change down the line.","index":171,"end_time":827.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":825.06,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So essentially we want to build in pieces, right?","index":172,"end_time":831.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":827.78,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"We don''t want to build one big chunk of or big process where it''s difficult to manage and difficult to change down the line.","index":173,"end_time":838.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":831.18,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So you know, I think the approach that we want to take here is essentially understand what is the core process that you want happening between Hotspot or understand basically the main flow.","index":174,"end_time":851.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":838.55,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"For example, let''s say right now, you know, hypothetically speaking, anything that comes into Hotspot is going to be a new lead.","index":175,"end_time":858.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":851.71,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Are we still going to handle those leads in Salesforce or are we just going to handle them in HubSpot specifically and then that data flow is going to happen in the Back end.","index":176,"end_time":866.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":858.35,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So that''s just one example that we can build upon.","index":177,"end_time":869.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":866.92,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"And you know, and understanding that, I think it''s easier for us to develop a system where we can add layers down the line rather than build something specific.","index":178,"end_time":878.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":869.6,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"You know, one big flow that does.","index":179,"end_time":880.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":878.12,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah, no, no, I, I get that.","index":180,"end_time":881.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":880.12,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So there''s, there''s a couple different flows.","index":181,"end_time":883.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":881.56,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So we''re going to have, HubSpot is going to be the place where we''re going to, to have customer communications and emails flow out from.","index":182,"end_time":890.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":883.24,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So like you''re thinking like basic contact information that''s going to go into one section of HubSpot and that''s what we''re going to use to send out our emails.","index":183,"end_time":898.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":890.68,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Another component is the research element that I mentioned before.","index":184,"end_time":903.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":898.5,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So for example, like connecting the data points to help us to understand kind of where the customers spend time on the website will help us then to put customers into automated workflows for better campaigns execution.","index":185,"end_time":917.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":903.78,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":186,"end_time":918.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":917.94,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So that''s another section then the other piece of it is the leads and prospecting.","index":187,"end_time":924.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":918.18,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":188,"end_time":924.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":924.63,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"So like when Salesforce was initially implemented, we had the marketing cloud.","index":189,"end_time":929.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":924.87,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So like it worked the way it was supposed to where you would set up marketing campaigns and then push them through to Salesforce for the front end sales teams to execute on the campaign and close the deal.","index":190,"end_time":941.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":929.31,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because we got rid of the, the marketing cloud, we weren''t able to do the element that we started to try to manage in, in the Salesforce marketing cloud.","index":191,"end_time":952.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":941.87,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right now we''re, we''re taking that back.","index":192,"end_time":954.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":952.67,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So essential we want to do is the website''s going to be built in HubSpot.","index":193,"end_time":957.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":954.19,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We''re going to capture the lead in, in that system and then the league, the lead is going to be either a marketing lead where as we have a preset kind of set of criteria that''s going to determine if they''re warm or not.","index":194,"end_time":976.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":957.77,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So for example is like if the form says, hey, like what stage of the home buying process are you in?","index":195,"end_time":981.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":976.33,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And they say the initial discovery phase, like we''re not going to send that to the MLOs because the mortgage process is, you know, six months potentially.","index":196,"end_time":990.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":981.09,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":197,"end_time":990.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":990.06,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We''re going to put that into a marketing funnel, send them a couple things, kind of monitor their behaviors on the website and how they engage with our campaigns.","index":198,"end_time":998.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":990.26,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then once they kind of switch into a, a warm lead, then we can pass that on and that''ll be a cue that marketing would kind of push to Salesforce.","index":199,"end_time":1007.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":998.1,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":200,"end_time":1008.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1007.94,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The second kind of set of leads is like if they come through the, the website or Any of our QR codes or forms or anything like that.","index":201,"end_time":1017.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1009.3,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And like they''re ready to make a decision or open an account.","index":202,"end_time":1022.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1017.95,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"They''ll pass directly to Salesforce the way they, you know, were before.","index":203,"end_time":1026.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1022.15,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The website was the primary driver of the leads into Salesforce.","index":204,"end_time":1032.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1027.91,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So all we have to do now is build out the website landing page to send the, to do something with the lead to kind of assess it before it passes to the, to the Salesforce side.","index":205,"end_time":1044.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1032.11,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So it''s kind of the same thing.","index":206,"end_time":1045.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1044.86,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It''s just we''re taking an extra step.","index":207,"end_time":1047.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1045.9,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"What we do have to talk about down the line and we''re not really there yet is what''s going to be the process for the, for the branch leads, the call center leads, the things that are captured by the sales teams.","index":208,"end_time":1062.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1047.98,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We would need that to be passed back to us so we could do like a campaign follow up or something with it.","index":209,"end_time":1069.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1063.02,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So that''s how I think about it.","index":210,"end_time":1072.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1070.43,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It''s the three things.","index":211,"end_time":1073.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1072.95,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It''s the customer kind of communications and campaigns.","index":212,"end_time":1076.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1074.11,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It''s the marketing kind of research component and then it''s the leads management.","index":213,"end_time":1080.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1076.71,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I think that we can kind of start to segment it that way and then obviously like break out the data that we''ll need into phases.","index":214,"end_time":1089.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1082.27,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Does that make sense or.","index":215,"end_time":1091.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1089.79,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, it makes sense definitely.","index":216,"end_time":1093.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1092.31,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So I guess the flow, the current, I guess the current direction right now would be website hotspot, Salesforce.","index":217,"end_time":1103.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1094.07,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Right.","index":218,"end_time":1103.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1103.15,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Salesforce being the place where you book the accounts, you handle that information and.","index":219,"end_time":1108.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1103.39,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"But it all starts basically is.","index":220,"end_time":1110.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1108.75,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I guess I''m trying to figure out the flow of information here.","index":221,"end_time":1114.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1111.43,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So yeah, it''s going to start on the website and it''s going to go through HubSpot and then eventually when certain criteria is met, that''s when it''s going to come to Salesforce.","index":222,"end_time":1123.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1114.91,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"That''s right, right, right.","index":223,"end_time":1125.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1123.69,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And that''ll be, you know, by design right now it''s, it''s set up where you know, once we build a, a landing page on the website, Victor connects it into Salesforce through like the web to lead forms.","index":224,"end_time":1137.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1125.65,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So essentially like he''s doing the same thing in webflow right now that he would be doing or mid would be doing in the, the website HubSpot management platform.","index":225,"end_time":1148.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1138.01,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because those web to lead forms, when you guys implemented Salesforce was set up to accept the date to, to accept it as like a campaign or a lead.","index":226,"end_time":1157.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1149.83,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It''s built that way.","index":227,"end_time":1159.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1158.39,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I guess what we''ll have to do is you know, obviously assess the stuff that''s going to be bi directional so things that are, you know, going to come from Mulesoft and the, and the core systems into HubSpot and then what''s going to be accepted back into your system?","index":228,"end_time":1175.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1159.43,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Mulesoft.","index":229,"end_time":1176.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1176.01,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then like, where is it going to go from there?","index":230,"end_time":1178.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1176.53,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":231,"end_time":1178.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1178.57,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because like mulesoft is going to have to take it and say let''s send it here in Salesforce or let''s send it here in Encompass.","index":232,"end_time":1185.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1178.85,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And I don''t even know if, if a compass has those, you know, bi.","index":233,"end_time":1188.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1185.21,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Directional syncs right now, basically one directional.","index":234,"end_time":1192.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1188.49,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So anything that goes from Encompass will be into.","index":235,"end_time":1195.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1192.89,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah, directly into Salesforce.","index":236,"end_time":1197.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1195.61,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Okay.","index":237,"end_time":1198.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1197.93,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"There''s nothing that updates Encompass right now.","index":238,"end_time":1201.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1198.37,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Okay.","index":239,"end_time":1202.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1201.8,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Encompass does have its own APIs and things of that nature that maybe we can resurface that later on.","index":240,"end_time":1207.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1202.6,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Okay.","index":241,"end_time":1208.6,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1208.04,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Okay.","index":242,"end_time":1210.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1209.64,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So Colin, just make a note and Victor too, like just put Encompass on like the API conversations because there''s going to be another API meeting where we''ll talk about a couple of different things because there''s something that the SBA team is.","index":243,"end_time":1222.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1210.08,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"There''s a software that the SBA team is working to launch that we''ll probably have to do some type of integration in and there''s HR portals and stuff like that too.","index":244,"end_time":1231.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1223.32,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So there''s a lot of different, you know, potential sinks.","index":245,"end_time":1236.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1231.48,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But I guess if, if Colin and Guille, they can work on kind of getting the whole list of data, the objects and all of the fields broken out into like a phase A, B and C. Colin, can you guys have like, how long do you need for that?","index":246,"end_time":1257.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1236.9,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I mean, we can, we can do that this week.","index":247,"end_time":1259.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1257.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":248,"end_time":1261.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1261.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we.","index":249,"end_time":1262.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1261.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Gabe and Ashley, I''m not sure if.","index":250,"end_time":1264.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1263.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You guys saw the.","index":251,"end_time":1265.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1264.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We put together a very lengthy plan document of the HubSpot implementation and that has references to lead scoring, to how the flow works, the properties that we were thinking.","index":252,"end_time":1275.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1265.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So basically what we''ll do next step is we''ll extract all of that out of the document that we wrote, put that into the spreadsheet of like, like Christine is saying to your A to your B to your C and we envision them all working together.","index":253,"end_time":1286.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1275.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we just need to agree on also like the same sync frequency.","index":254,"end_time":1290.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1286.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because for example, if someone fills out a form on the website, but they actually were already in HubSpot because maybe they''re a current customer of something else of another product that Ponte offers.","index":255,"end_time":1300.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1290.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We need to be able to understand that data, get that updated in the HubSpot record and then we can send them, you know, some sort of marketing communication of hey, you should interest in this or because you Have X, Y and Z.","index":256,"end_time":1309.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1300.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You might be interested in this.","index":257,"end_time":1310.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1309.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":258,"end_time":1312.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1311.69,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And the real time, I mean for me the preference would be like if we can get something real time.","index":259,"end_time":1316.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1312.05,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like I would love for that to happen because like to.","index":260,"end_time":1321.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1317.69,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"To the extent that we can start to do like customer satisfaction surveys, you know, if a customer like gives a review on our.","index":261,"end_time":1331.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1322.01,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"On our like location pages or Google listings, like we can send like a communication out.","index":262,"end_time":1336.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1331.97,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like so there''s a lot of things that are automated and what happens is unfortunately the way technology is today is it''s a great thing.","index":263,"end_time":1343.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1336.13,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It''s like a blessing and a curse at the same time.","index":264,"end_time":1345.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1343.65,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It''s like in the past marketing was get a little bit more time to kind of get to things before they became stale.","index":265,"end_time":1353.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1346.4,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right now my struggle is that, you know, something might.","index":266,"end_time":1358.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1353.76,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Might happen and then if I don''t either a know about it right away or have the tools to action on it right away, it becomes a missed opportunity right away.","index":267,"end_time":1366.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1358.64,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":268,"end_time":1367.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1366.76,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because like technology and social media and all of that have made everything so like in the moment.","index":269,"end_time":1372.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1367.04,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so that''s where I struggle.","index":270,"end_time":1375.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1373.68,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I guess you guys let me know what the system capabilities are for like sending things real time or like if there''s just certain things that just only can be sent batch uploads.","index":271,"end_time":1384.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1375.36,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That kind of decision I think would need to be driven by you guys because you know the capabilities of the data.","index":272,"end_time":1391.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1385.76,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think HubSpot could be set up.","index":273,"end_time":1393,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1391.36,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Correct me if I''m wrong, Colin.","index":274,"end_time":1394.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1393,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like to.","index":275,"end_time":1394.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1394.08,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"To kind of accept whatever strategy like we''re going to take.","index":276,"end_time":1397.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1394.72,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":277,"end_time":1398.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1397.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And it could even be different per platform.","index":278,"end_time":1400.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1398.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we could set up Salesforce to be every 12 hours or every.","index":279,"end_time":1403.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1400.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or right away or every 24 hours, whatever we want.","index":280,"end_time":1406.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1403.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then a different platform in a different way.","index":281,"end_time":1408.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1406.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":282,"end_time":1408.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1408.49,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"When you talk about Data Sync, I guess, Colin, I''m pretty sure Hotspot supports type of triggers.","index":283,"end_time":1417.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1409.37,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Right.","index":284,"end_time":1417.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1417.33,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"If you.","index":285,"end_time":1419.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1418.57,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"The user goes in, for example, the marketing team is in.","index":286,"end_time":1421.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1419.13,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"In there, gets a lead and they say, you know what, this is actually a hot lead.","index":287,"end_time":1424.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1421.85,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I could just press a button and send it over.","index":288,"end_time":1426.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1424.45,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"That is the type of thing that you, Christina, that, that you''re talking about, right?","index":289,"end_time":1430.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1427.44,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah, Salesforce.","index":290,"end_time":1433.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1431.84,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"And well with.","index":291,"end_time":1433.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1433.12,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"With me also, of course that, that''s.","index":292,"end_time":1435.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1433.68,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"That is supported, right?","index":293,"end_time":1436.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1435.32,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Okay.","index":294,"end_time":1437.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1436.88,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It''s something that is supported that we might have to configure and test, of course, but it is supported.","index":295,"end_time":1442.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1437.36,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I don''t think that there''s going to be.","index":296,"end_time":1443.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1442.68,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I guess my concern here is when we''re talking about Data Sync again, we''re talking about, for example, the contacts information that lives in Salesforce.","index":297,"end_time":1455.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1445.6,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"That contact information is actually updated every morning by the core file.","index":298,"end_time":1459.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1455.85,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So we do.","index":299,"end_time":1461.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1460.01,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"It''s not just a regular update.","index":300,"end_time":1462.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1461.21,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"We actually, I mean, it''s not a partial update where we check what change.","index":301,"end_time":1467.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1462.69,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s actually a full update.","index":302,"end_time":1470.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1467.77,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"It''s a blanket update.","index":303,"end_time":1471.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1470.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s a blanket update every single morning to the contact.","index":304,"end_time":1474.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1471.09,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So the thing with that is, for example, if you wanted to have that information updated as well in.","index":305,"end_time":1479.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1474.49,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"In hotspot, then I''ll see a potential of us hitting some type of block roadblock because, you know, we have.","index":306,"end_time":1488.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1481.63,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"That''s a lot of calls, right?","index":307,"end_time":1490.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1488.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":308,"end_time":1491.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1490.79,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So you.","index":309,"end_time":1491.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1491.07,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"You''re gonna, you''re gonna call out the APIs and it''s gonna.","index":310,"end_time":1493.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1491.31,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So yes, it''s gonna freeze the system.","index":311,"end_time":1495.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1493.87,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":312,"end_time":1496.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1496.43,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So we have to think about specifically when are the instances where we can create triggers and things of that.","index":313,"end_time":1502.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1496.75,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"You know, I''m pretty sure that for a single lead that is going to be sent over 100.","index":314,"end_time":1506.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1502.19,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Sure that Victor is not going to click update 100 records, you know.","index":315,"end_time":1511.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1506.75,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Oh, yeah, no, you''re.","index":316,"end_time":1513.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1511.71,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You''re spot on with that.","index":317,"end_time":1514.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1513.51,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"With that.","index":318,"end_time":1515.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1514.59,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It''s, it''s.","index":319,"end_time":1515.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1515.03,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And maybe Colin, as part of your ABC kind of setup, you would say, like, you know, these are the types of things that maybe if we can get in real time.","index":320,"end_time":1526.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1516.27,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So for example, like, I''m thinking like, anything at the kind of customer records, like, we''re okay to update daily.","index":321,"end_time":1534,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1526.31,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":322,"end_time":1534.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1534,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because that''s enough time for us to be able to capture changes.","index":323,"end_time":1537.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1534.28,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But for example, like, any like, type of like, account change would be cool to happen in real time because, like, if they open up a new account, like, then we can automate like a survey or a welcome letter or if.","index":324,"end_time":1551.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1538.04,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"They close an account or.","index":325,"end_time":1553.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1551.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right, right.","index":326,"end_time":1554.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1553.24,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like, we can even have like, abandonment letters sent out, like, stuff like that.","index":327,"end_time":1557.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1554.08,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But I guess the next steps, in my mind, because this is.","index":328,"end_time":1564.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1559.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think this was a helpful kind of conversation to kind of see how you guys are breaking it out on your end, is for us to admit to kind of break down this.","index":329,"end_time":1574.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1564.21,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"This big list into phases and attach kind of the preferred frequency.","index":330,"end_time":1580.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1574.53,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":331,"end_time":1581.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1580.65,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then for you guys to kind of look at that and say, okay, is this a doable?","index":332,"end_time":1585.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1581.17,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And is this, you know, like, what would the lift be required?","index":333,"end_time":1590.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1585.95,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That''s one part.","index":334,"end_time":1592.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1590.91,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The second part is, is that I think Ashley, maybe me, you have to kind of have a conversation to determine how our bandwidth and kind of like individual team projects, like overlap in terms of bandwidth, because what, what we''re tasked with is getting the website and, you know, campaigns and things launched based off of a timeline that we''re working with because we have contracts and things that are expiring.","index":335,"end_time":1618.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1593.07,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So just to give you background, when our website, with webflow, our contract with webflow expires, like, we have to already be launched because if we, if we''re, if we don''t, then it''s going to be, you know, a hundred thousand dollars that we have to, you know, sign a renewal because they don''t do month to month.","index":336,"end_time":1636.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1619.38,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So that''s why, like, at some point, your team is going to have priorities.","index":337,"end_time":1641.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1636.66,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And, you know, I, I get it totally.","index":338,"end_time":1643.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1641.64,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like, but we''ll have to have the conversations, like Betty, me, Louie and you to say, okay, like, I get it.","index":339,"end_time":1650.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1643.64,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like, right, like, marketing has to launch this.","index":340,"end_time":1652.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1650.64,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I have, I have dao.","index":341,"end_time":1654.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1652.96,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I have other projects.","index":342,"end_time":1655.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1654.36,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like, somebody has to tell us, like, where to prioritize.","index":343,"end_time":1659.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1655.6,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And if it''s, you know, you guys have to stop one thing and work on the website.","index":344,"end_time":1662.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1659.16,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Great.","index":345,"end_time":1663.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1662.8,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"If it''s.","index":346,"end_time":1663.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1663.12,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And if it''s, Betty has to tell me, like, hey, like, no, like, we just have to get another resource or we have to push our deadline.","index":347,"end_time":1669.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1663.48,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That''s just something that we''ll have to make sure that we''re aligned with because, like, we''re all working on the same team, right?","index":348,"end_time":1674.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1669.94,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And every project is important.","index":349,"end_time":1675.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1674.54,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I don''t want you guys to feel inundated, but I also don''t want to, you know, have to go to Betty and say, like, hey, like, we''re not, you know, making our timeline so we can, like, have that conversation, you know, Ashley, you know, because you giving me line of sight into some of your deliverables will help me kind of go to Betty and say, like, we''re going to run into this roadblock.","index":350,"end_time":1693.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1676.1,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then the next thing that we can do is start to assign, you know, proposed delivery dates for each of these things.","index":351,"end_time":1702.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1694.26,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Just way, like, then you can plan more effectively, just like, the way, you know, I can.","index":352,"end_time":1706.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1702.09,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So, I mean, does that sound like a good plan?","index":353,"end_time":1709.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1706.81,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, I think so.","index":354,"end_time":1711.09,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1709.45,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"We have, like, pending questions, and I think that will kind of help us better understand and align because, like, again, what I was trying to say in the email is it''s really depending on the flow, right?","index":355,"end_time":1722.25,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1711.09,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"If we keep things simple, more can get done.","index":356,"end_time":1725.45,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1722.25,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"But if we need to, you know, kind of build something out that''s way more complex, it might not be doable within that timeline.","index":357,"end_time":1733.53,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1725.45,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"And because we just.","index":358,"end_time":1734.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1733.53,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"We just don''t know yet what we''re building, it''s kind of hard to say, like, yeah, sure, we can absolutely do this.","index":359,"end_time":1741.29,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1734.73,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"You know, I don''t want to say, yes, we can do it.","index":360,"end_time":1743.01,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1741.29,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"And then the day comes and we''re like, oh wait, we didn''t know it was going to be this complex, you know.","index":361,"end_time":1747.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1743.01,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"So I think we need to identify those pieces first so that we can definitely align and shift whatever other priorities are going on outside as well.","index":362,"end_time":1759.01,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1747.85,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Colin, Sorry, I''m going back a little bit.","index":363,"end_time":1762.53,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1760.37,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Colin, you mentioned the document that you, that you and the team have created.","index":364,"end_time":1767.93,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1762.53,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"I don''t think that we received that.","index":365,"end_time":1770.69,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1767.93,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"So if it''s possible to share with us, I think that might help us understand a little bit better and go through the questions that we have on our side.","index":366,"end_time":1779.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1771.33,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Mm.","index":367,"end_time":1780.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1780.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then Christina, for when it comes to HubSpot, is it only the marketing team that will have access into it or is it going to be expected that the branches interact with HubSpot as well?","index":368,"end_time":1793.37,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1781.53,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Yeah, no, I don''t think that the strategy is to have this be a system that we start to conflate Salesforce.","index":369,"end_time":1802.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1794.33,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think Salesforce is, is going to just continue and the branches will kind of work within that system because that''s where the account opening is done and all that.","index":370,"end_time":1810.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1802.41,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"This is truly, although it.","index":371,"end_time":1812.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1810.33,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Behind the scenes.","index":372,"end_time":1813.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1812.49,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":373,"end_time":1814.53,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1814.05,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Although it is a CRM because that''s just the way it, it is.","index":374,"end_time":1819.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1814.93,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It''s truly like a marketing system.","index":375,"end_time":1821.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1819.41,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so the branches, I don''t, I don''t foresee needing, you know, access and we only have honestly, I think one or two more licenses left anyway, so.","index":376,"end_time":1830.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1821.65,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay.","index":377,"end_time":1831.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1831.01,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":378,"end_time":1832.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1831.73,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I mean that probably like makes it a lot less complicated because you don''t have to set up a lot of integrations between like individual profiles.","index":379,"end_time":1838.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1832.13,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":380,"end_time":1840.01,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1839.81,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"And it brings me to, to my next question.","index":381,"end_time":1841.97,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1840.01,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Since they''re not interacting with that, I''m assuming that within HubSpot there will be no changes to customer data such as updating their address or updating their email or phone number.","index":382,"end_time":1857.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1842.13,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Nothing like that.","index":383,"end_time":1858.37,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1857.49,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Right.","index":384,"end_time":1858.69,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1858.37,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Okay.","index":385,"end_time":1859.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1858.77,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":386,"end_time":1859.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1859.33,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So marketing is not going to edit any, any data.","index":387,"end_time":1864.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1859.77,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The only thing that you''ll have to extend accept on your side is an opt out.","index":388,"end_time":1869.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1864.45,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So the email system, because it''s going to be managed in, in the HubSpot platform, they''ll capture opt outs that''ll happen directly from an email.","index":389,"end_time":1879.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1870.04,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":390,"end_time":1880.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1879.72,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So you''ll have to be able to accept the opt out flag to put on the customer''s account as not wanting emails.","index":391,"end_time":1887.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1880.12,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The same way that HubSpot will have to capture anybody that opts out in a branch or at the, you know, the call center.","index":392,"end_time":1894.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1887.64,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So yeah, we''re not going to, we''re not going to modify data at all.","index":393,"end_time":1899.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1895.22,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You know, if a customer sends an email and says, hey, I need to change my address, it''s going to be like, no, that goes to the, to the call center or the.","index":394,"end_time":1906.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1899.86,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It''s going to manage the same kind of process or procedure that we have.","index":395,"end_time":1910.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1906.78,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":396,"end_time":1911.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1910.94,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So, okay, your source of truth is going to remain what it is.","index":397,"end_time":1914.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1911.38,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I do have to jump two minutes late to another call.","index":398,"end_time":1918.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1916.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we will send over the document.","index":399,"end_time":1920.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1918.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Ashley and Gabe, at any point, any questions pop up, please just send them over.","index":400,"end_time":1924.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1920.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We don''t want you guys feeling like you''re in the dark on anything.","index":401,"end_time":1927.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1924.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we''ll build out that phased approach timeline to make sure that, that we''re all on the same page as far as the properties and next steps.","index":402,"end_time":1932.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1927.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":403,"end_time":1933.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1933.27,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And initially I have another, like five minutes or so.","index":404,"end_time":1936.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1933.91,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"If you have other questions that, like, I can answer if mids needed, then we can, you know, we can just send them.","index":405,"end_time":1940.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1936.47,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You can send them through email and then we''ll try to get them answered.","index":406,"end_time":1943.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1940.95,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But I think we still have some more.","index":407,"end_time":1945.83,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1943.11,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Gabe, if.","index":408,"end_time":1946.47,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1945.83,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"I think Christina can, can answer.","index":409,"end_time":1948.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1946.87,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"If you can give us the five minutes.","index":410,"end_time":1949.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1948.51,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Yeah, no problem.","index":411,"end_time":1951.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1950.31,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"This is good.","index":412,"end_time":1951.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1951.31,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right, I will see you guys.","index":413,"end_time":1953.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1951.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"}],"dateString":"2026-01-05T18:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/81691347767?pwd=ZRzKZk4Rc2WjKaDAPIqRE5enPc8KD9.1","participants":["guille.santana@marketersindemand.com,tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com,gabriel.bencosme@poncebank.net,christina.zanca@poncebank.net,ashlie.taska@poncebank.net,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,betty.campiz@poncebank.net,victor.garcia@poncebank.net","guille.santana@marketersindemand.com","tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com","gabriel.bencosme@poncebank.net","christina.zanca@poncebank.net","ashlie.taska@poncebank.net","betty.campiz@poncebank.net","victor.garcia@poncebank.net"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KDTBY36A9KAHAC25284Q3YX1","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"negative","confidence":0.91,"bullets":["Surfaced lack of clarity on phase scope, with only 19 business days until go-live.","Christina flagged urgent need to avoid rework by locking naming conventions early.","Ashley raised concern timeline is unfeasible given complexity and undefined workflows.","Planned phased breakdown of fields and sync cadence to clarify implementation work.","Blocked decision-making tied to unclear priorities and need for cross-team resourcing."],"highlights":[{"quote":"19 days is not enough for everything that we''re hearing in these meetings.","speaker":"Ashlie Taska"},{"quote":"Somebody has to tell us where to prioritize... or we have to push our deadline.","speaker":"christinazanca"},{"quote":"We also don''t have... what is the baseline configuration?","speaker":"gabrielbencosme"}],"topics":["delivery","scope","risk","timeline"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-05T22:13:03Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Data Integration and Field Mapping**\n\nThe team agreed on the critical need to break down the data fields into phased priorities for a smooth HubSpot implementation.\n\n- **Colin Costigan committed to delivering a phased breakdown of the Encompass field mappings and HubSpot properties within one week** to clarify scope and priorities (32:13)  \n    - This phased approach will categorize fields into A, B, and C priority levels, helping to define what must be ready by day one and what can come later  \n    - Christina Zanca emphasized that finalizing field naming conventions early is important to avoid costly reprogramming later  \n    - The phased list will also include preferred sync frequencies to balance real-time needs with system capacity  \n    - The goal is to align marketing and technical teams on what data flows are essential for each phase to prevent scope creep and delays\n\n- **Gabriel Bencosme highlighted the importance of modular, incremental system design** where data flows are built piece by piece rather than one large chunk to ease management and future changes (13:14)  \n    - He clarified that HubSpot can handle complex data but starting with core processes and expanding later reduces risk  \n    - Gabriel underscored that the flow begins on the website, moves through HubSpot, and then passes leads to Salesforce when criteria are met  \n    - This staged flow supports marketing automation without overwhelming sales teams prematurely  \n    - He noted Encompass currently supports only one-way data sync into Salesforce, limiting direct updates back to Encompass\n\n## **Project Scope and Timeline Alignment**\n\nThe team identified the lack of clarity on project phases and scope as a key risk to meeting the tight **19-business-day timeline**.\n\n- **Ashley Taska and Christina Zanca agreed that narrowing down the initial scope for go-live is critical to meet the deadline** without overloading technical and marketing teams (08:34, 27:16)  \n    - Ashley emphasized uncertainty about the final build complexity makes committing to the timeline risky  \n    - Christina proposed a priority-based phased rollout that includes must-have fields for day one and secondary and tertiary features post-launch  \n    - Christina pointed out the contract expiration with Webflow creates a hard launch deadline to avoid a **$100,000 renewal fee** (27:16)  \n    - They agreed ongoing communication about bandwidth and priorities with senior stakeholders Betty and Louie is essential to prevent bottlenecks\n\n- **Colin noted that sharing the detailed HubSpot implementation plan document with Ashley and Gabriel will help clarify expectations and questions** (29:40)  \n    - This document includes lead scoring, data flow logic, and property definitions to guide development  \n    - Colin urged open communication to avoid surprises and ensure alignment  \n    - Ashley requested the document to better understand the scope and prepare questions for upcoming discussions\n\n## **Real-Time Data Sync and System Capabilities**\n\nThe group addressed the challenge of balancing real-time updates with system performance limits.\n\n- **Christina expressed a strong preference for real-time or near real-time sync for critical data like account openings or closures** to enable timely marketing actions such as surveys or abandonment emails (21:51, 25:11)  \n    - Colin confirmed HubSpot and Salesforce can support variable sync frequencies, including real-time triggers or batch updates based on data type (23:17)  \n    - Gabriel described the current core system performs a full daily update (a \"blanket update\") of contact data, which could cause API bottlenecks if replicated in real time (24:30)  \n    - The team recognized the need to carefully select which data points require real-time sync versus daily batch to avoid freezing the system (24:56)  \n    - Christina suggested assigning sync frequency per data type in the A/B/C phased list to optimize performance and responsiveness\n\n- **Gabriel confirmed HubSpot supports manual triggers for marketing teams to promote leads to Salesforce when deemed hot**, aligning with Christina’s requirement to control lead flow actively (23:29)  \n    - This trigger-based sync will help avoid flooding Salesforce with unqualified leads  \n    - The approach balances automation with human oversight for lead management  \n    - Testing and configuration of these triggers will be necessary to ensure reliability\n\n## **Platform Roles and User Access**\n\nThe team clarified the distinct roles of HubSpot and Salesforce and their user bases.\n\n- **Christina confirmed HubSpot will be used exclusively by the marketing team for campaign management and customer communications, not by sales branches** (29:54)  \n    - Branches will continue using Salesforce for account opening and sales processes  \n    - HubSpot will manage marketing data, campaign research, and lead nurturing without overlapping Salesforce functionality  \n    - Only one or two HubSpot licenses remain available, minimizing the need for broad user access setup (30:14)  \n    - This separation simplifies integration and reduces complexity for data syncing and user management\n\n- **Ashley verified that HubSpot users will not update customer contact data; changes like address updates remain in Salesforce or call center systems** (30:39)  \n    - The only exception is the opt-out flag for marketing emails, which HubSpot will manage and sync back to source systems  \n    - This maintains a single source of truth for customer data and reduces data conflicts  \n    - It also ensures compliance with marketing consent regulations\n\n## **Strategic Marketing Data Usage**\n\nThe team framed the broader business rationale behind the data integration and campaign management strategy.\n\n- **Christina emphasized the goal is to build a marketing system that enables campaign measurement, customer segmentation, and targeted communications based on integrated data** (10:57)  \n    - The system will allow marketers to analyze customer behaviors, like website engagement, to tailor campaigns more effectively  \n    - Integrating loan and account data supports understanding product utilization and campaign ROI  \n    - This data-driven approach aims to improve marketing investment efficiency and customer experience  \n    - The marketing team needs a reliable source of truth combining Encompass, Salesforce, and HubSpot data for analysis\n\n- **Christina outlined three main data flows to support marketing goals: customer communications, research insights, and lead management** (14:40)  \n    - Customer communications will rely on basic contact and product data in HubSpot for email and survey automation  \n    - Research will use additional data points to build behavioral profiles and optimize campaigns  \n    - Lead management will gate leads through HubSpot before passing qualified ones to Salesforce for sales follow-up  \n    - This segmentation supports focused workflows and clearer responsibility separation across teams\n\n- **The marketing team’s ability to act rapidly on fresh data was highlighted as a key competitive advantage**, given modern customers expect immediate, relevant engagement (21:51)  \n    - Delays in data sync risk missed opportunities and reduced customer satisfaction  \n    - Real-time triggers and automated workflows will help keep marketing timely and personalized  \n    - The system design must balance performance constraints with these business needs\n\n","outline":null,"keywords":["HubSpot integration","Salesforce sync","Encompass API","lead management","marketing automation","phased implementation"],"overview":"- **Data Integration Phased Approach:** Breakdown of Encompass field mappings into A, B, and C priorities for HubSpot implementation is essential.\n\n- **Project Timeline Risks:** Narrow initial scope for go-live is crucial to meet the tight 19-business-day timeline without overloading teams.\n\n- **Real-Time Data Sync Needs:** Emphasis on critical data sync in real-time to enhance timely marketing actions while managing system performance limits.\n\n- **Distinct Platform Roles:** HubSpot will be used solely by marketing for campaign management; Salesforce remains for sales processes.\n\n- **Strategic Data Usage:** Goal is to build a reliable marketing system for targeted communication using integrated data from Encompass, Salesforce, and HubSpot.  \n\n- **Rapid Data Actions:** Ability to act on fresh data is key for maintaining competitive edge and improving customer satisfaction.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nSend Ashley and Gabe the detailed HubSpot implementation plan document for review (29:41)\nExtract data field lists and organize into phased priority spreadsheets with preferred sync frequencies for internal and client review this week (20:57)\nRespond promptly to questions from Ashley and Gabe post-meeting to maintain transparency (32:01)\n\n**Gabriel Bencosme**\nCollaborate with Colin to define phased approach and technical feasibility based on system capabilities and integration complexities (00:00)\n\n**Ashley Taska**\nProvide feedback on phased field prioritization and proposed timelines once the plan document and spreadsheet are received (29:41)\nCoordinate internally to review project bandwidth and communicate priority adjustments needed with leadership (27:00)\n\n**Christina Zanca**\nLiaise with leadership (Betty and Louie) and marketing teams to align project priorities and escalate resourcing needs or deadline risks (27:00)\nMake note for Victor and Colin to include Encompass API in upcoming integration discussions given SBA and HR portal considerations (20:08)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"460c3c8e-1f32-4ada-97e2-c7ba99d7c6e1","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
