    2387,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85439302813?pwd=qMBHtkNo4lURIrnTCVFhLG0k15ZQca.1',
    '{"id":"01KDNFSETM7E0VBP2DNSNZRJD7","title":"Ponce Bank & MiD: Weekly Sync","summary":{"notes":"## **Branding and Design Updates**\n\nThe team decided to revert to the **old font, P22 Mackinaw, for headlines** while considering a new sub-font with full weight and style variations (09:22).\n\n- **Jane approved the new recommended sub-font visually**, pending confirmation of available weights and italics to match Proxima Nova''s flexibility (09:53).\n- **Sales sheets will switch to landscape format with a product tree** to help sales reps identify upsell opportunities and related products more easily (10:27).\n- **Trifold brochure edits are underway**, aligning with feedback and improving clarity (10:27).\n- **Homepage redesign is in progress**, integrating existing content and new material provided by Victor, aiming for a fresh user experience (10:53).\n- **Social media templates exist in Canva and are being updated with new fonts** before transferring to Jane’s account for quick, frequent brand announcement posts (11:10).\n- Christina stressed the need to differentiate between reusable templates and unique assets for various social media use cases to avoid creative constraints (12:50).\n- A meeting will be set to review brand assets with Jane’s team and coordinate template creation, involving Rebecca for workflow management (13:30).\n- **Logo issues surfaced with incorrect white knockout versions**, causing delays; Jane will locate the correct EPS file for proper conversion and use across designs (16:16).\n- The team is exploring how to better use compliance space on mailers, considering quadrant layouts and color differentiation inspired by competitors like Chase and TD for clearer communication (21:30).\n- Colin will research additional print vendors and mail houses to find a better fit for mailing requirements and HubSpot API integration for automation (23:27).\n\n## **Project Management and Meeting Structure**\n\nThe team agreed to separate meetings into two focused weekly sessions: one for **website and operational project management** and another for **creative and brand management led by Jane** (14:20).\n\n- Victor and Rebecca will coordinate scheduling and take lead on project management calls, while Christina and Jane will act as strategic partners for the website and creative sides, respectively (15:20).\n- This structure aims to avoid short, scattered discussions and improve focus, allowing 30 minutes per topic for better progress tracking (14:50).\n- Colin confirmed ongoing font updates and brand guideline revisions across all deliverables, with continued integration of social, email, and print elements into HubSpot workflows (32:00).\n\n## **Google Ads Account Recovery and Campaign Control**\n\nChristina reported being locked out of the **Google Ads account due to outdated recovery info linked to a former employee’s phone**, which escalated the lockout period from 5 to **30 days, expiring on the meeting day** (17:19).\n\n- Colin acknowledged the issue as common with multiple concurrent logins and committed to working with Google support to regain access (18:19).\n- The team requested a full audit of ad accounts to confirm ownership and access, as rogue campaigns linked to mortgage lending rates could impact spend and compliance (18:52).\n- Documentation such as tax forms may be needed for verification; Colin will coordinate with Christina and keep her updated on progress (19:30).\n\n## **Website, Data Integration, and Timeline Confidence**\n\nChristina expressed concern about the project''s timeline, noting that **they are less than four months from the January go-live date** and emphasized the need for a clear consensus on deadlines with executive stakeholders (25:31).\n\n- Colin reassured that the internal team can build HubSpot workflows quickly once data properties are ready but stressed dependency on the Ponte team for data preparation and system access (25:48).\n- A contingency plan was discussed: if key resources like Gabe or Ashley become unavailable, Colin’s team can step in, provided they receive MuleSoft and system access to avoid delays (27:29).\n- The website redesign is progressing independently of data integration, allowing a scalable launch with placeholders for data-dependent features to avoid hold-ups (29:51).\n- Christina recommended visually **color-coding the timeline by component**—website, social/digital, and data—to clarify dependencies and allow staggered go-lives that minimize financial risk (30:29).\n- Colin confirmed prior internal use of color codes and agreed to reintroduce them for clearer milestone tracking (31:45).\n\n## **Social Media Management and Platform Transition**\n\nThe team is moving to manage **social posting through HubSpot**, aiming to phase out Sprout Social by **February 1st** for streamlined operations (32:31).\n\n- Jane and Christina will manage the marketing@Ponce email login, sharing credentials with Rebecca, who will learn to operate social posting within HubSpot (33:18).\n- Jane raised concerns about shared logins tied to phone numbers and recommended separate personal sign-ons to prevent future lockouts or security issues (34:24).\n- Christina confirmed limited user licenses and that alerts will funnel to the shared marketing inbox, allowing team-wide visibility (34:40).\n- The HubSpot mobile app offers social management features, though the team needs to evaluate its capability for swift comment moderation and real-time engagement (35:41).\n- The team plans a 30-minute training session for Jane, Rebecca, and Colin to review HubSpot’s social tools and establish a clear content management and channel management strategy (36:10).\n- Duplicate posts occurred due to simultaneous Instagram live settings; a review of platform settings and posting workflows is planned to avoid future overlaps (36:45).\n- Colin rescheduled the social meeting to the following week to accommodate availability, indicating ongoing adjustment and learning as the platform is adopted (39:12).\n\n## **Upcoming Deliverables and Stakeholder Engagement**\n\n- Christina requested early visibility on website templates and sitemaps to provide timely feedback and reduce extensive redesigns later (37:30).\n- Colin is updating the sitemap to include missing pages and hidden content, aiming for a full site refresh aligned with brand updates (37:50).\n- The team will continue refining brand assets, social templates, and mailer options, prioritizing the integration of HubSpot workflows and external vendor selections (32:00, 23:27).\n- Coordination between creative, data, and digital teams will be formalized through the new meeting structure to maintain momentum and clear communication on dependencies and deadlines (14:20).","outline":null,"keywords":["Fonts","Brand Guidelines","Social Media Templates","Google Ads Recovery","Website Design","Project Timeline"],"overview":"- **Branding Changes:** Old font reinstated for headlines; new sub-font approved for visual consistency pending weight confirmation.  \n- **Sales Tools Update:** Landscape-format sales sheets will aid upselling; brochure edits underway to enhance clarity.  \n- **Google Ads Recovery:** Locked out due to outdated info; access recovery may take up to 30 days, audit requested for verification.  \n- **Project Timeline Concerns:** Less than four months until website launch; need for clear deadline agreements with stakeholders emphasized.  \n- **Social Media Management Transition:** Moving to HubSpot by February 1st; training session planned to streamline operations and strategies.  \n- **Stakeholder Communication:** Early visibility on website templates requested to avoid redesign delays; coordination to enhance deadline clarity.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nUpdate all designs and brand guidelines with P22 Mackinaw font and finalize font updates (10:27)\nTransfer updated social templates into Ponce’s Canva account and assist with video content templates (11:46)\nCoordinate with Christina and Rebecca to set up brand assets review meeting for clarity on templates vs. assets (13:26)\nInvestigate Google Ads account recovery process, liaise with Google, and request necessary business documentation from Christina as needed (17:19)\nContinue website homepage design and build emails in HubSpot; fix font and design issues and share status updates (20:36)\nResearch and recommend alternative mail providers or mail houses that accommodate compliance requirements and HubSpot API integration for mailings (23:53)\nProvide updated and color-coded project timeline distinguishing website, digital, and data components; prepare for integration meeting later (31:19)\nResend HubSpot marketing@poncebank.net user invite and assist Jane and Rebecca with access issues (38:25)\nPrepare social media management training session for Jane and Rebecca on HubSpot platform and app usage (36:25)\nReschedule social meeting due to unavailability later in the week (39:12)\n\n**Jane Trachet**\nReview and approve recommended body/sub headline fonts, ensure availability of font styles/weights/italics (09:04)\nManage marketing@poncebank.net HubSpot user account creation and share credentials/access with Rebecca (33:28)\nCollaborate with Rebecca and Colin to schedule and attend social media platform training (36:25)\nVerify the correct logos, seals, and regulatory disclaimers are applied to all digital assets (14:12)\n\n**Christina Zanca**\nCoordinate with Victor, Rebecca, and Colin on brand assets review meeting scheduling and feedback (13:26)\nProvide correct EPS logo files to replace problematic white knockout logos in design assets (16:44)\nKeep team informed on Google Ads recovery situation and provide any required verification documentation (17:24)\nFacilitate communication between teams regarding campaign status, rogue ads, and future campaign planning (19:34)\nMonitor project timelines, approve or escalate if deadlines at risk, and discuss live dates with Betty (25:31)\nProvide early feedback on website sitemap, templates, and content once visuals are shared (37:37)\nWork with Jane and Rebecca to troubleshoot HubSpot marketing email invite issues (38:40)\n\n**Victor Garcia**\nShare detailed content links for homepage design with Colin and assist in resource/project coordination (10:53)\nOversee project schedule coordination with Guille and Rebecca for meetings and workflows (15:44)\nSupport brand and creative coordination alongside Rebecca (15:44)\nCommunicate with team members on marketing email inbox and social account access as needed (33:28)\n\n**Rebecca Cruz**\nJoin brand assets review meeting to clarify template vs. asset creation (13:26)\nCoordinate social media posting workflows and platform access with Jane and Colin (33:28)\n"},"duration":39.779998779296875,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"christinazanca"},{"id":1,"name":"victor garcia"},{"id":2,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":3,"name":"christinazanca"},{"id":4,"name":"Jane"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hello, kame.","index":0,"end_time":241.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":240.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Hey.","index":1,"end_time":242.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":241.93,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":2,"end_time":242.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":242.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":3,"end_time":244.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":244.01,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":4,"end_time":245.889,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":244.37,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right.","index":5,"end_time":246.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":245.889,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Do you have a good weekend?","index":6,"end_time":268.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":268.02,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I did.","index":7,"end_time":271.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":270.9,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I did.","index":8,"end_time":272.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":271.7,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I had.","index":9,"end_time":274.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":273.78,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We have this thing called Day of the Other Reyes.","index":10,"end_time":279.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":274.74,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It''s like the last thing we do for the holidays.","index":11,"end_time":283.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":280.1,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And ate a lot of bread and hot chocolate, stuff like that.","index":12,"end_time":287.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":283.21,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That''s awesome.","index":13,"end_time":288.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":287.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it.","index":14,"end_time":308.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":288.49,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Hey, team.","index":15,"end_time":360.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":359.56,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Good morning.","index":16,"end_time":360.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":360.24,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Good morning, Victor.","index":17,"end_time":362.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":361.08,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Morning.","index":18,"end_time":363.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":363,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Let me.","index":19,"end_time":365.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":365.24,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Happy New Year to you both.","index":20,"end_time":374.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":373.4,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Happy New Year.","index":21,"end_time":376.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":375.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, Happy New Year.","index":22,"end_time":377.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":376.36,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"How was your weekend?","index":23,"end_time":381.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":380.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was good.","index":24,"end_time":383,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":382.2,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Quiet.","index":25,"end_time":383.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":383.16,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Busy.","index":26,"end_time":384.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":384.37,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Quiet and busy.","index":27,"end_time":387.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":385.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Quiet and busy.","index":28,"end_time":388.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":387.33,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Mid.","index":29,"end_time":391.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":391.57,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yo.","index":30,"end_time":392.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":391.93,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Okay, Just letting y'' all know.","index":31,"end_time":395.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":394.13,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"They''ll.","index":32,"end_time":398.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":397.73,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"They''ll be right on, but we can start.","index":33,"end_time":399.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":398.09,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Cool.","index":34,"end_time":400.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":399.81,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So what is on our agenda for today?","index":35,"end_time":414.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":411.5,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Just to update on a few of the projects that we''re working on, such as the sales sheets and brochures, the website, and then brand guidelines.","index":36,"end_time":423.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":415.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Also have a proof of the postcard to share, and then just making sure that we''re on the same page for our meeting later today.","index":37,"end_time":430.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":424.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":38,"end_time":431.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":431.42,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Perfect, Perfect, perfect.","index":39,"end_time":437.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":431.94,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Hello, everyone.","index":40,"end_time":471.68,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":470.96,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Hi, Jane.","index":41,"end_time":472.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":472,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Welcome back.","index":42,"end_time":473.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":472.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":43,"end_time":474.48,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":473.84,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":44,"end_time":476.16,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":474.72,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"All right.","index":45,"end_time":476.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":476.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":46,"end_time":478,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":477.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good, thank you.","index":47,"end_time":479.52,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":478.48,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":48,"end_time":480.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":479.84,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Hopefully some relaxation time.","index":49,"end_time":482.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":480.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I did.","index":50,"end_time":483.52,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":482.96,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Thank you so much.","index":51,"end_time":486.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":483.52,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Is there an agenda?","index":52,"end_time":487.93,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":486.89,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"I''m still backlogged in email, so.","index":53,"end_time":490.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":487.93,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":54,"end_time":491.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":490.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":55,"end_time":492.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":491.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not sure if we wanted to wait for Christina to join.","index":56,"end_time":495.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":493.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, we''re going to get started.","index":57,"end_time":496.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":495.69,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Okay.","index":58,"end_time":497.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":497.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":59,"end_time":499.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":498.57,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"All right, we''ll go ahead and share my screen.","index":60,"end_time":501.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":500.01,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"All right.","index":61,"end_time":506.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":506.25,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So, Jane, while you''re out, we delivered quite a few designs, and then we also made a comparison view of the old font versus the new font like you had asked for, which showed that to Christina, and she said, you know what?","index":62,"end_time":520.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":507.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let''s just go to the old font.","index":63,"end_time":521.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":520.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we are in the midst of updating several designs as well as the brand guidelines document to show that old font, the P22 Mackinaw.","index":64,"end_time":531.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":521.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And one thing I wanted to confirm there is for.","index":65,"end_time":534.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":532.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s like the.","index":66,"end_time":535.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":534.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The headline text for the body text.","index":67,"end_time":538.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":535.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Did you want to stick with the new one that was source Sans or go back to the Proxima Nova?","index":68,"end_time":543.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":538.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m happy to take a. I think my request was.","index":69,"end_time":547.6,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":544.96,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Let''s see it.","index":70,"end_time":548.4,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":547.6,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Let''s see your recommended sub font.","index":71,"end_time":551.12,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":548.56,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Yeah, and I can even just pull.","index":72,"end_time":553.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":552.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That up because that was just great.","index":73,"end_time":555.28,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":553.76,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"That was in our last presentation.","index":74,"end_time":557.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":556.24,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So I''ll just show the comparison.","index":75,"end_time":559.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":557.68,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"As.","index":76,"end_time":562.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":562.48,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Long as there are varieties of it.","index":77,"end_time":564.88,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":562.76,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"You know, one of the perks of the Proxima Nova is that there''s, you know, extra bold, a bold italic, and that really helps us.","index":78,"end_time":574.97,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":564.88,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"So that''s just one thing that we''d want to know for the new recommended one.","index":79,"end_time":581.69,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":576.89,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":80,"end_time":582.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":582.01,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So this was showing the difference in text, so obviously you can see with the headline.","index":81,"end_time":590.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":585.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is the old one.","index":82,"end_time":592.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":591.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":83,"end_time":593.05,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":592.41,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"And then the body text is relatively similar coming down.","index":84,"end_time":597.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":593.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s really hard to even see.","index":85,"end_time":598.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":597.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m.","index":86,"end_time":599.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":599.05,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"I think it looks totally fine.","index":87,"end_time":601.13,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":599.57,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"So I.","index":88,"end_time":602.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":601.21,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"The.","index":89,"end_time":602.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":602.41,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"So this is the new sub font.","index":90,"end_time":605.21,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":603.37,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"This is your sub font with.","index":91,"end_time":606.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":605.29,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m fine with it visually.","index":92,"end_time":608.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":606.81,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"It reads, but I would just.","index":93,"end_time":610.37,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":608.33,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"If you can just double check that it''s not one of those fonts that only has like.","index":94,"end_time":614.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":610.37,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s got a lot of variables in it.","index":95,"end_time":616.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":614.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s, you know, all of the font weights.","index":96,"end_time":619.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":616.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I think there''s even condensed and other versions of it as well.","index":97,"end_time":622.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":619.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then italic and all of that.","index":98,"end_time":623.53,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":622.33,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Yeah, as long as you confirm that.","index":99,"end_time":624.97,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":623.53,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"I think it''s visually works together.","index":100,"end_time":626.96,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":624.97,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":101,"end_time":627.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":627.04,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":102,"end_time":628.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":627.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So for that, yeah, we''re working through updates.","index":103,"end_time":632.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":629.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Christina gave us some feedback on a few sales sheets that we had designed last week.","index":104,"end_time":637.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":633.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re going to make it a landscape design and incorporate a product tree so that the sales reps can easily understand, you know, if they came in for this.","index":105,"end_time":647.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":638,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Here''s what they could upsell to or.","index":106,"end_time":649.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":647.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What they might need.","index":107,"end_time":649.96,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":649.32,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Great.","index":108,"end_time":650.32,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":649.96,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"That''s great.","index":109,"end_time":651.2,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":650.56,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":110,"end_time":652.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":651.73,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Same edits for the trifold brochure.","index":111,"end_time":655.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":653.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ve also started design on the homepage.","index":112,"end_time":659.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":656.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So taking the existing content there, as well as all the content, Victor, that you sent over in that email with many links, that was very helpful.","index":113,"end_time":665.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":659.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So thank you for sending that over.","index":114,"end_time":667.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":665.85,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Good morning, Christina.","index":115,"end_time":668.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":667.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hi.","index":116,"end_time":668.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":668.61,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"How are you guys doing?","index":117,"end_time":670.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":668.97,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right, now, Colin, one of the things that we really need yesterday is a one or two social templates to start with, because that is what we are pumping out, you know, if not daily, every other day.","index":118,"end_time":684,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":670.09,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"And it''s a quick chance for us to start both externally and internally really declaring that we''ve made a brand change.","index":119,"end_time":693,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":684,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"So if we could, you know, bump that request, that would be important.","index":120,"end_time":699.88,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":694.6,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":121,"end_time":700.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":699.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so we actually already have all those built out in Canva.","index":122,"end_time":703.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":700.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re just updating the fonts and then we can transfer them into your account.","index":123,"end_time":706.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":703.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Fabulous.","index":124,"end_time":706.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":706.53,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":125,"end_time":707.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":706.85,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Just before we transfer them, though, I want to set up just a quick.","index":126,"end_time":712.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":707.65,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Meeting to just review the brand assets.","index":127,"end_time":715.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":712.77,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Just me, you know, your team and Jane.","index":128,"end_time":719.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":715.57,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because I do have some questions and comments.","index":129,"end_time":723.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":719.01,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think it''s.","index":130,"end_time":724.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":723.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think it''s going to require us to determine what is a template versus what is an asset that we have to create from.","index":131,"end_time":735.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":726.13,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":132,"end_time":736.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":736.13,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I. I don''t want to set the stage where we get templates and stay within the confines of those templates.","index":133,"end_time":743.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":736.85,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I, I more want it to be.","index":134,"end_time":745.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":743.77,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Where like you.","index":135,"end_time":747.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":745.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Have an outline for.","index":136,"end_time":750.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":749.57,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You know, like this is kind of.","index":137,"end_time":753.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":750.93,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The lower third of a video, for example.","index":138,"end_time":755.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":753.45,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":139,"end_time":755.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":755.29,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And like we just take that image, pop it into the video.","index":140,"end_time":759.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":755.57,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":141,"end_time":759.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":759.21,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So like for social, like there might be a couple of different use cases.","index":142,"end_time":765.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":759.49,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":143,"end_time":766.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":765.64,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So more than just you upload loading.","index":144,"end_time":768.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":766.04,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The templates into canva, I think it''s like we upload, you know, the logos, the colors, some of the iconography, the, the whatchamacallit, the line drawings.","index":145,"end_time":781.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":768.12,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And we also need to gene identify some other line drawings that they need to do.","index":146,"end_time":786.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":781.48,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":147,"end_time":787.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":787.65,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because I don''t want it to be.","index":148,"end_time":788.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":787.81,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Where we always use the, the same line drawings.","index":149,"end_time":792.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":788.85,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":150,"end_time":792.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":792.29,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"In the, you know, in the, you know, in the, in the posts.","index":151,"end_time":797.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":792.49,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":152,"end_time":797.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":797.37,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then there''s a, there''s a difference between like just social posts and like social campaigns.","index":153,"end_time":806.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":799.17,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":154,"end_time":806.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":806.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I think it''s like how to.","index":155,"end_time":807.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":806.49,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"How does that blend in?","index":156,"end_time":808.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":807.73,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then Jane, it''s like.","index":157,"end_time":811.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":810.13,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"How do.","index":158,"end_time":814.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":814.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You have templates for certain things that.","index":159,"end_time":816.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":814.53,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Are going to be standard, so like.","index":160,"end_time":818.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":816.65,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Employee recognitions, branch closures, types of things are like what we can have them create image templates for and like when.","index":161,"end_time":827.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":818.33,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We need to post that and the.","index":162,"end_time":828.769,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":827.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Content''S always going to be the same, that we could use that image.","index":163,"end_time":831.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":828.769,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But for all the other social posts, I think it''s just more or less we create the, the graphics using the elements that are approved.","index":164,"end_time":839.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":831.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So maybe have Rebecca set up that meeting with, with mid and have her join because she''s going to be helping.","index":165,"end_time":848.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":839.18,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Coordinate the kind of the flow of a lot of those, those templates.","index":166,"end_time":852.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":848.5,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":167,"end_time":853.22,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":852.9,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"We also need to make sure that the appropriate and updated logos and, you know, insignias and seals and, you know, equal housing and all that is on everything.","index":168,"end_time":862.82,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":853.22,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":169,"end_time":864.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":864.03,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then I also don''t know, Colin.","index":170,"end_time":865.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":864.19,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"If it makes sense to.","index":171,"end_time":867.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":865.91,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I know we had talked about having two meetings, but now I''m just thinking like, does it make sense for like us to have like, almost like an operational like project meeting that''d be more for website, all of that.","index":172,"end_time":882.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":868.51,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then like maybe have a creative.","index":173,"end_time":884.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":882.15,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Meeting where Jane takes the lead on.","index":174,"end_time":887.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":885.07,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That meeting from a overall, like management perspective, you know what I mean?","index":175,"end_time":891.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":887.27,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, that can make sense, I think, because often we''ll hop into this and it''s like, all right, we have five minutes to talk about this specific thing and then five minutes to talk about the HubSpot project and then five minutes to talk about the website.","index":176,"end_time":903.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":892.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think having maybe 30 minutes.","index":177,"end_time":904.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":903.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Dedicated to each of those each week would be beneficial.","index":178,"end_time":906.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":904.75,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":179,"end_time":907.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":907.35,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So.","index":180,"end_time":907.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":907.75,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So like, I think then what we''ll do is I''ll obviously join both meetings.","index":181,"end_time":913.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":907.99,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":182,"end_time":913.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":913.15,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But what I would like to see is that.","index":183,"end_time":916.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":913.31,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Sorry, I think I saw that stupid line during cough.","index":184,"end_time":922.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":919.09,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''m with you.","index":185,"end_time":923.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":922.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ve had cough jobs all morning.","index":186,"end_time":924.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":923.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Victor and, and kind of Rebecca are going to take on kind of the, the, the like project management coordination of those calls and then me on the website.","index":187,"end_time":935.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":925.33,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''m going to be kind of the strategic partner.","index":188,"end_time":938.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":935.41,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Jane''s going to be that strategic partner on the creative side.","index":189,"end_time":941.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":939.09,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":190,"end_time":944.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":944.22,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So if we could start with the next meeting.","index":191,"end_time":946.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":944.62,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":192,"end_time":947.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":946.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Making those changes.","index":193,"end_time":948.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":947.14,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then you know, Guille, if you.","index":194,"end_time":951.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":948.86,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Want to just shoot Victor and Rebecca.","index":195,"end_time":954.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":951.74,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"A quick email for scheduling those, we can, you know, we can go from there.","index":196,"end_time":959.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":954.42,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":197,"end_time":960.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":960.22,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"And Jane, like I said, we''re going through and just updating the font based on the decision that Christina made last week.","index":198,"end_time":966.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":961.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we do have all of these in folder for review.","index":199,"end_time":969.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":966.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just variations of different social posts formatted for different channels as well as ad templates and things like that.","index":200,"end_time":977.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":969.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll get all of these loaded in as elements into your canva.","index":201,"end_time":980.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":977.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That way we can easily edit them as well as video.","index":202,"end_time":983.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":980.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we even have like starts of like what an intro would look like for video clips and how it would kind of fade in.","index":203,"end_time":989.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":983.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":204,"end_time":990.5,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":989.98,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Yes.","index":205,"end_time":990.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":990.5,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"And just saying it now, I think you don''t have the correct logo.","index":206,"end_time":997.65,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":991.34,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"I just want to say it sooner rather than later as you''re updating everything.","index":207,"end_time":1001.05,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":997.65,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"I think the knockout white logo is.","index":208,"end_time":1003.77,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1001.13,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"That''s what we provided them, unfortunately.","index":209,"end_time":1006.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1004.65,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like I, I had that.","index":210,"end_time":1008.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1006.93,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I ran into that issue this.","index":211,"end_time":1009.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1008.01,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"This weekend.","index":212,"end_time":1010.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1009.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"This week.","index":213,"end_time":1010.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1010.05,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I needed a logo and we couldn''t find it anywhere.","index":214,"end_time":1013.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1010.53,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"There is no logo that doesn''t have the white out.","index":215,"end_time":1016.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1013.93,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then I remembered back to my comment saying, hey, like what is what mid.","index":216,"end_time":1021.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1016.97,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Why are you doing that?","index":217,"end_time":1022.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1021.67,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That''s the logo that we gave them.","index":218,"end_time":1023.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1022.63,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So like go back to the.","index":219,"end_time":1024.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1023.87,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''ll go back and find.","index":220,"end_time":1026.19,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1025.31,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":221,"end_time":1026.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1026.19,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And see.","index":222,"end_time":1026.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1026.47,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":223,"end_time":1027.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1026.99,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And it looks like it was just wrongly converted.","index":224,"end_time":1029.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1027.35,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I.","index":225,"end_time":1029.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1029.63,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We have it.","index":226,"end_time":1030.35,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1029.87,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"I''ll find it.","index":227,"end_time":1030.83,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1030.35,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":228,"end_time":1031.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1030.83,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":229,"end_time":1031.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1031.07,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So maybe we just need to like do like another EPS file.","index":230,"end_time":1034.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1031.27,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":231,"end_time":1036.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1036.27,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, we can definitely make that change.","index":232,"end_time":1038.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1036.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Colin, quick, before I forget, I sent you an email this morning about the Google Ads account.","index":233,"end_time":1044.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1039.39,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I got it.","index":234,"end_time":1045.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1044.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":235,"end_time":1045.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1045.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I got it right on my list.","index":236,"end_time":1046.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1045.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know what happened.","index":237,"end_time":1048.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1046.99,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I surmise that I tried.","index":238,"end_time":1050.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1048.31,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So.","index":239,"end_time":1051.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1050.97,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So we were not able to access the ads account because the recovery phone.","index":240,"end_time":1057.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1051.37,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Number was from a prior employee.","index":241,"end_time":1060.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1057.01,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I went through the process to start to reset it and then Victor jumped in at the same time to try to reset it and I think.","index":242,"end_time":1069.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1060.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"They thought it was like a scam.","index":243,"end_time":1070.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1069.17,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Or something like that.","index":244,"end_time":1071.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1070.97,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So they locked out the account.","index":245,"end_time":1073.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1072.17,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Originally they told me I had a.","index":246,"end_time":1075.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1073.93,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Five day window for recovery link.","index":247,"end_time":1077.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1075.49,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Then I think then after Victor''s, Victor''s attempt, it went to 30 days.","index":248,"end_time":1082.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1078.46,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That 30 days was supposed to be today.","index":249,"end_time":1084.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1082.9,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So then I, I went back and I looked and I got that email.","index":250,"end_time":1088.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1085.58,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I don''t know if they feel like we.","index":251,"end_time":1090.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1088.7,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Our account got hacked and they''re holding it.","index":252,"end_time":1096.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1093.42,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I don''t know if you have any expertise in helping us regain access.","index":253,"end_time":1098.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1096.14,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":254,"end_time":1099.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1099.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So first off, super unfortunate, annoying situation that an employee hooked that up to.","index":255,"end_time":1105.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1099.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Their personal cell phone.","index":256,"end_time":1106.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1105.82,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Sorry you had to deal with that.","index":257,"end_time":1108.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1107.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But yes, we do help with this and even, you know, Google sometimes does blanket sweeps of things and misses.","index":258,"end_time":1116.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1108.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But yeah, it''s more than likely related to several different logins from several different points at the same time.","index":259,"end_time":1123.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1116.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll just have to work through Google support more than likely.","index":260,"end_time":1126.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1123.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Which is good to do now because I don''t think you guys are running any major campaigns right now, are you?","index":261,"end_time":1132.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1127.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, we weren''t.","index":262,"end_time":1133.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1132.6,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I mean at one point I think Victor still had access and we were.","index":263,"end_time":1139.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1133.64,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Supposed to closed off a lot of stuff.","index":264,"end_time":1142,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1139.6,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The problem is, is that there''s rogue, I''m sure rogue campaigns that Jen set up for mortgage world bankers and those would have more impact because they''re, they''re lending rate driven.","index":265,"end_time":1154,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1142,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So essentially like if you could do like a quick, just investigation of making sure that we own all of our ad accounts, get access.","index":266,"end_time":1161.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1154.32,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Obviously, you know, we''re not running or looking to run any campaigns, but that might change.","index":267,"end_time":1165.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1161.44,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I mean Betty might say, hey, run a, a CD campaign again.","index":268,"end_time":1168.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1165.28,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yep, we need to have access.","index":269,"end_time":1170.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1168.99,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So yeah, yeah, if you could, if you could just.","index":270,"end_time":1173.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1170.91,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll check into it, what''s needed.","index":271,"end_time":1174.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1173.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But, and if anything has to come through me.","index":272,"end_time":1176.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1174.75,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, if they need any verification, sometimes they''ll need some business documentation, tax forms, things like that.","index":273,"end_time":1183.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1178.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll send that over to you just up front.","index":274,"end_time":1186.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1183.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We don''t control the timeline that Google will operate on.","index":275,"end_time":1189.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1186.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can only bother them as much as we can bother them.","index":276,"end_time":1192.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1189.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":277,"end_time":1192.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1192.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But yeah, we''ll definitely take a look.","index":278,"end_time":1193.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1192.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And keep you posted.","index":279,"end_time":1194.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1193.59,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"You know, keep me posted.","index":280,"end_time":1195.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1194.31,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then, you know, if there''s anything.","index":281,"end_time":1197.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1195.63,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That you know, needs to be coordinated on our side, just keep.","index":282,"end_time":1201.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1197.63,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''m gonna tag Rebecca.","index":283,"end_time":1204.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1202.49,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That would kind of come under, I think like the creative campaign kind of perspective.","index":284,"end_time":1209.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1204.89,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I could also start the.","index":285,"end_time":1211.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1210.09,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The process in that email.","index":286,"end_time":1213.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1212.57,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I just, honestly, I didn''t know if.","index":287,"end_time":1214.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1213.73,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It was a scam, so I was like a little bit worried about it.","index":288,"end_time":1217.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1214.97,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But then, yeah, it looked like a legit email to us.","index":289,"end_time":1219.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1217.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":290,"end_time":1219.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1219.45,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Can''t really fake the domain that they sent it from.","index":291,"end_time":1223.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1221.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":292,"end_time":1224.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1223.93,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Being Google.","index":293,"end_time":1225.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1225.06,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":294,"end_time":1226.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1225.66,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":295,"end_time":1226.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1226.5,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right, well, keep me, you know.","index":296,"end_time":1228.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1226.9,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Keep me updated and we''ll go from there.","index":297,"end_time":1230.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1228.3,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''ll just.","index":298,"end_time":1231.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1230.54,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''ll let Betty know that, you know that that''s.","index":299,"end_time":1233.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1231.46,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That''s the way it is.","index":300,"end_time":1235.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1233.86,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":301,"end_time":1235.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1235.46,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Okay.","index":302,"end_time":1237.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1236.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I don''t know, Christina, if you heard me when you joined, but we are designing the homepage as well as building the emails into HubSpot.","index":303,"end_time":1244.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1237.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know you''re having trouble looking at the HTML file.","index":304,"end_time":1245.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1244.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We just move forward with building those since when we showed you the preview, you were good with those, so.","index":305,"end_time":1250.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1245.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then the other thing was work through vistaprint, so keep in mind, I''m pulling this up.","index":306,"end_time":1256.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1251.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We are obviously updating the font to the P22 instead of what it''s showing here, especially with how the ampersand looks.","index":307,"end_time":1263.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1256.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But every print provider is pretty much limiting this whole side to be dedicated to the postage, which makes this large compliance not look amazing.","index":308,"end_time":1278.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1264.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And you can see here what we need to change.","index":309,"end_time":1280.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1278.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Enjoy all the benefits title.","index":310,"end_time":1281.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1280.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we removed the checklist, Christina, based on your notes from last week.","index":311,"end_time":1285.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1282.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That they were just kind of basic.","index":312,"end_time":1287.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1285.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Anyways.","index":313,"end_time":1287.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1287.13,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Hold on one second.","index":314,"end_time":1291.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1290.17,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So like, just, just.","index":315,"end_time":1301.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1299.77,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''m just going to hold this up.","index":316,"end_time":1302.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1301.97,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like this is like a small postcard from.","index":317,"end_time":1306.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1302.93,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"From td.","index":318,"end_time":1306.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1306.01,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"This is how they did it.","index":319,"end_time":1308.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1307.46,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I mean, I get it here, but you see, like this is the block.","index":320,"end_time":1311.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1308.86,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like they.","index":321,"end_time":1312.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1311.54,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"They use this upper corner.","index":322,"end_time":1313.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1312.1,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So that kind of could be something that we.","index":323,"end_time":1315.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1313.5,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We think about.","index":324,"end_time":1317.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1316.9,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":325,"end_time":1318.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1317.94,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"If that''s a possibility where you have like the, I guess the terms.","index":326,"end_time":1325.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1319.38,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It''s like how you take advantage of that.","index":327,"end_time":1327.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1325.38,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And there was another.","index":328,"end_time":1328.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1327.22,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"There was another one that I had set aside for, but I obviously can''t find it.","index":329,"end_time":1334.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1329.14,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Hey, just pointing out the logo.","index":330,"end_time":1336.63,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1334.91,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"The white logo on this design is correct.","index":331,"end_time":1338.91,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1336.63,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"This one is correct.","index":332,"end_time":1340.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1340.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":333,"end_time":1341.47,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1341.07,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"You see how you see the entire helmet?","index":334,"end_time":1343.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1341.47,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Just something to look out for.","index":335,"end_time":1345.39,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1343.95,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":336,"end_time":1346.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1345.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s a true conversion into all white knockout.","index":337,"end_time":1349.069,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1346.43,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":338,"end_time":1350.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1349.87,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So it might be like the, like the EPS file had something.","index":339,"end_time":1353.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1350.47,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":340,"end_time":1353.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1353.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Something happened with that.","index":341,"end_time":1354.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1353.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":342,"end_time":1354.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1354.31,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Damn it.","index":343,"end_time":1356.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1355.79,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I thought I had another one from Chase.","index":344,"end_time":1358.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1356.39,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I can look.","index":345,"end_time":1359.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1358.23,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But.","index":346,"end_time":1360.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1360.73,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, we might.","index":347,"end_time":1364.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1363.53,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We might want to.","index":348,"end_time":1365.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1364.33,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We might want to just think about that.","index":349,"end_time":1367.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1365.69,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because I, I hate the disclosure like that.","index":350,"end_time":1369.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1367.21,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Another thing I''m thinking of is like, do we Add like the, the TD.","index":351,"end_time":1374.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1369.77,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Did like a color differentiator to kind of like break it up a little more.","index":352,"end_time":1378.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1374.53,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like that could be an option.","index":353,"end_time":1380.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1378.45,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And I mean, I know that they want the proof, but like, I think.","index":354,"end_time":1387.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1381.37,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It''S more in the bottom.","index":355,"end_time":1388.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1387.21,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like if you broke this up into four quadrants, the bottom right quadrant is the one where you have to stay away from.","index":356,"end_time":1395.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1388.85,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''m pretty sure then maybe that''s why you''re getting the issues with rubbing the disclosure across.","index":357,"end_time":1400.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1396.21,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So it''s like maybe if you, if you use the top right quadrant to extend that across, that could be another option.","index":358,"end_time":1407.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1400.97,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, so actually we did try a few things.","index":359,"end_time":1409.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1407.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So even like when we wanted to keep all the checklist of benefits, I even tried just having like a nice green banner across the top with the, the website and address and phone number, but it breaks off based on the placeholder they add in for the postage stamp.","index":360,"end_time":1423.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1409.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like they don''t print behind it.","index":361,"end_time":1424.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1423.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''ll just look at other vendors other than Vistaprint.","index":362,"end_time":1428.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1425.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I just wanted to go with a very reputable name.","index":363,"end_time":1430.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1428.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll look at other vendors.","index":364,"end_time":1432.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1431.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You might, you might need to look into an actual like mail house.","index":365,"end_time":1438,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1433.76,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, like not, not like a small business type of print mailhouse.","index":366,"end_time":1444,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1438.08,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like.","index":367,"end_time":1444.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1444,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":368,"end_time":1445.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1444.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Previously we were looking at like the post office senders, like Click to Mail and a few others like that.","index":369,"end_time":1450.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1445.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So yeah, we''ll look at those again.","index":370,"end_time":1453.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1450.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":371,"end_time":1456.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1456.32,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because I mean, eventually you''ll, you''ll probably want.","index":372,"end_time":1461.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1456.68,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"To give us a recommendation because.","index":373,"end_time":1465.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1463.6,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We''Re, we''re going to want to start.","index":374,"end_time":1466.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1465.28,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"To, with, with the HubSpot API, like.","index":375,"end_time":1469.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1466.56,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Plug them into the HubSpot API.","index":376,"end_time":1470.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1469.2,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So like, if you need a mailing to go out, like it''s like it.","index":377,"end_time":1472.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1470.84,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Just sentence like the files are batched, like.","index":378,"end_time":1475.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1472.92,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":379,"end_time":1475.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1475.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, so do some digging there.","index":380,"end_time":1478.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1477.12,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I mean, we may have a little bit more time than weekly.","index":381,"end_time":1482.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1478.56,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Well, we''ll prioritize that.","index":382,"end_time":1483.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1482.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I, I want to get this wrapped up.","index":383,"end_time":1484.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1483.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, no, I, I do.","index":384,"end_time":1486,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1484.96,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I do too.","index":385,"end_time":1486.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1486,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But we''re still waiting for some key decisions on some of the disclosures.","index":386,"end_time":1489.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1486.56,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And unfortunately the, the person that was.","index":387,"end_time":1492.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1489.76,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Leading that internally is no longer here now, so.","index":388,"end_time":1494.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1492.04,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":389,"end_time":1495.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1495.12,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"There''s going to be some, you know, some change management.","index":390,"end_time":1499.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1495.6,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The only other thing I''m thinking, like, you see how like Chase has like a trifold.","index":391,"end_time":1503.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1499.2,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I mean, I don''t.","index":392,"end_time":1505.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1504.56,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"This is probably not worth the trifold.","index":393,"end_time":1507.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1505.44,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And the expense there, but.","index":394,"end_time":1509.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1507.48,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, but definitely something to keep in mind.","index":395,"end_time":1511.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1509.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":396,"end_time":1512.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1512.24,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":397,"end_time":1513.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1512.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then for our meeting later today, so we got the encompass field lists received and we''ve documented that we''ve also got the sample CSV.","index":398,"end_time":1520.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1513.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It seems like Ashley and Gabe have access through the digital ponte bank.","index":399,"end_time":1525.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1520.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re reviewing the data masking requirements and then we have our meeting today to go over integration and workflows.","index":400,"end_time":1531.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1525.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":401,"end_time":1531.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1531.45,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"How are you realistically feeling about where we are with this whole project?","index":402,"end_time":1535.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1532.01,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":403,"end_time":1536.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1535.93,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because, like, I feel like we started some of the conversations in August and there was a lot of, like, background.","index":404,"end_time":1541.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1536.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Work that we did, but, like, I.","index":405,"end_time":1544.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1541.77,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Don''T know, I feel like it''s like January now.","index":406,"end_time":1546.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1544.45,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It''s like it really hit home that, like.","index":407,"end_time":1548.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1546.37,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":408,"end_time":1548.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1548.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are going live in less than four months.","index":409,"end_time":1552.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1548.57,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":410,"end_time":1553.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1553.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it was.","index":411,"end_time":1554.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1553.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was a lot of people that we were trying to coordinate schedules.","index":412,"end_time":1556.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1554.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":413,"end_time":1556.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1556.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To get on those calls.","index":414,"end_time":1557.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1556.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Ideal.","index":415,"end_time":1558.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1557.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Ideally, we would have had those before.","index":416,"end_time":1559.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1558.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we do this in a variety of ways.","index":417,"end_time":1563.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1561.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So obviously with this one, we''re reliant on Gabe and Ashley having some time, aside from their other projects, to just build things on their side.","index":418,"end_time":1573,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1563.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"From our side, we can build HubSpot very quickly.","index":419,"end_time":1575.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1573,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As far as, like, guys, we''ve shared all of this documentation.","index":420,"end_time":1578.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1575.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As long as a decision is made and a thumb is given up and that property is built on the other side, we feel very confident from our end of building the HubSpot integrations and workflows.","index":421,"end_time":1587.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1578.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":422,"end_time":1588.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1587.79,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Now, now, just hypothetically speaking, do you have the resources to support anything that''s assigned to Ponce if we need those resources for whatever reason?","index":423,"end_time":1598.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1588.19,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like, let''s just say, like, I don''t know, Gabe''s out, or, you know, a.","index":424,"end_time":1603.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1598.35,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Project, you know, comes up that we just have no control over.","index":425,"end_time":1606.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1603.95,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like, I. I guess I just.","index":426,"end_time":1608.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1606.95,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"At this point, I want to build a.","index":427,"end_time":1610.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1608.83,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"A contingency plan.","index":428,"end_time":1612.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1610.83,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, right.","index":429,"end_time":1613.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1612.59,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because I feel like every time I approach the.","index":430,"end_time":1618.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1613.51,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The, you know, the teams I hear, I get, you know, the why.","index":431,"end_time":1625.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1618.52,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like, I might have a roadblocker before.","index":432,"end_time":1628.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1625.88,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It''s just like, I could help you, and that''s fine.","index":433,"end_time":1633.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1629.48,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Everybody just is overwhelmed and all of that kind of stuff.","index":434,"end_time":1636.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1633.64,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But it doesn''t just give me a good, like, warm and fuzzy feeling that, like, this is going to go off without, you know, any issues.","index":435,"end_time":1642.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1636.6,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And I.","index":436,"end_time":1642.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1642.01,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The worst thing that I want to.","index":437,"end_time":1643.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1642.53,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Do is have to go to accounting and be like, we need to extend.","index":438,"end_time":1647.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1643.77,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Our contracts on certain things because we''re not ready.","index":439,"end_time":1649.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1647.05,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, I totally hear you.","index":440,"end_time":1650.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1649.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":441,"end_time":1651.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1650.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Capability wise, totally comfortable hopping into any system.","index":442,"end_time":1653.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1651.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It would just be relying on your end of, as far as, like, approving us to be in the system to make changes.","index":443,"end_time":1659.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1654.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":444,"end_time":1660.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1659.89,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so, like, you would need MuleSoft access then, like.","index":445,"end_time":1663.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1660.41,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, like if that''s the issue, like if Gabe and Ashley are unavailable, you know, to hit the timeline that we''ve laid out and even that we''ve adjusted since they came back with some feedback of it being too tight.","index":446,"end_time":1673.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1663.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, if they''re not comfortable with it, we are more than willing to hop in.","index":447,"end_time":1676.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1673.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s just getting access to the system.","index":448,"end_time":1678.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1676.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":449,"end_time":1679.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1678.99,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so like I guess what I want to see on this next meeting.","index":450,"end_time":1683.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1679.47,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And if it can happen for what, what today?","index":451,"end_time":1685.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1684.11,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We have the meeting or we have it today.","index":452,"end_time":1687.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1685.75,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yep.","index":453,"end_time":1688.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1687.51,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So I know I asked for the.","index":454,"end_time":1691.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1688.83,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Timeline and you guys gave it to me.","index":455,"end_time":1693.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1691.75,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Unfortunately, like I. I didn''t realize the first due date was going to be like the the second or the whatever the very early part of January because like realistically who''s.","index":456,"end_time":1701.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1693.47,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"There''s not a lot going on, you know, wise during the holidays because of pto.","index":457,"end_time":1704.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1701.26,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"What I think we need to come up to consensus.","index":458,"end_time":1707.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1705.26,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like it''s like I need to have the conversation with Betty.","index":459,"end_time":1710.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1707.26,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like this is a timeline that needs us to agree on now in order for us to make even 30th deadline.","index":460,"end_time":1717.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1710.46,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":461,"end_time":1718.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1717.82,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like, yep.","index":462,"end_time":1718.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1718.18,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And if it can''t be met, like then we need to figure that out.","index":463,"end_time":1722.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1719.02,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":464,"end_time":1722.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1722.22,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so yeah, so we''re feeling completely confident on our side in building everything that we have agreed to.","index":465,"end_time":1728.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1722.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s really just we''re contingent, we''re reliant on the PONTE team building this things on their side.","index":466,"end_time":1736.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1728.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right, right.","index":467,"end_time":1737.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1736.67,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And hypothetically speaking, a lot of the website development can move forward without necessarily the data component.","index":468,"end_time":1746.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1737.23,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So in my mind, as long as the data is in ready, tested and prepped before we launch, I think that we should be fine.","index":469,"end_time":1754.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1746.07,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But I guess at some point we.","index":470,"end_time":1756.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1754.87,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Need to because I know the timelines were converging, but we need to kind.","index":471,"end_time":1759.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1756.91,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Of say like what are the tasks assigned to the GPS data team or on ponset would impact our website go live like and.","index":472,"end_time":1770.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1759.55,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Or can we go live at some point with the website without data in the system understanding that it''s going to trip up with some of our metrics.","index":473,"end_time":1778.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1770.39,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like we''re not going to be able to do emails.","index":474,"end_time":1780.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1778.63,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But the website is kind of the thing that if we need to delay.","index":475,"end_time":1784.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1780.71,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Would have financial impact for us because.","index":476,"end_time":1786.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1784.91,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Of the webflow and all the other contracts.","index":477,"end_time":1790.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1786.95,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, I totally hear you.","index":478,"end_time":1791.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1790.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So monitor that for me, you know, over time.","index":479,"end_time":1794.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1791.67,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":480,"end_time":1794.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1794.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we kind of saw the writing on the wall a little bit over the last few weeks and Da and I and Tristan talked and we just started moving ahead with writing and designing the website.","index":481,"end_time":1801.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1794.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that that''s not a holdup in any case.","index":482,"end_time":1803.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1801.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And our mindset is just basically having a placeholder for any data impact on the page itself.","index":483,"end_time":1809.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1804.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And the way that we''re doing that is so, you know, if anything happens, God forbid it does.","index":484,"end_time":1816.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1810.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But if anything happens with the holdup on data, we would still hypothetically be able to go live with a completely refreshed website.","index":485,"end_time":1822.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1816.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"New content, new user flow and then we just like a website is, it''s organic.","index":486,"end_time":1827.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1822.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":487,"end_time":1827.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1827.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You continue to make updates and improve it.","index":488,"end_time":1829.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1827.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":489,"end_time":1829.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1829.47,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay.","index":490,"end_time":1830.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1830.56,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":491,"end_time":1831.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1830.88,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And I, I think that, you know, now what we can do is we can start to almost think about like the.","index":492,"end_time":1839.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1831.2,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"There''s three components.","index":493,"end_time":1843.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1842.08,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"There''s the data, there''s the digital, so social, email, and then there''s the website.","index":494,"end_time":1847.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1843.28,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"They''re all converging at the same time.","index":495,"end_time":1850.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1848.16,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But like would maybe have different go live dates because, for example, for email you''re going to need to have the IT teams and the data teams work together to whitelist our new, you know, or transfer the domains and emails and all that kind of stuff.","index":496,"end_time":1864.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1850.16,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And we''re going to need to have data in the system to send emails.","index":497,"end_time":1867.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1865.21,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But as long as I''m hearing like, and I''m feeling better now that like the website, even if it has to be scalable for launch, we can launch something.","index":498,"end_time":1879.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1868.81,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":499,"end_time":1880.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1879.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That makes me feel, you know, better.","index":500,"end_time":1882.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1880.45,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So maybe in the timeline we can start to color code these three different components.","index":501,"end_time":1888.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1884.36,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So like, website could be green, I.","index":502,"end_time":1890.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1888.68,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Don''T know, like whatever colors you choose.","index":503,"end_time":1892.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1890.4,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But, but try to kind of build out the timeline where they''re dependent on each other.","index":504,"end_time":1896.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1892.68,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So we, we push the needle forward.","index":505,"end_time":1899.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1896.92,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But like realistically, like in the background.","index":506,"end_time":1900.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1899.04,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We know that they''re not codependent.","index":507,"end_time":1904.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1900.92,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, I got you.","index":508,"end_time":1906.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1905,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we actually, it''s funny, we actually had it color coded when we were meeting internally, but I always remove those because colors can get ambiguous.","index":509,"end_time":1914.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1906.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll add those back.","index":510,"end_time":1915.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1914.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It seems like we''re on the right.","index":511,"end_time":1916.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1915.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":512,"end_time":1918.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1917.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For my own, you know, sake.","index":513,"end_time":1921.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1919.1,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":514,"end_time":1923.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1922.38,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":515,"end_time":1924.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1924.14,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Okay, so we''ll get all of the designs updated with the fonts and the brand guideline documents and everything.","index":516,"end_time":1930.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1925.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re building out the emails in HubSpot for those designs.","index":517,"end_time":1933.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1930.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Social is all connected in HubSpot.","index":518,"end_time":1934.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1933.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The GPS team has access to, well, work through some other vendors for the, the mailer just to see really how we can best use that compliance real estate.","index":519,"end_time":1945.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1934.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And, and then we''ll get the timelines updated like we talked about for our meeting later.","index":520,"end_time":1951.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1946.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, and, and one thing.","index":521,"end_time":1953.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1951.82,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So you said social is all connected.","index":522,"end_time":1955.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1953.98,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So the channels are connected.","index":523,"end_time":1957.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1955.66,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Is the.","index":524,"end_time":1957.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1957.34,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So we have the ability to manage the posts and all that through the HubSpot system.","index":525,"end_time":1963.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1959.02,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay so, so if you guys don''t don''t mind, can we set up just a quick overview of just like that.","index":526,"end_time":1971.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1963.58,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Platform, the social component and Jane, me.","index":527,"end_time":1976.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1971.11,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You and Rebecca would need you know.","index":528,"end_time":1980.549,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1976.23,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Social posting access but I think we need to post it.","index":529,"end_time":1984.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1980.549,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We need to kind of almost join under a shared user username.","index":530,"end_time":1990.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1985.71,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think right now it''s.","index":531,"end_time":1990.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1990.19,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We have the same one like marketing at whatever but I think it''s only one person can be logged in at the same time so.","index":532,"end_time":1998.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1990.99,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So we don''t have a marketing at user.","index":533,"end_time":2000.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1998.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The only users currently are.","index":534,"end_time":2002.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2000.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh actually you are correct.","index":535,"end_time":2008.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2007.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You do have a marketing yet.","index":536,"end_time":2009.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2008.5,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah and I, I have to.","index":537,"end_time":2010.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2009.74,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It looks like the invite''s pending.","index":538,"end_time":2012.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2010.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh I accepted mine.","index":539,"end_time":2014.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2012.94,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Oh you accepted yours?","index":540,"end_time":2015.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2014.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We didn''t accept.","index":541,"end_time":2015.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2015.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, I, I have another invite from.","index":542,"end_time":2018.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2016.06,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay, so then Jane, then I need you to be the manager of the marketing at Ponce Inbox and share that with Rebecca.","index":543,"end_time":2030.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2019.18,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So if you can resend the marketing one out.","index":544,"end_time":2035.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2031.17,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So Jane, when you see it, pick.","index":545,"end_time":2037.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2035.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It up, log in, create, create a.","index":546,"end_time":2040.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2037.41,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Password or whatever you have to create.","index":547,"end_time":2042.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2040.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then you will have to share that from a social perspective.","index":548,"end_time":2048.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2042.45,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So it''s like you could get in there if you needed to like review things, download data, approve post.","index":549,"end_time":2054.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2048.65,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Rebecca''s going to have to then learn.","index":550,"end_time":2055.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2054.51,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"How to post within there.","index":551,"end_time":2057.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2055.91,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So is there any training modules that are available in.","index":552,"end_time":2062.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2057.79,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"There are and I have a couple.","index":553,"end_time":2064.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2062.99,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Of questions and maybe you know the training will unveil them but one, is this associated with the phone number because that may lead like is there single sign on issues and stuff where perhaps Rebecca and I should each have our own sign on associated with their personal emails if it is attached to a phone number.","index":554,"end_time":2081.63,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2064.55,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"So we don''t get one of these messages again?","index":555,"end_time":2083.31,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2081.63,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"No, no, I think we did that.","index":556,"end_time":2086.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2083.93,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"With the GPS Team 1 we only have a certain number of licenses so like we said we can''t have the that and with the GPS team originally it was going to Ashley.","index":557,"end_time":2096.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2086.09,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I flagged to her that like updates.","index":558,"end_time":2100.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2096.89,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Or emails for like alerts and approvals and things like that will go to just that one email.","index":559,"end_time":2104.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2100.33,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So like I feel comfortable with having.","index":560,"end_time":2106.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2104.29,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It go to marketing because although you''ll.","index":561,"end_time":2108.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2106.29,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Manage the through that email all of the team will get those alerts.","index":562,"end_time":2112.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2108.41,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":563,"end_time":2113.38,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2112.82,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Okay, so if, if we need to.","index":564,"end_time":2115.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2113.62,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Make changes at some point in time like maybe Victor and I could, could share one or maybe I don''t need one.","index":565,"end_time":2121.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2115.18,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Maybe I''LL go manage it under the marketing.","index":566,"end_time":2124.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2122.02,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right now I''m, I''m keeping it there because I think my profile and then.","index":567,"end_time":2127.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2124.06,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"My one other question is, is there an app that goes along with the HubSpot for social management?","index":568,"end_time":2133.7,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2127.82,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"I know it''s been helpful in the past, like for those, you know, middle of the night awkward comments that need to be removed or responded to.","index":569,"end_time":2141.8,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2133.86,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Yeah, I know HubSpot does have a mobile app.","index":570,"end_time":2144.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2141.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m not sure about how strong the.","index":571,"end_time":2146.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2144.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Social feature is on it.","index":572,"end_time":2147.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2146.08,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Okay, let''s talk, Jane, because I think.","index":573,"end_time":2150.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2147.64,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We''Re going to have to reimagine the strategy and approach and do things both from like a content management within HubSpot.","index":574,"end_time":2161.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2151.56,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then like channel management within the channel specifically.","index":575,"end_time":2167.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2162.15,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So it''s like, like on our phones all like the Facebook meta manager.","index":576,"end_time":2172.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2167.87,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":577,"end_time":2172.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2172.19,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so yeah, it was more for listening and stuff.","index":578,"end_time":2174.47,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2172.39,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"But maybe the tutorial and you know, we.","index":579,"end_time":2177.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2174.47,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Let''s set up a meeting.","index":580,"end_time":2178.15,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2177.11,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"This is definitely worth 30 minutes, I think, Colin, for you, me and Rebecca to go through, you know.","index":581,"end_time":2184.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2178.15,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":582,"end_time":2186.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2185.99,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because I would, I would want, I would say we should start to try to use this by like at least February 1st and start to phase out, you know, sprout.","index":583,"end_time":2196.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2186.71,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And that also has to.","index":584,"end_time":2197.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2196.06,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We also have to figure out like we can''t be doing things in two places.","index":585,"end_time":2201.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2197.38,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I will tell you that I flagged to Rebecca.","index":586,"end_time":2204.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2201.14,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"There was three posts that double posted.","index":587,"end_time":2207.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2204.86,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We talked about it this morning.","index":588,"end_time":2208.38,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2207.26,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Yes.","index":589,"end_time":2208.66,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2208.38,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":590,"end_time":2208.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2208.66,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I don''t know if.","index":591,"end_time":2209.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2208.98,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"If it was because.","index":592,"end_time":2211.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2209.74,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":593,"end_time":2212.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2212.14,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Is it set to have the Instagram go live with.","index":594,"end_time":2216.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2212.7,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I believe it was set that way, but it shouldn''t be because we tailored the captions differently.","index":595,"end_time":2220.75,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2216.19,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":596,"end_time":2221.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2221.07,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So we just have to talk about, about that.","index":597,"end_time":2223.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2221.43,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":598,"end_time":2226.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2224.75,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think we''re, I think we''re good.","index":599,"end_time":2228.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2227.23,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You know, I think we''re getting a.","index":600,"end_time":2232.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2229.07,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Lot of, a lot of things done.","index":601,"end_time":2234.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2232.95,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"There''s going to be a point in.","index":602,"end_time":2235.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2234.47,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Time where I want now maybe Betty.","index":603,"end_time":2238.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2235.71,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Start to weigh in on some of the visuals.","index":604,"end_time":2240.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2238.63,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I would love to start to see anything that you have built out template, even if it''s a template wise for the website.","index":605,"end_time":2247.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2240.79,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Just so I can see structurally like where we are.","index":606,"end_time":2250.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2247.28,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think I''m just.","index":607,"end_time":2252.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2250.72,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think I reviewed a sitemap or a source.","index":608,"end_time":2255.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2253.28,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I don''t know at this point, like I think my brain is just fried.","index":609,"end_time":2257.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2255.28,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, you did.","index":610,"end_time":2258.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2257.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then, and then there was conversations of just other things that had been brought up by other team members.","index":611,"end_time":2262.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2258.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s when Victor sent over the laundry list of like various pages because in our research they weren''t actually connected to the Ponte website, so we''re updating the sitemap with those as well.","index":612,"end_time":2273.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2262.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, there''s some things that are hidden.","index":613,"end_time":2275.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2273.59,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"There''s some things that are, like.","index":614,"end_time":2277.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2275.83,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It''s still in our content management system as, like, pages that are not live, but they''re eventually going to be live.","index":615,"end_time":2283.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2277.43,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So when you''re ready to.","index":616,"end_time":2285.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2283.75,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"To share that, you know, let me.","index":617,"end_time":2287.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2285.35,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Let me know, because I definitely want to weigh in a little earlier so.","index":618,"end_time":2291.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2287.51,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You don''t have to do extensive changes.","index":619,"end_time":2293.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2291.71,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":620,"end_time":2294.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2293.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''s why we''re starting with the home page, so that we get all the design sense there, and then that way, you know, we.","index":621,"end_time":2298.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2294.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can march forward.","index":622,"end_time":2300.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2298.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I did send the.","index":623,"end_time":2301.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2300.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I resent the invite for marketing at Ponte to HubSpot.","index":624,"end_time":2304.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2301.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":625,"end_time":2306.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2305.93,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Let me just see if I got it in my inbox, because then if I did, then.","index":626,"end_time":2313.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2307.45,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"See, I don''t know that.","index":627,"end_time":2318.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2317.29,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":628,"end_time":2319.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2318.41,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I don''t.","index":629,"end_time":2319.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2319.01,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I didn''t get it.","index":630,"end_time":2320.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2319.45,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I don''t know if it.","index":631,"end_time":2320.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2320.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And if it doesn''t, here''s a link that someone can click if they''re signed.","index":632,"end_time":2324.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2320.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Into that as well, to accept.","index":633,"end_time":2325.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2324.61,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"All right, Jane, so why don''t you see if you can click in that link and work with Rebecca for.","index":634,"end_time":2331.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2327.14,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"For that.","index":635,"end_time":2332.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2331.9,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''m not getting anything to the marketing email box, but it might be that it''s going to spam the link that he just sent in the chat while you''re on mute.","index":636,"end_time":2342.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2332.38,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I don''t have anything yet, but sometimes it takes a little while.","index":637,"end_time":2346.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2343.86,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"Yeah, And I mean, he put it in the chat, too.","index":638,"end_time":2348.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2346.58,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So just before we log off, just grab that link and.","index":639,"end_time":2351.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2348.5,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay.","index":640,"end_time":2352.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2351.86,"speaker_name":"Jane"},{"text":"And then as far as scheduling a third meeting this week, could we possibly push the social meeting next week?","index":641,"end_time":2358.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2352.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m out Thursday, Friday for off for an on site.","index":642,"end_time":2361.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2358.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, no, that.","index":643,"end_time":2362.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2361.2,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That.","index":644,"end_time":2362.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2362.48,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That''s fine.","index":645,"end_time":2363.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2362.72,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"They''re gonna have to just play around with it a little bit, too, before, you know, before we get that, but.","index":646,"end_time":2368.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2363.76,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Cool.","index":647,"end_time":2370.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2370.08,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right, so this is.","index":648,"end_time":2371.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2370.64,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"This is gonna be.","index":649,"end_time":2372.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2371.72,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"This is gonna be good.","index":650,"end_time":2373.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2372.68,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":651,"end_time":2374.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2374,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":652,"end_time":2374.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2374.44,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"All righty.","index":653,"end_time":2375.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2374.88,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":654,"end_time":2376.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2375.68,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":655,"end_time":2376.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2376.16,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Good to see you guys again.","index":656,"end_time":2377.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2376.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we''ll see you in a few hours.","index":657,"end_time":2378.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2377.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, awesome.","index":658,"end_time":2379.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2378.56,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":659,"end_time":2379.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2379.2,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"}],"dateString":"2026-01-05T16:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85439302813?pwd=qMBHtkNo4lURIrnTCVFhLG0k15ZQca.1","participants":["tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com,jane.trachet@poncebank.net,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,victor.garcia@poncebank.net,rebecca.cruz@poncebank.net,guille.santana@marketersindemand.com,christina.zanca@poncebank.net","tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com","jane.trachet@poncebank.net","victor.garcia@poncebank.net","rebecca.cruz@poncebank.net","guille.santana@marketersindemand.com","christina.zanca@poncebank.net"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KDNFSETM7E0VBP2DNSNZRJD7","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Confirmed switch back to old font and approved new body font with needed weights.","Jane requested social templates prioritized; Colin confirmed assets are update-ready in Canva.","Christina proposed splitting meetings into creative and project tracks for better focus.","Access to Google Ads account is being recovered due to prior ownership and verification issues.","Contingency plan and timeline ownership discussed to mitigate reliance on third-party resources."],"highlights":[{"quote":"We also need to make sure that the appropriate and updated logos and... is on everything.","speaker":"Jane"},{"quote":"I want to build a contingency plan... I want to make sure this is going to go off without issues.","speaker":"christinazanca"},{"quote":"We would still hypothetically be able to go live with a completely refreshed website.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"}],"topics":["branding","delivery","launch","access","templates","social"],"model":"gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-05T18:29:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Branding and Design Updates**\n\nThe team decided to revert to the **old font, P22 Mackinaw, for headlines** while considering a new sub-font with full weight and style variations (09:22).\n\n- **Jane approved the new recommended sub-font visually**, pending confirmation of available weights and italics to match Proxima Nova''s flexibility (09:53).\n- **Sales sheets will switch to landscape format with a product tree** to help sales reps identify upsell opportunities and related products more easily (10:27).\n- **Trifold brochure edits are underway**, aligning with feedback and improving clarity (10:27).\n- **Homepage redesign is in progress**, integrating existing content and new material provided by Victor, aiming for a fresh user experience (10:53).\n- **Social media templates exist in Canva and are being updated with new fonts** before transferring to Jane’s account for quick, frequent brand announcement posts (11:10).\n- Christina stressed the need to differentiate between reusable templates and unique assets for various social media use cases to avoid creative constraints (12:50).\n- A meeting will be set to review brand assets with Jane’s team and coordinate template creation, involving Rebecca for workflow management (13:30).\n- **Logo issues surfaced with incorrect white knockout versions**, causing delays; Jane will locate the correct EPS file for proper conversion and use across designs (16:16).\n- The team is exploring how to better use compliance space on mailers, considering quadrant layouts and color differentiation inspired by competitors like Chase and TD for clearer communication (21:30).\n- Colin will research additional print vendors and mail houses to find a better fit for mailing requirements and HubSpot API integration for automation (23:27).\n\n## **Project Management and Meeting Structure**\n\nThe team agreed to separate meetings into two focused weekly sessions: one for **website and operational project management** and another for **creative and brand management led by Jane** (14:20).\n\n- Victor and Rebecca will coordinate scheduling and take lead on project management calls, while Christina and Jane will act as strategic partners for the website and creative sides, respectively (15:20).\n- This structure aims to avoid short, scattered discussions and improve focus, allowing 30 minutes per topic for better progress tracking (14:50).\n- Colin confirmed ongoing font updates and brand guideline revisions across all deliverables, with continued integration of social, email, and print elements into HubSpot workflows (32:00).\n\n## **Google Ads Account Recovery and Campaign Control**\n\nChristina reported being locked out of the **Google Ads account due to outdated recovery info linked to a former employee’s phone**, which escalated the lockout period from 5 to **30 days, expiring on the meeting day** (17:19).\n\n- Colin acknowledged the issue as common with multiple concurrent logins and committed to working with Google support to regain access (18:19).\n- The team requested a full audit of ad accounts to confirm ownership and access, as rogue campaigns linked to mortgage lending rates could impact spend and compliance (18:52).\n- Documentation such as tax forms may be needed for verification; Colin will coordinate with Christina and keep her updated on progress (19:30).\n\n## **Website, Data Integration, and Timeline Confidence**\n\nChristina expressed concern about the project''s timeline, noting that **they are less than four months from the January go-live date** and emphasized the need for a clear consensus on deadlines with executive stakeholders (25:31).\n\n- Colin reassured that the internal team can build HubSpot workflows quickly once data properties are ready but stressed dependency on the Ponte team for data preparation and system access (25:48).\n- A contingency plan was discussed: if key resources like Gabe or Ashley become unavailable, Colin’s team can step in, provided they receive MuleSoft and system access to avoid delays (27:29).\n- The website redesign is progressing independently of data integration, allowing a scalable launch with placeholders for data-dependent features to avoid hold-ups (29:51).\n- Christina recommended visually **color-coding the timeline by component**—website, social/digital, and data—to clarify dependencies and allow staggered go-lives that minimize financial risk (30:29).\n- Colin confirmed prior internal use of color codes and agreed to reintroduce them for clearer milestone tracking (31:45).\n\n## **Social Media Management and Platform Transition**\n\nThe team is moving to manage **social posting through HubSpot**, aiming to phase out Sprout Social by **February 1st** for streamlined operations (32:31).\n\n- Jane and Christina will manage the marketing@Ponce email login, sharing credentials with Rebecca, who will learn to operate social posting within HubSpot (33:18).\n- Jane raised concerns about shared logins tied to phone numbers and recommended separate personal sign-ons to prevent future lockouts or security issues (34:24).\n- Christina confirmed limited user licenses and that alerts will funnel to the shared marketing inbox, allowing team-wide visibility (34:40).\n- The HubSpot mobile app offers social management features, though the team needs to evaluate its capability for swift comment moderation and real-time engagement (35:41).\n- The team plans a 30-minute training session for Jane, Rebecca, and Colin to review HubSpot’s social tools and establish a clear content management and channel management strategy (36:10).\n- Duplicate posts occurred due to simultaneous Instagram live settings; a review of platform settings and posting workflows is planned to avoid future overlaps (36:45).\n- Colin rescheduled the social meeting to the following week to accommodate availability, indicating ongoing adjustment and learning as the platform is adopted (39:12).\n\n## **Upcoming Deliverables and Stakeholder Engagement**\n\n- Christina requested early visibility on website templates and sitemaps to provide timely feedback and reduce extensive redesigns later (37:30).\n- Colin is updating the sitemap to include missing pages and hidden content, aiming for a full site refresh aligned with brand updates (37:50).\n- The team will continue refining brand assets, social templates, and mailer options, prioritizing the integration of HubSpot workflows and external vendor selections (32:00, 23:27).\n- Coordination between creative, data, and digital teams will be formalized through the new meeting structure to maintain momentum and clear communication on dependencies and deadlines (14:20).","outline":null,"keywords":["Fonts","Brand Guidelines","Social Media Templates","Google Ads Recovery","Website Design","Project Timeline"],"overview":"- **Branding Changes:** Old font reinstated for headlines; new sub-font approved for visual consistency pending weight confirmation.  \n- **Sales Tools Update:** Landscape-format sales sheets will aid upselling; brochure edits underway to enhance clarity.  \n- **Google Ads Recovery:** Locked out due to outdated info; access recovery may take up to 30 days, audit requested for verification.  \n- **Project Timeline Concerns:** Less than four months until website launch; need for clear deadline agreements with stakeholders emphasized.  \n- **Social Media Management Transition:** Moving to HubSpot by February 1st; training session planned to streamline operations and strategies.  \n- **Stakeholder Communication:** Early visibility on website templates requested to avoid redesign delays; coordination to enhance deadline clarity.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nUpdate all designs and brand guidelines with P22 Mackinaw font and finalize font updates (10:27)\nTransfer updated social templates into Ponce’s Canva account and assist with video content templates (11:46)\nCoordinate with Christina and Rebecca to set up brand assets review meeting for clarity on templates vs. assets (13:26)\nInvestigate Google Ads account recovery process, liaise with Google, and request necessary business documentation from Christina as needed (17:19)\nContinue website homepage design and build emails in HubSpot; fix font and design issues and share status updates (20:36)\nResearch and recommend alternative mail providers or mail houses that accommodate compliance requirements and HubSpot API integration for mailings (23:53)\nProvide updated and color-coded project timeline distinguishing website, digital, and data components; prepare for integration meeting later (31:19)\nResend HubSpot marketing@poncebank.net user invite and assist Jane and Rebecca with access issues (38:25)\nPrepare social media management training session for Jane and Rebecca on HubSpot platform and app usage (36:25)\nReschedule social meeting due to unavailability later in the week (39:12)\n\n**Jane Trachet**\nReview and approve recommended body/sub headline fonts, ensure availability of font styles/weights/italics (09:04)\nManage marketing@poncebank.net HubSpot user account creation and share credentials/access with Rebecca (33:28)\nCollaborate with Rebecca and Colin to schedule and attend social media platform training (36:25)\nVerify the correct logos, seals, and regulatory disclaimers are applied to all digital assets (14:12)\n\n**Christina Zanca**\nCoordinate with Victor, Rebecca, and Colin on brand assets review meeting scheduling and feedback (13:26)\nProvide correct EPS logo files to replace problematic white knockout logos in design assets (16:44)\nKeep team informed on Google Ads recovery situation and provide any required verification documentation (17:24)\nFacilitate communication between teams regarding campaign status, rogue ads, and future campaign planning (19:34)\nMonitor project timelines, approve or escalate if deadlines at risk, and discuss live dates with Betty (25:31)\nProvide early feedback on website sitemap, templates, and content once visuals are shared (37:37)\nWork with Jane and Rebecca to troubleshoot HubSpot marketing email invite issues (38:40)\n\n**Victor Garcia**\nShare detailed content links for homepage design with Colin and assist in resource/project coordination (10:53)\nOversee project schedule coordination with Guille and Rebecca for meetings and workflows (15:44)\nSupport brand and creative coordination alongside Rebecca (15:44)\nCommunicate with team members on marketing email inbox and social account access as needed (33:28)\n\n**Rebecca Cruz**\nJoin brand assets review meeting to clarify template vs. asset creation (13:26)\nCoordinate social media posting workflows and platform access with Jane and Colin (33:28)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"eee5f467-000b-4b99-887e-5541f8a661af","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
