    '2026-01-05 15:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KDNJ78BN52MGXT4CQ6GEA0H1',
    'New North <> ThreatMark: Weekly Marketing Meeting',
    '{"Colin Costigan","Nina Belina","Colin Costigan","Greg Smith","Kate ThreatMark"}'::text[],
    2247,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/84564648866?pwd=JR6eWxlxKbgogzCqTNUawSLUUhQoEa.1',
    '{"id":"01KDNJ78BN52MGXT4CQ6GEA0H1","title":"New North <> ThreatMark: Weekly Marketing Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Budget and Advertising Strategy**\n\nThe team decided to maintain the current advertising budget while planning to increase overall ad spend in 2026, with a new focus on regional budget granularity for better tracking (06:31).  \n- Greg Smith emphasized carving the budget by region to improve visibility and control over spending.  \n- They agreed to convert all ad accounts to US dollars to reduce currency risk, with Greg leading the effort to transfer LinkedIn ad ownership and re-verify Google Ads in USD (09:26).  \n- This currency shift moves exchange risk to the CFO, easing financial management.  \n- The change will involve some administrative overhead but is expected to streamline future budgeting and reporting.  \n\nPlans to integrate an intent data provider, **Propensity**, were confirmed to support a pivot toward Account-Based Marketing (ABM) (07:58).  \n- Propensity was chosen over costlier options like 6sense due to better pricing and suitability for targeting about **1,000 accounts** rather than tens of thousands.  \n- The platform will help craft LinkedIn audiences based on target accounts, serving as a bottom-funnel advertising tool alongside broader brand awareness campaigns.  \n- Integrating intent signals into HubSpot will establish a more precise ABM structure, improving targeting and engagement measurement.  \n\nAd performance showed rising competition on Google, with brands like **Barracuda, MasterCard,** and **Solace** bidding on the Threatmark brand name, driving up cost-per-click (23:02).  \n- Despite this, LinkedIn ads generated over **65 leads from a $25,000 spend** in 2025, confirming its effectiveness as a lead source (27:11).  \n- Lead source tracking via HubSpot fields is functioning well, enabling better attribution and campaign optimizations (24:37).  \n\n## **Website and HubSpot Migration**\n\nThe first phase of the website migration will focus on the **Banking Fraud Summit site** as a proof of concept to validate the HubSpot platform before proceeding with the full Threatmark site migration (10:46).  \n- Greg requested an estimate of the effort required for the migration, emphasizing a straightforward copy-paste of content without branding or design changes (11:49).  \n- Threatmark will provide access to the current WordPress instance and source files to facilitate a smooth transition (12:03).  \n- Stage two involving the main site will require a more thoughtful redesign rather than a direct copy, contingent on the success of phase one (12:46).  \n- Colin committed to providing a migration quote promptly to support scheduling.  \n\n## **Events and Marketing Goals**\n\nThe marketing team plans to sponsor **eight trade shows** and run several proprietary events in 2026, with creative production efforts varying by event (13:20).  \n- Reach Desk has been onboarded as the swag provider to enhance event merchandising and engagement.  \n- Greg identified a need to improve branding consistency and creative quality, noting prior event materials were visually weak due to print issues and loose brand guidelines (14:44).  \n- Event materials for March sponsorships must be finalized by the end of January to meet deadlines (15:19).  \n\nKey marketing goals for 2026 include building a **$12 million marketing sourced pipeline**, which is the primary success metric (16:58).  \n- They aim to establish **500+ target accounts** for ABM with a **60% engagement rate**, sourced from intent data integration (18:30).  \n- The ABM program targets generating at least **32 qualified opportunities**, roughly half of the pipeline goal (18:50).  \n- Lead goals include **263 sales accepted leads** from marketing, with an aim to double the LinkedIn following and improve organic search volume by **10%** (19:56, 20:04).  \n- Greg acknowledged that while other metrics exist, the $12 million pipeline remains the central focus.  \n\n## **Content and Brand Development**\n\nThe team is preparing for two podcast episodes, including the **Kelly Paxton episode scheduled for February 7 at 6am Eastern**, with final guest title verification pending (22:38).  \n- Kate ThreatMark is managing guest info and will confirm details to proceed with production (22:41).  \n\nGreg shared plans to develop a new **first call pitch deck**, requesting creative support for a lightweight design effort (34:33).  \n- He also highlighted inspiration from the **Zero Fox website** for evolving Threatmark’s brand creative, noting it resonates well with leadership and aligns with podcast branding (35:47).  \n- Colin confirmed access to source files and willingness to develop ideas incorporating elements from Zero Fox’s polished style (36:36).  \n- This brand refinement aims to strengthen visual identity and support broader marketing efforts.  \n\n## **Strategic Marketing Initiatives and Competitive Positioning**\n\nThe team rejected the use of product comparison landing pages to avoid commoditizing Threatmark’s technology and diluting differentiation (29:27).  \n- Greg stressed the complexity of their enterprise tech makes simple feature comparisons ineffective and potentially harmful.  \n- Instead, they plan to commission a **third-party research survey** to create an original **State of Fraud report** as a gated asset and advertising tool (30:50).  \n- This report will also include a proprietary Threatmark customer metric to highlight competitive advantages without direct comparison.  \n- Colin suggested a potential phase two interactive benchmark tool, allowing prospects to input data and receive tailored insights, proven effective in other industries (32:08).  \n- This approach aligns with strategic goals to create differentiated, data-driven marketing assets that build credibility and drive engagement.  \n\n## **Operational and Creative Process Enhancements**\n\nGreg noted ongoing monitoring of creative performance and A/B testing, with top-performing ads focusing on **fraud liability** and **stop paying for scam losses** messaging (26:52).  \n- The brand awareness campaign is low volume but maintains a low cost-per-click, supporting broader visibility goals (27:02).  \n\nKate raised two operational priorities: progressing the **For Disruption white paper** based on feedback and updating the **website carousel**, which is ready for final review and deployment (33:20).  \n- Greg took responsibility for responding to feedback on the white paper to determine if revisions are necessary (33:38).  \n- Colin will verify carousel status and circulate updated files for testing and launch (34:04).  \n\nGreg also flagged the need for earlier notice on new product launches to prepare marketing materials, requesting at least a two-week lead time to optimize creative and promotional planning (26:39).  \n- This request supports smoother event and campaign execution aligned with product updates.","outline":null,"keywords":["ABM","Budget 2026","Website Migration","Lead Generation","Events & Sponsorships","Brand & Creative Vision"],"overview":"- **Budget Focus:** Maintain current ad budget, increase regional granularity for better tracking in 2026.  \n- **Ad Accounts Strategy:** Convert all ad accounts to USD to reduce currency risk, simplifying budgeting and reporting.  \n- **Event Plans:** Sponsor eight trade shows in 2026, finalize materials by January for March sponsorships.  \n- **Marketing Goals:** Aim for $12 million pipeline, 500+ target accounts, with 263 sales accepted leads from marketing.  \n- **Content Development:** Prepare for two podcast episodes, create a new pitch deck, and refine brand identity.  \n- **Research Initiatives:** Commission a State of Fraud report to differentiate and showcase Threatmark''s competitive advantage.","action_items":"\n**Greg Smith**\nShare detailed 2026 ad spend regional budget breakdown with Colin Costigan (06:31)\nProceed with repayment and transfer of LinkedIn ad account ownership to ThreatMark business manager and invite partners (09:26)\nProvide list of upcoming events with deadlines and creative requirements by end of current month (15:21)\nConfirm next steps on the For Disruption white paper feedback and respond accordingly (33:38)\nShare updates on Propensity integration and requests needing assistance (21:56)\nFollow up with team and Michal on creative vision aligning with ZeroFox inspiration (35:47)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nProvide an estimate and timeline for the Banking Fraud Summit site migration based on a 1:1 copy approach (11:49)\nReview final feedback on website carousel and launch update (33:42)\nPrepare ideas for branded Q2 booth items and marketing assets (26:23)\nDeliver detailed updates and wrap-up message including event schedules and ABM list requirements (21:20)\n\n**Kate ThreatMark**\nConfirm full title of guest for podcast episode as soon as received (22:38)\nCoordinate with Greg to review For Disruption white paper feedback and determine if revisions are needed (33:38)\nContinue communication for final feedback related to website carousel update (33:42)\nCoordinate with team on creative materials needed for upcoming sponsorships and swag (14:44)\n"},"duration":37.45000076293945,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":1,"name":"Nina Belina"},{"id":2,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":3,"name":"Greg Smith"},{"id":4,"name":"Kate ThreatMark"}],"sentences":[{"text":"How''s it going?","index":0,"end_time":210.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":209.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":1,"end_time":211.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":211.12,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"We had our first snow today, so it''s interesting we hadn''t had it in, like, while.","index":2,"end_time":220.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":212.8,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Do you like snow?","index":3,"end_time":222.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":221.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, I don''t mind it, but it was just changed because my phone and everybody''s phone in the last couple of days kept saying, it''s snowing, it''s snowing.","index":4,"end_time":231.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":223.28,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And there was no snow, so I felt like my phone and we were living a different.","index":5,"end_time":236.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":231.64,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Different reality from each other.","index":6,"end_time":237.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":236.22,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah, that''ll happen.","index":7,"end_time":239.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":238.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hello.","index":8,"end_time":243.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":242.86,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Happy New Year.","index":9,"end_time":244.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":243.34,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Happy New Year.","index":10,"end_time":245.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":244.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hi.","index":11,"end_time":245.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":245.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Happy New Year.","index":12,"end_time":246.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":245.78,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Hi.","index":13,"end_time":247.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":246.94,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"How was your holiday break?","index":14,"end_time":252.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":249.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know if you took any time off or anything like that.","index":15,"end_time":255.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":252.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, I took some time off.","index":16,"end_time":257.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":255.86,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"It was really great.","index":17,"end_time":258.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":257.3,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"A lot of family time, friends time.","index":18,"end_time":261.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":258.38,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So very peaceful.","index":19,"end_time":262.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":261.26,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Nice.","index":20,"end_time":263.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":262.98,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":21,"end_time":264.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":263.94,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"But it passed very fast.","index":22,"end_time":265.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":264.26,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yes, it always does.","index":23,"end_time":267.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":265.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, Greg.","index":24,"end_time":272.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":271.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey.","index":25,"end_time":273.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":273.14,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"How are we doing?","index":26,"end_time":274.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":274.1,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Doing all right.","index":27,"end_time":276.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":275.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good to see you.","index":28,"end_time":277.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":276.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Happy New Year.","index":29,"end_time":278.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":277.859,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Happy New Year.","index":30,"end_time":279.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":278.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Happy New Year.","index":31,"end_time":281.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":280.34,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"How was the last few weeks?","index":32,"end_time":287.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":284.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s good.","index":33,"end_time":289.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":288.94,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Relaxing.","index":34,"end_time":291.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":290.22,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Good.","index":35,"end_time":292.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":291.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hello.","index":36,"end_time":293.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":292.78,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Hey.","index":37,"end_time":294.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":294.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":38,"end_time":295.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":294.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, good.","index":39,"end_time":296.38,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":295.82,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"How is everyone doing?","index":40,"end_time":297.98,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":296.38,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Well.","index":41,"end_time":298.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":297.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And how was the last few weeks for you, Kate?","index":42,"end_time":300.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":298.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not bad.","index":43,"end_time":301.42,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":300.78,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Right.","index":44,"end_time":301.98,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":301.58,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"So we can land on.","index":45,"end_time":304.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":303.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was a good break.","index":46,"end_time":305.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":304.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It went by too fast and maybe we need one of those, like, every.","index":47,"end_time":310.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":305.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Quarter or something like that.","index":48,"end_time":311.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":310.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, like every.","index":49,"end_time":312.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":311.58,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Every couple of weeks.","index":50,"end_time":313.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":312.54,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":51,"end_time":314.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":313.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":52,"end_time":316.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":316.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, we have an agenda today, and then I do also just have a list of questions I want to go through just to establish, you know, 2026, making sure we''re always on the same page.","index":53,"end_time":325.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":316.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Should I start with my questions?","index":54,"end_time":328.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":327.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Maybe.","index":55,"end_time":328.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":328.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we''ll get into the agenda and we''ll see how everything lines up.","index":56,"end_time":331.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":328.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s fine.","index":57,"end_time":332.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":331.96,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay.","index":58,"end_time":333.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":333,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So a few things that I don''t have in our agenda that I want to make sure we talk through our budget outlines for 2026.","index":59,"end_time":339.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":334.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that being any paid channels that we''re operating on and making sure that we''re adhering to monthly budgets as we''ve talked about those on a recurring basis.","index":60,"end_time":348.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":341.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then with the progress with HubSpot, what we want to do with the website projects.","index":61,"end_time":355.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":349.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know the idea is to start with Banking Fraud Summit and then move into the larger Threatmark website.","index":62,"end_time":359.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":355.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So just wanted to talk through those.","index":63,"end_time":361.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":359.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Greg, one thing you had mentioned, and it''s kind of a pain in the neck, but it can be done because it will make our lives easier at some point is updating the ad accounts that we run to be all in US currency.","index":64,"end_time":373.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":362.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That would require, obviously, going through re verification on a few platforms, but just wanted to bring that up then.","index":65,"end_time":380.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":374.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any goals for 20, 26 and any updates regarding trade shows and ABM and where we can support there.","index":66,"end_time":387.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":380.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Those are a lot of questions, man.","index":67,"end_time":389.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":387.55,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"It''s a lot of questions.","index":68,"end_time":390.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":389.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, we''re jumping into it.","index":69,"end_time":393.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":391.39,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We''re not wasting any time.","index":70,"end_time":395.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":394.35,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay, let''s knock them down.","index":71,"end_time":397.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":396.35,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Budget.","index":72,"end_time":398.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":398.24,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We will have more budget for ad spend.","index":73,"end_time":403.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":398.8,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So what I would say is let''s just keep.","index":74,"end_time":407.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":404.08,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I think we want to rejigger things pretty, pretty holistically, but let''s just keep what we have now rolling because we will have more.","index":75,"end_time":420.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":408.32,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So where we''re at currently is fine.","index":76,"end_time":424.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":421.52,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"A and, and I''ll obviously share the specifics with you, but what I want to do is I actually want to carve it up by region.","index":77,"end_time":432.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":425.2,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So it''s not super useful for me to be like, oh, it''s this much.","index":78,"end_time":436.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":433.64,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I want to get a little bit more granular in that.","index":79,"end_time":439.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":436.92,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Just to give you a heads up on that.","index":80,"end_time":442.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":441.4,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I think what we wanted, we want to bring in an intent provider to start getting some intent data to back up a pivot to abm.","index":81,"end_time":452.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":442.76,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And one aspect of that is I think who we''re going to go with will actually end up crafting the LinkedIn audiences for us in the platform based on the target account.","index":82,"end_time":469.379,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":453.3,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So that''ll be kind of think of that as like your bottom of funnel advertising.","index":83,"end_time":474.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":469.38,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We''ll still want to do some broader like brand awareness type advertising.","index":84,"end_time":482.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":474.94,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"That''s, that''s broader and not as targeted.","index":85,"end_time":484.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":482.59,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"But then like the ABM portion of that we would run through the platform and bring in intent signals into HubSpot and start building out kind of a true ABM structure.","index":86,"end_time":495.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":484.67,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Is that just real quick, is that a like six sense or a like dream data type solution?","index":87,"end_time":503.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":496.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re most likely going to go with propensity.","index":88,"end_time":508.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":504.07,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Um, I don''t know if you''ve ever come on.","index":89,"end_time":512.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":509.38,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Hello.","index":90,"end_time":513.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":513.14,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I don''t know if you''ve ever worked with them or not.","index":91,"end_time":517.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":513.94,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"That tool specifically, it''s, it''s really well designed for companies our size from an approachability perspective.","index":92,"end_time":527.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":517.02,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So because like 6 cents is like cost 100 grand to open the door and the way they structure it is freaking camera.","index":93,"end_time":539.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":527.86,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"There we go.","index":94,"end_time":540.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":539.84,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"The way they structure it is way more consumption based.","index":95,"end_time":544.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":540.4,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So like we''re gonna go after a thousand accounts, not ten thousand or a hundred thousand accounts.","index":96,"end_time":550.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":545.84,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So it''s way more affordable for us from that perspective.","index":97,"end_time":553.919,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":550.88,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"They are a ingestor of $0.06 data.","index":98,"end_time":558.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":554.24,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So it''s one of their data sources.","index":99,"end_time":559.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":558.48,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So you get some of the $0.06 value out of that.","index":100,"end_time":563.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":560.08,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Right?","index":101,"end_time":564.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":564.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":102,"end_time":565.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":564.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s That I do want to go through the pain of migrating all of our ad platforms into USD.","index":103,"end_time":575.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":566.24,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I think it makes sense for us and I think it needs to be done.","index":104,"end_time":582.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":576.24,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"One of the things that I don''t fully understand and would love to understand is it feels to me like our LinkedIn account is like somehow nested under your account.","index":105,"end_time":596.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":582.56,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Is that correct?","index":106,"end_time":598.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":597.09,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s nested in our business manager.","index":107,"end_time":600.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":598.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But what you guys could do is set up a business manager and take ownership of the ad account and then invite us as partners.","index":108,"end_time":606.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":601.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think that''s what we need to do.","index":109,"end_time":608.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":606.61,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So we''ll effectively repatriate the LinkedIn account that I think is in USD.","index":110,"end_time":615.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":609.57,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I think the one that''s in pound sterling is Google Ads.","index":111,"end_time":620.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":615.61,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Google.","index":112,"end_time":621.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":621.09,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So I think it''s.","index":113,"end_time":624.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":622.52,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We''ll just have to go through re verification and stuff.","index":114,"end_time":627.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":624.36,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"But since that''s not the primary lead driver right now, I''m not worried about.","index":115,"end_time":632.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":627.36,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We can, we can do that as we do that, but it''d be good to get that denominated in USD.","index":116,"end_time":638.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":632.36,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Basically what that does is that shifts the currency risk off of us onto my cfo.","index":117,"end_time":645.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":639.24,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yes.","index":118,"end_time":645.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":645.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so I''m happy to do that.","index":119,"end_time":647.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":646.68,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay, next question.","index":120,"end_time":655,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":650.6,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Let''s see if I can get them all in order.","index":121,"end_time":656.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":655,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Your next question was.","index":122,"end_time":658.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":656.44,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So you probably saw we.","index":123,"end_time":663,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":661.64,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Maybe you didn''t.","index":124,"end_time":663.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":663.16,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I don''t know, you probably saw we executed a contract, so we''re ready to rock.","index":125,"end_time":669,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":663.84,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"You are correct.","index":126,"end_time":670.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":669.56,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Stage one is to tackle the Fraud Summit site.","index":127,"end_time":674.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":670.44,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So what I''d like to do there is I''d love, if it''d be possible for you guys to pull together basically an estimate for how much effort it would take to do the migration.","index":128,"end_time":687.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":675.48,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And then, you know, I''d love to understand what that looks like because part of that, part of that is just understanding how much work is going to go into migrating full site.","index":129,"end_time":697.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":688.34,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And these are apples and oranges.","index":130,"end_time":700.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":697.78,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I understand that, but I''d love to get a feel for what that might be and then the sooner the better.","index":131,"end_time":709.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":700.14,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yep.","index":132,"end_time":710.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":709.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And with that, is there any like branding changes color.","index":133,"end_time":715.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":710.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let just one to one pull it over.","index":134,"end_time":717.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":715.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Copy and paste.","index":135,"end_time":718.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":717.17,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Just copy and paste.","index":136,"end_time":719.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":718.01,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yep.","index":137,"end_time":719.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":719.29,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":138,"end_time":721.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":721.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So like any.","index":139,"end_time":725.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":723.73,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And like we can provide all the source files or you can download them from the WordPress and.","index":140,"end_time":730.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":725.33,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Or we can even probably give you access to the WordPress instance so that you don''t have to recreate anything or.","index":141,"end_time":738.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":730.61,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, that''d be perfect.","index":142,"end_time":739.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":738.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Possible.","index":143,"end_time":740.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":740.02,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":144,"end_time":741.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":740.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":145,"end_time":742.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":741.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, you''re doing great with getting these in order.","index":146,"end_time":744.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":742.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is where it''s gonna start falling apart.","index":147,"end_time":747.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":745.62,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So we said HubSpot.","index":148,"end_time":752.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":747.14,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Oh, you want to know about events?","index":149,"end_time":756.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":754.1,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Was that next?","index":150,"end_time":758.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":757.78,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"It was just we were talking about the website projects through HubSpot, so we said stage one was the Banking Fraud Summit.","index":151,"end_time":764.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":759.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t want to tackle stage two until.","index":152,"end_time":768.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":766.86,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yep, so that''s done.","index":153,"end_time":769.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":768.54,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Like, this is a, this is a proof of concept, right?","index":154,"end_time":771.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":769.82,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yes.","index":155,"end_time":771.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":771.66,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Like if, if we get through and we''re like, well, we hate this, then we''ll fall back and regroup.","index":156,"end_time":778.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":771.98,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"If we get through it, we''re like, this is, this is good.","index":157,"end_time":782.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":779.26,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We like.","index":158,"end_time":783.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":782.38,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Then.","index":159,"end_time":783.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":783.1,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Then let''s start tackling that.","index":160,"end_time":785.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":783.5,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Because the, the primary site will involve some level of thought to do things better.","index":161,"end_time":792.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":786.06,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"It will not be a copy and paste.","index":162,"end_time":794.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":792.81,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":163,"end_time":796.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":795.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":164,"end_time":797.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":797.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then, yes, it was goals and events.","index":165,"end_time":799.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":797.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Goals and events.","index":166,"end_time":801.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":800.29,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So let''s finish with goals.","index":167,"end_time":804.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":801.21,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We''ll do events first.","index":168,"end_time":805.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":804.05,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So Ilya has dutifully waded into the world of events and worked with the team to try and figure out where we might want to go.","index":169,"end_time":820.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":805.41,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I think we''ve got budget for, I think it was eight sponsorships and we''re going to run a handful of our own.","index":170,"end_time":831.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":820.67,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So among those eight sponsorships, there will be a varying level of work that we need to do to prep for that from a creative perspective.","index":171,"end_time":843.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":833.31,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We''ve brought on Reach Desk as a swag provider for us, so we''ll be able to start working with them for the actual, you know, merchandising component of it.","index":172,"end_time":859.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":844.35,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"But in terms of banners, booths, etc.","index":173,"end_time":863.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":860.02,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yes.","index":174,"end_time":863.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":863.46,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I will say I don''t think what we did for the last event, I don''t, I don''t think it landed.","index":175,"end_time":870.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":864.58,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"A lot of the design got washed out in the print and it just didn''t hit for me.","index":176,"end_time":876.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":870.18,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And I think we need to, we need to.","index":177,"end_time":879.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":876.15,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"The brand is just so loosey goosey right now.","index":178,"end_time":884.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":881.71,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yep.","index":179,"end_time":884.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":884.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And like, you know that, like, this is not a criticism on anyone.","index":180,"end_time":888.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":885.07,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We got to figure out how to punch it up and, and make it look good.","index":181,"end_time":893.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":889.47,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So.","index":182,"end_time":894.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":893.71,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yep.","index":183,"end_time":894.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":894.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I think the next logical question there is perhaps which one might be the first one that we would be marching towards?","index":184,"end_time":905.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":896.99,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And I''m not going to be able to answer that immediately, but I''m sure it''s pretty soon.","index":185,"end_time":916.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":910.21,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And.","index":186,"end_time":919.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":919.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you have a list?","index":187,"end_time":920.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":919.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is that what you''re pulling up?","index":188,"end_time":921.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":920.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, I have a big list, but then I have the ones that like, we were able to squeeze into the budget.","index":189,"end_time":927.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":921.73,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Come on.","index":190,"end_time":934.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":933.71,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Getting closer.","index":191,"end_time":949.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":948.35,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay, March.","index":192,"end_time":972.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":958.12,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"There''s plenty of time for that.","index":193,"end_time":974.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":972.84,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"March.","index":194,"end_time":977.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":977.24,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I think they''re all in March, so we probably have to have, probably have to have stuff teed up by the end of this month for that stuff.","index":195,"end_time":996.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":986.45,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So.","index":196,"end_time":997.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":996.89,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And I still have to go through the full list and make sure we agree we''re making all the right decisions there.","index":197,"end_time":1004.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":998.37,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yep.","index":198,"end_time":1005.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1004.85,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"But yeah.","index":199,"end_time":1006.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1005.7,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay.","index":200,"end_time":1006.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1006.22,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Goals.","index":201,"end_time":1007.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1007.14,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"12 million in marketing source pipeline.","index":202,"end_time":1011.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1009.22,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"That''s it.","index":203,"end_time":1016.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1016.1,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"That''s all we want.","index":204,"end_time":1018.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1017.62,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay.","index":205,"end_time":1020.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1020.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Salesforce data, as far as comparing that to performance last year, how accurate is that as a benchmark?","index":206,"end_time":1029.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1021.459,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, not.","index":207,"end_time":1030.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1029.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nope.","index":208,"end_time":1031.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1030.74,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Don''t.","index":209,"end_time":1033.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1032.71,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Don''t be doing that.","index":210,"end_time":1034.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1033.19,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So.","index":211,"end_time":1039.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1038.87,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"All right.","index":212,"end_time":1039.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1039.23,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"There are quite a few more goals than that.","index":213,"end_time":1041.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1039.59,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"There are a lot that nest under that.","index":214,"end_time":1043.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1042.07,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So a few of them that I think are.","index":215,"end_time":1047.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1043.99,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Are relevant for the conversation.","index":216,"end_time":1050.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1048.15,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Let me pull them.","index":217,"end_time":1053.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1052.23,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"To do.","index":218,"end_time":1062.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1061.68,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So 12 and pipe ones that would fall into kind of the scope of what we''re working on together.","index":219,"end_time":1072.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1064.16,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay.","index":220,"end_time":1082.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1081.36,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We want.","index":221,"end_time":1082.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1082.08,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So we''re going to start establishing Target accounts for ABM.","index":222,"end_time":1086,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1082.96,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"The goal is to have more than 500 of them.","index":223,"end_time":1089.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1086.81,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I think that we''re going to achieve that very quickly.","index":224,"end_time":1092.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1089.93,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"That''s not really a meaningful goal.","index":225,"end_time":1093.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1092.13,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"The actual goal that''s relevant here is 60% engagement across those accounts.","index":226,"end_time":1099.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1093.77,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So one of the things we''re going to be measuring is account engagement and that''s going to be coming through the intent work that we''re eventually going to get baked in.","index":227,"end_time":1110.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1100.97,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We want to source at least 32 opportunities through our ABM efforts.","index":228,"end_time":1117.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1111.85,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So two opportunities is not the full 12.","index":229,"end_time":1120.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1117.61,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"The full 12 shakes out to 66.","index":230,"end_time":1129.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1121.35,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So it''s about half of those opportunities we would care about that.","index":231,"end_time":1139.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1131.83,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We want to get.","index":232,"end_time":1145.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1144.4,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And sorry, Kate, I''m still committing us to this.","index":233,"end_time":1149.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1147.44,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Six case studies and four video testimonials next year.","index":234,"end_time":1154.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1150.4,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We want to.","index":235,"end_time":1162.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1161.12,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Actually let me give you our lead goals too because I think you''ll.","index":236,"end_time":1169.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1167.28,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"You''ll be keeping an eye on that.","index":237,"end_time":1171.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1170.38,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I''m going to give you the sales accepted lead goal because I think the MQL and top of funnel lead goals are just swags at.","index":238,"end_time":1187.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1176.14,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"With no data to actually suggest that that''s accurate.","index":239,"end_time":1191.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1187.82,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We''re looking for 263 sales accepted leads.","index":240,"end_time":1195.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1192.06,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":241,"end_time":1196.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1196.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For this year.","index":242,"end_time":1198.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1197.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":243,"end_time":1199.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1199.03,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay.","index":244,"end_time":1201.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1201.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"From.","index":245,"end_time":1202.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1201.99,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"From marketing.","index":246,"end_time":1203.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1202.35,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Right.","index":247,"end_time":1203.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1203.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":248,"end_time":1205.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1204.47,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We would very much like to double our LinkedIn following.","index":249,"end_time":1211.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1207.59,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"That''s the other one Kate''s scared of.","index":250,"end_time":1214.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1212.31,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"If you weren''t scared, we wouldn''t be having fun.","index":251,"end_time":1217.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1215.83,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And also work on a 10% improvement in organic search volume as measured by Google Search Console.","index":252,"end_time":1230.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1219.11,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Not by any type of cookie.","index":253,"end_time":1233.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1230.87,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Limited analytics.","index":254,"end_time":1234.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1233.55,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":255,"end_time":1235.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1234.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":256,"end_time":1237.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1237.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Fantastic.","index":257,"end_time":1238.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1238.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Am I missing anything in that list?","index":258,"end_time":1240.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1239.23,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"You''re asking me here?","index":259,"end_time":1246.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1245.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m applicate.","index":260,"end_time":1247.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1246.83,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":261,"end_time":1248.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1248.2,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"No, I think you.","index":262,"end_time":1253.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1252.92,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"You mentioned everything.","index":263,"end_time":1254.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1253.64,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Okay.","index":264,"end_time":1257.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1257.32,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"But if.","index":265,"end_time":1260.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1259.96,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"If we do the 12 million and marketing source pipe.","index":266,"end_time":1262.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1260.52,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"None of the other really matters.","index":267,"end_time":1264.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1262.72,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"That''s how it goes.","index":268,"end_time":1265.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1264.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The pie in the sky.","index":269,"end_time":1268.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1267.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":270,"end_time":1269.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1268.68,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":271,"end_time":1270.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1269.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":272,"end_time":1272.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1270.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":273,"end_time":1273.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1272.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, thank you for running through this.","index":274,"end_time":1274.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1273.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":275,"end_time":1277.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1276.48,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"You want to pop over to your agenda.","index":276,"end_time":1280.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1279.12,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":277,"end_time":1281.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1280.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I''ll just say so if you have a list and we can put this in our like wrap up message.","index":278,"end_time":1287.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1281.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But if you have a list of the events just so we know like, okay, they''re coming up in March this month we need to produce X, Y and Z and then any updates for the ABM lists and what we would need to do with those.","index":279,"end_time":1303.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1287.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I''ll.","index":280,"end_time":1304.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1303.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll get a quote back to you.","index":281,"end_time":1305.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1304.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For the Banking Fraud Summit website migration.","index":282,"end_time":1307.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1305.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":283,"end_time":1308.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1308.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":284,"end_time":1310.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1309.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then just keep us updated on propensity and anything you need us to do there.","index":285,"end_time":1313.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1310.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":286,"end_time":1314.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1313.84,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"All right.","index":287,"end_time":1317.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1316.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we wanted to go through just a few updates and Then performance recap, 2025 year interview and then just some ideas and notes for 2026 for the Kelly Paxton episode that is all scheduled to go live on the seventh Wednesday morning at 6am Eastern on the website Spotify, YouTube and Apple Podcasts.","index":288,"end_time":1347.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1324.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then Kate for the latest one that you submitted.","index":289,"end_time":1351.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1349.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re all good there.","index":290,"end_time":1353.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1352.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We just need the to make sure that we''re accurate on the full title for that guest.","index":291,"end_time":1357.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1353.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, she hasn''t got back to me yet, but I will send over as soon as she does.","index":292,"end_time":1361.05,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1358.25,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":293,"end_time":1362.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1361.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":294,"end_time":1363.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1363.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As soon as we have that, then.","index":295,"end_time":1364.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1363.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can start producing everything.","index":296,"end_time":1366.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1364.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any questions around Kelly Paxton or the other episode?","index":297,"end_time":1370.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1367.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Don''t think so.","index":298,"end_time":1374.97,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1374.01,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Cool.","index":299,"end_time":1376.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1375.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Going through just ad performance from the last few weeks.","index":300,"end_time":1381.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1378.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As expected, Google is very quiet.","index":301,"end_time":1384.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1381.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was a low spend, but we did see a competitor spike from brands like Barracuda and MasterCard and Solace bidding on the Threatmark brand name, which is interesting to see.","index":302,"end_time":1394.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1384.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The cost per click did increase pretty drastically for Google and the ad strength is average.","index":303,"end_time":1403.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1395.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re seeing a lot more competitors recognizing you guys as a brand, trying.","index":304,"end_time":1407.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1403.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To bid on those, especially from a Google Channel perspective.","index":305,"end_time":1411.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1407.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, go ahead.","index":306,"end_time":1412.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1411.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s great.","index":307,"end_time":1413.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1412.87,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I know.","index":308,"end_time":1416.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1416.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":309,"end_time":1417.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1417.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":310,"end_time":1417.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1417.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The bigger pockets are jumping into the sandbox.","index":311,"end_time":1420.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1417.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":312,"end_time":1421.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1420.65,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"No, that''s, that''s always annoying.","index":313,"end_time":1424.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1421.53,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":314,"end_time":1425.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1424.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But it''s something really great for the cost per click.","index":315,"end_time":1428.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1425.93,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"That''s the only thing that.","index":316,"end_time":1429.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1428.73,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":317,"end_time":1432.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1430.57,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And like, you know, it used to be that you would, you would go below the sponsored or you''d go above your organic would go above the sponsored results.","index":318,"end_time":1441.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1432.49,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So like you''d have organic then sponsored.","index":319,"end_time":1443.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1441.29,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"But I haven''t seen that in A long time.","index":320,"end_time":1445.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1443.37,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":321,"end_time":1447.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1447.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And now they even have it.","index":322,"end_time":1448.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1447.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s sponsored and then organic and then sponsored again.","index":323,"end_time":1450.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1448.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":324,"end_time":1452.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1451.09,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"On LinkedIn, we did see more leads coming through.","index":325,"end_time":1457.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1455.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So December 24th got another couple of leads.","index":326,"end_time":1460.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1458.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The 31st got four more leads.","index":327,"end_time":1462.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1460.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think even this morning we got a few more leads that we haven''t.","index":328,"end_time":1465.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1462.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Baked into the slide deck.","index":329,"end_time":1466.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1465.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But the new ad rotations seem to be working well and all of those are mapping properly as far as we can see for the fields that we set up.","index":330,"end_time":1475.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1466.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Greg, the lead source and lead source detail.","index":331,"end_time":1477.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1475.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":332,"end_time":1478.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1477.87,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"The lead source and lead source details seem to be firing nicely, which is great.","index":333,"end_time":1482.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1478.23,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"The couple of the last EMEA ones that came through were kind of junky, but I.","index":334,"end_time":1491.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1484.51,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"No reason to suggest that there''s anything that needs to be tweaked on that.","index":335,"end_time":1497.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1493.07,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I think when we pivot to more of an ABM approach there, I''ll want to see how that.","index":336,"end_time":1507.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1497.19,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"How the quality shakes out.","index":337,"end_time":1509.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1507.78,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"But yeah, so I think.","index":338,"end_time":1511.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1509.78,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"All good on that.","index":339,"end_time":1512.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1511.38,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We''re.","index":340,"end_time":1512.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1512.26,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We''re still.","index":341,"end_time":1513.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1512.62,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"It seems like we''re still producing at the right volume that we need to there.","index":342,"end_time":1519.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1514.26,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"The Q2 campaign specifically I''ve been really pleased by, because the team can actually action off of those.","index":343,"end_time":1526.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1519.38,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And in the US because we can''t really sell outside of the Q2 ecosystem right now, really hard for us to sell outside of it.","index":344,"end_time":1536.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1527.62,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And so just, just for context, we''re going to obviously double down on that with an ABM approach and that''s one of the big events that we''re going to go to, etc.","index":345,"end_time":1547.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1537.28,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"But we need to pick what the next Q2 is and go after those accounts as well.","index":346,"end_time":1552.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1547.92,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":347,"end_time":1553.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1553.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that way we can open up our serviceable universe.","index":348,"end_time":1556.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1553.48,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"But yeah, absolutely.","index":349,"end_time":1557.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1556.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And is the Q2 conference, is that in May again?","index":350,"end_time":1561.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1558.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think it was May last year.","index":351,"end_time":1562.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1561.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I think.","index":352,"end_time":1563.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1562.82,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I think it''s June.","index":353,"end_time":1565.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1564.5,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"June, yeah, it''s.","index":354,"end_time":1567.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1565.78,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And it''s in Austin, Texas.","index":355,"end_time":1568.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1567.54,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So they pick like the worst possible time to go to Austin, Texas.","index":356,"end_time":1573.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1568.9,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Super hot.","index":357,"end_time":1574.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1573.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Super hot.","index":358,"end_time":1575.459,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1574.58,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I think it''s June.","index":359,"end_time":1577.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1576.5,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We don''t have the prospectus yet, so we''re expecting to get that sometime in the next few weeks.","index":360,"end_time":1583.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1578.26,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":361,"end_time":1584.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1583.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, we''ll start thinking through some catchy booth items.","index":362,"end_time":1588.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1584.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know last year, Kate, we worked on the quiz and a few other items to try and attract some extra visitors to the booth.","index":363,"end_time":1595.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1588.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Extra foot traffic.","index":364,"end_time":1596.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1595.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll start thinking through those as well.","index":365,"end_time":1597.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1596.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, cool.","index":366,"end_time":1599,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1598.12,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":367,"end_time":1600.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1599.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As long as it would.","index":368,"end_time":1602.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1600.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It would be great to get a little bit more than like two weeks heads up if you guys Drop a brand new product.","index":369,"end_time":1606.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1602.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No.","index":370,"end_time":1607.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1607.48,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":371,"end_time":1612.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1612.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":372,"end_time":1613,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1612.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then always monitoring also creative performance in our AB test.","index":373,"end_time":1616.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1613,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So fraud liability and stop paying for scam losses.","index":374,"end_time":1619.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1616.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Worth the top performing creatives.","index":375,"end_time":1620.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1619.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":376,"end_time":1621.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1621.14,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Good to know.","index":377,"end_time":1622.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1621.86,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"For ad roll, obviously it''s more of a brand awareness play.","index":378,"end_time":1625.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1622.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s low volume, but the cost.","index":379,"end_time":1626.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1625.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Per click is staying very low.","index":380,"end_time":1627.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1626.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":381,"end_time":1628.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1628.58,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Looking at just kind of a holistic year.","index":382,"end_time":1633.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1631.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Interview Google Ads.","index":383,"end_time":1635.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1633.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"84,000 impressions, 3,000 clicks.","index":384,"end_time":1637.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1635.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Obviously more vanity metrics.","index":385,"end_time":1638.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1637.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The the biggest one.","index":386,"end_time":1639.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1638.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"LinkedIn Ads has proved to be a great channel for Threatmark as we expected going into it, but with $25,000 invested generating over 65 leads, obviously as you guys continue to work with the sales team for improving reporting, we can have better backend attribution as far as.","index":387,"end_time":1658.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1640.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, these leads actually led to these.","index":388,"end_time":1660.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1658.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Opportunities and deals, but it''s great to.","index":389,"end_time":1663.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1660.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"See the lead volumes working there.","index":390,"end_time":1665.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1663.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":391,"end_time":1665.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1665.35,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":392,"end_time":1668.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1667.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":393,"end_time":1670.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1669.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then just a few ideas that we were noting down.","index":394,"end_time":1672.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1670.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So even on LinkedIn we''re seeing competitors and Google as well, you know, bidding on your name or bidding with the same audiences.","index":395,"end_time":1679.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1672.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so we''re seeing that there may be an opportunity to get a little bit more tech focused.","index":396,"end_time":1686.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1681.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So not so almost similar to what we were going to do with the BioCatch campaign before we kind of toss that to the side pretty quickly.","index":397,"end_time":1693.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1686.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There may be some opportunity to play on different technologies in the space, maybe even doing some video ads or maybe even bringing on and utilizing some of the clips from the conversations that Michael is having on the podcast.","index":398,"end_time":1708.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1694.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Podcast as well.","index":399,"end_time":1709.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1709,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Another couple options are creating landing pages that are more comparison based or even showing, you know, possibly just better features over tools like BioCatch and Threat Matrix and a few others.","index":400,"end_time":1724.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1712.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then for the Q2 audience, obviously as you guys give us some more target account information, we''ll be able to expand a little bit there, knowing it is still likely going to be a relatively small audience that we''re bidding on.","index":401,"end_time":1736.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1725.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So competition is just always going to be a bit more expensive in that space.","index":402,"end_time":1739.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1736.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we anticipate it''s going to be pricey.","index":403,"end_time":1741.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1739.75,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":404,"end_time":1742.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1742.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''m not sure if, if Q2 would offer any sort of budget incentive for ads if you partnered on anything.","index":405,"end_time":1749.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1742.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just some ideas.","index":406,"end_time":1751.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1750.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I doubt Q2 would.","index":407,"end_time":1753.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1752.07,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"They''re.","index":408,"end_time":1757.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1757.03,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"They''re different.","index":409,"end_time":1758.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1757.47,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Alloy might.","index":410,"end_time":1760.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1759.99,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Alloy might.","index":411,"end_time":1766.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1765.6,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Kate might.","index":412,"end_time":1766.96,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1766.32,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"It might.","index":413,"end_time":1767.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1767.36,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":414,"end_time":1768.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1767.92,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Kate.","index":415,"end_time":1768.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1768.32,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We should keep that in our back pocket.","index":416,"end_time":1770.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1768.6,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So we asked them if they would be open to co sponsoring.","index":417,"end_time":1774.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1770.32,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"They''re a Q2 partner as well.","index":418,"end_time":1776.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1774.4,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And we asked them if they might be open to co sponsoring Happy Hour at the conference with us.","index":419,"end_time":1782.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1777.2,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And so I think that''s the, the gateway drug into shared cost type stuff.","index":420,"end_time":1788,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1782.8,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"But would, I''d be curious to see if they would be open to doing like a joint go to market campaign that has, you know, shared costs and shared shared outcomes.","index":421,"end_time":1799.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1788,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, that might be.","index":422,"end_time":1801.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1800.01,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"That might be.","index":423,"end_time":1802.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1801.77,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"That''s something that''s on my mind for sure.","index":424,"end_time":1804.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1802.65,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I do not want to do comparison pages.","index":425,"end_time":1808.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1806.57,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"They commoditize our product set and put us into a position where we simplify the technical capabilities that we have in a way that makes it hard to differentiate.","index":426,"end_time":1823.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1809.53,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So yeah, I''ll keep fighting that.","index":427,"end_time":1827.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1823.58,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Like I might lose that fight.","index":428,"end_time":1828.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1827.34,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I''ve lost it once or twice before.","index":429,"end_time":1830.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1828.7,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"They never, I''ve never found them to work in complex enterprise tech.","index":430,"end_time":1836.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1831.58,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, especially I mean even talking to the sales team, it seems like most of the conversations they go better if there''s an actual conversation.","index":431,"end_time":1843.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1837.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":432,"end_time":1843.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1843.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because a feature for feature stack up is going to be very similar between threatmark and a bunch of other tools versus like showing them the platform.","index":433,"end_time":1850.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1843.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":434,"end_time":1850.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1850.2,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, so, so that''s not, that''s not where I want to put my, put my bets, but where we are putting a big bet and, and this will factor into a lot of the work that we''re doing together is.","index":435,"end_time":1864.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1850.68,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I probably should have mentioned this earlier.","index":436,"end_time":1866.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1865.48,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We are working on selecting a third party research company to run a survey for us to get some primary research and develop our own, you know, state of fraud report type thing.","index":437,"end_time":1883.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1867.72,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So not only will that be a tremendous asset from a gated asset perspective and from an advertising perspective, etc, but I think it''s one of the things that I want to do in there.","index":438,"end_time":1898.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1884.68,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We''ll see if we''re successful.","index":439,"end_time":1900.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1899.49,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"One of the things I want to do is I want to send the same survey that we send to the broad market to all of our customers and get a threat mark is better metric that has enough data behind it that we can use in those types of scenarios where we would have done a comparison landing page.","index":440,"end_time":1919.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1900.45,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So saying A versus B, saying this is how our customers thrive and showing them versus the balance of the market.","index":441,"end_time":1928.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1919.33,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":442,"end_time":1930,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1928.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This may be similar to what you''re talking about or maybe depending on the data that''s collected, not as straightforward but one thing that we''ve really seen work is that tangible interactive document asset that someone can download.","index":443,"end_time":1942.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1930,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So for example, one of our clients developed based on all their own data an industry benchmark report.","index":444,"end_time":1947.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1942.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So they work with companies in construction, health care, X, Y and Z.","index":445,"end_time":1951.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1947.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If an HR person goes and fills out a few Quick questions on a page about, you know, their PTO policies and things like that.","index":446,"end_time":1960.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1952.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It will, once they hit submit, it will create a customized PDF with where they sit in the competitive landscape, below average, average or above average.","index":447,"end_time":1970.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1960.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then also give them some tips and point them towards a sales call.","index":448,"end_time":1973.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1970.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I don''t know if that could be a similar thing we can think about here.","index":449,"end_time":1976.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1973.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, like, I think, I think that would be like a phase two, but that myself before and it tends to be pretty successful.","index":450,"end_time":1982.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1976.08,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Well, so yeah.","index":451,"end_time":1984.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1982.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":452,"end_time":1985.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1984.85,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":453,"end_time":1986.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1985.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Very exciting.","index":454,"end_time":1987.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1986.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":455,"end_time":1988.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1988.29,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"All right.","index":456,"end_time":1990.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1989.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that is everything that we had.","index":457,"end_time":1992.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1990.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Was there anything that you guys were hoping to chat through that we did.","index":458,"end_time":1994.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1992.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not talk through today?","index":459,"end_time":1995.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1994.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Two things top of mind for me would be we are sitting on the for disruption white paper.","index":460,"end_time":2008.77,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2000.93,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"We did have some feedback from Macau.","index":461,"end_time":2010.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2009.01,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Greg and I haven''t spoken about it yet actually about whether or not we need to do anything about it or we think we can progress.","index":462,"end_time":2018.05,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2010.93,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I need to, I need to respond to that.","index":463,"end_time":2019.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2018.37,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Let me, let me take that one.","index":464,"end_time":2021.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2019.89,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay.","index":465,"end_time":2021.89,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2021.33,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Because.","index":466,"end_time":2022.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2022.29,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Might mean that we need to do another iteration.","index":467,"end_time":2028.13,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2024.49,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I''m not sure.","index":468,"end_time":2028.69,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2028.13,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I don''t think so.","index":469,"end_time":2029.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2028.93,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay.","index":470,"end_time":2030.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2030.13,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And then the second point was around getting the carousel of the white of the website updated.","index":471,"end_time":2038.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2032.85,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"And if we can get that live at some point.","index":472,"end_time":2040.97,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2038.81,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I can''t remember where we left it, if we were waiting on final feedback from us.","index":473,"end_time":2044.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2041.05,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, I think we sent over an updated version, but I''ll check.","index":474,"end_time":2047.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2044.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Obviously we had some rotating time off last week, so.","index":475,"end_time":2052.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2048.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll check and I think we got that updated.","index":476,"end_time":2054.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2052.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll send it over to you guys.","index":477,"end_time":2055.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2054.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think just let us know where it sits and then we can try one out.","index":478,"end_time":2063.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2058.49,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":479,"end_time":2064.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2063.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":480,"end_time":2067.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2066.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Anything else?","index":481,"end_time":2068.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2067.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think that''s all.","index":482,"end_time":2070.83,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2069.71,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"One thing on my radar that might pop up.","index":483,"end_time":2077.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2073.39,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We''re going to start working through some new what, what I would call like a first call deck.","index":484,"end_time":2084.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2080.19,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So it''s like a pitch deck kind of thing.","index":485,"end_time":2085.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2084.15,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I might need some creative assistance on that.","index":486,"end_time":2088.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2086.59,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"It won''t be a heavy lift.","index":487,"end_time":2092.069,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2090.309,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"It''ll be pretty lightweight.","index":488,"end_time":2093.989,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2092.069,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Also another thing that I think is interesting to share with this group because as we''re talking about brand, I''m trying to calibrate on like what, what we want the creative vision for the brand to look like and what Michal really, you know, we''ll find to be interesting.","index":489,"end_time":2114.549,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2094.629,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And I take a look at the zero Fox website.","index":490,"end_time":2121.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2115.35,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"They''re.","index":491,"end_time":2123.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2122.55,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"They''re not like a pseudo competitor of ours really more cyber security.","index":492,"end_time":2125.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2123.11,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"But the, the creative I think on there is resonating with him well and not super far off from.","index":493,"end_time":2136.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2127.35,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"From where we are.","index":494,"end_time":2138.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2137.11,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I think it''s just a little bit more polished and, like, one of the things that they''re doing.","index":495,"end_time":2143.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2138.39,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Let me just pull it up really quick.","index":496,"end_time":2145.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2143.92,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We''re.","index":497,"end_time":2147.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2147.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll just say we''re very familiar with this brand.","index":498,"end_time":2150.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2148.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, are you?","index":499,"end_time":2152.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2151.44,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"That''s funny.","index":500,"end_time":2154.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2153.28,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I''ll leave it at that.","index":501,"end_time":2158.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2157.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, fair enough.","index":502,"end_time":2159.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2158.96,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So, yeah, I thought, too, like, looking at, like, some of these brand elements are pretty consistent with what we''ve been doing with the podcast, so there''s, like, a nice, nice path towards that as well.","index":503,"end_time":2183.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2162.32,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So I''d be curious, if you''re very familiar with this brand, how you might think integrating some of the elements of.","index":504,"end_time":2192.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2183.73,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Of that brand design into.","index":505,"end_time":2194.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2193.17,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"To what we''re doing.","index":506,"end_time":2195.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2195.01,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":507,"end_time":2197.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2196.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think we have all the source files, maybe.","index":508,"end_time":2200.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2198.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sounds like you might.","index":509,"end_time":2202.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2201.65,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":510,"end_time":2205.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2204.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we could definitely come up with some ideas there.","index":511,"end_time":2206.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2205.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I just.","index":512,"end_time":2207.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2207.17,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I think it was the first.","index":513,"end_time":2209.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2207.97,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"First one that I kind of was like, oh, I''ve got a thread I can pull on that sounds like I understand directionally, like, where we''re trying to go from that perspective, so.","index":514,"end_time":2220.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2209.49,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":515,"end_time":2222.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2221.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":516,"end_time":2223.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2223.02,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"All right, well, great catching up with you guys.","index":517,"end_time":2225.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2223.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll send over some updates and.","index":518,"end_time":2227.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2225.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Really excited for this year.","index":519,"end_time":2230.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2229.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think we''ve been great.","index":520,"end_time":2232.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2230.94,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Got a lot of momentum, a lot of good stuff.","index":521,"end_time":2234.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2232.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":522,"end_time":2235.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2234.78,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Cool.","index":523,"end_time":2235.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2235.42,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"All right, see you guys.","index":524,"end_time":2237.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2236.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thanks, Colin.","index":525,"end_time":2238.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2237.42,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Thanks, Nina.","index":526,"end_time":2238.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2238.1,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Bye.","index":527,"end_time":2239.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2238.7,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"}],"dateString":"2026-01-05T15:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/84564648866?pwd=JR6eWxlxKbgogzCqTNUawSLUUhQoEa.1","participants":["colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,kate.burwood@threatmark.com,gregory.smith@threatmark.com,nina.belina@marketersindemand.com,iulia.lungu@threatmark.com","kate.burwood@threatmark.com","gregory.smith@threatmark.com","nina.belina@marketersindemand.com","iulia.lungu@threatmark.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KDNJ78BN52MGXT4CQ6GEA0H1","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.95,"bullets":["Confirmed $12M marketing-sourced pipeline goal with supporting metrics: 263 SALs and 60% ABM engagement.","Greg approved migration to USD ad accounts; Colin to assist LinkedIn ownership transition.","Team progressing on Banking Fraud Summit website; Greg requested migration effort estimate ASAP.","Eight event sponsorships confirmed; creative refresh needed after weak prior booth impact.","Propensity selected for intent data to scale ABM; integration with HubSpot planned."],"highlights":[{"quote":"We will have more budget for ad spend.","speaker":"Greg Smith"},{"quote":"12 million in marketing source pipeline. That''s it. That''s all we want.","speaker":"Greg Smith"},{"quote":"LinkedIn Ads has proved to be a great channel for Threatmark.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"}],"topics":["budget","abm","events","pipeline","delivery","branding"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-05T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Budget and Advertising Strategy**\n\nThe team decided to maintain the current advertising budget while planning to increase overall ad spend in 2026, with a new focus on regional budget granularity for better tracking (06:31).  \n- Greg Smith emphasized carving the budget by region to improve visibility and control over spending.  \n- They agreed to convert all ad accounts to US dollars to reduce currency risk, with Greg leading the effort to transfer LinkedIn ad ownership and re-verify Google Ads in USD (09:26).  \n- This currency shift moves exchange risk to the CFO, easing financial management.  \n- The change will involve some administrative overhead but is expected to streamline future budgeting and reporting.  \n\nPlans to integrate an intent data provider, **Propensity**, were confirmed to support a pivot toward Account-Based Marketing (ABM) (07:58).  \n- Propensity was chosen over costlier options like 6sense due to better pricing and suitability for targeting about **1,000 accounts** rather than tens of thousands.  \n- The platform will help craft LinkedIn audiences based on target accounts, serving as a bottom-funnel advertising tool alongside broader brand awareness campaigns.  \n- Integrating intent signals into HubSpot will establish a more precise ABM structure, improving targeting and engagement measurement.  \n\nAd performance showed rising competition on Google, with brands like **Barracuda, MasterCard,** and **Solace** bidding on the Threatmark brand name, driving up cost-per-click (23:02).  \n- Despite this, LinkedIn ads generated over **65 leads from a $25,000 spend** in 2025, confirming its effectiveness as a lead source (27:11).  \n- Lead source tracking via HubSpot fields is functioning well, enabling better attribution and campaign optimizations (24:37).  \n\n## **Website and HubSpot Migration**\n\nThe first phase of the website migration will focus on the **Banking Fraud Summit site** as a proof of concept to validate the HubSpot platform before proceeding with the full Threatmark site migration (10:46).  \n- Greg requested an estimate of the effort required for the migration, emphasizing a straightforward copy-paste of content without branding or design changes (11:49).  \n- Threatmark will provide access to the current WordPress instance and source files to facilitate a smooth transition (12:03).  \n- Stage two involving the main site will require a more thoughtful redesign rather than a direct copy, contingent on the success of phase one (12:46).  \n- Colin committed to providing a migration quote promptly to support scheduling.  \n\n## **Events and Marketing Goals**\n\nThe marketing team plans to sponsor **eight trade shows** and run several proprietary events in 2026, with creative production efforts varying by event (13:20).  \n- Reach Desk has been onboarded as the swag provider to enhance event merchandising and engagement.  \n- Greg identified a need to improve branding consistency and creative quality, noting prior event materials were visually weak due to print issues and loose brand guidelines (14:44).  \n- Event materials for March sponsorships must be finalized by the end of January to meet deadlines (15:19).  \n\nKey marketing goals for 2026 include building a **$12 million marketing sourced pipeline**, which is the primary success metric (16:58).  \n- They aim to establish **500+ target accounts** for ABM with a **60% engagement rate**, sourced from intent data integration (18:30).  \n- The ABM program targets generating at least **32 qualified opportunities**, roughly half of the pipeline goal (18:50).  \n- Lead goals include **263 sales accepted leads** from marketing, with an aim to double the LinkedIn following and improve organic search volume by **10%** (19:56, 20:04).  \n- Greg acknowledged that while other metrics exist, the $12 million pipeline remains the central focus.  \n\n## **Content and Brand Development**\n\nThe team is preparing for two podcast episodes, including the **Kelly Paxton episode scheduled for February 7 at 6am Eastern**, with final guest title verification pending (22:38).  \n- Kate ThreatMark is managing guest info and will confirm details to proceed with production (22:41).  \n\nGreg shared plans to develop a new **first call pitch deck**, requesting creative support for a lightweight design effort (34:33).  \n- He also highlighted inspiration from the **Zero Fox website** for evolving Threatmark’s brand creative, noting it resonates well with leadership and aligns with podcast branding (35:47).  \n- Colin confirmed access to source files and willingness to develop ideas incorporating elements from Zero Fox’s polished style (36:36).  \n- This brand refinement aims to strengthen visual identity and support broader marketing efforts.  \n\n## **Strategic Marketing Initiatives and Competitive Positioning**\n\nThe team rejected the use of product comparison landing pages to avoid commoditizing Threatmark’s technology and diluting differentiation (29:27).  \n- Greg stressed the complexity of their enterprise tech makes simple feature comparisons ineffective and potentially harmful.  \n- Instead, they plan to commission a **third-party research survey** to create an original **State of Fraud report** as a gated asset and advertising tool (30:50).  \n- This report will also include a proprietary Threatmark customer metric to highlight competitive advantages without direct comparison.  \n- Colin suggested a potential phase two interactive benchmark tool, allowing prospects to input data and receive tailored insights, proven effective in other industries (32:08).  \n- This approach aligns with strategic goals to create differentiated, data-driven marketing assets that build credibility and drive engagement.  \n\n## **Operational and Creative Process Enhancements**\n\nGreg noted ongoing monitoring of creative performance and A/B testing, with top-performing ads focusing on **fraud liability** and **stop paying for scam losses** messaging (26:52).  \n- The brand awareness campaign is low volume but maintains a low cost-per-click, supporting broader visibility goals (27:02).  \n\nKate raised two operational priorities: progressing the **For Disruption white paper** based on feedback and updating the **website carousel**, which is ready for final review and deployment (33:20).  \n- Greg took responsibility for responding to feedback on the white paper to determine if revisions are necessary (33:38).  \n- Colin will verify carousel status and circulate updated files for testing and launch (34:04).  \n\nGreg also flagged the need for earlier notice on new product launches to prepare marketing materials, requesting at least a two-week lead time to optimize creative and promotional planning (26:39).  \n- This request supports smoother event and campaign execution aligned with product updates.","outline":null,"keywords":["ABM","Budget 2026","Website Migration","Lead Generation","Events & Sponsorships","Brand & Creative Vision"],"overview":"- **Budget Focus:** Maintain current ad budget, increase regional granularity for better tracking in 2026.  \n- **Ad Accounts Strategy:** Convert all ad accounts to USD to reduce currency risk, simplifying budgeting and reporting.  \n- **Event Plans:** Sponsor eight trade shows in 2026, finalize materials by January for March sponsorships.  \n- **Marketing Goals:** Aim for $12 million pipeline, 500+ target accounts, with 263 sales accepted leads from marketing.  \n- **Content Development:** Prepare for two podcast episodes, create a new pitch deck, and refine brand identity.  \n- **Research Initiatives:** Commission a State of Fraud report to differentiate and showcase Threatmark''s competitive advantage.","action_items":"\n**Greg Smith**\nShare detailed 2026 ad spend regional budget breakdown with Colin Costigan (06:31)\nProceed with repayment and transfer of LinkedIn ad account ownership to ThreatMark business manager and invite partners (09:26)\nProvide list of upcoming events with deadlines and creative requirements by end of current month (15:21)\nConfirm next steps on the For Disruption white paper feedback and respond accordingly (33:38)\nShare updates on Propensity integration and requests needing assistance (21:56)\nFollow up with team and Michal on creative vision aligning with ZeroFox inspiration (35:47)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nProvide an estimate and timeline for the Banking Fraud Summit site migration based on a 1:1 copy approach (11:49)\nReview final feedback on website carousel and launch update (33:42)\nPrepare ideas for branded Q2 booth items and marketing assets (26:23)\nDeliver detailed updates and wrap-up message including event schedules and ABM list requirements (21:20)\n\n**Kate ThreatMark**\nConfirm full title of guest for podcast episode as soon as received (22:38)\nCoordinate with Greg to review For Disruption white paper feedback and determine if revisions are needed (33:38)\nContinue communication for final feedback related to website carousel update (33:42)\nCoordinate with team on creative materials needed for upcoming sponsorships and swag (14:44)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"68aa76df-de32-488f-b724-72400a97a377","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
