    '{"id":"01KDDPEG315TPJJ2S7GDGJ87EP","title":"Data Assessment // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **ABM Campaign Strategy and Targeting**\n\nThe team agreed to focus the ABM campaign on **IT consulting firms** facing operational pain points, especially around **delivery, utilization, and staffing**, to improve lead quality and conversion (06:07).\n\n- **Colin Costigan** highlighted that deals mostly come from companies with operational challenges rather than those just searching for software, so the campaign targets roles responsible for delivery and resource management (06:45).\n    - Messaging will emphasize CV and skills visibility, RFP execution, and lightly include AI to address emerging market interest.\n    - The campaign will avoid broad software buyer audiences and instead focus on pain points to increase engagement and qualification.\n    - The rationale is to align with customer needs and increase campaign ROI by targeting the most relevant decision makers.\n    - This approach reflects a shift toward solution-driven marketing rather than product-driven outreach.\n\n- The **contact list** was refined to approximately **555 contacts**, primarily from IT consulting companies, aiming to expand closer to **1,000 contacts** for greater reach and campaign velocity (10:59).\n    - The team plans to enrich contacts with email addresses using tools like Apollo and ZoomInfo while maintaining low bounce rates through server verification.\n    - Contacts span multiple offices per company to maximize exposure and potential conversion across regions (13:54).\n    - **Axel Völker** and others will review titles and companies for relevance, removing non-IT consulting firms like Bonial and others mismatched by LinkedIn classifications.\n    - German job titles were added to increase list size and accuracy, supporting regional targeting.\n\n- The campaign will personalize content based on pain points such as CV skills management and RFP responsiveness, using dynamic tokens for tailored messaging per contact (19:55).\n    - Education-focused emails will integrate success stories and testimonials to build credibility.\n    - Initial outreach will be awareness-based, gently pushing for demos to avoid overwhelming prospects early.\n\n## **Campaign Execution and Assets**\n\nThe plan includes sending emails from **Bettina’s profile** with warming efforts already underway, complemented by LinkedIn messages to increase touchpoints and engagement (23:14).\n\n- Six email addresses across three domains have been set up for sending under Bettina’s name to diversify outreach and maintain deliverability (23:18).\n    - Bettina’s LinkedIn profile will be connected to the campaign platform by Monday, with support offered for setup to ensure smooth launch.\n    - Initial email volume will start with a few hundred per week, scaling up as engagement allows.\n\n- Colin will share all campaign documents, including emails, contact lists, and LinkedIn copy, for review and translation with the local marketing team to ensure regional relevance and quality (22:42).\n    - Feedback will be collected via links to allow iterative refinements before final launch.\n    - Ads will be written and translated once email copy is approved to maintain a consistent multi-channel approach.\n\n- The existing **landing page** will be redesigned to improve information hierarchy and add new CTAs, incorporating explainer videos and integration highlights to boost conversion rates (20:39).\n    - The aim is to better showcase how Desi Dollo solves operational friction by structuring skills and project experience behind the scenes.\n    - The redesign will be tested with the ABM audience to measure impact before wider rollout.\n\n## **Product Offering and Market Expansion Strategy**\n\nThe team discussed exploring new offerings for smaller IT services companies and internal IT teams to increase profitability and market coverage beyond current IT consulting targets (24:23).\n\n- **Axel Völker** noted that companies with fewer than **50 employees**, and even some up to a few hundred, currently generate limited profit from software sales alone, suggesting a need for bundled software and consulting packages (25:00).\n    - These packages would help smaller companies lacking complex systems by providing a consulting operating system or basic project management solutions.\n    - The goal is to create a service offering that integrates with their existing workflows to increase adoption and value.\n\n- A potential **bench management as a service** model was proposed to help clients manage underutilized staff and increase billable utilization (26:41).\n    - This service would provide hands-on resource management with the eventual goal of automating the process using AI.\n    - The approach offers immediate value by reducing bench time while preparing for future AI-driven efficiencies.\n\n- Colin and Axel agreed AI will play a crucial role in the product’s evolution, with plans to start with a “black box” human-assisted resource manager service to build trust before rolling out AI automation (27:02).\n    - Colin emphasized the market’s increasing acceptance of AI in operational roles and suggested using demo videos to illustrate value.\n    - This phased approach balances innovation with customer comfort and adoption challenges.\n\n- The expansion discussion will continue internally to define specific offerings and messaging for these new segments before launching campaigns targeting them (24:23).\n\n## **Operational and Technical Details**\n\nThe team confirmed that contact enrichment uses multiple data sources and validation processes to keep **bounce rates low**, ensuring high campaign deliverability and engagement (13:24).\n\n- Colin described the technical enrichment process involving **seven different tools** with server bounce tests to maintain list hygiene (13:32).\n    - This reduces wasted sends and protects domain reputation, which is critical for campaign success.\n\n- The integration of LinkedIn outreach alongside emails is designed to increase touch frequency and contextual relevance, leveraging Bettina’s profile for personalized contact (22:39).\n    - Instructions and support will be provided to Bettina for connecting her LinkedIn profile to the outreach platform by Monday (23:57).\n    - Eli’s prior experience with setup will assist troubleshooting if needed.\n\n- The campaign infrastructure includes multiple domain email addresses to spread sending volume and reduce risk of deliverability issues (23:18).\n    - These operational details reflect attention to scaling the campaign while maintaining quality and engagement.\n\n## **Market Positioning and Competitive Insights**\n\nThe focus remains firmly on **IT consulting and IT services** as the core market, with internal IT groups as a secondary target once the initial campaign shows traction (28:56).\n\n- Axel stressed that the current market knowledge is strongest in IT consulting, and expanding beyond requires more research and offering refinement (28:56).\n    - Internal IT teams in larger companies are promising targets due to likely budget availability for tools.\n    - The team will monitor results and adjust market segments accordingly.\n\n- The competitive landscape includes emerging AI-driven resource management tools, making it important to clearly communicate Desi Dollo’s value and differentiation (27:52).\n    - The campaign’s messaging aims to balance AI innovation with operational pain points to appeal broadly.\n    - Early education and demo content are designed to ease adoption and build trust.\n\n- Current client base does not include automotive OEMs or manufacturing, so any expansion into those industries will require distinct messaging and possibly different campaign tracks (29:32).\n    - The team agreed to keep the initial campaign focused to maximize impact before broadening scope.\n\n## **Timeline and Next Steps**\n\nThe campaign is set to launch shortly after **Bettina returns to the office on Monday**, with initial outreach planned to start at a controlled pace and then scale (23:51).\n\n- Colin will send the campaign assets, including instructions to connect LinkedIn profiles, by Monday to enable a smooth start (23:57).\n    - Translation and feedback cycles for emails and ads will happen immediately afterward to finalize content.\n    - Ads will be created and translated only after email copy approval to ensure consistency (21:40).\n\n- The landing page redesign and testing will follow the initial campaign launch, aiming to incorporate new explainer videos and CTAs (20:39).\n    - Success will be measured by engagement metrics and conversion rates from the ABM audience.\n\n- The internal discussion about expanding offerings to smaller IT companies and internal IT teams will continue, with no immediate campaign planned until the product and messaging are defined (24:23).\n    - AI-driven services development is a parallel long-term effort that will shape future product direction and marketing.","outline":null,"keywords":["ABM campaign","IT consulting","contact list enrichment","bench management","operational pain points","AI automation"],"overview":"- **ABM Campaign Focus:** Target IT consulting firms facing operational issues to improve lead quality and conversion rates. \n\n- **Contact List Strategy:** Refined to 555 contacts, aiming to reach 1,000, enhancing regional targeting with enriched data.\n\n- **Campaign Personalization:** Content will address specific pain points with dynamic tokens for tailored messaging and success stories to build credibility.\n\n- **New Service Offerings:** Exploring bundled packages for smaller firms, combining software and consulting to increase adoption and profitability.\n\n- **AI Integration Plan:** Begin with a human-assisted service model, gradually introducing AI to enhance efficiency in resource management. \n\n- **Launch Timeline:** Campaign set to start after Bettina returns, with assets shared for testing and feedback before broader rollout.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nUpload the ABM campaign plan to SharePoint and Pulse for team access (07:24)\nRemove irrelevant companies such as Media Klan, Manage Now, Bonial, and incorrectly classified firms from the contact list (11:49)\nSend contact list and email copy to the team for review and translation feedback (18:44)\nShare instructions with Bettina for connecting her LinkedIn profile to Hay Reach and provide support if needed (23:56)\nUpload all campaign documents to Markup for markup and comments (28:29)\n\n**Axel Völker**\nReview and provide feedback on the contact list, especially concerning job titles and companies for filtering (11:23)\nDiscuss internally potential expanded offerings for smaller IT services companies including possible bundles of software and consulting services (25:55)\nCoordinate with team on translating and adjusting emails/landing pages and share feedback (22:35)\n\n**Bettina**\nWarm up and execute LinkedIn messaging using Hay Reach platform once profile is connected (23:15)\n\n**Eli**\nAssist Bettina with Hay Reach LinkedIn integration and provide support as needed (23:56)\n\n**Guille Santana**\nSupport review of contact list and campaign targeting strategy as needed \n"},"duration":30.209999084472656,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Guille Santana"},{"id":1,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":2,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":3,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":4,"name":"Axel Völker"},{"id":5,"name":"Colin Costigan"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Morning, Colleen.","index":0,"end_time":259.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":258.66,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Good morning.","index":1,"end_time":260.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":259.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Happy New Year.","index":2,"end_time":262.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":261.46,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Happy New Year.","index":3,"end_time":264.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":263.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How you doing?","index":4,"end_time":264.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":264.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":5,"end_time":266.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":265.7,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":6,"end_time":267.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":266.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":7,"end_time":268.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":267.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Little sick still, but no, I''ll be all right.","index":8,"end_time":272.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":268.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s Friday.","index":9,"end_time":276.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":275.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, at least.","index":10,"end_time":277.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":276.9,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Hi.","index":11,"end_time":287.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":286.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, Hendrik.","index":12,"end_time":288.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":287.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":13,"end_time":289.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":288.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m good.","index":14,"end_time":291.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":290.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":15,"end_time":292.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":291.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":16,"end_time":293.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":292.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hi, max.","index":17,"end_time":306.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":305.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You guys enjoy the last few days?","index":18,"end_time":313.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":311.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s great.","index":19,"end_time":316.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":315.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Always good to get a reset.","index":20,"end_time":318.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":317.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, Happy New Year.","index":21,"end_time":335.42,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":333.98,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Hey.","index":22,"end_time":336.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":335.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Happy New Year, Axel.","index":23,"end_time":337.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":336.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":24,"end_time":337.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":337.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey.","index":25,"end_time":337.98,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":337.58,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"First meeting of the New Year.","index":26,"end_time":340.22,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":338.3,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yes.","index":27,"end_time":341.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":340.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":28,"end_time":344.3,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":343.9,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Oh, Henrik is also there.","index":29,"end_time":346.22,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":344.78,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay, good.","index":30,"end_time":347.06,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":346.22,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I didn''t know.","index":31,"end_time":347.58,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":347.06,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I saw no one because I''m in the office and no one is in the office, so I saw no one is in.","index":32,"end_time":352.22,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":347.58,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":33,"end_time":354.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":354.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I see Eli''s joining.","index":34,"end_time":357.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":356.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do we have anyone else joining today on our side?","index":35,"end_time":361.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":357.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t think.","index":36,"end_time":361.89,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":361.25,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay, everybody.","index":37,"end_time":364.05,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":362.21,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Happy New Year.","index":38,"end_time":364.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":364.05,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah, Happy New Year.","index":39,"end_time":366.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":365.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Happy New Year.","index":40,"end_time":366.97,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":366.17,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yes.","index":41,"end_time":367.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":366.97,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Very excited.","index":42,"end_time":368.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":367.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ve got a few big documents to go through today, everything that we''ve put together for the new ABM campaign.","index":43,"end_time":374.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":368.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"In the Docs region.","index":44,"end_time":375.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":374.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I''ll be sharing some assets.","index":45,"end_time":376.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":375.409,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"With you guys for translation and review.","index":46,"end_time":378.77,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":376.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"After this as well.","index":47,"end_time":380.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":379.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, good.","index":48,"end_time":382.77,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":381.41,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Right.","index":49,"end_time":385.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":385.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just adjust my screens.","index":50,"end_time":389.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":387.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, first, starting out with the ABM plan.","index":51,"end_time":392.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":390.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Axel, you''ve seen this document before in.","index":52,"end_time":395.14,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":392.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Max, I know we walked through kind.","index":53,"end_time":396.7,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":395.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Of a light version of the last.","index":54,"end_time":397.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":396.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"One when we met last week, but.","index":55,"end_time":400.22,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":397.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''Ll be sending this over for you guys to review.","index":56,"end_time":402.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":400.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ve got some of the highlights in.","index":57,"end_time":404.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":402.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Here, but essentially, as you guys have seen before, this details out almost every.","index":58,"end_time":407.66,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":404.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Aspect of our campaign, from who we''re.","index":59,"end_time":409.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":407.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Targeting, how we''re communicating with them, how.","index":60,"end_time":411.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":409.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Does scoring them work, where are they.","index":61,"end_time":413.91,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":411.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Going, what counts as a qualified lead.","index":62,"end_time":416.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":413.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Et cetera, and what are we even.","index":63,"end_time":418.51,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":416.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Offering in this campaign?","index":64,"end_time":419.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":418.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so that document has a table.","index":65,"end_time":422.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":419.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Of contents to break it down in a much simpler way, as well as an executive overview.","index":66,"end_time":426.43,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":422.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But, Max, you''ll remember all the tools.","index":67,"end_time":429.11,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":427.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Even that we were going through are.","index":68,"end_time":431.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":429.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Detailed in this document to show how an engagement layer works versus event management versus data management.","index":69,"end_time":437.95,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":431.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So all of that is broken down in here.","index":70,"end_time":439.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":438.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":71,"end_time":441.64,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":441.36,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Is that in the share.","index":72,"end_time":443.36,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":441.64,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"The SharePoint.","index":73,"end_time":444.32,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":443.36,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I can add it to the SharePoint after this call.","index":74,"end_time":446.24,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":444.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it''ll be available in Pulse as well.","index":75,"end_time":448.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":446.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, good.","index":76,"end_time":452.88,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":450.24,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"All right, I''ll add that to SharePoint.","index":77,"end_time":456.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":454.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so, you know, at a high level, you know, we''ve had a lot of conversations, and the deals that it.","index":78,"end_time":464.56,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":458.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Seems like you guys are able to.","index":79,"end_time":465.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":464.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Win along with largely come from companies feeling an operational pain point, not ones.","index":80,"end_time":470.43,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":465.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That are just searching for a software solution.","index":81,"end_time":472.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":470.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"In general.","index":82,"end_time":472.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":472.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we want to focus on IT consulting.","index":83,"end_time":475.23,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":472.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Firms that are feeling pain and looking to scale, and especially roles that are.","index":84,"end_time":480.47,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":475.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Accountable for delivery, utilization, staffing.","index":85,"end_time":483.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":480.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We talked about that word bench, even though we''re going to test using the.","index":86,"end_time":486.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":483.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Exact word bench or not, and having our messaging really anchored in CVs skills.","index":87,"end_time":492.74,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":486.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Visibility, RFP, execution, while talking also about AI, even though we''re kind of still figuring out exactly how to message that value proposition.","index":88,"end_time":501.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":492.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so does all that still feel good?","index":89,"end_time":507.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":504.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And like we''re picking up the right pain points of the docs region, as.","index":90,"end_time":511.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":507.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Far as you guys know.","index":91,"end_time":512.46,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":511.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, obviously, before we hop in, we don''t know the exact science of everyone''s brain.","index":92,"end_time":516.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":512.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":93,"end_time":517.58,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":517.02,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So benchmade probably become a bigger issue because there''s companies that have a bench issue or have people on the bench, so.","index":94,"end_time":527.71,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":517.74,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Because not all in this.","index":95,"end_time":530.71,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":528.43,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So some industries have big problems, like automotive.","index":96,"end_time":533.35,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":530.71,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And if you do a lot of consulting for automotive, you definitely have a bench problem.","index":97,"end_time":538.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":533.35,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So.","index":98,"end_time":538.909,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":538.51,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":99,"end_time":540.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":540.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I saw a mix of.","index":100,"end_time":542.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":540.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not everyone was purely IT consulting and IT services.","index":101,"end_time":545.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":542.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"In the list that you had sent.","index":102,"end_time":546.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":545.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Over, Axel, there were some engineering consultants, some automotive as well.","index":103,"end_time":553.24,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":546.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So kind of wanted to know, like, are we.","index":104,"end_time":556.28,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":553.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are we able to expand our net.","index":105,"end_time":558.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":557,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If we did have like a smaller.","index":106,"end_time":560.16,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":558.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Campaign on the side for not IT focused?","index":107,"end_time":563.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":560.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You mean on the.","index":108,"end_time":565.68,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":564.92,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"In the.","index":109,"end_time":565.92,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":565.68,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"In the customer list or which list?","index":110,"end_time":567.56,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":565.92,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, in the customer list.","index":111,"end_time":568.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":567.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The customer list is mostly IT consulting, I would say.","index":112,"end_time":575.03,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":568.8,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We have.","index":113,"end_time":575.75,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":575.11,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We had customers that were not IT consulting, but not a lot of them.","index":114,"end_time":581.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":575.75,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So I think.","index":115,"end_time":583.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":582.55,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I mean, we can.","index":116,"end_time":584.23,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":583.35,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think for this campaign, we should stick with IT consulting, but we were thinking about expanding or offering to other industries.","index":117,"end_time":593.75,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":584.63,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":118,"end_time":594.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":594.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I think we first would have to define the offering there and what the pain points are in the messaging.","index":119,"end_time":601.27,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":594.99,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":120,"end_time":602.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":601.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we use the.","index":121,"end_time":603.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":602.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, you.","index":122,"end_time":607.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":606.51,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"You''re hard to understand.","index":123,"end_time":608.03,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":607.11,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Like, like auto manufacturers, for example.","index":124,"end_time":611.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":608.59,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"You can already hear your.","index":125,"end_time":614.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":613.23,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"There''s what?","index":126,"end_time":615.23,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":614.51,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, there seems to be an issue with your microphone or something.","index":127,"end_time":618.27,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":615.79,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Can you hear me now?","index":128,"end_time":623.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":622.19,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":129,"end_time":623.47,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":623.03,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I thought that the idea was that the auto manufacturing companies had IT teams.","index":130,"end_time":630.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":625.55,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"They likely do have IT teams, but.","index":131,"end_time":634.53,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":633.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They would have different pain points than.","index":132,"end_time":636.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":634.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"An IT consulting firm would be experiencing.","index":133,"end_time":638.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":636.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":134,"end_time":640.21,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":639.81,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":135,"end_time":641.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":641.09,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"But, yeah, Axel, thank you for sharing the list.","index":136,"end_time":647.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":645.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we used the customer list, obviously as a negative, and then used the.","index":137,"end_time":651.09,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":647.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Lost opportunities list to add to.","index":138,"end_time":653.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":651.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We were actually.","index":139,"end_time":654.53,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":653.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We had most of them in our list already, which means that our targeting was pretty good.","index":140,"end_time":658.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":654.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":141,"end_time":659.53,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":659.09,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But yeah, we use those to add a few more to our campaign.","index":142,"end_time":661.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":659.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the next slide I''ll get into.","index":143,"e