nd over.","index":402,"end_time":1439.45,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1437.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The instructions for her to connect her LinkedIn profile to Hay Reach.","index":403,"end_time":1443.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1439.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If she has any questions, I''m happy.","index":404,"end_time":1446.29,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1444.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To hop on a call or anything.","index":405,"end_time":1447.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1446.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Eli, I know you went through that as well, so I know that you.","index":406,"end_time":1451.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1447.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Set up your profile and connected it, so.","index":407,"end_time":1453.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1451.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah, it''s pretty quick.","index":408,"end_time":1456.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1454.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You basically just log into LinkedIn, you.","index":409,"end_time":1459.02,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1456.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Know, once you log into the website.","index":410,"end_time":1460.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1459.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":411,"end_time":1461.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1460.7,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Good, let''s see how it goes.","index":412,"end_time":1465.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1463.5,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And then we, yeah, we.","index":413,"end_time":1466.46,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1465.26,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So currently I, we or I am thinking about our offering and as you mentioned that can we expand bond that maybe so kind of something more to our existing target group or expand the target group like internal IT companies.","index":414,"end_time":1491.65,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1466.78,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But we have to first I think discuss this a bit internally and see how, what options we have.","index":415,"end_time":1498.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1492.29,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Because so currently we''re leaving out a pretty large part of the IIT services companies which is basically companies with below 50 or so people, which we never really, I mean even, even if you sell to them, we''re never really making any, any money with them.","index":416,"end_time":1520.84,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1499.01,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And even companies was below 500 or a few hundred, we are struggling to make that somewhat profitable.","index":417,"end_time":1530.36,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1520.84,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And the question is, should we actually sell them something else like not just software, but some package of software and consulting?","index":418,"end_time":1541.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1532.19,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Because they are, they''re not.","index":419,"end_time":1542.83,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1541.55,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So where it works well with our customers is where we integrate in their systems.","index":420,"end_time":1547.309,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1542.99,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''s larger companies want to do that anyway, smallers don''t want to do that and maybe they don''t even have a CRM or whatever.","index":421,"end_time":1555.47,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1547.63,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So I wonder if you can sell them some package where like we''ll establish some kind of consulting operating system for you.","index":422,"end_time":1566.12,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1557.16,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And it''s a combination of, it''s actually more like a service offering.","index":423,"end_time":1570.4,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1566.28,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, like a professional service.","index":424,"end_time":1571.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1570.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, I think that could be really strong.","index":425,"end_time":1574.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1572.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean a lot of those companies are likely operating.","index":426,"end_time":1577.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1574.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It could be as simple as a.","index":427,"end_time":1578.68,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1577.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Spreadsheet that they''re using to track their teams utilization.","index":428,"end_time":1582.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1578.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It could be just maybe like their basic project management system.","index":429,"end_time":1586.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1583.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, it could be like a Trello type solution.","index":430,"end_time":1589.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1587.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It could be really anything.","index":431,"end_time":1591.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1589.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I think something like that and.","index":432,"end_time":1593.31,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1591.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Layering on, on top of that professional services could definitely be a way to make it more profitable for those smaller sized companies.","index":433,"end_time":1600.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1593.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, or even I thought about maybe something like bench management as a service.","index":434,"end_time":1604.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1601.03,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"You have people on the bench.","index":435,"end_time":1605.83,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1604.55,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We try to manage that bench and get them off the bench because that''s really what is adding a value for them.","index":436,"end_time":1614.08,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1606.39,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Right.","index":437,"end_time":1614.4,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1614.08,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Not A tool that no one is using.","index":438,"end_time":1616.12,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1614.4,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But yeah, we have to think about that a bit.","index":439,"end_time":1618.8,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1616.36,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But maybe there''s some other opportunities.","index":440,"end_time":1622.2,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1618.8,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, very eager to continue that conversation as well as the direction that AI.","index":441,"end_time":1626.4,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1622.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is heading, not only with Desi Dalo, but just in the region as well.","index":442,"end_time":1630.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1626.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that was actually kind of the idea.","index":443,"end_time":1633.88,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1631.64,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So at some point you want to automate all this with AI so you have your virtual resource manager managing your bench and everything instead of some employee.","index":444,"end_time":1643.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1633.88,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But we''re not quite there yet.","index":445,"end_time":1646.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1643.87,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But we could start like a black box.","index":446,"end_time":1650.15,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1647.43,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So we do it for you, and you don''t really care if it''s AI or human.","index":447,"end_time":1654.47,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1650.31,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"You get a human contact.","index":448,"end_time":1656.71,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1655.51,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And then we try to automate it on our side.","index":449,"end_time":1660.39,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1658.15,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So we provide some service that is like a resource manager working for them and then we try to automate that.","index":450,"end_time":1669.15,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1661.67,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":451,"end_time":1670.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1669.95,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We have to.","index":452,"end_time":1671.23,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1670.51,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think there''s a lot of.","index":453,"end_time":1673.87,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1672.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think there''s a lot to.","index":454,"end_time":1675.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1673.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To be said there because I see.","index":455,"end_time":1677.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1675.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A lot of companies coming out with.","index":456,"end_time":1678.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1677.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Their own versions of, you know, smart agents or whatever they''re referring to them as.","index":457,"end_time":1682.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1678.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I think it''s.","index":458,"end_time":1684.71,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1683.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s kind of just where the world.","index":459,"end_time":1685.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1684.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is going, so it''s becoming more normalized.","index":460,"end_time":1687.67,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1685.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And people won''t be as thrown off.","index":461,"end_time":1690.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1687.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I guess, by, oh, AI would be.","index":462,"end_time":1692.42,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1690.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Managing this for me.","index":463,"end_time":1693.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1692.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I think we would just need.","index":464,"end_time":1695.1,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1694.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A test case, maybe a video to.","index":465,"end_time":1697.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1695.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Show for how that can be done.","index":466,"end_time":1699.78,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1697.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I think that that could be.","index":467,"end_time":1701.06,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1699.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A very valuable point to show in.","index":468,"end_time":1702.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1701.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"These emails and ads.","index":469,"end_time":1703.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1702.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":470,"end_time":1705.54,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1705.06,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"All right, good.","index":471,"end_time":1709.22,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1706.5,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":472,"end_time":1710.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1709.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, I will.","index":473,"end_time":1711.22,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1710.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I will upload all of these to.","index":474,"end_time":1713.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1711.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Markup and send them over.","index":475,"end_time":1713.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1713.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":476,"end_time":1714.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1713.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Eli, do you have a question?","index":477,"end_time":1715.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1714.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Don''t you kind of want to see what the market wants a little bit?","index":478,"end_time":1720.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1717.49,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Axel, Like, I know you talked about how, you know, what if there''s, you know, grocery stores or, I don''t know, some things like that in Germany that only require, you know, a few different features to.","index":479,"end_time":1734.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1720.01,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah, we know what the market.","index":480,"end_time":1737.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1736.45,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Basically the market we know is IT consulting and IT services.","index":481,"end_time":1741.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1737.97,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So we''d start with that market.","index":482,"end_time":1742.77,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1741.41,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, I think there''s still a lot of potential in that market, and then we can see how we expand.","index":483,"end_time":1750.16,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1743.68,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So the next market would be internal IT organization of larger companies that are kind of similar.","index":484,"end_time":1756.08,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1750.16,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It''s like internal IT services, but I think let''s start and see how it goes and expand from there.","index":485,"end_time":1764.24,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1756.08,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, and if they have internal IT.","index":486,"end_time":1765.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1764.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Teams, they likely have the budget for.","index":487,"end_time":1767.24,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1765.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A tool as well.","index":488,"end_time":1768.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1767.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, probably.","index":489,"end_time":1771.21,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1770.25,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So we do have some car manufacturing clients now.","index":490,"end_time":1775.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1772.17,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Correct.","index":491,"end_time":1775.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1775.25,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"No, we don''t.","index":492,"end_time":1777.13,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1776.09,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Oh, no, we didn''t.","index":493,"end_time":1778.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1777.21,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Okay.","index":494,"end_time":1779.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1778.81,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"No.","index":495,"end_time":1779.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1779.45,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Got it.","index":496,"end_time":1782.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1781.69,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Any other questions?","index":497,"end_time":1786.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1785.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No.","index":498,"end_time":1789.93,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1789.53,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":499,"end_time":1791.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1790.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, thank you all very much.","index":500,"end_time":1794.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1792.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hope you had a great holiday.","index":501,"end_time":1796.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1794.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Very excited for 2026, and very excited.","index":502,"end_time":1798.93,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1796.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To get this campaign underway.","index":503,"end_time":1800.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1798.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, me too.","index":504,"end_time":1801.27,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1800.47,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"All right.","index":505,"end_time":1801.83,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1801.43,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":506,"end_time":1802.23,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1801.83,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"All right, well, thank you all very much for your time.","index":507,"end_time":1803.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1802.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":508,"end_time":1804.83,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1804.31,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Bye.","index":509,"end_time":1805.35,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1804.83,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"}],"dateString":"2026-01-02T14:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/86344108572?pwd=qdakcUFJbrjywReJlBZ3DxNLrBYqXb.1","participants":["tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,joachim.giesen@uni-jena.de,guille.santana@marketersindemand.com,nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com,voelker@data-assessment.com,bebinger@decidalo.com,osbaldeston@data-assessment.com,pollex@data-assessment.com","tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com","joachim.giesen@uni-jena.de","guille.santana@marketersindemand.com","nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com","voelker@data-assessment.com","bebinger@decidalo.com","osbaldeston@data-assessment.com","pollex@data-assessment.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KDDPEG315TPJJ2S7GDGJ87EP","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Reviewed ABM campaign plan targeting IT consulting firms with clear scoring, messaging, and assets.","Agreed to remove misclassified companies and refine target list with better industry filters.","Proposed creation of new landing page and explainer content to improve messaging and conversion.","Discussed expansion into professional services for small firms to improve profitability.","Aligned on AI opportunities to support future service offerings like bench management as-a-service."],"highlights":[{"quote":"Very excited for 2026, and very excited to get this campaign underway.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"So that is a list for LinkedIn and for email or what is it?","speaker":"Axel Völker"},{"quote":"Yeah, we know what the market... basically the market we know is IT consulting and IT services.","speaker":"Axel Völker"}],"topics":["campaign","targeting","AI","delivery","growth"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-02T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **ABM Campaign Strategy and Targeting**\n\nThe team agreed to focus the ABM campaign on **IT consulting firms** facing operational pain points, especially around **delivery, utilization, and staffing**, to improve lead quality and conversion (06:07).\n\n- **Colin Costigan** highlighted that deals mostly come from companies with operational challenges rather than those just searching for software, so the campaign targets roles responsible for delivery and resource management (06:45).\n    - Messaging will emphasize CV and skills visibility, RFP execution, and lightly include AI to address emerging market interest.\n    - The campaign will avoid broad software buyer audiences and instead focus on pain points to increase engagement and qualification.\n    - The rationale is to align with customer needs and increase campaign ROI by targeting the most relevant decision makers.\n    - This approach reflects a shift toward solution-driven marketing rather than product-driven outreach.\n\n- The **contact list** was refined to approximately **555 contacts**, primarily from IT consulting companies, aiming to expand closer to **1,000 contacts** for greater reach and campaign velocity (10:59).\n    - The team plans to enrich contacts with email addresses using tools like Apollo and ZoomInfo while maintaining low bounce rates through server verification.\n    - Contacts span multiple offices per company to maximize exposure and potential conversion across regions (13:54).\n    - **Axel Völker** and others will review titles and companies for relevance, removing non-IT consulting firms like Bonial and others mismatched by LinkedIn classifications.\n    - German job titles were added to increase list size and accuracy, supporting regional targeting.\n\n- The campaign will personalize content based on pain points such as CV skills management and RFP responsiveness, using dynamic tokens for tailored messaging per contact (19:55).\n    - Education-focused emails will integrate success stories and testimonials to build credibility.\n    - Initial outreach will be awareness-based, gently pushing for demos to avoid overwhelming prospects early.\n\n## **Campaign Execution and Assets**\n\nThe plan includes sending emails from **Bettina’s profile** with warming efforts already underway, complemented by LinkedIn messages to increase touchpoints and engagement (23:14).\n\n- Six email addresses across three domains have been set up for sending under Bettina’s name to diversify outreach and maintain deliverability (23:18).\n    - Bettina’s LinkedIn profile will be connected to the campaign platform by Monday, with support offered for setup to ensure smooth launch.\n    - Initial email volume will start with a few hundred per week, scaling up as engagement allows.\n\n- Colin will share all campaign documents, including emails, contact lists, and LinkedIn copy, for review and translation with the local marketing team to ensure regional relevance and quality (22:42).\n    - Feedback will be collected via links to allow iterative refinements before final launch.\n    - Ads will be written and translated once email copy is approved to maintain a consistent multi-channel approach.\n\n- The existing **landing page** will be redesigned to improve information hierarchy and add new CTAs, incorporating explainer videos and integration highlights to boost conversion rates (20:39).\n    - The aim is to better showcase how Desi Dollo solves operational friction by structuring skills and project experience behind the scenes.\n    - The redesign will be tested with the ABM audience to measure impact before wider rollout.\n\n## **Product Offering and Market Expansion Strategy**\n\nThe team discussed exploring new offerings for smaller IT services companies and internal IT teams to increase profitability and market coverage beyond current IT consulting targets (24:23).\n\n- **Axel Völker** noted that companies with fewer than **50 employees**, and even some up to a few hundred, currently generate limited profit from software sales alone, suggesting a need for bundled software and consulting packages (25:00).\n    - These packages would help smaller companies lacking complex systems by providing a consulting operating system or basic project management solutions.\n    - The goal is to create a service offering that integrates with their existing workflows to increase adoption and value.\n\n- A potential **bench management as a service** model was proposed to help clients manage underutilized staff and increase billable utilization (26:41).\n    - This service would provide hands-on resource management with the eventual goal of automating the process using AI.\n    - The approach offers immediate value by reducing bench time while preparing for future AI-driven efficiencies.\n\n- Colin and Axel agreed AI will play a crucial role in the product’s evolution, with plans to start with a “black box” human-assisted resource manager service to build trust before rolling out AI automation (27:02).\n    - Colin emphasized the market’s increasing acceptance of AI in operational roles and suggested using demo videos to illustrate value.\n    - This phased approach balances innovation with customer comfort and adoption challenges.\n\n- The expansion discussion will continue internally to define specific offerings and messaging for these new segments before launching campaigns targeting them (24:23).\n\n## **Operational and Technical Details**\n\nThe team confirmed that contact enrichment uses multiple data sources and validation processes to keep **bounce rates low**, ensuring high campaign deliverability and engagement (13:24).\n\n- Colin described the technical enrichment process involving **seven different tools** with server bounce tests to maintain list hygiene (13:32).\n    - This reduces wasted sends and protects domain reputation, which is critical for campaign success.\n\n- The integration of LinkedIn outreach alongside emails is designed to increase touch frequency and contextual relevance, leveraging Bettina’s profile for personalized contact (22:39).\n    - Instructions and support will be provided to Bettina for connecting her LinkedIn profile to the outreach platform by Monday (23:57).\n    - Eli’s prior experience with setup will assist troubleshooting if needed.\n\n- The campaign infrastructure includes multiple domain email addresses to spread sending volume and reduce risk of deliverability issues (23:18).\n    - These operational details reflect attention to scaling the campaign while maintaining quality and engagement.\n\n## **Market Positioning and Competitive Insights**\n\nThe focus remains firmly on **IT consulting and IT services** as the core market, with internal IT groups as a secondary target once the initial campaign shows traction (28:56).\n\n- Axel stressed that the current market knowledge is strongest in IT consulting, and expanding beyond requires more research and offering refinement (28:56).\n    - Internal IT teams in larger companies are promising targets due to likely budget availability for tools.\n    - The team will monitor results and adjust market segments accordingly.\n\n- The competitive landscape includes emerging AI-driven resource management tools, making it important to clearly communicate Desi Dollo’s value and differentiation (27:52).\n    - The campaign’s messaging aims to balance AI innovation with operational pain points to appeal broadly.\n    - Early education and demo content are designed to ease adoption and build trust.\n\n- Current client base does not include automotive OEMs or manufacturing, so any expansion into those industries will require distinct messaging and possibly different campaign tracks (29:32).\n    - The team agreed to keep the initial campaign focused to maximize impact before broadening scope.\n\n## **Timeline and Next Steps**\n\nThe campaign is set to launch shortly after **Bettina returns to the office on Monday**, with initial outreach planned to start at a controlled pace and then scale (23:51).\n\n- Colin will send the campaign assets, including instructions to connect LinkedIn profiles, by Monday to enable a smooth start (23:57).\n    - Translation and feedback cycles for emails and ads will happen immediately afterward to finalize content.\n    - Ads will be created and translated only after email copy approval to ensure consistency (21:40).\n\n- The landing page redesign and testing will follow the initial campaign launch, aiming to incorporate new explainer videos and CTAs (20:39).\n    - Success will be measured by engagement metrics and conversion rates from the ABM audience.\n\n- The internal discussion about expanding offerings to smaller IT companies and internal IT teams will continue, with no immediate campaign planned until the product and messaging are defined (24:23).\n    - AI-driven services development is a parallel long-term effort that will shape future product direction and marketing.","outline":null,"keywords":["ABM campaign","IT consulting","contact list enrichment","bench management","operational pain points","AI automation"],"overview":"- **ABM Campaign Focus:** Target IT consulting firms facing operational issues to improve lead quality and conversion rates. \n\n- **Contact List Strategy:** Refined to 555 contacts, aiming to reach 1,000, enhancing regional targeting with enriched data.\n\n- **Campaign Personalization:** Content will address specific pain points with dynamic tokens for tailored messaging and success stories to build credibility.\n\n- **New Service Offerings:** Exploring bundled packages for smaller firms, combining software and consulting to increase adoption and profitability.\n\n- **AI Integration Plan:** Begin with a human-assisted service model, gradually introducing AI to enhance efficiency in resource management. \n\n- **Launch Timeline:** Campaign set to start after Bettina returns, with assets shared for testing and feedback before broader rollout.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nUpload the ABM campaign plan to SharePoint and Pulse for team access (07:24)\nRemove irrelevant companies such as Media Klan, Manage Now, Bonial, and incorrectly classified firms from the contact list (11:49)\nSend contact list and email copy to the team for review and translation feedback (18:44)\nShare instructions with Bettina for connecting her LinkedIn profile to Hay Reach and provide support if needed (23:56)\nUpload all campaign documents to Markup for markup and comments (28:29)\n\n**Axel Völker**\nReview and provide feedback on the contact list, especially concerning job titles and companies for filtering (11:23)\nDiscuss internally potential expanded offerings for smaller IT services companies including possible bundles of software and consulting services (25:55)\nCoordinate with team on translating and adjusting emails/landing pages and share feedback (22:35)\n\n**Bettina**\nWarm up and execute LinkedIn messaging using Hay Reach platform once profile is connected (23:15)\n\n**Eli**\nAssist Bettina with Hay Reach LinkedIn integration and provide support as needed (23:56)\n\n**Guille Santana**\nSupport review of contact list and campaign targeting strategy as needed \n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"45a24905-cf48-4e12-aa39-5bac7706d30d","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
