    1756,
    'https://teams.microsoft.com/l/meetup-join/19:meeting_ZWQ2YmU5YTItNGQ2ZS00ZmI0LWEwOTYtODA3NTA3MjU1ZmU3@thread.v2/0?context={"Tid":"e9bbebf5-9250-454e-81fe-af7712d7b7cf","Oid":"a1bc1144-310a-41e5-aece-6acc110f565e"}',
    '{"id":"01KD5SAAF9SRSGYWMRF33M8P8C","title":"New North/Noetic final touchbase via mtg","summary":{"notes":"## **Campaign Performance and Analysis**\n\nThe team agreed to create a detailed campaign performance overview by industry to decide future focus areas (02:32).\n\n- **Colin Costigan** will prepare a formal report summarizing campaign results across industries including healthcare, attractions, heads of marketing, and AI campaigns (02:32)\n    - Early data shows LinkedIn engagement and conversions primarily on AI and healthcare infographics, but conversion to pipeline is limited due to the 8 out of 10 scoring threshold\n    - The report will include a table listing all engaged contacts with LinkedIn URLs and form responses for easy follow-up\n    - Nancie emphasized the importance of understanding aggregate industry performance before examining channel-specific results, to inform continuation or pivoting of efforts\n    - Colin will place the campaign wrap-up and AI-specific results in the analysis folder within the shared zip file for centralized access\n\n- The team noted distinct performance patterns: attractions generated many engagements but low conversions due to small players; heads of marketing had narrow traction amid competition; healthcare results remain unclear and require deeper insight (19:23)\n    - This differentiation will shape decisions on which industries and tactics to prioritize going forward\n    - Colin confirmed he will provide a holistic cross-channel summary per industry to clarify these outcomes\n    - The analysis will help decide if they continue or pause campaigns in specific sectors\n\n## **File Organization and Asset Management**\n\nColin outlined a comprehensive, well-organized folder structure designed to streamline access to all campaign-related files and documentation (03:31).\n\n- The folder system sequentially covers launch materials, research, strategy roadmaps, foundations (channel plans and sequencing), and execution folders broken down by type and industry (03:31)\n    - Research includes detailed competitor analysis, industry snapshots, and target account empathy maps to ground strategy decisions\n    - Roadmaps present high-level marketing strategy and ideal customer profiles; foundation folders document how campaigns are built and segmented by channels\n    - Execution folders segment materials by campaign type and industry, supporting easy retrieval within 30 seconds per Colin’s organizational rule\n    - Lists for outreach are to be consolidated into a master spreadsheet with tabs per campaign and industry to improve clarity and cleanup\n\n- Rachel Curtis confirmed podcast-related assets are fully organized by episode and month, with pending additions for recent episodes and AI-specific visual corrections (13:05)\n    - Colin committed to adding missing Instagram carousel assets and updating AI imagery flagged by Rachel for quality issues\n    - All design packages and playbooks, including infographics and social media formats, are stored centrally for quick team access\n\n- Paid media assets, including ad creatives and LinkedIn contact lists, are included in designated folders, with monthly receipts tracked for financial oversight (17:37)\n    - Contact lists used for paid campaigns will be synchronized with the master outreach spreadsheet to ensure consistency\n\n## **Subscription and Platform Management**\n\nThe team clarified ownership and billing responsibility for key podcast and marketing platforms to ensure seamless control and cost management (23:19).\n\n- On **Buzzsprout**, Colin confirmed Noada Consultants holds admin rights and billing ownership, with Rachel and Nancie discussing adding internal team members for continuity in emergencies (23:19)\n    - Rachel plans to coordinate with Racky to add team visibility and remove inactive users to maintain access control\n    - Colin will share login details securely via Teams chat\n\n- For **Heyreach**, the subscription is under client control with a monthly cost of **$79**, and billing can be transferred directly to the client credit card before the month-end cutoff to avoid overlap (25:27)\n    - Nancie highlighted the importance of completing this transfer promptly to maintain uninterrupted service\n    - Colin provided step-by-step guidance on accessing billing settings to update payment methods\n\n- The team agreed to monitor these platform transitions closely to prevent service gaps and maintain efficient operations\n\n## **Process Improvements and Next Steps**\n\nThe team emphasized simplifying file retrieval and campaign tracking to improve operational efficiency and decision-making clarity (10:04).\n\n- Colin will clean up and standardize naming conventions across all lists and campaign files to reduce search time and duplication (10:44)\n    - Nancie requested a master spreadsheet tabbed by campaign sequence: healthcare, attractions, heads of marketing, AI, plus a re-engagement tab for cross-cutting efforts\n    - This structure will support sequential review and help the team track progress and performance chronologically\n\n- The zip folder containing all campaign assets and analysis will be uploaded to Box, with contingency plans to break up the upload if the file size exceeds system limits (22:17)\n    - Rachel will coordinate the upload and alert Colin if the process becomes too time-consuming, to divide and conquer as needed\n\n- Colin will send the final AI campaign report, updated podcast episode files, and corrected AI visuals promptly to close outstanding content and quality gaps (14:00)\n    - He also confirmed his availability, noting he will be out on Wednesday and Thursday this week, so the team plans communication accordingly (28:02)\n\n- The group agreed to continue monitoring engagement and conversions closely to refine targeting and tactics as campaigns evolve, prioritizing data-driven decisions on industry focus and channel mix","outline":null,"keywords":["AI Campaign","Podcast Management","Campaign Analysis","Subscription Transfer","Marketing Roadmap","Contact List Organization"],"overview":"- **Campaign Overview:** Detailed performance report to be created by industry for focused strategy moving forward. \n\n- **Industry Insights:** Strong engagement in attractions but low conversions; healthcare results unclear; heads of marketing face stiff competition.\n\n- **File Management:** New folder structure implemented for easy access to campaign materials, including outreach and execution folders.\n\n- **Subscription Control:** Buzzsprout owned by Noada Consultants; Heyreach monthly cost of $79 with client billing to be updated before cutoff.\n\n- **Process Enhancements:** Standardize naming conventions and streamline file retrieval to improve efficiency and decision-making tracking.\n\n- **Next Steps:** Finalize and distribute the AI campaign report, update podcast assets, and monitor campaign engagement for optimization.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nPrepare and send formal written report on AI campaign results, listing contacts and form completions (02:25)\nClean and consolidate all campaign contact lists into one master Excel spreadsheet with separate tabs by campaign in chronological order (11:30)\nEnsure carousel Instagram infographic assets are included and correctly filed in shared drive (17:10)\nSend completed podcast episodes for Chris, Joe, and AI assets after review (14:10)\nConduct AI-specific podcast cleanup for image and video quality issues and send updates (14:50)\nCompile holistic campaign performance analysis by industry and place report into analysis folder in the zip package (20:29)\nZip all project files and reports and send to clients for upload to Box, provide alternative instructions if upload issues arise (22:05)\nSend login credentials and access details to Buzzsprout and Heyreach accounts to Noetic team via Teams chat (24:55)\nCoordinate with Rachel and Racky on subscription and billing transfer for Heyreach credit card management before month-end (25:50)\n"},"duration":29.270000457763672,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":1,"name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"id":2,"name":"Rachel Curtis"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Weather, but I feel like that''s part of seeing little kids during the holidays.","index":0,"end_time":4.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":1,"end_time":4.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":4.32,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"There''s so much going around.","index":2,"end_time":6.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":4.96,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"There''s a lot of flu.","index":3,"end_time":7.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":6.48,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":4,"end_time":8.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":8.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I hope it''s not flu.","index":5,"end_time":10.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":9.04,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Like, I hope it''s just a cold.","index":6,"end_time":12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":10.44,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"That''s what I''m hoping for as well.","index":7,"end_time":13.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":12.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":8,"end_time":14.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":13.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":9,"end_time":14.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":14.2,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"You do sound a little froggy.","index":10,"end_time":15.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":14.48,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"I''m trying.","index":11,"end_time":17.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":16.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m trying.","index":12,"end_time":18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":17.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How''s your guys?","index":13,"end_time":19.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":18.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Holiday and weekend and everything?","index":14,"end_time":21.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":19.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nice.","index":15,"end_time":22.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":22.4,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Rachel and I are holding down the fort here, so.","index":16,"end_time":27.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":23.36,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Nice.","index":17,"end_time":28.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":28.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And your husband''s knee recovery?","index":18,"end_time":31.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":29.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":19,"end_time":33.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":32.87,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":20,"end_time":33.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":33.27,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"He''s doing pretty well.","index":21,"end_time":35.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":33.83,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"He overdid it at first and he.","index":22,"end_time":37.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":35.27,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"I think, you know, the day you have surgery, you feel better than you.","index":23,"end_time":43.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":38.31,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Like, it''s still the drug.","index":24,"end_time":44.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":43.75,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"You have some overconfidence.","index":25,"end_time":46.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":44.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":26,"end_time":47.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":46.95,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"And I think he just did too much.","index":27,"end_time":48.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":47.31,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"And so the second day and the third day, he was, like, not good.","index":28,"end_time":51.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":48.59,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"So super sore and, like, why am I so sore?","index":29,"end_time":54.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":51.83,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"You know?","index":30,"end_time":55.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":54.91,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":31,"end_time":57.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":56.75,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"But now he''s good.","index":32,"end_time":60.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":58.43,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Like, he even took the dog out yesterday and walked her and seemed okay.","index":33,"end_time":66.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":60.75,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"So thank you for asking.","index":34,"end_time":67.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":66.31,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":35,"end_time":67.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":67.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that was knee, too.","index":36,"end_time":69.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":68.029,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"You only have two knees, so hopefully we''re done now.","index":37,"end_time":74.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":70.19,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":38,"end_time":77.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":74.75,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"That''s the problem when you do a lot of sports when you''re young and then you get older and it''s a problem.","index":39,"end_time":82.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":77.07,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"I definitely already reap the, I guess, benefits of playing sports.","index":40,"end_time":89.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":84.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":41,"end_time":90.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":89.94,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":42,"end_time":91.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":90.9,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Knees is where it tends to show up.","index":43,"end_time":93.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":91.7,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":44,"end_time":93.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":93.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Knees and stress.","index":45,"end_time":94.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":93.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We wanted to make sure, first and foremost, we go through the file.","index":46,"end_time":98.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":95.46,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"We just want to make sure we understand everything and we''re recording so we can have that, you know, for the rest of the team.","index":47,"end_time":105.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":98.86,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"We would love to touch on campaign results, understanding we''re out there with this AI campaign at such a weird time, but we want to pause on that just to see, frankly, whether or not it''s something we should pick up and continue.","index":48,"end_time":120.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":107.09,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"So we would love to touch on that.","index":49,"end_time":124.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":122.53,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"And then I think we have some bits and bobs regarding subscriptions and podcast stuff.","index":50,"end_time":131.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":124.01,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"So that''s what we were thinking.","index":51,"end_time":133.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":131.74,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":52,"end_time":133.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":133.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I have all the stuff for the, like, assets and access and everything for the report on the campaign.","index":53,"end_time":140.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":134.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was going to type something up.","index":54,"end_time":141.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":140.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was just out the last couple of days of last week, so I''m going to type something up formally for you guys just so you have that to review.","index":55,"end_time":147.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":141.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, that''s fine.","index":56,"end_time":148.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":147.58,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Do you have any kind of a headline, like, have you peeked at it?","index":57,"end_time":151.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":148.46,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"I mean, we''ve seen some conversions coming through on the LinkedIn side of things with people responding to not only The.","index":58,"end_time":160.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":152.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The new document that we put out for this campaign, for the AI campaign, but also for the infographics for healthcare, are still getting some engagement.","index":59,"end_time":170.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":161.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''re not moving into pipedrive because they''re hitting, like, that 8 out of 10.","index":60,"end_time":174.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":170.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if they do something else, that would happen.","index":61,"end_time":176.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":174.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I mean, we are seeing some engagement, so I think.","index":62,"end_time":179.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":176.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think it might still be worth it just to send them an email.","index":63,"end_time":181.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":179.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":64,"end_time":182.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":182.31,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"So when you send that right up, can you just list out who they are?","index":65,"end_time":186.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":183.03,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll put a table and I''ll say, like, name, LinkedIn, URL, and like, what form they filled out.","index":66,"end_time":192.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":186.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I agreed.","index":67,"end_time":193.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":192.4,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"It''s worth at least looking at them and seeing who they are and if we might want to do something with them.","index":68,"end_time":200.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":193.72,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":69,"end_time":203.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":202.24,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"So we''ll leave that one there.","index":70,"end_time":204.639,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":203.2,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Should we dig in on the file?","index":71,"end_time":206.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":205.12,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Yeah, we can start with that.","index":72,"end_time":208.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":207.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"When I say file, I really mean all the files.","index":73,"end_time":211.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":208.6,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Every file?","index":74,"end_time":212.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":211.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":75,"end_time":212.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":212.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":76,"end_time":214.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":213.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can you guys see my screen?","index":77,"end_time":216.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":214.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":78,"end_time":216.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":216.7,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Yes.","index":79,"end_time":217.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":216.9,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Cool.","index":80,"end_time":217.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":217.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re in Google Drive, and everything is just in one folder.","index":81,"end_time":221.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":217.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll be zipping this up.","index":82,"end_time":223.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":221.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is just your contract number with us internally.","index":83,"end_time":225.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":223.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is the folder we''ll be zipping up, and this has everything.","index":84,"end_time":228.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":226.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So in here, we layer out basically all of the steps of our process that we''ve taken with you guys.","index":85,"end_time":234.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":229.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So launch is going to have files from when you met with Tristan and Joe in December and January, mapping out, you know, all the kickoffs and everything.","index":86,"end_time":244.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":234.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Research documents will be in here in our initial roadmaps and updated roadmaps for every quarter.","index":87,"end_time":249.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":245.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I can dive into these a little bit.","index":88,"end_time":251.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":249.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"These will have, like, asset intake forms, kickoff decks from our meetings, and clearly labeled with all the dates of when those meetings occurred.","index":89,"end_time":259.039,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":252,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":90,"end_time":262,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":261.2,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"For research, this will hold the massive research document that you guys read through during our calls as well.","index":91,"end_time":271.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":262.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this goes through competitors, industry snapshots, all sorts of data like that.","index":92,"end_time":278.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":272.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And this gets into the industry sectors, too?","index":93,"end_time":287.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":283.94,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Yes.","index":94,"end_time":288.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":288.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ve actually switched away from.","index":95,"end_time":293.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":291.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A few months after we did this, we switched away from doing it in a slide deck because we were like, we''re just putting way too much information into a deck, so we started putting everything into a document.","index":96,"end_time":301.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":294.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, this will have competitive analysis and things like that as well.","index":97,"end_time":307.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":303.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":98,"end_time":309.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":308.65,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"And that''s competitive analysis, competitors to us.","index":99,"end_time":313.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":309.17,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Yes.","index":100,"end_time":313.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":313.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Correct.","index":101,"end_time":313.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":313.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":102,"end_time":315.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":313.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And there''s a little table of contents up here, too, so you click on that when you open the PDF as well.","index":103,"end_time":322.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":315.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Social media reports, just different reports that we ran on the website, things like that.","index":104,"end_time":326.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":322.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Competitor ad Libraries, competitor, website, metrics.","index":105,"end_time":333.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":328.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":106,"end_time":335.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":334.54,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Then we had our alignment as well.","index":107,"end_time":338.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":336.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so that was just a slide deck again, that this was part of the growth engine process we went through.","index":108,"end_time":347.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":338.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Joe and Tristan, this is when they were still meeting with you before we even started working with Tanya or Rachel.","index":109,"end_time":353.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":347.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is where we aligned on everything, like what is hunting versus farming, all of the pipedrive metrics.","index":110,"end_time":363.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":358.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so we have exports out of pipedrive for those moments in time as well.","index":111,"end_time":366.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":363.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":112,"end_time":373.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":373.2,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Then we get into number three being the roadmap.","index":113,"end_time":378.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":375.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so this is our initial roadmap right here.","index":114,"end_time":384.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":378.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this goes through the entire marketing strategy, target market.","index":115,"end_time":388.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":385.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is like bringing every bit of research that was done to that point into a marketing strategy.","index":116,"end_time":393.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":388.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so this will go through all of our six step process.","index":117,"end_time":396.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":393.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You''ll see that this aligns with all the folder names as well.","index":118,"end_time":398.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":396.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then it goes through the ideal target accounts that we set up.","index":119,"end_time":402.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":400.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nancy, I think this is one of the first times that I actually met with you and we went through an ABM plan and everything like that.","index":120,"end_time":408.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":402.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A lot of that information came out of this roadmap.","index":121,"end_time":410.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":408.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Mm.","index":122,"end_time":412.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":411.71,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"So this does a empathy map for all the target accounts, things like that, And then your story brand framework.","index":123,"end_time":427.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":415.069,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So making the customer the hero.","index":124,"end_time":430.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":429,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And what do they get out of working with Noetic?","index":125,"end_time":433.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":431.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The PDF looks like it formatted a little bit weird, but that might just be the preview.","index":126,"end_time":437,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":433.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But all that stuff is in here.","index":127,"end_time":440.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":439.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then next one was the roadmap that we built in Q4.","index":128,"end_time":447.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":442.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So not a lot of different information.","index":129,"end_time":461.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":460.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re still targeting healthcare with Mayo Clinic being kind of a pillar in that the Detroit Zoo consumer goods.","index":130,"end_time":471.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":461.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And it just kind of reiterates.","index":131,"end_time":474.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":473.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we just update those every few months just to make sure we have up to date information.","index":132,"end_time":478.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":474.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we get into foundation.","index":133,"end_time":483.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":482.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is where plan documents will live.","index":134,"end_time":485.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":483.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you know, when we met for the ABM campaigns, the presentations that we put together for our present or for showing you guys exactly how we put all that stuff together, how we want to approach content, how we''re segmenting the accounts, all of that information lives in here as well.","index":135,"end_time":504.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":486.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What accounts were you using?","index":136,"end_time":506.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":505.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What different channels of messaging and outreach, things like that.","index":137,"end_time":511.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":507.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So from a language standpoint, when we''re in roadmap, we''re talking about like at the highest level plan, we''re talking about ideal customer profile, we''re talking about industries.","index":138,"end_time":526.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":515.97,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"When we get into foundation, we''re now talking about the how we''re talking about channels and sequencing and such.","index":139,"end_time":536.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":526.61,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":140,"end_time":537.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":537.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":141,"end_time":538.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":537.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, you know, you can think about this pretty sequential.","index":142,"end_time":540.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":538.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So starting our relationship, doing a bunch of research, laying out the entire marketing strategy, and then as part of that strategy, all of the different plans and channels and everything that go into mechanics.","index":143,"end_time":550.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":540.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":144,"end_time":550.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":550.28,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Is foundation.","index":145,"end_time":551.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":550.68,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Okay.","index":146,"end_time":552.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":551.84,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"And then execution goes campaign by campaign.","index":147,"end_time":556.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":552.8,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":148,"end_time":557.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":557.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this will break up things a little bit more by like, you know, was it an ABM campaign where we''re working on case studies, things for the podcast, any work in pipedrive, any work for paid media, playbooks, different things like that.","index":149,"end_time":573.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":557.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So those have been segmented just into folders to make the organization a bit easier.","index":150,"end_time":577.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":573.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But for example, here''s my question on that.","index":151,"end_time":580.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":577.74,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Sorry to interrupt you in execution.","index":152,"end_time":582.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":580.3,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"I see that you have it like by thing.","index":153,"end_time":585.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":583.02,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Right.","index":154,"end_time":585.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":585.66,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"By type.","index":155,"end_time":586.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":585.98,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"What about by campaign?","index":156,"end_time":589.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":587.43,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Like, here''s all we did for attractions.","index":157,"end_time":593.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":589.75,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Here''s all we did for healthcare.","index":158,"end_time":594.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":593.27,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":159,"end_time":595.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":595.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if we click into abm, so we have attractions here.","index":160,"end_time":597.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":595.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I see.","index":161,"end_time":598.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":598.31,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"So you have a thing, but then it goes into by industry.","index":162,"end_time":603.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":599.19,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Yep.","index":163,"end_time":604.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":604.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we try to be very organized.","index":164,"end_time":607.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":605.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I have a rule of, like, if it takes us longer than 30 seconds to look for a file, we''ve set something up wrong.","index":165,"end_time":611.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":607.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s how we break it down in here.","index":166,"end_time":614.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":613.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you have aioffer.","index":167,"end_time":615.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":614.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So image ads.","index":168,"end_time":617.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":616.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We created the email sequence, the web pages, resources that we got from you guys.","index":169,"end_time":622.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":617.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Healthcare in here as well, re engagement campaigns.","index":170,"end_time":631.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":626.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then also lists have been added here.","index":171,"end_time":635.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":631.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so I know you mentioned also cleaning up these lists.","index":172,"end_time":641.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":638.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Mm.","index":173,"end_time":643.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":643.27,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"So what I was going to do is just combine these and just make sure that all of the naming conventions, because I know we cleaned them up a few months ago and I think you were happy there.","index":174,"end_time":653.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":644.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I''m just going to go back through and just make sure that everything is just neatly named and organized for the campaigns that we ran.","index":175,"end_time":660.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":653.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think.","index":176,"end_time":661.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":660.63,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"I. I mean, ideally, I think it would be one master spreadsheet where tab by tab, you would be seeing re engagement, cleaned up.","index":177,"end_time":677.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":665.83,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Attractions, health care, the new heads of marketing.","index":178,"end_time":688.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":679.62,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"What am I missing?","index":179,"end_time":690.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":689.3,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Attractions, Healthcare, marketing.","index":180,"end_time":695.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":691.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"AI was a mix of all of those audiences.","index":181,"end_time":698.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":695.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was.","index":182,"end_time":699.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":698.51,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":183,"end_time":700.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":699.31,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"I don''t know that, like, AI could have its own tab, but I think, like, if I think my brain goes sequential.","index":184,"end_time":708.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":700.55,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"So we started with attractions.","index":185,"end_time":713.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":708.43,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"We started with healthcare.","index":186,"end_time":715.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":713.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"With healthcare.","index":187,"end_time":716.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":715.79,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Then we did attractions.","index":188,"end_time":718.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":717.63,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re going to do education.","index":189,"end_time":720.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":719.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then we switched to attractions.","index":190,"end_time":722.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":720.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then we switch.","index":191,"end_time":723.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":722.27,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"No, no, we were going to do.","index":192,"end_time":725.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":723.87,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"We were going to do education after attractions, and that''s where we made the change.","index":193,"end_time":733.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":727.92,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"So we went higher education, then we went attractions.","index":194,"end_time":737.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":733.6,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"I''m sorry, we went healthcare.","index":195,"end_time":740.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":737.76,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"We went Attractions.","index":196,"end_time":742.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":740.72,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"We were gonna go higher education.","index":197,"end_time":743.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":742.16,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"We didn''t.","index":198,"end_time":744.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":743.76,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"We went to heads of marketing and then we went to AI.","index":199,"end_time":748.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":744.44,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Yes.","index":200,"end_time":749.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":748.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":201,"end_time":750.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":749.6,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"So ideally we''d have a tab for each of those, like in that order.","index":202,"end_time":754.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":750.4,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"And then the addition is that re engagement was sort of like going across.","index":203,"end_time":757.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":754.04,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"But I don''t know that AI would warrant a tab because as you said, it''s not.","index":204,"end_time":764.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":758.14,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"It wasn''t like list based per se.","index":205,"end_time":767.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":764.22,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Yeah, it was, it was like this is pretty relevant to almost everyone.","index":206,"end_time":771.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":768.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So let''s see if we cast a wide net, you know what we can do.","index":207,"end_time":775.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":772.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, exactly.","index":208,"end_time":777.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":776.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Tracking this, Rach.","index":209,"end_time":778.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":777.34,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Yes.","index":210,"end_time":779.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":779.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we did.","index":211,"end_time":780.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":779.9,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"You were there.","index":212,"end_time":781.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":780.54,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Yes.","index":213,"end_time":782.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":781.98,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"And then Rachel, this is where you will see all of your files for the metamorphosis moment.","index":214,"end_time":790.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":785.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So instead of content plan assets, we have everything broken down by episodes and this is the folder that you are in all of the time.","index":215,"end_time":796.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":790.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh great.","index":216,"end_time":798.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":797.88,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Then the frameworks, all those are broken out by month.","index":217,"end_time":802.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":799.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":218,"end_time":803.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":803.32,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"And you''ll even see when we started with the new template, Nancy, when you would send back like this is the one I sent to the client.","index":219,"end_time":813.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":805.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We just created a final from client and added that exact document in here as well.","index":220,"end_time":818.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":814.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it.","index":221,"end_time":824.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":823.65,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"And then that was quite incomplete though.","index":222,"end_time":829.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":826.37,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Is.","index":223,"end_time":829.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":829.53,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Did I just not send you back?","index":224,"end_time":831.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":830.05,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"This is just from like the few episodes in October.","index":225,"end_time":835.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":832.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, I see.","index":226,"end_time":835.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":835.46,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"We''re just looking at the month.","index":227,"end_time":836.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":835.98,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, gotcha, gotcha.","index":228,"end_time":838.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":837.06,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"So like we don''t have, I think Chris and Joe yet.","index":229,"end_time":846.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":840.18,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Is that going to be added to here when it''s available, the episodes?","index":230,"end_time":850.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":846.66,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, let me check with.","index":231,"end_time":853.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":851.379,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I also sent an email last week about the AI all over Nancy''s face and I wanted to see like when those would come in, if.","index":232,"end_time":864.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":854.02,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"It would also be updated.","index":233,"end_time":865.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":864.32,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":234,"end_time":866.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":866.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''m still checking.","index":235,"end_time":868.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":866.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m still digging out of my email from being out the last couple days.","index":236,"end_time":870.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":868.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It looks like we did wrap up Chris and Joe.","index":237,"end_time":873.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":871.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''ll send those over.","index":238,"end_time":874.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":873.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":239,"end_time":876.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":875.4,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"After I take a look at them and yeah, and then I''ll.","index":240,"end_time":882,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":876.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll go through the emails.","index":241,"end_time":883,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":882,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":242,"end_time":883.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":883,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we also have Christine Calvin as well.","index":243,"end_time":886.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":883.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":244,"end_time":887.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":887.25,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"And then I''m more concerned also just about the AI.","index":245,"end_time":891.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":887.65,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I went back to post some of them and I looked and Nancy''s face is not real and her eyes are rolling in circles.","index":246,"end_time":899.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":891.49,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"So I sent that list over to make sure that those are also fixed.","index":247,"end_time":904.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":899.73,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yep.","index":248,"end_time":904.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":904.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll get that in right away.","index":249,"end_time":906.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":904.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":250,"end_time":907.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":906.93,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Of course.","index":251,"end_time":908.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":908.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I know you''re asking also about the show elements and designs and everything.","index":252,"end_time":913.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":910.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So all of those are in here in Your full design package.","index":253,"end_time":917.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":913.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":254,"end_time":918.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":917.94,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"So that includes like any images, the video, like before and after assets, and the main one that audio.","index":255,"end_time":928.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":920.34,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":256,"end_time":929.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":928.58,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yep.","index":257,"end_time":930.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":929.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":258,"end_time":931.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":931.139,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Of course, Playbook documents that we worked on will be in here.","index":259,"end_time":938.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":932.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s all the different Playbooks.","index":260,"end_time":940.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":939.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then do you have.","index":261,"end_time":947.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":946.33,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"You call them the Playbook?","index":262,"end_time":951.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":949.61,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"What do you call them?","index":263,"end_time":954.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":953.93,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"I call them the chunked out.","index":264,"end_time":957.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":955.61,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"But yeah, the infographics.","index":265,"end_time":959.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":957.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The infographics, yeah, yeah, they''re right here.","index":266,"end_time":961.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":959.45,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Include that and the Instagram ones here too.","index":267,"end_time":967.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":963.13,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Right.","index":268,"end_time":967.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":967.21,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"The Instagram I think we made there was like an Instagram formatted for Instagram, like out of a Playbook.","index":269,"end_time":978.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":970.3,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"It was a carousel.","index":270,"end_time":979.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":978.62,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I think it was on the last one.","index":271,"end_time":984.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":982.7,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Where it was a chunked out Playbook for Instagram.","index":272,"end_time":994.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":991.34,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Mm.","index":273,"end_time":995.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":995.38,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Covers.","index":274,"end_time":1009.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1008.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is that it?","index":275,"end_time":1024.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1023.71,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"We had the care.","index":276,"end_time":1026.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1025.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I know exactly what she''s talking about.","index":277,"end_time":1028.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1026.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It should be in here, but it''s not.","index":278,"end_time":1036.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1031.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''ll add that in here.","index":279,"end_time":1039.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1036.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":280,"end_time":1041.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1041.15,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Okay.","index":281,"end_time":1049.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1049.48,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"And then paid media.","index":282,"end_time":1058.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1057,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this will have a bunch of ad campaigns and images that we''ve created for the ad campaigns, as well as contact lists that we''ve uploaded straight to LinkedIn and then the monthly receipts folder that I know Rocky and Tiffany have been checking out as well.","index":283,"end_time":1074.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1058.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How does the.","index":284,"end_time":1076.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1075.17,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"How does this contact list relate to?","index":285,"end_time":1082.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1078.69,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"I''m just thinking organizationally, like, is this essentially a tab that will be in that master Excel with all the lists?","index":286,"end_time":1094.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1083.49,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Yeah, exactly.","index":287,"end_time":1095.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1094.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":288,"end_time":1095.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1095.13,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Okay.","index":289,"end_time":1096.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1095.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s redundant with that, but I agree it belongs in both places.","index":290,"end_time":1101.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1097.95,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"That''s good.","index":291,"end_time":1102.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1101.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then execution.","index":292,"end_time":1108.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1106.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m sorry, Analysis.","index":293,"end_time":1110.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1108.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this will have all the slide decks for the meetings that we''ve had during our engagement.","index":294,"end_time":1115.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1110.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you guys ever need to go through those for historical context.","index":295,"end_time":1117.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1115.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great.","index":296,"end_time":1119.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1119.07,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"As well as some.","index":297,"end_time":1121.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1120.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then the dashboard report.","index":298,"end_time":1122.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1121.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So these are all the images of the slides they asked us to take.","index":299,"end_time":1125.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1123.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The screenshots of data box.","index":300,"end_time":1127.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1125.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":301,"end_time":1128.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1127.65,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"So my question on this is, ideally I would like some way of knowing like how a campaign did holistically, but I say that aware of the fact that like attractions turned on and off and ran for about a quarter, whereas health care, I think we ran like longer and overlapping and same thing with cmo.","index":302,"end_time":1156.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1128.29,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"So I don''t know if what I''m asking is really a thing because of the overlap.","index":303,"end_time":1162.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1156.54,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"So are you looking for just how did, from an email standpoint, how did.","index":304,"end_time":1167.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1163.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Healthcare perform more so across it all, how well did we do?","index":305,"end_time":1173.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1167.82,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Because I''m thinking cross channel from a campaign perspective, you know, how did we do with attractions, how did we do with healthcare?","index":306,"end_time":1182.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1174.26,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"How did we do with heads of Marketing, like I can tell you, I think the narrative at the highest level is that we got like when it came to attractions, we got a lot of looks, we got a lot of engagement, but no conversion because these were small time attractions who really seemed to get a lot of value from the playbook but, but weren''t converting.","index":307,"end_time":1202.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1182.72,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Whereas heads of marketing, we just got much more narrow traction.","index":308,"end_time":1213.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1203.13,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"We did get, we did get some traction, but we got much more narrow traction than we thought.","index":309,"end_time":1217.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1213.49,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"And it''s a very competitive audience and I just don''t think we did as well as we at all as we had hoped there.","index":310,"end_time":1223.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1217.57,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"I think with healthcare, that''s where I''m kind of the most fuzzy, like.","index":311,"end_time":1228.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1224.25,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Yeah, so in my analysis then I''ll include, I''ll do like a overview of all the campaigns and then a breakdown of each different industry.","index":312,"end_time":1238.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1229.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":313,"end_time":1240.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1239.09,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"I just again, you know, in the go forward, like I''m not, it''s not to say that I''m not interested in how did ABM do versus how did paid do or whatever, but you know, how did we do collectively in a given industry is the first stop because it''s like do we, do we continue to pursue that industry and did the tactics that we use, you know, generally work?","index":314,"end_time":1265.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1240.09,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"I think attractions is the clearest story.","index":315,"end_time":1269.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1266.2,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"I think it''s just too many small players who just don''t have enough, you know, marketing activity going on against the things we do, the services we do.","index":316,"end_time":1280.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1270.92,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"But I don''t have a clean story like that for the other ones and I just want to have it for the go forward.","index":317,"end_time":1285.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1281.08,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":318,"end_time":1286.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1286.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":319,"end_time":1287.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1286.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Put that together.","index":320,"end_time":1287.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1287.15,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":321,"end_time":1288.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1288.03,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Of course.","index":322,"end_time":1289.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1288.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And the last folder you''ll see in here is just, it''s noetic underscore mid and this is just documents that you guys have shared with us throughout our engagement.","index":323,"end_time":1296.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1290.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":324,"end_time":1298.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1297.63,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"And when you do that email that you''re going to do, can that also sit somewhere as like, I don''t know, maybe analysis?","index":325,"end_time":1311.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1299.47,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Yeah, the analysis.","index":326,"end_time":1312.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1312.03,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Yeah, I would, I would put that under actually I would put that into an analysis folder and I''ll just do like a campaign wrap up.","index":327,"end_time":1321.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1313.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, okay.","index":328,"end_time":1322.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1321.47,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":329,"end_time":1324.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1324.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But if you guys have any questions as you''re going through that, obviously let me know.","index":330,"end_time":1328.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1326.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I''ll get the updates made and then send that over to you with the package folder.","index":331,"end_time":1332.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1328.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":332,"end_time":1332.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1332.15,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Really appreciate you pulling all this together in an organized manner.","index":333,"end_time":1336.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1332.59,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Of course.","index":334,"end_time":1336.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1336.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Rachel, where should we house this?","index":335,"end_time":1341.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1337.31,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"We have a folder in box that we could put it in.","index":336,"end_time":1346.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1343.27,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Although it''s just the whole thing is a link.","index":337,"end_time":1349.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1347.59,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Right.","index":338,"end_time":1349.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1349.67,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"It''ll be like a Zip folder.","index":339,"end_time":1353.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1351.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, so we could put the zip folder in our box and just try to do it that way.","index":340,"end_time":1359.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1354.23,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah, we have to see if it''ll.","index":341,"end_time":1361.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1359.75,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"We also have a little buffer.","index":342,"end_time":1362.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1361.43,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Luckily that we can ask them for a little bit longer.","index":343,"end_time":1366.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1362.83,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"So we can definitely try it that way.","index":344,"end_time":1368.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1366.17,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah, I. I haven''t tried to load a zip to box.","index":345,"end_time":1374.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1368.65,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"I think it can handle it, but I don''t know.","index":346,"end_time":1378.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1376.01,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"So we''ll.","index":347,"end_time":1380.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1379.69,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"We''ll find you if we struggle, Colin.","index":348,"end_time":1382.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1380.29,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"I mean, first place, like download different sections and then we re upload them.","index":349,"end_time":1386.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1382.29,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":350,"end_time":1386.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1386.53,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Tedious, but it could be done.","index":351,"end_time":1388.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1386.93,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":352,"end_time":1388.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1388.17,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Yep.","index":353,"end_time":1389.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1388.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I know Buzzsprout and Haybridge were the other platforms that we wanted to focus on, so Buzzsprout.","index":354,"end_time":1395.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1390.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can send you, I think.","index":355,"end_time":1397.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1396.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Rachel, you are logged in, correct?","index":356,"end_time":1398.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1397.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":357,"end_time":1399.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1399.47,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Because you''ve been using that.","index":358,"end_time":1400.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1399.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":359,"end_time":1401.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1400.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, yeah, I went in.","index":360,"end_time":1402.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1401.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You guys are actually already the admin on the account.","index":361,"end_time":1404.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1402.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You own the subscription and you own the.","index":362,"end_time":1406.589,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1404.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the person who can get in and do billing is admin.","index":363,"end_time":1411.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1406.589,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yes.","index":364,"end_time":1412.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1411.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":365,"end_time":1413.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1412.91,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"That would explain why I can''t see anything.","index":366,"end_time":1415.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1413.43,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"My other question for this is how do I link Spotify?","index":367,"end_time":1419.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1416.24,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":368,"end_time":1420.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1420.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if you go to directories up here and hit get listed, just do it that way.","index":369,"end_time":1424.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1420.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":370,"end_time":1425.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1424.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This will give you the instructions to do that.","index":371,"end_time":1427.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1425.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, thank you.","index":372,"end_time":1429.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1428.24,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"So just so I''m clear, so on Buzzsprout, do you think we are squared away in that we''re the owner of it?","index":373,"end_time":1438.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1430.48,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":374,"end_time":1438.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1438.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it has admin at Noada Consultants listed as the billing administration.","index":375,"end_time":1442.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1438.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But can you have more than one admin?","index":376,"end_time":1447.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1444.07,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Do you know if that''s a thing you can.","index":377,"end_time":1450.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1447.43,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Okay, then I think it would be helpful.","index":378,"end_time":1454.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1451.99,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Nancy, what we can do is talk to Racky, and I think one of us also needs to be on it.","index":379,"end_time":1458.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1454.31,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":380,"end_time":1459.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1459.35,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Just so we have visibility.","index":381,"end_time":1460.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1459.83,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Like, I''m the one that''s in it all the time.","index":382,"end_time":1462.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1460.91,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"If there was an emergency or something we needed.","index":383,"end_time":1464.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1462.55,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":384,"end_time":1465.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1465.03,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"And Racky was out.","index":385,"end_time":1466.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1465.39,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"You know, it''s good to have one of our emails too.","index":386,"end_time":1468.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1466.47,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":387,"end_time":1469.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1469.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So Racky has the ability to add team members.","index":388,"end_time":1472,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1469.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So Racky would be able to remove Christie.","index":389,"end_time":1475.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1472.88,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":390,"end_time":1476.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1475.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And this is a dead email address, so this doesn''t.","index":391,"end_time":1478.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1476.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No one has access to this.","index":392,"end_time":1479.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1478.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":393,"end_time":1480.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1480.32,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"I was just saying two spots.","index":394,"end_time":1483.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1480.96,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":395,"end_time":1484.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1484.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":396,"end_time":1484.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1484.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You can remove her.","index":397,"end_time":1485.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1484.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, no problem.","index":398,"end_time":1486.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1485.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":399,"end_time":1487.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1486.64,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":400,"end_time":1487.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1487.08,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Okay.","index":401,"end_time":1488.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1487.6,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"All right.","index":402,"end_time":1488.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1488.12,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"We can do that.","index":403,"end_time":1489.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1488.52,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"And so then I think it''s just.","index":404,"end_time":1493.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1489.68,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Hey, reach.","index":405,"end_time":1494.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1493.44,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Yep.","index":406,"end_time":1495.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1494.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so I''ll.","index":407,"end_time":1496.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1495.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can even send logins into the teams chat.","index":408,"end_time":1501.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1497.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let''s do that right now.","index":409,"end_time":1505.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1504.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And.","index":410,"end_time":1516.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1516.44,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"And on this column, like in the other ones, you all owned the subscription and you couldn''t transfer it.","index":411,"end_time":1525.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1516.84,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"But in the case of heyreach, you can.","index":412,"end_time":1526.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1525.21,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Yeah, so like heyreach and Smart Lead, it''s just as simple as, like a credit card because it''s not under like a management account, but the other ones are under our like marketers and demand managed account, if that makes sense.","index":413,"end_time":1538.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1527.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It does make sense.","index":414,"end_time":1540.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1539.41,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":415,"end_time":1541.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1540.53,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"So this is not under a managed account.","index":416,"end_time":1543.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1541.01,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"And so with this login, we should be able to go in there and transfer it to our credit card.","index":417,"end_time":1552.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1543.25,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":418,"end_time":1553.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1552.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you''ll do is hit the settings cog.","index":419,"end_time":1555.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1553.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And this is the same login, Nancy, that you''ve used to connect your LinkedIn profile to the account and then go to billing.","index":420,"end_time":1561.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1555.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And you can see we have you on the growth plan here for $79 a month.","index":421,"end_time":1566.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1562.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And if you go to billing details, then you can just change the payment method.","index":422,"end_time":1571.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1566.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And this credit card is one that we''ve set up for you when we onboarded you as a client.","index":423,"end_time":1577.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1572.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it will be canceled at the end of the month.","index":424,"end_time":1579.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1577.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":425,"end_time":1580.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1579.67,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Okay.","index":426,"end_time":1581.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1581.03,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"So we just have to make sure we do this before end of month.","index":427,"end_time":1584.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1581.51,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Yep.","index":428,"end_time":1585.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1585.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":429,"end_time":1588.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1588.15,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"All right.","index":430,"end_time":1589.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1588.71,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"And then again on this or Buzzsprout, if we struggle, we''ll find you, of course.","index":431,"end_time":1594.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1589.19,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":432,"end_time":1595.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1594.63,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Does that make sense, Rachel?","index":433,"end_time":1599.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1597.35,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"I''m going to talk to Raki on that one because I want to make sure we do the credit card that she wants.","index":434,"end_time":1606.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1599.64,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Yep.","index":435,"end_time":1607.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1607.4,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Okay, sounds good.","index":436,"end_time":1610.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1609.24,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"All right, and then you have Colin in your inbox, you have the podcast AI cleanup thing that''s needed.","index":437,"end_time":1617.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1610.84,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"You''re going to send us the AI specific campaign results, but also an overview against each campaign.","index":438,"end_time":1625.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1617.4,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"And you''ll put that in the analysis place of the zip file.","index":439,"end_time":1630.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1625.24,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"You''ll send us the zip file.","index":440,"end_time":1632.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1631,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"We will hope to load that as is.","index":441,"end_time":1637.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1633.48,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"But.","index":442,"end_time":1637.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1637.56,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"But Rachel, let''s.","index":443,"end_time":1639.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1638.68,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Let''s talk about that.","index":444,"end_time":1640.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1639.84,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"If it.","index":445,"end_time":1641.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1640.72,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"I mean, I think it''s going to really take a minute for Box to load it, but I think Box will probably be able to do it.","index":446,"end_time":1646.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1641.48,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"But then if it can''t, let''s figure out if we need to divide and conquer because I don''t want you spending hours loading files.","index":447,"end_time":1655.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1647.16,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Yep.","index":448,"end_time":1657.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1656.61,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"They miss anything?","index":449,"end_time":1659.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1658.85,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"I don''t think so.","index":450,"end_time":1661.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1660.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No.","index":451,"end_time":1661.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1661.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m gonna make sure that the carousel images are in there.","index":452,"end_time":1664.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1661.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m sure they are.","index":453,"end_time":1664.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1664.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just need to make sure they''re in the right folder.","index":454,"end_time":1667.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1664.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then.","index":455,"end_time":1667.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1667.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":456,"end_time":1668.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1668.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The analysis in the zip file and.","index":457,"end_time":1670.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1668.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then going through Rachel''s emails.","index":458,"end_time":1672.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1670.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":459,"end_time":1674.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1672.93,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"And if you questions, please let me know because.","index":460,"end_time":1676.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1674.05,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Yeah, of course.","index":461,"end_time":1677.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1676.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Colin, what are your days in this week?","index":462,"end_time":1680.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1678.49,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Just so we know not to bother you if you''re out.","index":463,"end_time":1682.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1680.33,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"I am out.","index":464,"end_time":1683.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1682.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Wednesday and Thursday.","index":465,"end_time":1684.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1683.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This week, same.","index":466,"end_time":1686.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1684.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":467,"end_time":1687.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1686.49,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"Okay.","index":468,"end_time":1689.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1688.73,"speaker_name":"Rachel Curtis"},{"text":"All right, great.","index":469,"end_time":1690.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1689.69,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"I hope you feel better, and I hope it doesn''t go full blown.","index":470,"end_time":1693.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1690.41,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":471,"end_time":1694.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1693.769,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I really appreciate it.","index":472,"end_time":1695.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1694.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great chatting with you guys.","index":473,"end_time":1696.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1695.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, thanks so much.","index":474,"end_time":1697.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1696.49,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"I''ll see you in a minute.","index":475,"end_time":1703.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1702.49,"speaker_name":"Nancie McDonnell Ruder"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":476,"end_time":1705.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1704.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"}],"dateString":"2025-12-29T14:00:00.000Z","host_email":"nancie@noeticconsultants.com","meeting_link":"https://teams.microsoft.com/l/meetup-join/19:meeting_ZWQ2YmU5YTItNGQ2ZS00ZmI0LWEwOTYtODA3NTA3MjU1ZmU3@thread.v2/0?context={\"Tid\":\"e9bbebf5-9250-454e-81fe-af7712d7b7cf\",\"Oid\":\"a1bc1144-310a-41e5-aece-6acc110f565e\"}","participants":["nancie@noeticconsultants.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,rachel@noe